WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.820
Scholastic audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:17.820 --> 00:00:21.719
Book 14, The Dangerous Gift, by 2ET

00:00:21.719 --> 00:00:24.359
Sutherland, read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:42.420 --> 00:00:48.899
The Lost Continent Prophecy.

00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:57.780
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire. to

00:00:57.780 --> 00:01:00.479
the land across the sea, where dragons

00:01:00.479 --> 00:01:03.000
are poisoned and dragons are dying, and

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:04.260
no one can ever be free.

00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:07.619
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:11.219
A secret hides within their book, a

00:01:11.219 --> 00:01:14.340
secret buried far below may save those

00:01:14.340 --> 00:01:15.299
brave enough to look.

00:01:15.359 --> 00:01:19.680
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:22.140
to the dragons who flee from the hive.

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:25.439
Face a great evil with talons united

00:01:25.439 --> 00:01:28.439
where none of the tribes will survive.

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:43.200
Prologue.

00:01:43.319 --> 00:01:46.859
Sortell blanked awake in a haze of

00:01:46.859 --> 00:01:47.159
smoke.

00:01:47.219 --> 00:01:49.859
Smoke clung to the air and filled his

00:01:49.859 --> 00:01:50.159
nose.

00:01:50.219 --> 00:01:52.560
Even the savannah grass seem to still

00:01:52.560 --> 00:01:54.299
have wisps of smoke clinging to its

00:01:54.299 --> 00:01:55.260
blades.

00:01:55.319 --> 00:01:56.879
There were dragons all around him.

00:01:56.939 --> 00:02:01.019
Hundreds, maybe 1000s of dragons, that he

00:02:01.019 --> 00:02:01.739
didn't know any of them.

00:02:01.799 --> 00:02:05.819
They were all lying in the tall grass, and

00:02:05.819 --> 00:02:08.219
on the other side of the smoky sky, he

00:02:08.219 --> 00:02:09.599
could see the blurred outline of the

00:02:09.599 --> 00:02:09.840
sun.

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:13.020
The last thing he remembered was falling

00:02:13.020 --> 00:02:15.659
asleep at night, in the jungle, next to

00:02:15.659 --> 00:02:17.460
blue and cricket and sundew.

00:02:17.460 --> 00:02:20.639
Before that, he could remember lying

00:02:20.639 --> 00:02:22.800
there, listening to the carnivorous

00:02:22.800 --> 00:02:25.319
plants rustle and slither nearby, thinking

00:02:25.319 --> 00:02:26.400
about the battle to come.

00:02:26.460 --> 00:02:29.460
He remembered watching Blue rub his

00:02:29.460 --> 00:02:31.500
wrists nervously at the spots where his

00:02:31.500 --> 00:02:33.060
flame silk glowed in the dark.

00:02:33.180 --> 00:02:35.340
Flame silk.

00:02:35.460 --> 00:02:36.419
Fire.

00:02:36.479 --> 00:02:39.479
Blue is going to set the bonfire of heart

00:02:39.479 --> 00:02:41.939
of salvation aflame, and the smoke would

00:02:41.939 --> 00:02:43.379
be the antidote to the breath of evil.

00:02:43.439 --> 00:02:46.259
His fire was going to set all the hive

00:02:46.259 --> 00:02:48.360
wings free from wasps' mind control.

00:02:48.419 --> 00:02:51.120
If it worked, maybe there wouldn't be a

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:51.599
battle at all.

00:02:51.659 --> 00:02:55.020
The smoke in the air suggested that there

00:02:55.020 --> 00:02:57.900
had definitely been a fire, a much bigger

00:02:57.900 --> 00:02:59.879
fire than one pile of roots could have

00:02:59.879 --> 00:03:00.780
produced, in fact.

00:03:00.900 --> 00:03:02.819
But what had happened?

00:03:02.879 --> 00:03:05.099
How did I get here?

00:03:05.159 --> 00:03:08.280
He pushed himself up to standing and

00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:08.639
winced.

00:03:08.699 --> 00:03:10.800
Everything hurt.

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:13.680
His muscles ached as though he'd been

00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:14.460
flying for days.

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:17.340
Even his claws felt bruised and sore.

00:03:17.460 --> 00:03:20.219
From the sounds of the moaning and

00:03:20.219 --> 00:03:22.379
grumbling around him, many of these

00:03:22.379 --> 00:03:24.000
strange dragons felt the same way.

00:03:24.060 --> 00:03:27.360
He suddenly realized that most of them

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:28.139
were hive wings.

00:03:28.199 --> 00:03:29.699
His enemies.

00:03:29.759 --> 00:03:33.780
Why am I lying in the savannah, surrounded

00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:34.560
by hive wings?

00:03:34.680 --> 00:03:36.479
Did they capture me?

00:03:36.599 --> 00:03:40.139
If so, they were doing a pathetic job of

00:03:40.139 --> 00:03:40.979
keeping him prisoner.

00:03:41.039 --> 00:03:43.199
No one was even looking at him.

00:03:43.259 --> 00:03:45.000
It wasn't tied up.

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:47.039
He could fly away right now.

00:03:47.099 --> 00:03:49.199
Which way, though?

00:03:49.259 --> 00:03:51.539
Which way was blue?

00:03:51.659 --> 00:03:53.460
Or Luna.

00:03:53.520 --> 00:03:55.979
If I could fly to Luna, I would.

00:03:56.039 --> 00:03:58.680
So what if there was an entire ocean

00:03:58.680 --> 00:03:59.219
between them?

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:01.199
He would find his way there?

00:04:01.259 --> 00:04:02.219
To her?

00:04:02.340 --> 00:04:06.240
Just as soon as he figured out where in

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:07.139
Pentala he was.

00:04:07.199 --> 00:04:10.439
He squinted around. looking for a

00:04:10.439 --> 00:04:10.860
landmark.

00:04:10.919 --> 00:04:13.620
Even if there was nothing but Savannah

00:04:13.620 --> 00:04:14.699
around him, that would be a clue.

00:04:14.819 --> 00:04:19.500
But there was something. 2 hives, visible

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:21.660
in the distance, with glimmering webs

00:04:21.660 --> 00:04:22.680
stretching between them.

00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:25.620
Which meant the poison jungle should be

00:04:25.620 --> 00:04:26.579
in the other...

00:04:26.579 --> 00:04:29.699
A cloud of black smoke covered the

00:04:29.699 --> 00:04:32.160
horizon behind him, reaching from ground

00:04:32.160 --> 00:04:32.879
to sky.

00:04:32.939 --> 00:04:35.459
Is that the jungle?

00:04:35.519 --> 00:04:38.160
And suddenly he had a memory.

00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:41.639
A memory of standing beside blue, as

00:04:41.639 --> 00:04:44.100
flame silk spiraled out of blue's wrists

00:04:44.100 --> 00:04:45.060
onto the pile of roots.

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:48.240
Sortell remembered his own claws

00:04:48.240 --> 00:04:50.339
clutching a spear with sharp thorns

00:04:50.339 --> 00:04:51.899
twisting from one end.

00:04:51.959 --> 00:04:54.600
He remembered staring at the rows of hive

00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:57.300
wings, all of them eerily still and white

00:04:57.300 --> 00:04:57.839
eyed.

00:04:57.899 --> 00:05:00.240
They hadn't moved as he and Blue

00:05:00.240 --> 00:05:01.259
approached the pyre.

00:05:01.319 --> 00:05:03.720
They hadn't swarmed forward to try to

00:05:03.720 --> 00:05:04.079
stop them.

00:05:04.199 --> 00:05:06.360
They hadn't even looked at him.

00:05:06.420 --> 00:05:09.839
He remembered now how that had worried

00:05:09.839 --> 00:05:10.079
him.

00:05:10.139 --> 00:05:13.199
But he'd put his faith in the antidote.

00:05:13.259 --> 00:05:16.500
He'd watched the green tinged smoke rise

00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:18.839
and fill the air, drifting over the front

00:05:18.839 --> 00:05:21.779
ranks of the high wing army, slinking

00:05:21.779 --> 00:05:23.639
around his own head, and blues.

00:05:23.699 --> 00:05:27.300
And then he'd felt his claws twitch and

00:05:27.300 --> 00:05:28.319
sink into the ground.

00:05:28.379 --> 00:05:31.439
His wings opened, but he hadn't moved

00:05:31.439 --> 00:05:31.680
them.

00:05:31.740 --> 00:05:34.980
His head turned toward blue, and his

00:05:34.980 --> 00:05:37.259
mouth moved, and something that wasn't

00:05:37.259 --> 00:05:38.519
him spoke through him.

00:05:38.639 --> 00:05:41.519
Two little silk wings.

00:05:41.579 --> 00:05:44.519
All for me, just what I always wanted.

00:05:44.579 --> 00:05:46.800
And one of them a flame silk.

00:05:46.920 --> 00:05:50.279
So nice when a plan sprouts exactly the

00:05:50.279 --> 00:05:51.240
way it's supposed to.

00:05:51.360 --> 00:05:55.439
Blue had stared back at him, his talons

00:05:55.439 --> 00:05:56.579
also firmly planted.

00:05:56.639 --> 00:05:59.220
The leaf wings flying down from the trees

00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:00.660
would not have been able to tell that

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:01.500
there was anything wrong.

00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:04.560
Only Swordtail could see the panic in

00:06:04.560 --> 00:06:05.160
Blue's eyes.

00:06:05.220 --> 00:06:07.740
Only the 2 of them knew that they were

00:06:07.740 --> 00:06:10.259
paralyzed inside their bodies, controlled

00:06:10.259 --> 00:06:12.660
by someone, or something else.

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:16.139
It felt like the tox in the hive wings

00:06:16.139 --> 00:06:18.600
used on misbehavors way prisoners, but

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:18.959
worse.

00:06:19.019 --> 00:06:22.079
The rest of his memories came flooding

00:06:22.079 --> 00:06:22.259
back.

00:06:22.319 --> 00:06:25.139
The smoke spreading over the leaf wings

00:06:25.139 --> 00:06:28.439
Sequoia and Belladonna and Nettle, caught

00:06:28.439 --> 00:06:31.139
by the breath of evil, just as Sortell

00:06:31.139 --> 00:06:33.779
was, Blue's talons turning toward the

00:06:33.779 --> 00:06:36.779
jungle, his fire burning it all down.

00:06:36.839 --> 00:06:40.439
Soartell crouched into the savannah grass

00:06:40.439 --> 00:06:41.399
trying to breathe.

00:06:41.459 --> 00:06:43.259
It was morning now.

00:06:43.319 --> 00:06:45.600
They must have spent the whole previous

00:06:45.600 --> 00:06:47.579
day scorching the poison jungle.

00:06:47.639 --> 00:06:50.399
He remembered being in the squadron that

00:06:50.399 --> 00:06:52.259
was sent to gather all the breath of evil

00:06:52.259 --> 00:06:54.420
from its hidden lair before the fire

00:06:54.420 --> 00:06:55.259
reached that area.

00:06:55.319 --> 00:06:58.620
He also remembered searching for the rest

00:06:58.620 --> 00:06:59.519
of the leaf wings.

00:06:59.579 --> 00:07:02.339
The thing inside him had driven him

00:07:02.339 --> 00:07:04.379
relentlessly through the crackling

00:07:04.379 --> 00:07:06.779
smoking trees, looking for sundew and

00:07:06.779 --> 00:07:08.759
cricket, and the young leaf winged

00:07:08.759 --> 00:07:09.060
princess.

00:07:09.120 --> 00:07:12.240
That was probably why he was so sore and

00:07:12.240 --> 00:07:13.680
singed and scratched up.

00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:16.379
It was a miracle he hadn't been eaten by

00:07:16.379 --> 00:07:18.180
a frantic dying plant along the way.

00:07:18.240 --> 00:07:21.120
But he didn't remember finding any leaf

00:07:21.120 --> 00:07:21.480
wings.

00:07:21.540 --> 00:07:25.019
Sortell jumped to his feet, ignoring the

00:07:25.019 --> 00:07:25.980
pain in his talons.

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:28.860
He's fun, searching the savannah around

00:07:28.860 --> 00:07:29.339
him.

00:07:29.399 --> 00:07:33.180
Hundreds of hive wings, a few leaf wings

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:34.319
but nobody he recognized.

00:07:34.379 --> 00:07:36.000
No sundo.

00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:38.459
How had she escaped the smoke by the

00:07:38.459 --> 00:07:39.060
battlefield?

00:07:39.180 --> 00:07:40.560
Oh, wait.

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:43.319
She hadn't been there when Blue went to

00:07:43.319 --> 00:07:43.980
burn the roots.

00:07:44.100 --> 00:07:46.199
He didn't know where she'd gone.

00:07:46.259 --> 00:07:49.019
But maybe that meant her mind hadn't been

00:07:49.019 --> 00:07:49.439
taken over.

00:07:49.500 --> 00:07:52.620
And if they'd searched all day for her

00:07:52.620 --> 00:07:55.379
with no luck, maybe she'd really escaped

00:07:55.379 --> 00:07:57.779
along with cricket and the rest of the

00:07:57.779 --> 00:07:59.160
leaf wings who hadn't been near the

00:07:59.160 --> 00:07:59.399
smoke.

00:07:59.459 --> 00:08:01.379
Where could they be?

00:08:01.500 --> 00:08:05.160
He lifted one talon gingerly, then the

00:08:05.160 --> 00:08:05.339
other.

00:08:05.399 --> 00:08:08.040
He was controlling himself right now.

00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:10.620
His head felt curiously light.

00:08:10.680 --> 00:08:12.959
As if it had been caught in the grip of

00:08:12.959 --> 00:08:15.480
someone's talons all night, and they just

00:08:15.480 --> 00:08:15.899
released him.

00:08:16.019 --> 00:08:17.519
Cautiously.

00:08:17.579 --> 00:08:19.620
He started walking through the grass

00:08:19.620 --> 00:08:21.839
toward a flicker of bright blue wings

00:08:21.839 --> 00:08:23.100
near one of the shrubs.

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:24.420
Blue?

00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:26.399
If he could find blue.

00:08:26.459 --> 00:08:27.660
They could fly away together.

00:08:27.720 --> 00:08:30.360
Maybe the mind control had been

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:30.899
temporary.

00:08:30.959 --> 00:08:33.240
Or maybe it didn't work over long

00:08:33.240 --> 00:08:33.779
distances.

00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:36.600
Maybe they could fly out over the ocean

00:08:36.600 --> 00:08:39.240
as far as they could possibly get, and

00:08:39.240 --> 00:08:40.500
escape its clutches that way.

00:08:40.559 --> 00:08:42.659
It was blue.

00:08:42.720 --> 00:08:45.659
Sortell could see soot smudged along

00:08:45.659 --> 00:08:48.720
Blue's face and limbs and wings, but it

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:51.840
was unmistakably him, asleep, with his

00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:52.980
brow furrowed in worry.

00:08:53.039 --> 00:08:56.100
Sortell was a few steps away from his

00:08:56.100 --> 00:08:58.259
friend, when his legs suddenly froze.

00:08:58.320 --> 00:09:01.679
He felt a chill sweep through him, all

00:09:01.679 --> 00:09:03.899
his scales shivering away from believing

00:09:03.899 --> 00:09:05.399
that they'd been taken over again.

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:07.679
Nice try.

00:09:07.740 --> 00:09:09.779
His own voice whispered.

00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:12.600
His wings folded in, and he dropped to

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:15.480
the ground, stuck in place, trapped.

00:09:15.539 --> 00:09:19.080
So close to blue, but so far from

00:09:19.080 --> 00:09:19.440
himself.

00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:23.519
She has me in her claws, he thought.

00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:25.440
But she can't read my mind.

00:09:25.500 --> 00:09:27.600
She can't stop me from thinking.

00:09:27.659 --> 00:09:29.159
Or hoping.

00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:31.500
Blue and I may be stuck here.

00:09:31.620 --> 00:09:33.659
But I believe sundoo and cricket

00:09:33.659 --> 00:09:34.200
escaped.

00:09:34.320 --> 00:09:36.600
Maybe they went to find Luna.

00:09:36.659 --> 00:09:39.600
And if they did, I know they'll come back

00:09:39.600 --> 00:09:40.080
for us.

00:09:40.139 --> 00:09:42.240
They'll find a way to set us free.

00:09:42.299 --> 00:09:45.720
We just have to survive until they do.

00:09:45.779 --> 00:09:50.039
Part one.

00:09:50.100 --> 00:09:52.980
Blizzards and buried magic.

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:55.620
Chapter one.

00:09:55.679 --> 00:09:58.980
The youngest queen in the history of the

00:09:58.980 --> 00:10:02.100
Ice Kingdom was going to be the very best

00:10:02.100 --> 00:10:03.960
queen of the Ice Wings ever.

00:10:04.019 --> 00:10:05.519
Ever ever.

00:10:05.580 --> 00:10:07.019
The best.

00:10:07.080 --> 00:10:10.080
She was going to keep all her dragons

00:10:10.080 --> 00:10:10.500
safe.

00:10:10.559 --> 00:10:13.200
They were all going to be healthy and

00:10:13.200 --> 00:10:15.899
prosperous and safe, and no one was going

00:10:15.899 --> 00:10:18.659
to die of any more evil magic plagues

00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:20.100
like the one that killed the previous

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:20.639
queen.

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:22.559
No one.

00:10:22.679 --> 00:10:24.779
Not on her watch.

00:10:24.840 --> 00:10:28.679
Queen Snowfall had a plan, or at least

00:10:28.679 --> 00:10:31.620
she had a firm death grip on an idea that

00:10:31.620 --> 00:10:32.700
was kind of like a plan.

00:10:32.759 --> 00:10:37.259
That plan was, stay away from other

00:10:37.259 --> 00:10:37.860
dragons.

00:10:37.919 --> 00:10:41.759
No more getting involved in other tribes

00:10:41.759 --> 00:10:42.419
stupid wars.

00:10:42.480 --> 00:10:45.480
No more summits with queens who talked

00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:48.539
down to her, or eyed her as if she might

00:10:48.539 --> 00:10:49.919
be the one to start the next war.

00:10:49.980 --> 00:10:52.919
No more interactions with Nightwings

00:10:52.919 --> 00:10:53.519
ever.

00:10:53.580 --> 00:10:57.480
None of this intertribal, peace talk

00:10:57.480 --> 00:10:59.759
empathy building drum circle nonsense.

00:10:59.879 --> 00:11:02.879
Ice Wings were a great tribe.

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:05.580
They didn't need any other tribes.

00:11:05.639 --> 00:11:08.580
Those subjects of hers who wanted to go

00:11:08.580 --> 00:11:11.460
explore, to meet other dragons, and study

00:11:11.460 --> 00:11:13.440
in their perilous flammable schools.

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:16.620
They needed to be stuffed into igloos

00:11:16.620 --> 00:11:18.299
until they came to their senses.

00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:21.840
Her counsel had talked her into letting a

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:24.360
few ice wings go to Jade Mountain Academy

00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:25.139
for now.

00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:27.720
Instead of using her excellent igloo

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:27.960
plan.

00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:30.179
There had been so much alarming

00:11:30.179 --> 00:11:32.940
enthusiasm for the idea of connecting

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:33.899
with the other tribes.

00:11:34.019 --> 00:11:35.759
Why?

00:11:35.759 --> 00:11:36.659
was her question.

00:11:36.720 --> 00:11:40.080
How could anyone even want to be around

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:42.240
strange dragons after what had happened

00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:43.080
to their tribe?

00:11:43.139 --> 00:11:45.779
She was hoping the students they'd sent

00:11:45.779 --> 00:11:47.879
would come back with stories about how

00:11:47.879 --> 00:11:50.519
terrible the academy was, and that by

00:11:50.519 --> 00:11:52.740
then, all the other curious ice wings

00:11:52.740 --> 00:11:54.539
would have forgotten about ever wanting

00:11:54.539 --> 00:11:54.840
to leave.

00:11:54.899 --> 00:11:59.279
No, in Snowfall's vision of her reign, all

00:11:59.279 --> 00:12:02.159
ice wings would stay in the kingdom, where

00:12:02.159 --> 00:12:03.179
she could keep an eye on them.

00:12:03.240 --> 00:12:06.360
Other dragons would stay out of the

00:12:06.360 --> 00:12:07.919
kingdom, and there would be no more

00:12:07.919 --> 00:12:10.019
dealing with tribes that weren't them.

00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:13.019
It was a good plan, a straightforward

00:12:13.019 --> 00:12:18.899
plan, a nice, safe, brilliant plan, Except

00:12:18.899 --> 00:12:19.860
for the problems.

00:12:19.919 --> 00:12:24.179
Problems like queens who kept sending her

00:12:24.179 --> 00:12:27.179
messages about alliances and trade and

00:12:27.179 --> 00:12:29.159
building more schools like Jade Mountain

00:12:29.159 --> 00:12:29.580
Academy.

00:12:29.639 --> 00:12:34.139
Shut up, Queen Ruby, go away, Queen Glory

00:12:34.139 --> 00:12:36.659
deal with your own stupid dragons, Queen

00:12:36.659 --> 00:12:37.080
Thorn.

00:12:37.200 --> 00:12:40.379
Problems like the ice wings on her own

00:12:40.379 --> 00:12:42.240
council, who wanted to meet with the

00:12:42.240 --> 00:12:45.059
night wings and try to build a bridge

00:12:45.059 --> 00:12:48.419
over centuries of violence and hatred.

00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:51.360
After the blast of magic empathy that had

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:52.320
ended their last battle.

00:12:52.440 --> 00:12:56.399
Problems like not knowing exactly where

00:12:56.399 --> 00:12:58.440
everyone was, and having to wonder

00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:00.360
whether the missing dragons in question

00:13:00.360 --> 00:13:03.059
had left the ice kingdom or were still

00:13:03.059 --> 00:13:06.120
lurking around somewhere, maybe plotting

00:13:06.120 --> 00:13:07.620
some cold blooded murder.

00:13:07.679 --> 00:13:11.100
Most urgent, though, was the problem that

00:13:11.100 --> 00:13:14.519
100s of strange dragons were apparently

00:13:14.519 --> 00:13:16.740
flying toward her shores at that very

00:13:16.740 --> 00:13:17.279
moment.

00:13:17.340 --> 00:13:21.299
You're sure they aren't night wings?

00:13:21.360 --> 00:13:22.620
She demanded again.

00:13:22.679 --> 00:13:26.639
Her scout managed not to sigh, but she

00:13:26.639 --> 00:13:28.740
could tell that he wanted to, which was

00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:31.559
very disrespectful, and maybe she should

00:13:31.559 --> 00:13:32.220
have him punished.

00:13:32.279 --> 00:13:35.580
Wasn't that what a fierce, powerful very

00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:37.019
best queen ever would do?

00:13:37.080 --> 00:13:40.320
Punish dragons for disobeying her, or

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:42.659
thinking about disobeying her, or making

00:13:42.659 --> 00:13:44.639
faces as if they were trying not to make

00:13:44.639 --> 00:13:45.659
faces?

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:48.120
I could see flashes of different colors

00:13:48.120 --> 00:13:48.960
from their scales.

00:13:49.019 --> 00:13:50.159
He repeated.

00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:54.120
I promise you, my queen, mostly green, but

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:55.799
many, many other colors as well.

00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:58.259
No black dragons.

00:13:58.320 --> 00:13:59.940
They're not night wings.

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:03.120
Snowfall paced from one corner of the

00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:04.019
balcony to the other.

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:06.840
They were high on one of the tallest

00:14:06.840 --> 00:14:09.000
spires of the palace, with the wind

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.919
whisking pellets of ice all around them.

00:14:10.980 --> 00:14:13.860
The sun was low in the sky off to the

00:14:13.860 --> 00:14:16.620
west, painting the clouds gold and orange

00:14:16.620 --> 00:14:17.940
as it sank into the sea.

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:21.120
She knew they were out there, but no

00:14:21.120 --> 00:14:22.980
matter how fiercely snowfall glared at

00:14:22.980 --> 00:14:23.159
it.

00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:25.500
She couldn't see any dragons flying out

00:14:25.500 --> 00:14:25.980
of the sunset.

00:14:26.039 --> 00:14:29.159
She wondered if Nightwings had found a

00:14:29.159 --> 00:14:30.360
way to disguise their scales.

00:14:30.419 --> 00:14:33.600
Maybe Dark Stalker wasn't really gone

00:14:33.600 --> 00:14:36.480
even though all those not ice wings at

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.460
the Jade Mountain Academy promised he

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:39.419
was.

00:14:39.480 --> 00:14:41.759
Maybe he was still out there, and he'd

00:14:41.759 --> 00:14:43.259
come up with a way to turn night wings

00:14:43.259 --> 00:14:45.779
into multicolored rainbow dragons, and

00:14:45.779 --> 00:14:47.580
then he'd sent them far out into the

00:14:47.580 --> 00:14:50.639
ocean to fly in an enormous arc so they

00:14:50.639 --> 00:14:52.320
could come at the ice kingdom from the

00:14:52.320 --> 00:14:55.379
west and avoid the great ice cliff, and

00:14:55.379 --> 00:14:56.879
soon they would be her to kill her and

00:14:56.879 --> 00:14:57.659
her entire tribe.

00:14:57.720 --> 00:15:01.019
This was not far-fetched freaking out.

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:04.259
This was completely reasonable, justified

00:15:04.259 --> 00:15:04.980
freaking out.

00:15:05.039 --> 00:15:08.100
Her scout was looking at her as if he

00:15:08.100 --> 00:15:09.419
thought she might be losing her mind

00:15:09.419 --> 00:15:09.600
though.

00:15:09.720 --> 00:15:12.960
She had to put her queen face back on, and

00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:15.600
act as if an invasion of alarming rainbow

00:15:15.600 --> 00:15:18.120
dragons was the sort of thing excellent

00:15:18.120 --> 00:15:20.159
queens, such as herself, could easily

00:15:20.159 --> 00:15:20.580
handle.

00:15:20.639 --> 00:15:21.720
No problem.

00:15:21.779 --> 00:15:25.500
Well, if they're not night wings?

00:15:25.559 --> 00:15:26.220
What are they?

00:15:26.340 --> 00:15:27.600
She asked.

00:15:27.659 --> 00:15:30.659
He hesitated, and she answered her own

00:15:30.659 --> 00:15:30.960
question.

00:15:31.019 --> 00:15:33.179
Rain wings?

00:15:33.240 --> 00:15:34.679
I mean, rain wings.

00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:35.340
Of course.

00:15:35.399 --> 00:15:38.279
That's the only tribe with many colors, so

00:15:38.279 --> 00:15:40.139
perhaps with sea wings?

00:15:40.200 --> 00:15:41.340
Those can be green.

00:15:41.399 --> 00:15:43.740
It's probably a group of rain wings and

00:15:43.740 --> 00:15:44.700
sea wings.

00:15:44.759 --> 00:15:47.820
Why would rain wings and sea wings form

00:15:47.820 --> 00:15:49.620
an alliance to invade my kingdom from the

00:15:49.620 --> 00:15:49.860
west?

00:15:49.919 --> 00:15:51.840
Her brain screamed.

00:15:51.899 --> 00:15:54.360
Coral and Glory have betrayed me.

00:15:54.419 --> 00:15:56.940
They decided I'm too young to be queen

00:15:56.940 --> 00:15:58.139
and they're coming for my throne.

00:15:58.259 --> 00:16:01.320
Which is very unfair because glory is the

00:16:01.320 --> 00:16:04.019
same age as I am and she's queen of 2

00:16:04.019 --> 00:16:04.500
tribes.

00:16:04.559 --> 00:16:08.159
All right, Queen Glory probably wasn't

00:16:08.159 --> 00:16:09.899
coming to depose Snowfall because of her

00:16:09.899 --> 00:16:10.139
age.

00:16:10.200 --> 00:16:11.820
See?

00:16:11.879 --> 00:16:13.139
Her brain could figure that out.

00:16:13.200 --> 00:16:16.500
And so it was, ipso facto, working

00:16:16.500 --> 00:16:19.259
perfectly reasonably, and that meant all

00:16:19.259 --> 00:16:20.519
these other worries were entirely

00:16:20.519 --> 00:16:21.240
legitimate.

00:16:21.299 --> 00:16:25.080
Also, the rain wing tribe hadn't invaded

00:16:25.080 --> 00:16:27.240
another kingdom in literally 100s of

00:16:27.240 --> 00:16:27.480
years.

00:16:27.539 --> 00:16:30.419
They hadn't even participated in the War

00:16:30.419 --> 00:16:31.799
of Sandwing Succession.

00:16:31.860 --> 00:16:35.039
All they wanted to do was snooze around

00:16:35.039 --> 00:16:36.600
the rainforest eating papayas.

00:16:36.659 --> 00:16:39.720
They would be an utterly useless invasion

00:16:39.720 --> 00:16:40.139
force.

00:16:40.200 --> 00:16:42.840
If Glory did want to invade another

00:16:42.840 --> 00:16:44.639
kingdom, she'd have to do it with her

00:16:44.639 --> 00:16:47.100
night wings, who liked attacking and

00:16:47.100 --> 00:16:49.200
killing and stabbing and violence and

00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:50.460
lying and destroying things.

00:16:50.519 --> 00:16:54.419
So maybe glory found a way to turn night

00:16:54.419 --> 00:16:57.240
wings into rainbow dragons, and sent them

00:16:57.240 --> 00:16:59.759
this way, and so they are night wings

00:16:59.759 --> 00:17:00.120
after all.

00:17:00.179 --> 00:17:03.539
Snowfall rubbed her head, which was

00:17:03.539 --> 00:17:05.460
throbbing as though someone had shoved

00:17:05.460 --> 00:17:06.660
icicles through her temples.

00:17:06.720 --> 00:17:10.079
I don't think.

00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:13.200
The rain wings and sea wings would attack

00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:15.420
us, the scout said cautiously.

00:17:15.480 --> 00:17:17.940
Is your job thinking?

00:17:18.059 --> 00:17:20.759
Snowfall shouted, making him jump.

00:17:20.819 --> 00:17:23.459
Are you an expert thinker?

00:17:23.519 --> 00:17:25.740
Did we accidentally assign you to

00:17:25.740 --> 00:17:26.339
scouting?

00:17:26.400 --> 00:17:28.440
Because we missed your giant, amazing

00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:31.019
brain, and all the amazing things?

00:17:31.079 --> 00:17:32.519
It could have shared with us?

00:17:32.579 --> 00:17:34.559
Does it seem likely that your thinking

00:17:34.559 --> 00:17:35.640
would interest me?

00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:39.359
No, Your Majesty, he stammered.

00:17:39.420 --> 00:17:41.819
No, she agreed.

00:17:41.880 --> 00:17:43.799
You are a scout.

00:17:43.859 --> 00:17:46.680
Go scout again and come back with real

00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:47.940
actual information.

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:51.839
He flew away immediately, and then she

00:17:51.839 --> 00:17:53.460
spent 7 minutes worrying about whether

00:17:53.460 --> 00:17:55.380
she'd been too harsh with him, and

00:17:55.380 --> 00:17:56.819
whether an excellent queen would have

00:17:56.819 --> 00:17:59.339
said any of that, and whether a certain

00:17:59.339 --> 00:18:01.079
sister of hers would have been more

00:18:01.079 --> 00:18:04.619
serene, and therefore more excellent, and

00:18:04.619 --> 00:18:06.960
then another 12 minutes growling at

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:09.119
herself about how excellent queens didn't

00:18:09.119 --> 00:18:11.099
2nd guess themselves, and how she needed

00:18:11.099 --> 00:18:13.019
to be more decisive, and then she

00:18:13.019 --> 00:18:15.119
realized that she was accidentally

00:18:15.119 --> 00:18:17.160
thinking about murdery black dragons

00:18:17.160 --> 00:18:18.420
trying to murder her again.

00:18:18.720 --> 00:18:20.700
And she had to lie down and cover her

00:18:20.700 --> 00:18:21.420
face for a moment.

00:18:21.480 --> 00:18:25.859
When she finally sat up, her aunt Tundra

00:18:25.859 --> 00:18:27.420
was standing in the doorway of the

00:18:27.420 --> 00:18:29.819
balcony, watching her with impassive

00:18:29.819 --> 00:18:30.599
raised eyebrows.

00:18:30.660 --> 00:18:32.519
Hello.

00:18:32.579 --> 00:18:34.619
Snowfall said haughtily.

00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:37.680
I was definitely not panicking.

00:18:37.740 --> 00:18:40.740
I was resting my eyes in a very normal

00:18:40.740 --> 00:18:41.579
queenly fashion.

00:18:41.640 --> 00:18:44.039
I do not need to explain myself.

00:18:44.099 --> 00:18:47.519
I am the queen, and therefore, whatever I

00:18:47.519 --> 00:18:49.259
do is queenly, no matter what her

00:18:49.259 --> 00:18:49.980
eyebrows think.

00:18:50.039 --> 00:18:51.839
Good evening.

00:18:51.900 --> 00:18:53.460
Said her aunt.

00:18:53.519 --> 00:18:55.259
It is time for the wall.

00:18:55.380 --> 00:18:58.920
Of course it is, Snowfall said.

00:18:58.980 --> 00:19:01.079
How marvelous.

00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:03.299
My favorite part of the day.

00:19:03.420 --> 00:19:07.559
Tundra had a face that repelled sarcasm.

00:19:07.619 --> 00:19:10.859
No matter what snowfall said, no matter

00:19:10.859 --> 00:19:13.380
her tone of voice, it all slid right off

00:19:13.380 --> 00:19:14.700
that frozen expression.

00:19:14.759 --> 00:19:17.819
Tundra inclined her head slightly, and

00:19:17.819 --> 00:19:19.799
held out the jeweled box that contained

00:19:19.799 --> 00:19:20.880
the ice wing crown.

00:19:20.940 --> 00:19:24.660
As a little dragonet princess, Snowfall

00:19:24.660 --> 00:19:26.160
had looked forward to wearing the crown

00:19:26.160 --> 00:19:27.180
her entire life.

00:19:27.240 --> 00:19:30.839
Diamonds, sparkles, power.

00:19:30.900 --> 00:19:33.299
Everything she'd always wanted.

00:19:33.359 --> 00:19:36.240
Until the moment it officially became

00:19:36.240 --> 00:19:39.059
hers, when it became clear what Queen

00:19:39.059 --> 00:19:41.279
Snowfall had had to lose to get it.

00:19:41.339 --> 00:19:44.460
And now it was her least favorite thing

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:44.880
in the world.

00:19:44.940 --> 00:19:46.680
Well.

00:19:46.799 --> 00:19:49.680
Maybe Tundra's face was her least

00:19:49.680 --> 00:19:50.640
favorite thing in the world?

00:19:50.700 --> 00:19:53.220
But they usually came together, so she

00:19:53.220 --> 00:19:54.839
could hate them both simultaneously.

00:19:54.900 --> 00:19:58.380
Snowfall opened the box with an irritated

00:19:58.380 --> 00:20:00.480
sigh and lifted out the glittering

00:20:00.480 --> 00:20:02.640
diamond encrusted monstrosity.

00:20:02.700 --> 00:20:06.359
Spiraling spikes like icicles jutted up

00:20:06.359 --> 00:20:08.400
into the air, around a cluster of

00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:10.259
crystalline jewels and twisted silver

00:20:10.259 --> 00:20:10.680
arches.

00:20:10.740 --> 00:20:13.980
It weighed as much as a small polar bear

00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:16.140
and made her neck hurt the moment she put

00:20:16.140 --> 00:20:16.440
it on.

00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:19.259
But she couldn't let tundra see that.

00:20:19.319 --> 00:20:22.259
She tipped her chin up and flared her

00:20:22.259 --> 00:20:23.880
wings to usher her aunt ahead of her.

00:20:23.940 --> 00:20:26.759
Everyone says the war is over.

00:20:26.819 --> 00:20:29.519
Everyone says Dark Stalker is gone.

00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:32.579
Everyone says the night wings won't

00:20:32.579 --> 00:20:33.180
attack us again.

00:20:33.240 --> 00:20:35.400
But everyone could be wrong.

00:20:35.460 --> 00:20:38.640
The night wings can't be trusted.

00:20:38.700 --> 00:20:40.500
They want me dead.

00:20:40.559 --> 00:20:42.480
They want all of us dead.

00:20:42.539 --> 00:20:45.420
If I could find a way to wipe them all

00:20:45.420 --> 00:20:47.039
out first, I should.

00:20:47.099 --> 00:20:50.880
Tundra's necklace of sky wing teeth

00:20:50.880 --> 00:20:52.799
clicked noisily as they strode through

00:20:52.799 --> 00:20:53.279
the palace.

00:20:53.339 --> 00:20:56.099
Snowfall pressed her talons to her eyes

00:20:56.099 --> 00:20:57.900
for a moment, trying to drive the

00:20:57.900 --> 00:20:58.500
headache away.

00:20:58.619 --> 00:21:02.400
Being the queen, it turned out, was like

00:21:02.400 --> 00:21:03.960
living inside a snowstorm that never

00:21:03.960 --> 00:21:04.259
ended.

00:21:04.319 --> 00:21:07.799
She tried so hard to start each day all

00:21:07.799 --> 00:21:11.220
new, with a list and a plan and energy.

00:21:11.279 --> 00:21:13.319
She'd get so much done.

00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:16.559
Each new problem was a mere snowflake.

00:21:16.619 --> 00:21:18.779
She could tackle them one by one.

00:21:18.839 --> 00:21:21.720
Little, sparkly, quick melting problems.

00:21:21.779 --> 00:21:25.200
Except the snowflakes piled up faster

00:21:25.200 --> 00:21:25.980
than she could fly.

00:21:26.039 --> 00:21:29.880
Sparkles on sparkles on fluff on ice, on

00:21:29.880 --> 00:21:33.359
cold, on heavy, wet layers of slush and

00:21:33.359 --> 00:21:34.559
freezing clumps.

00:21:34.619 --> 00:21:37.559
And by night, she was buried far below

00:21:37.559 --> 00:21:37.980
them.

00:21:38.039 --> 00:21:41.819
And then, every night, just when it was

00:21:41.819 --> 00:21:42.660
all too much.

00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:45.180
Her Aunt Tundra would appear with her

00:21:45.180 --> 00:21:48.359
cold marble face, and that meant it was

00:21:48.359 --> 00:21:48.960
time for the wall.

00:21:49.079 --> 00:21:52.140
According to the ancient tradition of the

00:21:52.140 --> 00:21:52.559
tribe.

00:21:52.619 --> 00:21:55.500
Every night, the queen of the ice wings

00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:57.660
had to consider the wall that listed

00:21:57.660 --> 00:21:59.940
every important dragon in the tribe, and

00:21:59.940 --> 00:22:01.859
then she had to adjust the rankings of

00:22:01.859 --> 00:22:03.720
all the dragons in the aristocracy.

00:22:03.779 --> 00:22:06.660
Every night.

00:22:06.720 --> 00:22:09.359
His idea was this?

00:22:09.480 --> 00:22:12.900
Snowfall had always considered the wall

00:22:12.900 --> 00:22:16.200
known as the gift of order, to be one of

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:17.579
the best magic things in the kingdom.

00:22:17.700 --> 00:22:21.059
She used to wake up before the sun and

00:22:21.059 --> 00:22:23.339
soar down to the courtyard to see where

00:22:23.339 --> 00:22:24.599
her name was each morning.

00:22:24.660 --> 00:22:28.799
She loved watching the word, snowfall

00:22:28.799 --> 00:22:31.740
climb higher and higher as she worked and

00:22:31.740 --> 00:22:34.319
trained and studied, until she was at the

00:22:34.319 --> 00:22:36.420
very top of the dragonette's side of the

00:22:36.420 --> 00:22:36.779
rankings.

00:22:36.839 --> 00:22:38.519
And there it stayed.

00:22:38.640 --> 00:22:40.079
Moon after moon.

00:22:40.140 --> 00:22:43.319
Apart from that unfortunate blip when her

00:22:43.319 --> 00:22:44.700
cousins messed everything up for a few

00:22:44.700 --> 00:22:44.940
days.

00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:48.960
But then winter was gone, and Hailstorm

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:50.940
moved over to the adult wall, and

00:22:50.940 --> 00:22:52.619
snowfall was in her proper place at the

00:22:52.619 --> 00:22:55.259
top again, and it was excellent to look

00:22:55.259 --> 00:22:55.500
at.

00:22:55.559 --> 00:22:59.460
Best Dragonette in the whole kingdom, the

00:22:59.460 --> 00:23:01.200
wall reassured her, morning after

00:23:01.200 --> 00:23:01.619
morning.

00:23:01.680 --> 00:23:03.539
You are doing great.

00:23:03.599 --> 00:23:05.279
Even your mother thinks so.

00:23:05.339 --> 00:23:07.920
She put you right here at the top because

00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:10.559
she sees how undeniably great you are.

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:13.740
Sometimes it felt like a secret message

00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:15.000
from Queen Glacier.

00:23:15.059 --> 00:23:19.019
Like, don't worry, I remember you, even

00:23:19.019 --> 00:23:20.279
though we haven't been in the same room

00:23:20.279 --> 00:23:20.819
in a while.

00:23:20.940 --> 00:23:23.339
I am quite pleased to have a daughter

00:23:23.339 --> 00:23:23.759
like you.

00:23:23.819 --> 00:23:26.220
I appreciate that you are not

00:23:26.220 --> 00:23:26.880
embarrassing me.

00:23:26.940 --> 00:23:29.400
It wasn't like that now.

00:23:29.460 --> 00:23:32.460
The wall did not tell Snowball.

00:23:32.519 --> 00:23:33.839
She was undeniably great anymore.

00:23:33.900 --> 00:23:36.900
It said, well?

00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:41.220
And make some decisions, and stop

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:41.880
tithering.

00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:44.819
And a good queen would have no trouble

00:23:44.819 --> 00:23:45.180
with this.

00:23:45.299 --> 00:23:48.839
And what happened to being the best queen

00:23:48.839 --> 00:23:49.140
ever?

00:23:49.200 --> 00:23:51.480
Why are you such a disaster?

00:23:51.539 --> 00:23:55.859
There were no more messages, unspoken or

00:23:55.859 --> 00:23:57.299
otherwise, from her mother.

00:23:57.359 --> 00:24:02.460
Now the word snowfall was set apart, in

00:24:02.460 --> 00:24:04.559
its own little queen corner, off by

00:24:04.559 --> 00:24:04.920
itself.

00:24:04.980 --> 00:24:08.339
Now the task of reordering the rankings

00:24:08.339 --> 00:24:11.160
every night was her job, and Snowfall had

00:24:11.160 --> 00:24:13.140
begun to suspect that the gift of order

00:24:13.140 --> 00:24:15.779
was less a gift, and more an act of

00:24:15.779 --> 00:24:16.619
twisted revenge.

00:24:16.680 --> 00:24:20.099
Some queen must have angered her anima

00:24:20.099 --> 00:24:23.400
somehow, and he or she had responded by

00:24:23.400 --> 00:24:26.160
crafting this torture device, perfectly

00:24:26.160 --> 00:24:28.740
designed to drive ice wing queens insane

00:24:28.740 --> 00:24:29.759
for the rest of time.

00:24:29.819 --> 00:24:33.480
Once upon a time, Snowfall had thought

00:24:33.480 --> 00:24:35.099
she would love this part of being Queen.

00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:37.980
The fate of all her dragons in her own

00:24:37.980 --> 00:24:40.920
talons, the power to lift up those most

00:24:40.920 --> 00:24:42.960
loyal and knock down her enemies.

00:24:43.019 --> 00:24:45.359
But it didn't feel like power.

00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:48.900
It felt like work, pinning her down like

00:24:48.900 --> 00:24:50.099
the weight of the crown.

00:24:50.160 --> 00:24:54.180
Icy rain drizzled down, as snowfall

00:24:54.180 --> 00:24:55.559
stared up at the wall of rankings.

00:24:55.680 --> 00:24:58.259
The light globe floating over her

00:24:58.259 --> 00:25:00.059
shoulder lit up the names in front of

00:25:00.059 --> 00:25:00.240
her.

00:25:00.299 --> 00:25:03.900
Behind her, the 3 moons illuminated the

00:25:03.900 --> 00:25:04.680
snowy courtyard.

00:25:04.740 --> 00:25:09.660
Silver, empty, cold and wet, speckled

00:25:09.660 --> 00:25:11.460
with weird shadows from the light tree.

00:25:11.519 --> 00:25:13.380
Empty.

00:25:13.440 --> 00:25:17.339
Only 20 ice wings had died of the plague

00:25:17.339 --> 00:25:20.220
only, +13 more in the battle with the

00:25:20.220 --> 00:25:22.200
night wings, but since snowfall became

00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:25.140
queen, the palace had felt as empty as if

00:25:25.140 --> 00:25:27.119
the entire tribe had vanished into thin

00:25:27.119 --> 00:25:29.099
air the day Queen Glacier died.

00:25:29.160 --> 00:25:33.359
The entire tribe, that is, in addition to

00:25:33.359 --> 00:25:34.799
the one sister who had actually

00:25:34.799 --> 00:25:35.519
vanished.

00:25:35.579 --> 00:25:38.220
Maybe the rest of the ice wings

00:25:38.220 --> 00:25:40.019
deliberately made themselves scarce

00:25:40.019 --> 00:25:40.980
whenever they saw her coming.

00:25:41.039 --> 00:25:43.559
Maybe that was always what it was like

00:25:43.559 --> 00:25:44.099
for a queen.

00:25:44.160 --> 00:25:48.480
Well, Tundra asked smoothly.

00:25:48.539 --> 00:25:50.819
Who are you going to move?

00:25:50.880 --> 00:25:54.180
Yeah, agreed the wall.

00:25:54.240 --> 00:25:56.099
Your mother never took this long.

00:25:56.220 --> 00:25:58.740
Snowfall's head hurt.

00:25:58.799 --> 00:26:00.839
Her teeth hurt.

00:26:00.900 --> 00:26:03.240
Why did her teeth hurt?

00:26:03.299 --> 00:26:05.519
Every night?

00:26:05.579 --> 00:26:06.839
She had to do this.

00:26:06.900 --> 00:26:10.200
Even when she had much more urgent crises

00:26:10.200 --> 00:26:12.420
to deal with than the hierarchy of palace

00:26:12.420 --> 00:26:12.900
dragons.

00:26:12.960 --> 00:26:15.660
Such as the dragons that were coming

00:26:15.660 --> 00:26:17.519
across the ocean right at this moment

00:26:17.519 --> 00:26:20.460
preparing to tramp their dangerous talons

00:26:20.460 --> 00:26:22.319
all over her snowy kingdom.

00:26:22.380 --> 00:26:25.079
She wished she had a list of their names

00:26:25.079 --> 00:26:28.200
and an entire history of their tribes, and

00:26:28.200 --> 00:26:30.599
an explanation for their behavior, and an

00:26:30.599 --> 00:26:31.859
outline of what they were planning to do

00:26:31.859 --> 00:26:33.839
when they got here, plus a battle

00:26:33.839 --> 00:26:35.099
strategy for getting rid of them.

00:26:35.160 --> 00:26:37.740
Tundra cleared her throat.

00:26:37.799 --> 00:26:39.240
Right.

00:26:39.299 --> 00:26:40.619
The wall.

00:26:40.680 --> 00:26:43.920
Snowfall adjusted a heavy crown on her

00:26:43.920 --> 00:26:44.759
aching head.

00:26:44.819 --> 00:26:47.279
She couldn't remember even seeing half

00:26:47.279 --> 00:26:48.180
these dragons today.

00:26:48.240 --> 00:26:50.759
How is she supposed to know whether they

00:26:50.759 --> 00:26:52.259
deserve to move up or down?

00:26:52.319 --> 00:26:55.859
When everyone avoided her or spoke to her

00:26:55.859 --> 00:26:57.480
in polite monosyllables.

00:26:57.539 --> 00:26:59.339
Where was she supposed to hear about the

00:26:59.339 --> 00:27:02.220
squabbles, mistakes, outrages, or

00:27:02.220 --> 00:27:03.839
triumphs in their freezing little

00:27:03.839 --> 00:27:04.980
aristocratic world?

00:27:05.039 --> 00:27:08.279
How did mother always know everything?

00:27:08.400 --> 00:27:11.940
Snowfall glanced sideways at her aunt?

00:27:12.000 --> 00:27:15.720
Tundra had lost her husband, Norwhal, and

00:27:15.720 --> 00:27:17.160
the ice wing night wing battle.

00:27:17.220 --> 00:27:20.400
One of her children lived in exile, and

00:27:20.400 --> 00:27:22.079
another was in prison awaiting trial

00:27:22.079 --> 00:27:24.180
while the 3rd was recovering from a very

00:27:24.180 --> 00:27:25.380
bizarre magic spell.

00:27:25.500 --> 00:27:28.079
Snowfall didn't know quite what to think

00:27:28.079 --> 00:27:29.220
of Hillstorm these days.

00:27:29.279 --> 00:27:33.180
He seemed rigidly perfect on the outside

00:27:33.180 --> 00:27:35.940
and all melted together on the inside.

00:27:36.059 --> 00:27:39.359
Tundra looked exactly the same, though.

00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:43.500
Snowfall never saw a hint of sadness or

00:27:43.500 --> 00:27:45.660
rage or resentment in her face.

00:27:45.720 --> 00:27:48.720
Even though they both knew perfectly well

00:27:48.720 --> 00:27:51.240
the tundra had always hoped her daughter

00:27:51.240 --> 00:27:53.339
Icicle, would take the throne from

00:27:53.339 --> 00:27:54.900
glacier before snowfall could.

00:27:54.960 --> 00:27:57.599
Never going to happen now.

00:27:57.660 --> 00:27:59.099
Snowfall thought.

00:27:59.160 --> 00:28:01.559
After all those years of competing.

00:28:01.619 --> 00:28:04.140
Suddenly, I'm the queen, and icicles

00:28:04.140 --> 00:28:06.059
locked in the dungeon for being a traitor

00:28:06.059 --> 00:28:07.859
and none of it was up to me in the end.

00:28:07.920 --> 00:28:10.079
She lifted her chin.

00:28:10.140 --> 00:28:14.579
Act like a queen, all the time, no matter

00:28:14.579 --> 00:28:15.720
how much your teeth hurt.

00:28:15.779 --> 00:28:18.599
Hellstorm could go up a notch.

00:28:18.720 --> 00:28:21.539
He had annoyed her at all today. and it

00:28:21.539 --> 00:28:23.640
would please Tundra, so perhaps she'd let

00:28:23.640 --> 00:28:25.440
Snowfall cut this short without too many

00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:25.859
more changes.

00:28:25.920 --> 00:28:29.099
Snowfall stabbed her claws into

00:28:29.099 --> 00:28:30.779
Hellstorm's name and dragged him up a

00:28:30.779 --> 00:28:30.960
spot.

00:28:31.019 --> 00:28:33.720
She left Tundra's name where it was.

00:28:33.839 --> 00:28:36.900
Safely in the 1st circle ever since

00:28:36.900 --> 00:28:39.059
narwhal sacrificed himself to save the

00:28:39.059 --> 00:28:39.539
new queen.

00:28:39.599 --> 00:28:43.200
She also left Crystal up among the top 10

00:28:43.200 --> 00:28:45.779
names, even though she could feel Tundra

00:28:45.779 --> 00:28:47.640
glaring at it intently every night.

00:28:47.640 --> 00:28:50.519
Wherever Crystal was, she was still a

00:28:50.519 --> 00:28:50.880
princess.

00:28:50.940 --> 00:28:53.400
She hadn't done anything terrible that

00:28:53.400 --> 00:28:54.299
Snowfall knew of.

00:28:54.359 --> 00:28:57.839
She wasn't definitely out there trying to

00:28:57.839 --> 00:29:00.180
raise an army to steal snowfall's throne

00:29:00.180 --> 00:29:02.579
and she wasn't certainly hiding in the

00:29:02.579 --> 00:29:04.619
palace, trying to poison snowfall's

00:29:04.619 --> 00:29:04.859
food.

00:29:04.920 --> 00:29:07.740
She was only maybe doing those things.

00:29:07.799 --> 00:29:10.440
Snowfall could knock her down the list

00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:13.319
for maybe crimes, even if the maybeness

00:29:13.319 --> 00:29:14.940
of them was terrifying enough.

00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:17.759
If she left Crystal's name and place.

00:29:17.819 --> 00:29:19.740
She hoped it would look as though she

00:29:19.740 --> 00:29:21.359
wasn't afraid of her sister at all.

00:29:21.420 --> 00:29:25.319
She reordered a few other names, trying

00:29:25.319 --> 00:29:27.539
to keep her eyebrows arched in a bored

00:29:27.539 --> 00:29:28.319
haughty way.

00:29:28.380 --> 00:29:31.799
So easy, this boring task.

00:29:31.859 --> 00:29:33.539
Her eyebrows yawned.

00:29:33.599 --> 00:29:35.640
Easiest task in the world.

00:29:35.700 --> 00:29:38.160
Definitely not, frying all my brain

00:29:38.160 --> 00:29:38.700
cells.

00:29:38.759 --> 00:29:40.619
Really?

00:29:40.680 --> 00:29:42.839
Tundra said once.

00:29:42.900 --> 00:29:45.720
As snowfalls lit her uncle permafrost

00:29:45.720 --> 00:29:48.839
down a notch for pointing out, again, how

00:29:48.839 --> 00:29:51.000
easy it would be for sea wings to invade

00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:52.859
from the northern oceanside of the ice

00:29:52.859 --> 00:29:55.380
kingdom, a reminder that snowfall really

00:29:55.380 --> 00:29:57.599
did not need right now, thanks very

00:29:57.599 --> 00:29:57.839
much.

00:29:57.900 --> 00:30:00.539
Tundra snapped her jaw shut.

00:30:00.660 --> 00:30:02.339
A snowfall glared at her.

00:30:02.400 --> 00:30:05.700
Finally, Snowfall stepped back, shaking

00:30:05.700 --> 00:30:06.299
her talons.

00:30:06.359 --> 00:30:09.059
Her claws felt as if they might shiver

00:30:09.059 --> 00:30:10.559
into a 1000000 pieces in a moment.

00:30:10.619 --> 00:30:13.500
The wall always made them feel that way

00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:16.380
and they were always fine after a while

00:30:16.380 --> 00:30:17.339
but it was unpleasant.

00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:23.279
That's your final decision, Tundra said

00:30:23.279 --> 00:30:25.740
with just a hint of skepticism in her

00:30:25.740 --> 00:30:28.380
voice, easily denied if Snowfall had

00:30:28.380 --> 00:30:28.920
snapped at her.

00:30:28.980 --> 00:30:30.359
Yes.

00:30:30.420 --> 00:30:33.059
Snowfall couldn't take another moment of

00:30:33.059 --> 00:30:33.299
this.

00:30:33.359 --> 00:30:35.759
She had to figure out what to do about

00:30:35.759 --> 00:30:36.720
the approaching dragons.

00:30:36.779 --> 00:30:40.140
The only other ice wing who knew was the

00:30:40.140 --> 00:30:41.339
scout who'd reported it to her.

00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:45.359
That animus Sandwing, Jerboa, knew too.

00:30:45.480 --> 00:30:48.420
Snowfall had gone to her for a spell to

00:30:48.420 --> 00:30:50.460
protect them, but it hadn't been any help

00:30:50.460 --> 00:30:53.220
because animus magic was broken, or

00:30:53.220 --> 00:30:55.920
Draboa was lying to her, and either way

00:30:55.920 --> 00:30:56.519
she was useless.

00:30:56.579 --> 00:30:59.339
So Snowfall needed to deal with the

00:30:59.339 --> 00:31:02.220
invasion by herself, somehow, although so

00:31:02.220 --> 00:31:04.200
far her strategy of pacing around her at

00:31:04.200 --> 00:31:06.119
their own room all night, hadn't been

00:31:06.119 --> 00:31:06.960
particularly effective.

00:31:07.019 --> 00:31:08.759
Even so.

00:31:08.940 --> 00:31:10.380
Alone.

00:31:10.440 --> 00:31:12.180
That was what she wanted to be.

00:31:12.240 --> 00:31:16.140
Or, specifically, somewhere far away from

00:31:16.140 --> 00:31:16.740
tundra.

00:31:16.799 --> 00:31:19.799
She wrestled the giant crown off her head

00:31:19.799 --> 00:31:22.079
and shoved it into her aunt's talons.

00:31:22.140 --> 00:31:24.000
Her headache eased a little.

00:31:24.059 --> 00:31:27.359
Go away, she snapped.

00:31:27.420 --> 00:31:28.140
Now.

00:31:28.259 --> 00:31:32.400
Tundra bowed and swept off, leaving only

00:31:32.400 --> 00:31:34.319
a faint vibration of disapproval in the

00:31:34.319 --> 00:31:34.920
air behind her.

00:31:34.980 --> 00:31:38.039
She never said anything obvious to remind

00:31:38.039 --> 00:31:40.619
Snowfall that only a few months ago.

00:31:40.680 --> 00:31:43.019
Tundra and Narwhal had been practically

00:31:43.019 --> 00:31:45.180
2nd in command to Quinn Glacier.

00:31:45.240 --> 00:31:48.000
She never even hinted at memories of

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:48.960
their former relationship.

00:31:49.019 --> 00:31:52.559
Back then, Snowfall had been so careful

00:31:52.559 --> 00:31:55.140
about every word she said, afraid of

00:31:55.140 --> 00:31:56.880
offending her aunt and falling down the

00:31:56.880 --> 00:31:57.720
ranks as a result.

00:31:57.779 --> 00:32:01.319
Snowfall knew Tundra must hate the fact

00:32:01.319 --> 00:32:03.180
that she had to bow to her niece now.

00:32:03.240 --> 00:32:06.839
And probably Snowfall wasn't helping the

00:32:06.839 --> 00:32:09.000
situation by barking at her and ordering

00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:09.359
her around.

00:32:09.420 --> 00:32:11.579
She couldn't help it though.

00:32:11.640 --> 00:32:13.680
She was too overwhelmed by everything

00:32:13.680 --> 00:32:16.319
else to add being more polite to Aunt

00:32:16.319 --> 00:32:17.339
Tundra to her list.

00:32:17.460 --> 00:32:20.940
If there was one upside to being queen

00:32:20.940 --> 00:32:23.220
surely it was that she could finally snap

00:32:23.220 --> 00:32:24.299
at dragons who deserved it.

00:32:24.359 --> 00:32:25.740
Couldn't she?

00:32:25.799 --> 00:32:27.720
Maybe she couldn't.

00:32:27.779 --> 00:32:32.039
Maybe that was worst queen behavior, not

00:32:32.039 --> 00:32:32.940
best queen.

00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:35.700
Maybe she was messing this all up every

00:32:35.700 --> 00:32:36.839
time she opened her mouth.

00:32:36.900 --> 00:32:39.420
She glanced up at the wall again.

00:32:39.480 --> 00:32:42.059
The wall didn't say anything.

00:32:42.119 --> 00:32:43.079
Of course it didn't.

00:32:43.140 --> 00:32:43.980
It was a wall.

00:32:44.039 --> 00:32:46.440
But it was clearly thinking about how

00:32:46.440 --> 00:32:49.440
civil Queen Glacier always was, and it

00:32:49.440 --> 00:32:50.579
was definitely judging her.

00:32:50.640 --> 00:32:53.039
This is sane.

00:32:53.099 --> 00:32:55.559
It is normal to feel judged by magic

00:32:55.559 --> 00:32:55.980
walls.

00:32:56.039 --> 00:32:58.680
I am a perfectly sane queen with a well

00:32:58.680 --> 00:33:00.720
functioning brain and everything is

00:33:00.720 --> 00:33:01.500
fine.

00:33:01.559 --> 00:33:04.440
Something snapped in the courtyard behind

00:33:04.440 --> 00:33:04.680
her.

00:33:04.740 --> 00:33:08.099
Snowfall whirled around and stared

00:33:08.099 --> 00:33:09.660
through the icy raindrops.

00:33:09.720 --> 00:33:14.400
It all looked the same, pale, icy, wet

00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:15.359
weird shadows.

00:33:15.420 --> 00:33:17.400
But it wasn't empty.

00:33:17.460 --> 00:33:19.440
Someone was there.

00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:21.900
Someone was watching her.

00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:26.220
Chapter 2.

00:33:26.460 --> 00:33:29.220
It's Dark Stalker.

00:33:29.279 --> 00:33:31.259
He is here to finish the job of killing

00:33:31.259 --> 00:33:31.680
us all.

00:33:31.740 --> 00:33:33.180
Or another night wing.

00:33:33.240 --> 00:33:34.920
Or crystal.

00:33:34.980 --> 00:33:37.259
Definitely a murdery dragon about to kill

00:33:37.259 --> 00:33:37.440
me.

00:33:37.559 --> 00:33:41.160
Show yourself, Snowfall shouted.

00:33:41.220 --> 00:33:42.599
I know you're there.

00:33:42.660 --> 00:33:46.259
She inhaled a gust of frost breath, ready

00:33:46.259 --> 00:33:48.599
to unleash freezing death on her assassin

00:33:48.599 --> 00:33:50.640
and charged toward the tree of light.

00:33:50.700 --> 00:33:54.119
A figure moved among the branches, wings

00:33:54.119 --> 00:33:56.460
spreading, and snowfall bared her teeth.

00:33:56.579 --> 00:33:59.400
Ah, the figure shouted.

00:33:59.460 --> 00:34:01.680
Stop. snowfall, it's me.

00:34:01.740 --> 00:34:04.559
The dragon tumbled out of the tree and

00:34:04.559 --> 00:34:07.079
landed awkwardly among its roots, trying

00:34:07.079 --> 00:34:09.840
to stand and bow and duck behind the

00:34:09.840 --> 00:34:10.860
trunk at the same time.

00:34:10.920 --> 00:34:13.500
Snowfalls get into a stop.

00:34:13.559 --> 00:34:17.159
The dragon's scales were white, freckled

00:34:17.159 --> 00:34:18.659
with dark blue, not black.

00:34:18.780 --> 00:34:20.340
Not a night wing.

00:34:20.400 --> 00:34:22.860
The dark blue meant it wasn't crystal

00:34:22.860 --> 00:34:23.219
either.

00:34:23.280 --> 00:34:26.219
She swallowed her frost breath back down

00:34:26.219 --> 00:34:27.960
and lowered her head to squint at the

00:34:27.960 --> 00:34:28.199
spy.

00:34:28.260 --> 00:34:30.420
Lynx?

00:34:30.539 --> 00:34:33.239
Hi, said the dragonette.

00:34:33.300 --> 00:34:35.940
Hello, thank you for not freezing me.

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:37.260
Hi, Snowfall.

00:34:37.380 --> 00:34:39.360
Queen, snowfall.

00:34:39.420 --> 00:34:41.340
Snowfall snapped automatically.

00:34:41.400 --> 00:34:43.920
Ling's had been her biggest competition

00:34:43.920 --> 00:34:45.539
all through school and training.

00:34:45.599 --> 00:34:48.179
At least, Dr. Hillstorm was captured by

00:34:48.179 --> 00:34:49.019
Skywings.

00:34:49.079 --> 00:34:51.360
She was only the daughter of a minor

00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:53.880
noble, but she was hardworking and clever

00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:55.500
and good at making teachers like her.

00:34:55.559 --> 00:34:57.960
And Snowfall had wanted to strangle her

00:34:57.960 --> 00:34:59.340
more than a 1000 times.

00:34:59.400 --> 00:35:03.599
Right, Link said, glancing over her

00:35:03.599 --> 00:35:04.860
shoulder as though she was already

00:35:04.860 --> 00:35:06.000
regretting this conversation.

00:35:06.059 --> 00:35:08.219
Queen snowfall.

00:35:08.280 --> 00:35:09.000
Sorry.

00:35:09.059 --> 00:35:12.059
She didn't sound sorry.

00:35:12.119 --> 00:35:12.300
Sorry.

00:35:12.360 --> 00:35:14.579
She sounded like she always had

00:35:14.579 --> 00:35:17.219
challenging snowfall to races around the

00:35:17.219 --> 00:35:19.739
palace, or arguing over points of ice

00:35:19.739 --> 00:35:20.519
wing law in class.

00:35:20.579 --> 00:35:23.099
Snowfall narrowed her eyes.

00:35:23.159 --> 00:35:25.920
Lynx was still a year away from moving to

00:35:25.920 --> 00:35:28.440
the adult wall, and without snowfall, or

00:35:28.440 --> 00:35:31.019
any of the cousins left on there, Lynx

00:35:31.019 --> 00:35:32.519
had been sitting easily at the top of the

00:35:32.519 --> 00:35:33.360
dragonette list.

00:35:33.420 --> 00:35:35.760
But snowfall could move her down.

00:35:35.820 --> 00:35:38.940
Snowfall could flick her all the way into

00:35:38.940 --> 00:35:40.440
the 7th circle if she wanted to.

00:35:40.500 --> 00:35:43.320
Snowfall was the queen now.

00:35:43.440 --> 00:35:46.500
Deciding that lynx was a disrespectful

00:35:46.500 --> 00:35:48.780
nobody who deserved to be squashed back

00:35:48.780 --> 00:35:51.719
into her place, was absolutely Snowfall's

00:35:51.719 --> 00:35:51.840
job.

00:35:51.900 --> 00:35:54.480
What are you doing here?

00:35:54.599 --> 00:35:56.099
Snowfall demanded.

00:35:56.159 --> 00:35:57.780
Are you spying on me?

00:35:57.840 --> 00:35:59.699
A normal dragon?

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:01.920
With a healthy fear of punishment?

00:36:01.980 --> 00:36:03.059
Would have denied it immediately.

00:36:03.119 --> 00:36:06.599
But Lynx made a rueful phase, spread her

00:36:06.599 --> 00:36:08.699
wings and said, I am, actually.

00:36:08.760 --> 00:36:10.500
What?

00:36:10.500 --> 00:36:11.400
You are?

00:36:11.519 --> 00:36:13.619
Snowfall's gal, Datter.

00:36:13.679 --> 00:36:14.639
Why?

00:36:14.699 --> 00:36:16.920
Is she working with the Nightwings?

00:36:16.980 --> 00:36:18.659
Or the invading dragons?

00:36:18.719 --> 00:36:19.860
Or crystal?

00:36:19.920 --> 00:36:21.300
Or all of the above?

00:36:21.360 --> 00:36:23.519
Or writing to my cousin Winter about what

00:36:23.519 --> 00:36:25.019
a terrible job I'm doing?

00:36:25.079 --> 00:36:26.880
They were always too friendly, those

00:36:26.880 --> 00:36:27.119
two.

00:36:27.179 --> 00:36:30.179
Maybe she's convinced him to round up a

00:36:30.179 --> 00:36:31.559
bunch of ceilings to attack us.

00:36:31.619 --> 00:36:34.019
I don't know why, but it's possible.

00:36:34.079 --> 00:36:36.239
Because I'm worried about you.

00:36:36.300 --> 00:36:37.860
Ling said frankly.

00:36:37.920 --> 00:36:39.360
Snowfall.

00:36:39.420 --> 00:36:40.559
Are you all right?

00:36:40.619 --> 00:36:42.780
Snowfalls?

00:36:42.840 --> 00:36:43.920
Entire brain?

00:36:43.980 --> 00:36:45.000
Stopped working.

00:36:45.059 --> 00:36:47.880
It just rolled over and lay there.

00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:50.280
Suddenly full of nothing to say after

00:36:50.280 --> 00:36:52.199
months of nonstop yelling about

00:36:52.199 --> 00:36:52.860
everything.

00:36:52.920 --> 00:36:57.119
Her mouth was all, hello, any thoughts?

00:36:57.179 --> 00:37:00.059
And the response was apparently, nope

00:37:00.059 --> 00:37:02.579
just flap around like a bewildered walrus

00:37:02.579 --> 00:37:03.000
for a while.

00:37:03.059 --> 00:37:05.099
Snowfall?

00:37:05.099 --> 00:37:07.260
Link said after a moment.

00:37:07.320 --> 00:37:10.199
Are you, did I break you?

00:37:10.260 --> 00:37:12.900
She reached out and tapped lightly on

00:37:12.900 --> 00:37:13.860
Snowfall's forehead.

00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:17.340
Nobody tapped on the queen's forehead.

00:37:17.460 --> 00:37:20.099
Snowfall jumped back and stared at her.

00:37:20.219 --> 00:37:23.280
Nobody asked if the queen was all right

00:37:23.280 --> 00:37:23.699
either.

00:37:23.760 --> 00:37:26.639
She had never been asked that question

00:37:26.639 --> 00:37:29.460
and certainly not since she became ruler

00:37:29.460 --> 00:37:30.780
of the whole Ice Kingdom.

00:37:30.840 --> 00:37:33.539
Of course, I'm all right.

00:37:33.599 --> 00:37:34.800
She snapped.

00:37:34.860 --> 00:37:36.539
I am the queen.

00:37:36.599 --> 00:37:40.800
Those 2 things don't necessarily go

00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:41.219
together.

00:37:41.280 --> 00:37:42.599
Links observed.

00:37:42.659 --> 00:37:45.659
I think maybe the opposite, actually.

00:37:45.719 --> 00:37:48.059
Why don't you think I'm all right?

00:37:48.179 --> 00:37:49.860
Snowball demanded.

00:37:49.920 --> 00:37:51.300
What are you trying to say?

00:37:51.360 --> 00:37:53.400
Do you think you'd be better at this than

00:37:53.400 --> 00:37:53.579
me?

00:37:53.639 --> 00:37:55.500
Oh my goodness.

00:37:55.559 --> 00:37:58.500
Length edged away a step and looked even

00:37:58.500 --> 00:37:59.219
more concerned.

00:37:59.340 --> 00:38:01.440
Not even remotely.

00:38:01.500 --> 00:38:03.000
I never want to be queen.

00:38:03.059 --> 00:38:05.280
The correct answer?

00:38:05.340 --> 00:38:09.059
Snowfall said in an icy voice, is no

00:38:09.059 --> 00:38:09.900
snowfall.

00:38:09.960 --> 00:38:11.219
You're doing amazing.

00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:13.739
You are doing amazing.

00:38:13.860 --> 00:38:15.119
Lanks cried.

00:38:15.179 --> 00:38:16.679
See?

00:38:16.739 --> 00:38:17.940
Now I don't believe you.

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:21.000
Snowfall wrenched a globe off the tree

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:22.679
and batted it up at one of the windows

00:38:22.679 --> 00:38:24.239
that overlooked the courtyard.

00:38:24.300 --> 00:38:26.760
Some aristocrat was going to wake up in

00:38:26.760 --> 00:38:28.679
the morning and be very confused about

00:38:28.679 --> 00:38:31.079
why he had a 2nd light globe bobbing

00:38:31.079 --> 00:38:31.920
gently around his room.

00:38:31.980 --> 00:38:34.860
Links watched it sail over their heads.

00:38:34.920 --> 00:38:37.139
Then returned her gaze to Snowfall.

00:38:37.260 --> 00:38:40.260
I'm just worried about the fact that the

00:38:40.260 --> 00:38:41.760
only dragons you ever get to talk to

00:38:41.760 --> 00:38:45.000
anymore are old and bossy and kind of

00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:45.239
mean.

00:38:45.300 --> 00:38:48.179
Snowfall let out a snort.

00:38:48.239 --> 00:38:51.179
That certainly described the Council of

00:38:51.179 --> 00:38:53.159
Powerful Ice Wings who'd nominated

00:38:53.159 --> 00:38:55.139
themselves to guide the new young queen.

00:38:55.260 --> 00:38:59.039
Some would say, I'm bossy, and kind of

00:38:59.039 --> 00:39:01.559
mean too, she said to Lynx haughtily.

00:39:01.619 --> 00:39:06.719
Oh, you are, Ling said, which was not the

00:39:06.719 --> 00:39:09.119
correct answer either, but that means you

00:39:09.119 --> 00:39:11.519
need to order some kind, agreeable

00:39:11.519 --> 00:39:12.480
dragons to hang out with you.

00:39:12.539 --> 00:39:15.300
Once that won't make your brain hurt all

00:39:15.300 --> 00:39:15.599
the time.

00:39:15.719 --> 00:39:18.360
Like you, I suppose?

00:39:18.420 --> 00:39:19.920
Snowfall asked.

00:39:19.980 --> 00:39:22.800
How does she know that my brain hurts all

00:39:22.800 --> 00:39:23.159
the time?

00:39:23.219 --> 00:39:24.840
No.

00:39:24.900 --> 00:39:26.880
No, Link said.

00:39:26.940 --> 00:39:29.340
I'm not agreeable at all.

00:39:29.400 --> 00:39:32.460
You'd be like, fetch me a narwhal, and

00:39:32.460 --> 00:39:34.739
I'd be all, why?

00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:37.800
narwhals are heavy and I'm reading.

00:39:37.860 --> 00:39:41.099
And you'd say, but I want one right now.

00:39:41.159 --> 00:39:44.699
And I'd say, then go get one, bossy tail

00:39:44.699 --> 00:39:47.760
and you'd bellow, I am your queen, and

00:39:47.760 --> 00:39:50.460
I'd be like, yes, but this book is at a

00:39:50.460 --> 00:39:51.719
really exciting part, though.

00:39:51.780 --> 00:39:55.079
And then you'd probably have me

00:39:55.079 --> 00:39:55.679
executed.

00:39:55.739 --> 00:39:57.780
I'd be so irritating.

00:39:57.840 --> 00:39:59.820
You already know this about me.

00:39:59.880 --> 00:40:02.460
How do you know that my brain hurts all

00:40:02.460 --> 00:40:02.760
the time?

00:40:02.820 --> 00:40:04.559
Snowfall blurted.

00:40:04.619 --> 00:40:07.860
I mean, that is, what makes you think

00:40:07.860 --> 00:40:09.480
that my brain hurts all the time?

00:40:09.539 --> 00:40:13.920
Well, Ling said carefully, flicking her

00:40:13.920 --> 00:40:14.159
tail.

00:40:14.219 --> 00:40:16.920
You haven't stopped frowning since the

00:40:16.920 --> 00:40:17.760
beginning of the plague.

00:40:17.880 --> 00:40:20.039
That would give anyone a headache, I'd

00:40:20.039 --> 00:40:20.159
think.

00:40:20.280 --> 00:40:22.079
And my brain is always tired?

00:40:22.199 --> 00:40:24.119
When all we have to do is study and train

00:40:24.119 --> 00:40:25.739
and stay at the top of the Dragonette

00:40:25.739 --> 00:40:26.159
rankings.

00:40:26.219 --> 00:40:29.280
You have to do all the queen stuff.

00:40:29.340 --> 00:40:34.079
And, you know, also the, The sad bit.

00:40:34.139 --> 00:40:36.119
No, no.

00:40:36.179 --> 00:40:39.179
Snowfall's damped right over Lynx's last

00:40:39.179 --> 00:40:39.420
words.

00:40:39.480 --> 00:40:41.039
No time for that.

00:40:41.099 --> 00:40:43.199
I can handle all the queen stuff.

00:40:43.260 --> 00:40:45.480
I'm not a lowly noble like you.

00:40:45.539 --> 00:40:47.280
I can do everything just fine.

00:40:47.340 --> 00:40:49.980
This is what I've been preparing for my

00:40:49.980 --> 00:40:50.340
whole life.

00:40:50.400 --> 00:40:54.480
Sure, but there was supposed to be more

00:40:54.480 --> 00:40:55.980
of a whole life 1st.

00:40:56.039 --> 00:40:57.840
Lang's pointed out.

00:40:57.900 --> 00:41:00.840
Like, a couple more decades at least, I

00:41:00.840 --> 00:41:01.199
imagine.

00:41:01.260 --> 00:41:04.619
You don't know that, Snowfall said.

00:41:04.679 --> 00:41:07.380
Maybe I was planning to challenge mother

00:41:07.380 --> 00:41:09.659
for the throne like next week anyway.

00:41:09.719 --> 00:41:12.599
Because I'm so already ready to be

00:41:12.599 --> 00:41:13.139
queen.

00:41:13.199 --> 00:41:15.900
The light from the tree was too bright

00:41:15.900 --> 00:41:17.460
and she could feel her eyes watering.

00:41:17.519 --> 00:41:19.920
She turned to pace back to the wall

00:41:19.920 --> 00:41:22.079
rubbing her face with one talon.

00:41:22.139 --> 00:41:24.659
A couple more decades with mother as

00:41:24.659 --> 00:41:25.019
their queen.

00:41:25.139 --> 00:41:26.519
Maybe longer.

00:41:26.579 --> 00:41:28.739
That was what they should have had.

00:41:28.800 --> 00:41:31.019
That was what dark stalker stole.

00:41:31.079 --> 00:41:33.900
She hadn't really had a plan for

00:41:33.900 --> 00:41:35.579
challenging her mother anytime soon.

00:41:35.639 --> 00:41:38.039
She thought there would be plenty of time

00:41:38.039 --> 00:41:39.539
ahead of them before she had to worry

00:41:39.539 --> 00:41:40.019
about that.

00:41:40.139 --> 00:41:43.079
Or that certain sisters would get there

00:41:43.079 --> 00:41:43.739
1st.

00:41:43.800 --> 00:41:47.820
I guess I don't know, Link said, catching

00:41:47.820 --> 00:41:48.179
up to her.

00:41:48.239 --> 00:41:51.480
And walking beside her instead of a few

00:41:51.480 --> 00:41:52.139
steps behind.

00:41:52.199 --> 00:41:55.199
How had this dragon done so well in her

00:41:55.199 --> 00:41:55.500
exams?

00:41:55.619 --> 00:41:58.679
Did she not know any royal etiquette at

00:41:58.679 --> 00:41:59.099
all?

00:41:59.159 --> 00:42:01.800
I guess, Links went on.

00:42:01.860 --> 00:42:04.920
Maybe it had to be sooner because you

00:42:04.920 --> 00:42:07.199
needed to challenge her before icicle did

00:42:07.199 --> 00:42:07.320
right?

00:42:07.440 --> 00:42:09.000
Or someone else?

00:42:09.059 --> 00:42:10.920
Maybe it's better this way.

00:42:10.980 --> 00:42:13.440
With her giving you the throne instead of

00:42:13.440 --> 00:42:14.519
you having to take it?

00:42:14.579 --> 00:42:16.500
I could have taken it.

00:42:16.559 --> 00:42:17.940
Snowfall is shorter.

00:42:18.000 --> 00:42:19.619
Anytime I wanted to.

00:42:19.679 --> 00:42:23.280
She remembered Queen Glacier lying on her

00:42:23.280 --> 00:42:25.440
deathbed, gripping one of Snowfall's

00:42:25.440 --> 00:42:27.599
talons and staring intently up at her.

00:42:27.719 --> 00:42:30.659
She remembered her sister's watching from

00:42:30.659 --> 00:42:33.000
the queen's other side, Crystal's eyes

00:42:33.000 --> 00:42:34.440
glittering in the blue twilight.

00:42:34.500 --> 00:42:36.179
Manx sobbing.

00:42:36.239 --> 00:42:40.440
I will not have our tribe suffer the fate

00:42:40.559 --> 00:42:42.420
of the kingdom of sand.

00:42:42.480 --> 00:42:45.239
Glacier breathed between spasms of

00:42:45.239 --> 00:42:45.599
coughing.

00:42:45.659 --> 00:42:49.860
There will be no war of ice wing

00:42:49.860 --> 00:42:50.400
succession.

00:42:50.460 --> 00:42:52.980
Do you 3 understand me?

00:42:53.099 --> 00:42:57.300
Mink nodded frantically, although, at age

00:42:57.300 --> 00:42:59.579
two, she knew almost nothing about the

00:42:59.579 --> 00:43:01.980
war. and probably couldn't even name the

00:43:01.980 --> 00:43:06.059
sisters, Blister, Blaze, and Burn, that

00:43:06.059 --> 00:43:08.219
she and Crystal, and Snowfall, might

00:43:08.219 --> 00:43:08.519
become.

00:43:08.699 --> 00:43:13.139
We promise mother, Crystal said, in her

00:43:13.139 --> 00:43:14.579
frail, slippery, sweet voice.

00:43:14.639 --> 00:43:17.820
They were all sick at that point, although

00:43:17.820 --> 00:43:20.039
they didn't know yet that the plague came

00:43:20.039 --> 00:43:21.300
from Dark Stalker's magic.

00:43:21.360 --> 00:43:23.880
But Crystal had draped herself in

00:43:23.880 --> 00:43:26.820
diaphanous scarf fails, that managed to

00:43:26.820 --> 00:43:28.440
make even the plague look glamorous.

00:43:28.500 --> 00:43:30.780
Nobody wants another war.

00:43:30.840 --> 00:43:33.960
Even though Crystal had actually fought

00:43:33.960 --> 00:43:35.820
in the War of Sandwing succession.

00:43:35.880 --> 00:43:38.159
She hadn't come back noticeably tougher

00:43:38.159 --> 00:43:39.360
or more aggressive.

00:43:39.420 --> 00:43:43.019
She actually seemed a bit less there.

00:43:43.079 --> 00:43:45.960
She kept staring out of windows and

00:43:45.960 --> 00:43:48.300
losing track of conversations, probably

00:43:48.300 --> 00:43:50.340
thinking about all the deaths she'd

00:43:50.340 --> 00:43:51.840
witnessed, Snowfall guessed.

00:43:51.900 --> 00:43:54.539
She could easily believe that Crystal

00:43:54.539 --> 00:43:56.820
didn't want the tribe, or especially

00:43:56.820 --> 00:43:59.039
herself, to face any more battles.

00:43:59.159 --> 00:44:02.820
We'll just fight each other, Snowfall

00:44:02.820 --> 00:44:03.119
said.

00:44:03.179 --> 00:44:05.340
We won't drag anyone else into it.

00:44:05.400 --> 00:44:07.800
A normal duel, over in a day.

00:44:07.920 --> 00:44:10.320
Could I be crystal in a fight?

00:44:10.380 --> 00:44:13.559
Maybe right now, while she's sicker with

00:44:13.559 --> 00:44:14.400
a plague than I am.

00:44:14.460 --> 00:44:16.559
Crystal was 3 years older.

00:44:16.619 --> 00:44:20.099
Slightly taller, a little lazy, and a bit

00:44:20.099 --> 00:44:20.940
of an overthinker.

00:44:20.940 --> 00:44:23.880
Snowfall could probably use those last 2

00:44:23.880 --> 00:44:25.019
to her advantage.

00:44:25.079 --> 00:44:27.719
Do I really have to kill her though?

00:44:27.780 --> 00:44:30.539
Snowfall didn't know if she could handle

00:44:30.539 --> 00:44:31.800
one more dead ice wing.

00:44:31.920 --> 00:44:34.739
She didn't know if her claws could add to

00:44:34.739 --> 00:44:35.460
the death toll.

00:44:35.519 --> 00:44:39.179
Mink sniffled, and snowfall felt a small

00:44:39.179 --> 00:44:40.380
lurch in her chest.

00:44:40.440 --> 00:44:42.840
Mink wouldn't want to be queen, would

00:44:42.840 --> 00:44:43.139
she?

00:44:43.199 --> 00:44:45.780
Surely she wouldn't try to be in the

00:44:45.780 --> 00:44:46.199
duel.

00:44:46.260 --> 00:44:50.099
No, Glacier snarled.

00:44:50.159 --> 00:44:52.800
She crushed Snowfall's wrist in her

00:44:52.800 --> 00:44:54.300
talons with painful ferocity.

00:44:54.420 --> 00:44:57.420
You will not fight each other.

00:44:57.539 --> 00:45:01.739
I am going to choose the next I swing

00:45:01.739 --> 00:45:02.159
queen.

00:45:02.219 --> 00:45:04.860
Crystal rubbed the edges of her wings

00:45:04.860 --> 00:45:07.260
together, a nervous habit that made a

00:45:07.260 --> 00:45:09.480
jittering sound, which drove Snowfall

00:45:09.480 --> 00:45:09.780
mad.

00:45:09.840 --> 00:45:12.300
But Crystal started.

00:45:12.360 --> 00:45:15.179
But that, that's never.

00:45:15.539 --> 00:45:18.420
You must swear on the spirits beneath the

00:45:18.420 --> 00:45:20.760
ice, Glacier said fiercely.

00:45:20.820 --> 00:45:24.659
Whoever I choose to be queen, the other 2

00:45:24.659 --> 00:45:25.500
will support her.

00:45:25.559 --> 00:45:28.800
You'll help her save the tribe and keep

00:45:28.800 --> 00:45:29.280
the peace.

00:45:29.340 --> 00:45:33.599
No duels, no fighting, no war.

00:45:33.659 --> 00:45:35.219
Do you understand?

00:45:35.280 --> 00:45:38.820
Snowfall glanced across at her sister's.

00:45:38.940 --> 00:45:41.880
Of course, mother would choose crystal

00:45:41.880 --> 00:45:44.940
the oldest, the calmest, the one other

00:45:44.940 --> 00:45:45.840
dragons liked.

00:45:45.900 --> 00:45:48.480
Crystal had never clawed her way to the

00:45:48.480 --> 00:45:50.699
top of the rankings like Snowfall, but

00:45:50.699 --> 00:45:52.199
she didn't seem to care even half as

00:45:52.199 --> 00:45:52.440
much.

00:45:52.500 --> 00:45:55.619
To swearing this oath means snowfall

00:45:55.619 --> 00:45:57.059
would have to give up on the throne

00:45:57.059 --> 00:45:57.360
forever.

00:45:57.420 --> 00:45:59.579
For how long?

00:45:59.579 --> 00:46:00.780
she asked.

00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:01.920
I mean.

00:46:02.219 --> 00:46:05.280
Tradition says no one should challenge a

00:46:05.280 --> 00:46:06.780
new queen for the 1st month of her

00:46:06.780 --> 00:46:07.199
reign.

00:46:07.260 --> 00:46:08.880
Is that what you mean?

00:46:08.940 --> 00:46:10.860
Or for longer?

00:46:10.920 --> 00:46:14.460
Longer, glacier raft.

