irresistible stillness around them.

00:57:27.420 --> 00:57:30.480
Queen, snowfall.

00:57:30.539 --> 00:57:32.460
Snowfall reminded her.

00:57:32.519 --> 00:57:34.980
It was kind of peaceful not to be able to

00:57:34.980 --> 00:57:36.059
see the palace.

00:57:36.119 --> 00:57:38.099
This was what she wanted for the whole

00:57:38.099 --> 00:57:38.519
tribe.

00:57:38.579 --> 00:57:41.760
A wall of solid scales around them

00:57:41.760 --> 00:57:43.800
blocking everything else out.

00:57:43.860 --> 00:57:47.940
Queen snowfall. links echoed.

00:57:48.000 --> 00:57:49.920
You said they'll be here tomorrow?

00:57:50.039 --> 00:57:52.920
So let's fly to the western coast and

00:57:52.920 --> 00:57:53.280
meet them.

00:57:53.340 --> 00:57:56.639
Let's find out who they are and what they

00:57:56.639 --> 00:57:58.440
want before we panic.

00:57:58.559 --> 00:58:02.460
I mean, bit late for that, clearly, but

00:58:02.460 --> 00:58:05.099
we can save the more epic panicking for

00:58:05.099 --> 00:58:06.840
when we actually know something.

00:58:06.900 --> 00:58:09.480
We, Snowfall said.

00:58:09.599 --> 00:58:12.480
Meaning me and my whole army.

00:58:12.539 --> 00:58:18.360
Meaning, you and me, Link said, and one

00:58:18.360 --> 00:58:19.619
guard, if you must.

00:58:19.739 --> 00:58:21.480
Terrible plan.

00:58:21.599 --> 00:58:22.860
Snowfall said.

00:58:22.920 --> 00:58:24.059
The worst.

00:58:24.119 --> 00:58:25.199
I hate it.

00:58:25.260 --> 00:58:26.940
Great.

00:58:27.000 --> 00:58:29.099
Links granddadder.

00:58:29.159 --> 00:58:31.440
See you at the front gate at dawn.

00:58:31.559 --> 00:58:35.280
She trotted away, like a dragon with no

00:58:35.280 --> 00:58:37.679
worries in the whole world, and snowfall

00:58:37.679 --> 00:58:39.599
was left, staring into the walls of the

00:58:39.599 --> 00:58:42.900
palace, pale shimmering blue drizzled

00:58:42.900 --> 00:58:44.460
down through the translucent ice

00:58:44.460 --> 00:58:46.619
reflecting the weather outside with

00:58:46.619 --> 00:58:47.939
phosphorescent magic.

00:58:48.000 --> 00:58:51.420
The gift of elegance, crafted by a long

00:58:51.420 --> 00:58:53.099
ago animus with no sense at all.

00:58:53.159 --> 00:58:55.679
Why couldn't it be a gift of

00:58:55.679 --> 00:58:56.460
invincibility?

00:58:56.519 --> 00:59:00.179
Or a gift of unlimited, every queen gets

00:59:00.179 --> 00:59:03.900
magic now, or a gift of crush your

00:59:03.900 --> 00:59:05.099
enemies with one thought.

00:59:05.219 --> 00:59:09.420
It was so unfair, and deeply suspicious

00:59:09.420 --> 00:59:12.539
that animus magic stopped working, exactly

00:59:12.539 --> 00:59:15.420
when Snowfall found out about Cherboa.

00:59:15.480 --> 00:59:17.940
She should have had at least one animus

00:59:17.940 --> 00:59:18.300
gift.

00:59:18.360 --> 00:59:20.820
She had so many great ideas.

00:59:20.880 --> 00:59:24.360
Didn't animus dragons know about the

00:59:24.360 --> 00:59:26.699
danger from other tribes 2000 years ago?

00:59:26.820 --> 00:59:29.639
Was the one who made the great ice cliff

00:59:29.639 --> 00:59:30.599
the only smart one?

00:59:30.659 --> 00:59:34.199
Suddenly a thought hit her, a thought so

00:59:34.199 --> 00:59:34.619
brilliant.

00:59:34.739 --> 00:59:35.880
It made her gasp.

00:59:35.940 --> 00:59:39.780
There were other animus dragons before we

00:59:39.780 --> 00:59:42.300
lost Prince Arctic, other gifts.

00:59:42.420 --> 00:59:45.000
She knew where she needed to go.

00:59:45.059 --> 00:59:48.000
The forbidden treasury.

00:59:48.119 --> 00:59:52.380
Chapter 3.

00:59:52.679 --> 00:59:56.699
Most of the ice wing treasure, including

00:59:56.699 --> 00:59:59.519
Snowfall's awful crown, was kept in the

00:59:59.519 --> 01:00:02.099
regular treasury, a guarded vault close

01:00:02.099 --> 01:00:03.179
to the center of the palace.

01:00:03.239 --> 01:00:06.840
But there was another treasure, one known

01:00:06.840 --> 01:00:09.179
only to a few, and spoken of in

01:00:09.179 --> 01:00:09.780
whispers.

01:00:09.840 --> 01:00:12.719
It was buried in an ice cave deep below

01:00:12.719 --> 01:00:14.820
the palace, and the only way to get there

01:00:14.820 --> 01:00:16.619
was through a secret passage from the

01:00:16.619 --> 01:00:17.639
Queen's own rooms.

01:00:17.760 --> 01:00:21.480
No one but queens and princesses, had

01:00:21.480 --> 01:00:23.699
been down there in 100s of years, or

01:00:23.699 --> 01:00:25.019
perhaps ever.

01:00:25.079 --> 01:00:28.199
Only the queens and princesses, were even

01:00:28.199 --> 01:00:28.920
sure it was real.

01:00:28.980 --> 01:00:31.980
Had it been conjured by an animus

01:00:31.980 --> 01:00:34.920
sometime long ago, a gift of secrets?

01:00:34.980 --> 01:00:38.639
Or did a queen in their ancient past once

01:00:38.639 --> 01:00:40.679
order workers to carve out the cave and

01:00:40.679 --> 01:00:42.179
the passage with their own claws?

01:00:42.239 --> 01:00:44.460
Snowfall didn't know.

01:00:44.519 --> 01:00:46.500
She didn't think her mother had known

01:00:46.500 --> 01:00:48.780
either, although now she wished she had

01:00:48.780 --> 01:00:49.440
asked more questions.

01:00:49.500 --> 01:00:53.400
At the door of her royal chambers, a tiny

01:00:53.400 --> 01:00:54.719
dragonette was sitting between the

01:00:54.719 --> 01:00:55.739
guards.

01:00:55.800 --> 01:00:58.619
Her eyes were large and dark blue, and

01:00:58.619 --> 01:01:00.599
her scales were white, with feathery

01:01:00.599 --> 01:01:02.699
patterns of gray along her wings, like

01:01:02.699 --> 01:01:04.380
whiskers, or tufts of fur.

01:01:04.440 --> 01:01:06.960
The guards had clearly been chatting with

01:01:06.960 --> 01:01:09.059
her, but they snapped to attention as

01:01:09.059 --> 01:01:10.800
snowfall approached, and the little

01:01:10.800 --> 01:01:12.420
dragon scrambled to her feet as well.

01:01:12.480 --> 01:01:15.960
Hi, Snowfall, Mink blurted.

01:01:16.019 --> 01:01:19.500
Um, um, um, I made you something.

01:01:19.619 --> 01:01:22.380
She reached into a small pouch slung

01:01:22.380 --> 01:01:24.480
across her back and brought out a tiny

01:01:24.480 --> 01:01:27.480
block of ice carved with great care into

01:01:27.480 --> 01:01:30.480
as far as snowfall could tell, a blob.

01:01:30.539 --> 01:01:33.539
Make gently placed it into snowfalls

01:01:33.539 --> 01:01:35.159
talons with an expression of bashful

01:01:35.159 --> 01:01:35.519
pride.

01:01:35.579 --> 01:01:39.960
Oh, uh, thank you.

01:01:40.019 --> 01:01:42.480
Snowfall turned it around a few times

01:01:42.480 --> 01:01:44.400
wondering which end was up.

01:01:44.460 --> 01:01:46.260
It's...

01:01:46.260 --> 01:01:47.460
Great.

01:01:47.519 --> 01:01:50.760
It's a mink, her little sister said.

01:01:50.820 --> 01:01:52.019
Like me.

01:01:52.079 --> 01:01:54.719
But um, an actual mink?

01:01:54.780 --> 01:01:55.920
Not a dragon mink.

01:01:55.980 --> 01:01:57.179
See the whiskers?

01:01:57.179 --> 01:01:58.260
And the ears?

01:01:58.320 --> 01:02:00.000
Sure.

01:02:00.059 --> 01:02:02.159
Snowfall said doubtfully.

01:02:02.219 --> 01:02:06.599
It's just to say, I love you, Mink said

01:02:06.599 --> 01:02:07.079
shyly.

01:02:07.139 --> 01:02:10.559
This would have been sweet, if it weren't

01:02:10.559 --> 01:02:12.420
for the fact that Mink loved literally

01:02:12.420 --> 01:02:12.960
everyone.

01:02:13.019 --> 01:02:16.260
Snowfall was pretty sure every dragon in

01:02:16.260 --> 01:02:18.659
the whole palace had at least one of Manx

01:02:18.659 --> 01:02:19.739
I love you gifts.

01:02:19.800 --> 01:02:22.260
The queen's room was still cluttered with

01:02:22.260 --> 01:02:22.440
them.

01:02:22.500 --> 01:02:25.619
Miniature unidentifiable ice sculptures

01:02:25.619 --> 01:02:26.519
on every surface.

01:02:26.579 --> 01:02:29.940
Snowfall hadn't seen her tiny flipperty

01:02:29.940 --> 01:02:31.980
gibbet sister very much since becoming

01:02:31.980 --> 01:02:32.219
queen.

01:02:32.280 --> 01:02:34.619
There were dragons in charge of her

01:02:34.619 --> 01:02:36.840
education and training, and Snowfall

01:02:36.840 --> 01:02:38.760
assumed they had carried on since Queen

01:02:38.760 --> 01:02:40.739
Glacier's death, the same as they had

01:02:40.739 --> 01:02:40.920
before.

01:02:40.980 --> 01:02:43.860
Manx life shouldn't have worked very much

01:02:43.860 --> 01:02:44.099
at all.

01:02:44.159 --> 01:02:49.440
Well, thank you, Snowfall said, aware of

01:02:49.440 --> 01:02:50.340
the guard's eyes on her.

01:02:50.400 --> 01:02:52.920
Now, I'm very busy, so.

01:02:52.920 --> 01:02:55.500
Oh, can't I please come in?

01:02:55.619 --> 01:02:56.820
Mink pleated.

01:02:56.880 --> 01:02:59.400
I miss mommy's room.

01:02:59.460 --> 01:03:01.619
Snowfall frowned at her.

01:03:01.679 --> 01:03:03.599
You miss her room?

01:03:03.659 --> 01:03:07.199
I slept in there sometimes when I

01:03:07.199 --> 01:03:09.900
couldn't fall asleep, Meg explained.

01:03:09.960 --> 01:03:12.119
That figured.

01:03:12.179 --> 01:03:15.059
Snowfall would never have dared to crawl

01:03:15.059 --> 01:03:16.380
into her mother's room in the middle of

01:03:16.380 --> 01:03:16.679
the night.

01:03:16.800 --> 01:03:20.219
It was highly against the rules, and

01:03:20.219 --> 01:03:21.659
would almost certainly have gotten her

01:03:21.659 --> 01:03:23.099
knocked down a few spots on the wall.

01:03:23.159 --> 01:03:25.619
Training herself to go back to sleep

01:03:25.619 --> 01:03:28.380
alone was part of being a 1st circle kind

01:03:28.380 --> 01:03:28.980
of dragon.

01:03:28.980 --> 01:03:31.679
But that wasn't the kind of thing Mink

01:03:31.679 --> 01:03:32.099
worried about.

01:03:32.159 --> 01:03:34.860
If she weren't everyone's beloved

01:03:34.860 --> 01:03:37.380
princess, she'd probably be stuck in the

01:03:37.380 --> 01:03:38.519
6th circle her whole life.

01:03:38.579 --> 01:03:42.300
You can sleep in there now, Snowfall

01:03:42.300 --> 01:03:42.599
said.

01:03:42.659 --> 01:03:43.739
It's my room.

01:03:43.800 --> 01:03:46.320
She had enough trouble sleeping without

01:03:46.320 --> 01:03:48.360
adding a fidgety little snuggle lizard

01:03:48.360 --> 01:03:49.019
into the situation.

01:03:49.079 --> 01:03:53.460
I know, Mink said, her wings drooping.

01:03:53.519 --> 01:03:56.219
I just want to see it again.

01:03:56.280 --> 01:03:58.440
Snowfall side.

01:03:58.500 --> 01:04:01.559
If she sent Mink away now, these guards

01:04:01.559 --> 01:04:02.940
would probably tell everyone in the

01:04:02.940 --> 01:04:04.679
palace that she'd hurt her sister's

01:04:04.679 --> 01:04:05.039
feelings.

01:04:05.099 --> 01:04:08.159
Not an excellent queen move for sure.

01:04:08.219 --> 01:04:11.940
Besides, she should probably know about

01:04:11.940 --> 01:04:12.960
the forbidden treasury.

01:04:13.019 --> 01:04:16.320
Queen Glacier had taken Snowfall down

01:04:16.320 --> 01:04:18.719
there only once, when she was 4 years old

01:04:18.719 --> 01:04:21.000
and she done the same with Crystal 3

01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:21.599
years before that.

01:04:21.719 --> 01:04:23.699
But not mink.

01:04:23.760 --> 01:04:25.260
She was still too young.

01:04:25.320 --> 01:04:28.619
I should show it to her With crystal

01:04:28.619 --> 01:04:28.920
gone?

01:04:28.980 --> 01:04:30.300
If anything happens to me.

01:04:30.360 --> 01:04:33.119
This secret could be lost forever.

01:04:33.179 --> 01:04:35.639
Snowfall shivered.

01:04:35.699 --> 01:04:38.219
It was extremely strange to think of

01:04:38.219 --> 01:04:40.559
little mink as her sole heir, even

01:04:40.559 --> 01:04:42.420
stranger to think that snowfall should

01:04:42.420 --> 01:04:44.579
teach her how to be queen, just in case.

01:04:44.639 --> 01:04:47.579
Snowfall wasn't cut out to be a patient

01:04:47.579 --> 01:04:50.699
teacher, and Mink definitely wasn't cut

01:04:50.699 --> 01:04:51.900
out to be a ruthless queen.

01:04:51.960 --> 01:04:56.639
All right, come in, Snowfall said

01:04:56.639 --> 01:04:57.239
grumbly.

01:04:57.300 --> 01:05:00.539
Mink squeaked happily, and bounded into

01:05:00.539 --> 01:05:01.320
the room ahead of her.

01:05:01.380 --> 01:05:04.199
Nobody else is allowed in for the rest of

01:05:04.199 --> 01:05:04.559
the night.

01:05:04.619 --> 01:05:06.539
Snowfall ordered the guards.

01:05:06.599 --> 01:05:09.719
Did that sound cool and calm or strange

01:05:09.719 --> 01:05:10.619
and paranoid?

01:05:10.679 --> 01:05:13.139
Wasn't this a perfectly normal thing for

01:05:13.139 --> 01:05:13.920
a queen to command?

01:05:13.980 --> 01:05:17.340
The guards expressions were impassive

01:05:17.340 --> 01:05:17.940
unmoving.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:19.980
What were they thinking about her?

01:05:20.039 --> 01:05:23.400
Did they find her queenly or ridiculous?

01:05:23.460 --> 01:05:27.119
In the main chamber, the bed dominated

01:05:27.119 --> 01:05:27.960
the center of the room.

01:05:28.019 --> 01:05:30.420
A block of ice carved into whorls and

01:05:30.420 --> 01:05:32.579
drifts, where a dragon body could fit

01:05:32.579 --> 01:05:33.000
perfectly.

01:05:33.059 --> 01:05:36.659
As snowfall shut the doors, Mink leaped

01:05:36.659 --> 01:05:38.820
onto the bed and wriggled around, looking

01:05:38.820 --> 01:05:40.139
ridiculously comfortable.

01:05:40.199 --> 01:05:43.619
The truth was, snowfall still hadn't

01:05:43.619 --> 01:05:44.460
slept in her mother's bed.

01:05:44.519 --> 01:05:47.280
She couldn't stop thinking of it as her

01:05:47.280 --> 01:05:47.880
mother's bed.

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:50.159
She wasn't sure how she ever would.

01:05:50.219 --> 01:05:53.519
Most queens killed their predecessor on a

01:05:53.519 --> 01:05:56.280
battlefield, or in an arena, or before

01:05:56.280 --> 01:05:58.559
the whole court in a blood stained throne

01:05:58.559 --> 01:05:58.980
room.

01:05:59.099 --> 01:06:01.500
They didn't watch them slip away into

01:06:01.500 --> 01:06:04.320
darkness, in the very spot where they

01:06:04.320 --> 01:06:06.119
then had to fall asleep for the rest of

01:06:06.119 --> 01:06:06.840
their lives.

01:06:06.900 --> 01:06:09.900
It was just as comfortable up on top of

01:06:09.900 --> 01:06:11.099
the jewel cabinet anyway.

01:06:11.159 --> 01:06:15.059
Or on the polar bear rug by the window, or

01:06:15.059 --> 01:06:16.800
in the icy bathtub in the next room.

01:06:16.920 --> 01:06:20.760
Fine, nowhere at all was comfortable, but

01:06:20.760 --> 01:06:21.480
that was fine.

01:06:21.539 --> 01:06:23.820
Queens didn't complain about their

01:06:23.820 --> 01:06:24.599
sleeping quarters.

01:06:24.659 --> 01:06:27.420
Real queens probably didn't need as much

01:06:27.420 --> 01:06:29.039
sleep as regular dragons anyway.

01:06:29.099 --> 01:06:32.219
Off, she ordered her sister.

01:06:32.280 --> 01:06:34.079
I have to show you something.

01:06:34.139 --> 01:06:36.599
Mink hopped off the bed immediately.

01:06:36.659 --> 01:06:37.679
Her eyes wide.

01:06:37.739 --> 01:06:40.800
Snowfall braced her talons against the

01:06:40.800 --> 01:06:42.900
spot at the foot of the bed, the one her

01:06:42.900 --> 01:06:45.179
mother had shown her, and pushed.

01:06:45.239 --> 01:06:48.719
The bed slid aside soundlessly, revealing

01:06:48.719 --> 01:06:50.400
a hole underneath that plunged into

01:06:50.400 --> 01:06:51.239
endless darkness.

01:06:51.300 --> 01:06:55.079
Wow, Mink breathed.

01:06:55.199 --> 01:06:57.179
Wow, oh wow.

01:06:57.239 --> 01:06:59.340
Why is there a hole in the floor?

01:06:59.460 --> 01:07:02.639
I never, ever knew there was a big hole

01:07:02.639 --> 01:07:03.239
under the bed.

01:07:03.360 --> 01:07:07.139
It's a secret for queens, Snowfall said.

01:07:07.199 --> 01:07:09.059
Mink's face fell.

01:07:09.179 --> 01:07:11.099
Oh, she said.

01:07:11.159 --> 01:07:13.500
Not from me then.

01:07:13.619 --> 01:07:17.039
Well, Snowfall said reluctantly.

01:07:17.099 --> 01:07:19.500
It could be for you, one day.

01:07:19.679 --> 01:07:22.019
If anything happens to me and you have to

01:07:22.019 --> 01:07:22.679
become queen.

01:07:22.739 --> 01:07:24.179
What?

01:07:24.300 --> 01:07:25.260
M cried.

01:07:25.320 --> 01:07:27.599
No, I don't want to be.

01:07:27.659 --> 01:07:29.039
What's going to happen to you?

01:07:29.099 --> 01:07:30.960
Nothing.

01:07:31.019 --> 01:07:32.219
Snowfall said.

01:07:32.280 --> 01:07:35.460
I'm going to be clean for ages and ages.

01:07:35.519 --> 01:07:38.039
But you should see it anyway, just in

01:07:38.039 --> 01:07:38.940
case.

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:40.380
Hang on to your light globe and follow

01:07:40.380 --> 01:07:40.619
me.

01:07:40.679 --> 01:07:43.920
She clasped her own light globe in her

01:07:43.920 --> 01:07:46.739
front talons, spread her wings, and dove

01:07:46.739 --> 01:07:47.340
into the chasm.

01:07:47.400 --> 01:07:50.159
The walls glittered around them as they

01:07:50.159 --> 01:07:53.880
spun down and down and down, until soon

01:07:53.880 --> 01:07:56.099
all she could see above and below them

01:07:56.099 --> 01:07:56.699
was darkness.

01:07:56.760 --> 01:08:00.480
Finally, her light reflected off a smooth

01:08:00.480 --> 01:08:02.579
glassy surface at the bottom of the hole

01:08:02.579 --> 01:08:04.079
several heartbeats away.

01:08:04.139 --> 01:08:07.079
She banged her wings and slowed to a

01:08:07.079 --> 01:08:09.659
gentle drift until she felt her claws

01:08:09.659 --> 01:08:10.019
touch down.

01:08:10.139 --> 01:08:13.380
A little thump behind her, announced to

01:08:13.380 --> 01:08:15.179
the arrival of her sister a snowfall

01:08:15.179 --> 01:08:16.680
released her light globe to drift over

01:08:16.680 --> 01:08:17.579
her shoulder once more.

01:08:17.640 --> 01:08:20.340
Oh my gosh, 0 my gosh.

01:08:20.399 --> 01:08:23.459
Mink whispered, trying to crawl under one

01:08:23.459 --> 01:08:25.259
of Snowfall's wings to press against her

01:08:25.259 --> 01:08:25.439
side.

01:08:25.500 --> 01:08:27.420
What is this place?

01:08:27.479 --> 01:08:30.779
Teaching her little sister about royal

01:08:30.779 --> 01:08:31.679
secrets was one thing.

01:08:31.800 --> 01:08:34.859
Snuggling was quite another, and

01:08:34.859 --> 01:08:36.659
definitely not on her list of queen

01:08:36.659 --> 01:08:37.319
responsibilities.

01:08:37.380 --> 01:08:40.800
Snowfall wiggled away, and took a step

01:08:40.800 --> 01:08:42.359
into the dark corridor before them.

01:08:42.420 --> 01:08:46.319
This is the forbidden treasury, she

01:08:46.319 --> 01:08:46.619
said.

01:08:46.680 --> 01:08:49.560
You must never tell anyone where it is or

01:08:49.560 --> 01:08:50.220
how to get here.

01:08:50.279 --> 01:08:53.699
There are secrets down here, and magic

01:08:53.699 --> 01:08:55.199
that only a queen can use.

01:08:55.260 --> 01:08:57.840
She realized she'd slipped into her

01:08:57.840 --> 01:09:00.000
mother's voice, echoing the words Queen

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:01.439
Glacier had said to her on this very

01:09:01.439 --> 01:09:01.800
spot.

01:09:01.859 --> 01:09:05.279
I won't tell, Mink breathed.

01:09:05.340 --> 01:09:07.260
I promise, promise.

01:09:07.319 --> 01:09:10.499
The walls around them were blackest ice.

01:09:10.560 --> 01:09:12.600
Gleaming with silvery filaments and

01:09:12.600 --> 01:09:13.800
bubbles when the light hit them.

01:09:13.859 --> 01:09:16.439
Snowfall led the way to the passage

01:09:16.439 --> 01:09:17.039
spiral.

01:09:17.100 --> 01:09:20.039
It coiled in on itself like a snail shell

01:09:20.039 --> 01:09:22.079
with alcoves cut into the eyes at eye

01:09:22.079 --> 01:09:23.159
level every few steps.

01:09:23.220 --> 01:09:26.520
Well, eye level for an older dragon.

01:09:26.579 --> 01:09:28.739
They were slightly above snowfall's head

01:09:28.739 --> 01:09:30.779
but she could stretch her neck up and see

01:09:30.779 --> 01:09:31.140
into them.

01:09:31.199 --> 01:09:34.140
Everything was too high for mink to reach

01:09:34.140 --> 01:09:34.560
without flying.

01:09:34.619 --> 01:09:37.260
The 1st 2 alcoves were empty.

01:09:37.319 --> 01:09:39.899
They had been when Snowfall visited with

01:09:39.899 --> 01:09:40.559
Glacier too.

01:09:40.619 --> 01:09:43.500
She didn't know what had been in them, or

01:09:43.500 --> 01:09:45.300
if they'd been left empty in anticipation

01:09:45.300 --> 01:09:46.680
of gifts that had never arrived.

01:09:46.739 --> 01:09:48.659
Thank you, night wings.

01:09:48.720 --> 01:09:50.939
Her light glittered off something

01:09:50.939 --> 01:09:52.680
shimmery in the 3rd alcove, and she

01:09:52.680 --> 01:09:53.159
paused.

01:09:53.220 --> 01:09:56.340
It was a tiara, delicate and elegant.

01:09:56.399 --> 01:09:59.279
Much lighter and smaller than her hideous

01:09:59.279 --> 01:10:01.020
crown, and prettier too.

01:10:01.079 --> 01:10:02.520
Hmm.

01:10:02.640 --> 01:10:05.399
She nudged the light globe closer to the

01:10:05.399 --> 01:10:07.500
wall, where words were carved into the

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:07.680
ice.

01:10:07.739 --> 01:10:10.260
The gift of strength.

01:10:10.319 --> 01:10:11.880
Use cautiously.

01:10:11.939 --> 01:10:16.199
Ooh, strength sounded promising.

01:10:16.260 --> 01:10:18.300
This would definitely be useful.

01:10:18.359 --> 01:10:20.819
Would it make the whole kingdom stronger

01:10:20.819 --> 01:10:21.239
somehow?

01:10:21.300 --> 01:10:23.460
Or specifically just whoever wore the

01:10:23.460 --> 01:10:24.060
tiara?

01:10:24.119 --> 01:10:27.000
Snowfall thought for a moment, then

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:28.859
lifted out the tiara, and placed it

01:10:28.859 --> 01:10:29.640
carefully on her head.

01:10:29.760 --> 01:10:32.399
Nothing dramatic happened.

01:10:32.460 --> 01:10:34.020
She felt the same.

01:10:34.140 --> 01:10:36.600
It fits so comfortably she could hardly

01:10:36.600 --> 01:10:37.319
tell she was wearing it.

01:10:37.380 --> 01:10:39.840
She glanced down at Mink.

01:10:39.899 --> 01:10:41.640
What do you think?

01:10:41.699 --> 01:10:44.279
The little dragon's eyes were shining.

01:10:44.340 --> 01:10:46.319
It's so pretty.

01:10:46.380 --> 01:10:47.640
She breathed.

01:10:47.699 --> 01:10:49.079
Can I try it on?

01:10:49.199 --> 01:10:51.720
No, no, definitely not.

01:10:51.779 --> 01:10:53.520
Snowfall said quickly.

01:10:53.579 --> 01:10:56.159
Everything down here is only for queens.

01:10:56.220 --> 01:10:58.859
You can look, but you can't touch, all

01:10:58.859 --> 01:10:59.159
right?

01:10:59.220 --> 01:11:02.880
Mink's face fell, and her wings drooped

01:11:02.880 --> 01:11:03.539
on either side of her.

01:11:03.600 --> 01:11:06.359
Snowfall turned away quickly before she

01:11:06.359 --> 01:11:07.859
could see any tears in her sister's

01:11:07.859 --> 01:11:08.100
eyes.

01:11:08.159 --> 01:11:12.239
Come on, let's see what else there is, she

01:11:12.239 --> 01:11:12.899
said briskly.

01:11:12.960 --> 01:11:16.140
She trotted forward, and she heard Mink's

01:11:16.140 --> 01:11:17.939
tiny claws scrambling on the ice to keep

01:11:17.939 --> 01:11:18.119
up.

01:11:18.180 --> 01:11:22.020
The next alcove held a scepter, carved

01:11:22.020 --> 01:11:24.180
from some dark blue rock, with little

01:11:24.180 --> 01:11:25.500
diamonds set into it.

01:11:25.560 --> 01:11:27.720
Snowfall disliked it immediately.

01:11:27.779 --> 01:11:30.180
It reminded her of night wings.

01:11:30.239 --> 01:11:32.819
The gift of compromise.

01:11:32.880 --> 01:11:33.899
Read the inscription.

01:11:33.960 --> 01:11:36.359
No, thank you.

01:11:36.420 --> 01:11:38.279
Snowfall thought furiously.

01:11:38.340 --> 01:11:40.680
She didn't read the rest of the carved

01:11:40.680 --> 01:11:42.840
words, which covered half the wall under

01:11:42.840 --> 01:11:43.560
the alcove.

01:11:43.680 --> 01:11:47.340
Compromise was not what the ice wings

01:11:47.340 --> 01:11:47.699
needed.

01:11:47.760 --> 01:11:50.819
They needed a strong queen, who could do

01:11:50.819 --> 01:11:53.399
impressive, giant, scary magic things

01:11:53.399 --> 01:11:56.100
like maybe shoot lightning bolts from her

01:11:56.100 --> 01:11:58.439
claws, or suddenly grow to 3 times her

01:11:58.439 --> 01:12:01.619
size, or flick her tail and make it rain

01:12:01.619 --> 01:12:03.180
poisonous scorpions.

01:12:03.239 --> 01:12:05.520
Compromise indeed.

01:12:05.579 --> 01:12:08.399
Make fluttered her wings to get high

01:12:08.399 --> 01:12:10.680
enough to see the scepter, but snowfall

01:12:10.680 --> 01:12:11.760
was already whisking away.

01:12:11.819 --> 01:12:16.260
Not useful, she called. striding to the

01:12:16.260 --> 01:12:16.920
next alcove.

01:12:16.979 --> 01:12:19.439
This one held a ring.

01:12:19.500 --> 01:12:21.479
A weird looking ring.

01:12:21.539 --> 01:12:25.800
It had a milky, pink, gold, white, green

01:12:25.800 --> 01:12:28.979
opal set into the center of it, and the

01:12:28.979 --> 01:12:30.420
rest of the ring looked like silver

01:12:30.420 --> 01:12:33.180
dragon tails, winding around the opal, and

01:12:33.180 --> 01:12:34.800
the space where a dragon's claw would

01:12:34.800 --> 01:12:34.979
go.

01:12:35.039 --> 01:12:37.439
Snowfall studied it for a moment.

01:12:37.500 --> 01:12:40.319
The opal was kind of mesmerizing.

01:12:40.380 --> 01:12:43.079
The more she looked at it, the more

01:12:43.079 --> 01:12:44.579
flecks of different colors she could see

01:12:44.579 --> 01:12:45.000
in it.

01:12:45.060 --> 01:12:48.960
This one said, The gift of vision.

01:12:49.020 --> 01:12:50.760
No other notes.

01:12:50.880 --> 01:12:53.399
Well, that was pretty straightforward.

01:12:53.460 --> 01:12:54.899
Better vision?

01:12:54.960 --> 01:12:56.699
Snowfall would take that.

01:12:56.819 --> 01:12:59.340
It wasn't as useful as strength or

01:12:59.340 --> 01:13:01.560
scorpion hail, but maybe it would help

01:13:01.560 --> 01:13:03.300
her see the mystery dragons from much

01:13:03.300 --> 01:13:03.840
farther away.

01:13:03.899 --> 01:13:07.500
Maybe she'd be able to identify them long

01:13:07.500 --> 01:13:09.180
before they hit the shores of the ice

01:13:09.180 --> 01:13:09.539
kingdom.

01:13:09.600 --> 01:13:13.079
She lifted it out, and slipped it on one

01:13:13.079 --> 01:13:14.279
of her front left claws.

01:13:14.340 --> 01:13:18.539
It was a bit too big, as if it had been

01:13:18.539 --> 01:13:20.699
designed for a bigger older dragon.

01:13:20.760 --> 01:13:22.319
A real queen.

01:13:22.380 --> 01:13:24.000
Snowfall side.

01:13:24.119 --> 01:13:26.399
Shut up, brain.

01:13:26.460 --> 01:13:27.539
Stop thinking like that.

01:13:27.659 --> 01:13:29.399
This is my gift now.

01:13:29.460 --> 01:13:31.380
That makes me a real queen.

01:13:31.439 --> 01:13:35.279
She stormed onto the next alcove, which

01:13:35.279 --> 01:13:35.699
was empty.

01:13:35.760 --> 01:13:38.699
Whatever had been written underneath, had

01:13:38.699 --> 01:13:40.500
been violently scratched out sometime

01:13:40.500 --> 01:13:40.859
long ago.

01:13:40.979 --> 01:13:43.560
Snowfall wondered if there was any

01:13:43.560 --> 01:13:46.439
explanation in one of the old ice wing

01:13:46.439 --> 01:13:46.979
history books.

01:13:47.100 --> 01:13:49.500
Not that she had time for history right

01:13:49.500 --> 01:13:49.739
now.

01:13:49.800 --> 01:13:51.720
Three moons.

01:13:51.779 --> 01:13:54.600
After that was an alcove that seemed to

01:13:54.600 --> 01:13:55.560
have been added later.

01:13:55.619 --> 01:13:57.720
It wasn't at the same distance from the

01:13:57.720 --> 01:14:00.119
others, and it looked hacked out of the

01:14:00.119 --> 01:14:01.560
ice instead of beautifully carved.

01:14:01.619 --> 01:14:04.800
The item inside looked like an unwearable

01:14:04.800 --> 01:14:06.000
mystery piece of silver.

01:14:06.060 --> 01:14:08.640
The scribble scratch writing underneath

01:14:08.640 --> 01:14:11.579
said, part of the gift of understanding

01:14:11.579 --> 01:14:12.600
which was weird.

01:14:12.659 --> 01:14:13.920
Part of?

01:14:14.460 --> 01:14:15.060
Where was the rest?

01:14:15.119 --> 01:14:17.039
And not helpful either.

01:14:17.159 --> 01:14:19.500
Bah, humbug understanding.

01:14:19.560 --> 01:14:22.140
Snowball was getting nervous.

01:14:22.199 --> 01:14:25.020
The walls were spiraling in tighter and

01:14:25.020 --> 01:14:26.760
tighter. soon they'd be at the end.

01:14:26.880 --> 01:14:29.579
Wasn't there anything down here that

01:14:29.579 --> 01:14:31.319
could destroy an invading army with one

01:14:31.319 --> 01:14:32.520
swoop if she wanted to?

01:14:32.579 --> 01:14:36.420
Absolutely useless animus idiots.

01:14:36.479 --> 01:14:40.260
The next treasure, though, looked a lot

01:14:40.260 --> 01:14:41.340
more promising.

01:14:41.399 --> 01:14:45.180
Pale silver wristbands set with diamonds

01:14:45.180 --> 01:14:46.079
and underneath.

01:14:46.199 --> 01:14:49.319
Snowfall read the inscription and

01:14:49.319 --> 01:14:49.680
smiled.

01:14:49.739 --> 01:14:53.880
Well, it's not exactly what I wanted.

01:14:54.000 --> 01:14:57.060
But it'll definitely give those invading

01:14:57.060 --> 01:15:00.539
dragons quite an unwelcome surprise.

01:15:00.600 --> 01:15:04.680
Chapter 4.

01:15:04.920 --> 01:15:08.279
Snowfall arrived at the front gate at

01:15:08.279 --> 01:15:10.439
dawn with 5 guards, because she was the

01:15:10.439 --> 01:15:12.239
queen, and she did what she liked, and

01:15:12.239 --> 01:15:13.680
Lynx didn't get to decide all the

01:15:13.680 --> 01:15:13.920
things.

01:15:13.979 --> 01:15:14.819
So there.

01:15:14.880 --> 01:15:17.939
Links was waiting at the gate, looking

01:15:17.939 --> 01:15:19.439
unfairly well rested.

01:15:19.500 --> 01:15:22.020
She kind of rolled her eyes at the 5

01:15:22.020 --> 01:15:24.600
guards, but she didn't say anything, so

01:15:24.600 --> 01:15:26.100
Snowfall didn't have to threaten her face

01:15:26.100 --> 01:15:27.359
1st thing in the morning.

01:15:27.420 --> 01:15:30.420
They flew south and west along the coast

01:15:30.420 --> 01:15:32.699
out toward the farthest peninsula that

01:15:32.699 --> 01:15:33.539
reached into the ocean.

01:15:33.659 --> 01:15:37.020
The ocean that was supposed to be so big

01:15:37.020 --> 01:15:38.100
no one could cross it.

01:15:38.100 --> 01:15:40.859
So even if there was a continent full of

01:15:40.859 --> 01:15:42.779
dangerous dragons on the other side

01:15:42.779 --> 01:15:43.920
they'd have to stay over there.

01:15:43.979 --> 01:15:47.159
If Lynx was right, how had they gotten

01:15:47.159 --> 01:15:47.340
here?

01:15:47.399 --> 01:15:48.840
And why now?

01:15:48.960 --> 01:15:52.319
Why would they arrive right when I've

01:15:52.319 --> 01:15:53.340
just become queen?

01:15:53.399 --> 01:15:55.439
Did they hear about me and decide to

01:15:55.439 --> 01:15:57.180
invade because they think I'm young and

01:15:57.180 --> 01:15:58.800
useless and I'll be easy to defeat?

01:15:58.859 --> 01:16:02.100
She gnawed at these questions as they

01:16:02.100 --> 01:16:04.920
flew and the sun rose higher, setting the

01:16:04.920 --> 01:16:06.960
snow below them into a dazzling blaze of

01:16:06.960 --> 01:16:07.439
sparkles.

01:16:07.500 --> 01:16:10.319
It was so beautiful and pure out here.

01:16:10.380 --> 01:16:13.079
All these untouched snow drifts

01:16:13.079 --> 01:16:14.100
stretching out below them.

01:16:14.159 --> 01:16:18.000
No murder plots, or magic plagues, or

01:16:18.000 --> 01:16:20.039
untrustworthy dragons anywhere to be

01:16:20.039 --> 01:16:20.279
seen.

01:16:20.340 --> 01:16:24.359
You look tired, Link said after a little

01:16:24.359 --> 01:16:24.600
while.

01:16:24.659 --> 01:16:27.779
That's treason, and no, I don't.

01:16:27.840 --> 01:16:29.279
Snowfall snapped.

01:16:29.399 --> 01:16:31.199
Did you sleep at all?

01:16:31.260 --> 01:16:32.279
Lang asked.

01:16:32.340 --> 01:16:35.579
Did Snowfall ever actually sleep?

01:16:35.640 --> 01:16:38.460
Or did her brain just slide a little

01:16:38.460 --> 01:16:39.119
underwater?

01:16:39.180 --> 01:16:41.760
Where the worries were blurrier, and

01:16:41.760 --> 01:16:43.500
night wings stalked around in the dark

01:16:43.500 --> 01:16:44.399
trying to kill her.

01:16:44.460 --> 01:16:47.340
Did it count as sleeping when she woke up

01:16:47.340 --> 01:16:48.779
more tired than she'd been before?

01:16:48.840 --> 01:16:51.899
Could she even call it waking up?

01:16:51.899 --> 01:16:53.279
When it felt more as though all her

01:16:53.279 --> 01:16:55.859
worries suddenly became so pressing that

01:16:55.859 --> 01:16:56.760
her eyes flew open.

01:16:56.819 --> 01:17:00.060
The arrival of dawn only seemed to shove

01:17:00.060 --> 01:17:02.159
her from a drifting haze of nebulous

01:17:02.159 --> 01:17:04.739
problems, straight into a blistering ice

01:17:04.739 --> 01:17:05.399
storm of them.

01:17:05.520 --> 01:17:08.640
Last night, she hadn't even tried.

01:17:08.699 --> 01:17:11.460
No, she answered length.

01:17:11.520 --> 01:17:12.720
I was very busy.

01:17:12.840 --> 01:17:14.939
Length tilted her head.

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:16.199
Doing what?

01:17:16.260 --> 01:17:19.140
You might find this hard to imagine

01:17:19.140 --> 01:17:20.220
Snowfall said.

01:17:20.279 --> 01:17:23.039
The queens have a lot to do, actually.

01:17:23.100 --> 01:17:27.300
But... when everyone else is asleep?

01:17:27.420 --> 01:17:28.800
Length asked again.

01:17:28.859 --> 01:17:31.439
What did you do specifically?

01:17:31.500 --> 01:17:34.500
Snowfall tipped her wings to catch an air

01:17:34.500 --> 01:17:34.859
current?

01:17:34.920 --> 01:17:37.979
Last night, specifically?

01:17:38.039 --> 01:17:39.539
I visited the treasury.

01:17:39.600 --> 01:17:42.180
She knew Lynx would think she meant the

01:17:42.180 --> 01:17:43.260
regular royal treasury.

01:17:43.319 --> 01:17:46.739
And then I spent absolutely forever

01:17:46.739 --> 01:17:49.079
trying to make a certain pathetic seal

01:17:49.079 --> 01:17:51.300
eyed princess go away, but she ended up

01:17:51.300 --> 01:17:53.699
falling asleep on my bed in the middle of

01:17:53.699 --> 01:17:55.380
my lecture, which was very rude.

01:17:55.439 --> 01:18:00.180
Ooh, the treasury, Lang said.

01:18:00.239 --> 01:18:02.520
I thought you looked extra sparkly

01:18:02.520 --> 01:18:02.819
today.

01:18:02.880 --> 01:18:05.340
Is this to impress the strange dragons?

01:18:05.399 --> 01:18:07.619
She flicked her tail at Snowball's

01:18:07.619 --> 01:18:08.159
accessories.

01:18:08.220 --> 01:18:12.000
Sure, Snowfall said, rolling her eyes.

01:18:12.060 --> 01:18:13.800
Wow, oh wow.

01:18:13.859 --> 01:18:15.600
I really hope they think I'm extra

01:18:15.600 --> 01:18:16.619
sparkly too.

01:18:16.680 --> 01:18:19.199
All right, sarcasm face.

01:18:19.319 --> 01:18:21.479
Links flicked her tail at snowfall

01:18:21.479 --> 01:18:21.779
again.

01:18:21.840 --> 01:18:24.180
Then what's all this about?

01:18:24.239 --> 01:18:27.359
Snowfall held out our front talons?

01:18:27.420 --> 01:18:29.579
Where the diamond crusted wristbands

01:18:29.579 --> 01:18:31.920
glittered alongside sleek fitted knife

01:18:31.920 --> 01:18:32.340
sheets.

01:18:32.399 --> 01:18:34.979
The tiara of strength was perched on her

01:18:34.979 --> 01:18:35.579
horns.

01:18:35.640 --> 01:18:37.920
The ring of vision was still on the front

01:18:37.920 --> 01:18:40.560
left claw where she put it, but so far

01:18:40.560 --> 01:18:42.420
she hadn't noticed any improvement in her

01:18:42.420 --> 01:18:42.899
eyesight.

01:18:42.899 --> 01:18:45.600
Maybe she had to activate it somehow.

01:18:45.659 --> 01:18:48.539
If Lynx couldn't guess why she was

01:18:48.539 --> 01:18:50.939
wearing all of this, maybe she wasn't cut

01:18:50.939 --> 01:18:52.680
out for the new council Snowball was

01:18:52.680 --> 01:18:53.399
thinking about after all.

01:18:53.520 --> 01:18:57.539
Just as she had that thought, Lynx's eyes

01:18:57.539 --> 01:18:58.079
widened.

01:18:58.199 --> 01:19:03.000
Wait, she said, lowering her voice, even

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:04.800
though the guards were flying a perimeter

01:19:04.800 --> 01:19:06.539
around them, just out of earshot.

01:19:06.600 --> 01:19:07.979
Snowfall.

01:19:08.039 --> 01:19:10.439
You don't mean the forbidden treasury, do

01:19:10.439 --> 01:19:10.619
you?

01:19:10.680 --> 01:19:13.199
Are those jewels animus touched?

01:19:13.319 --> 01:19:16.979
Snowfall smiled slyly, letting the sun

01:19:16.979 --> 01:19:18.479
catch on the opal in her ring.

01:19:18.539 --> 01:19:21.000
I'm glad to see your brain does work

01:19:21.000 --> 01:19:21.420
sometimes.

01:19:21.479 --> 01:19:25.319
But you can't go to the forbidden

01:19:25.319 --> 01:19:25.739
treasury.

01:19:25.800 --> 01:19:27.239
It's forbidden.

01:19:27.300 --> 01:19:28.739
It's right there in the name.

01:19:28.800 --> 01:19:31.079
And you definitely can't take things out

01:19:31.079 --> 01:19:31.500
of it.

01:19:31.560 --> 01:19:35.220
Of course I can, Snowball snapped.

01:19:35.279 --> 01:19:38.340
I'm the queen, even though you can't seem

01:19:38.340 --> 01:19:38.939
to remember that.

01:19:39.000 --> 01:19:41.640
I'm literally the only dragon allowed in

01:19:41.640 --> 01:19:42.479
a forbidden treasury.

01:19:42.539 --> 01:19:43.739
It's my treasury.

01:19:43.800 --> 01:19:47.520
Yeah, but isn't all that stuff forbidden

01:19:47.520 --> 01:19:47.939
for a reason.

01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:51.779
It's forbidden to dragons who would be

01:19:51.779 --> 01:19:54.060
too weak to use it properly, Snowball

01:19:54.060 --> 01:19:54.359
said.

01:19:54.420 --> 01:19:56.279
Not queens.

01:19:56.340 --> 01:19:58.680
And besides, this is an emergency.

01:19:58.739 --> 01:20:00.659
And why would we keep stuff like that

01:20:00.659 --> 01:20:02.399
around if not for exactly this?

01:20:02.460 --> 01:20:05.939
Links tilted her wings, looking puzzled.

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:07.619
An emergency?

01:20:07.680 --> 01:20:11.399
You are a very poor listener, Snowfall

01:20:11.399 --> 01:20:11.880
shouted.

01:20:11.939 --> 01:20:14.100
Animus magic is broken.

01:20:14.159 --> 01:20:16.439
No one can cast any more spells.

01:20:16.500 --> 01:20:18.779
We can't make anything to protect

01:20:18.779 --> 01:20:20.100
ourselves from the invaders.

01:20:20.159 --> 01:20:21.840
But...

01:20:21.840 --> 01:20:26.399
Hasn't that been the case for like 2000

01:20:26.399 --> 01:20:26.880
years?

01:20:26.939 --> 01:20:28.140
Links asked.

01:20:28.199 --> 01:20:30.960
Ice Wings haven't had an animist dragon

01:20:30.960 --> 01:20:32.100
since Prince Arctic.

01:20:32.159 --> 01:20:35.039
Snowfall didn't want to tell her about

01:20:35.039 --> 01:20:37.859
Jerboa, the difficult sandwing animus

01:20:37.859 --> 01:20:40.380
that Queen Glacier had found and formed

01:20:40.380 --> 01:20:41.520
some kind of alliance with.

01:20:41.640 --> 01:20:44.340
Glacier had told Snowfall to go find

01:20:44.340 --> 01:20:46.560
Jerboa, in the hopes that the animus

01:20:46.560 --> 01:20:48.180
could stop the plague, but they were too

01:20:48.180 --> 01:20:48.359
late.

01:20:48.479 --> 01:20:52.020
And, of course, now it turned out, the

01:20:52.020 --> 01:20:53.819
sand wing was perfectly useless.

01:20:53.880 --> 01:20:57.659
Now, right when Snowfall needed her.

01:20:57.720 --> 01:21:01.199
Maybe the invading dragons somehow know

01:21:01.199 --> 01:21:03.960
that too, or maybe they froze everyone's

01:21:03.960 --> 01:21:04.680
animus magic.

01:21:04.800 --> 01:21:08.520
Irrelevant and classified.

01:21:08.640 --> 01:21:10.260
She hissed at lengths.

01:21:10.319 --> 01:21:13.260
The important part is that I realize we

01:21:13.260 --> 01:21:14.579
can use something we already have.

01:21:14.640 --> 01:21:17.159
The forbidden treasury is where we keep

01:21:17.159 --> 01:21:19.619
our ancient magic from 1000s of years ago

01:21:19.619 --> 01:21:22.260
before we lost our animus bloodline.

01:21:22.319 --> 01:21:25.380
Back then, every animus dragon made a

01:21:25.380 --> 01:21:25.979
gift for the tribe.

01:21:26.039 --> 01:21:30.000
I realized, because I am a genius, that

01:21:30.000 --> 01:21:31.380
there's a chance one of those could save

01:21:31.380 --> 01:21:33.960
us, and I could find it in the forbidden

01:21:33.960 --> 01:21:34.319
treasury.

01:21:34.380 --> 01:21:37.680
I never saw Queen Glacier wearing any of

01:21:37.680 --> 01:21:39.779
that, Link said cautiously.

01:21:39.840 --> 01:21:42.600
Maybe my mother was not as brilliant as

01:21:42.600 --> 01:21:44.579
everyone thinks. snowfall said.

01:21:44.699 --> 01:21:47.640
Maybe if she'd thought of this, she could

01:21:47.640 --> 01:21:48.899
have found something in the treasury to

01:21:48.899 --> 01:21:51.659
protect us all, and maybe she'd still be

01:21:51.659 --> 01:21:51.840
alive.

01:21:51.960 --> 01:21:55.319
She tipped her head up until her eyes

01:21:55.319 --> 01:21:56.039
stopped watering.

01:21:56.100 --> 01:21:58.500
The thought of magic lying under the

01:21:58.500 --> 01:22:01.560
palace, forgotten, unused, going to

01:22:01.560 --> 01:22:01.979
waste.

01:22:02.039 --> 01:22:04.199
It made her claws itch to stab

01:22:04.199 --> 01:22:04.560
something.

01:22:04.619 --> 01:22:06.779
All right.

01:22:06.840 --> 01:22:09.420
So what do all those jewels do?

01:22:09.479 --> 01:22:10.739
Lang asked.

01:22:10.800 --> 01:22:13.920
I'm not telling you, Snowball snapped.

01:22:13.979 --> 01:22:17.460
But you do know.

01:22:17.520 --> 01:22:19.319
Links asked nervously.

01:22:19.380 --> 01:22:22.380
I mean, you understand each of the things

01:22:22.380 --> 01:22:22.920
you're wearing.

01:22:22.979 --> 01:22:24.659
You can control them.

01:22:24.720 --> 01:22:27.600
Snowfall, Castro, a withering look.

01:22:27.659 --> 01:22:30.119
Of course, she said.

01:22:30.180 --> 01:22:32.579
Most of them were stored with notes from

01:22:32.579 --> 01:22:33.840
the queens who used them.

01:22:33.899 --> 01:22:36.479
She squinted at a shape moving below them

01:22:36.479 --> 01:22:39.479
but it was only an Arctic hair, and it

01:22:39.479 --> 01:22:41.340
looked the same as Arctic hairs always

01:22:41.340 --> 01:22:42.119
did from up in the sky.

01:22:42.180 --> 01:22:45.180
She'd kind of expected the gift of vision

01:22:45.180 --> 01:22:47.640
to actually, you know, do something to

01:22:47.640 --> 01:22:48.119
her vision.

01:22:48.180 --> 01:22:50.159
Maybe that one was broken.

01:22:50.220 --> 01:22:52.380
Lynx didn't need to know about that.

01:22:52.439 --> 01:22:54.720
Most of them?

01:22:54.779 --> 01:22:56.340
Length squeaked.

01:22:56.399 --> 01:22:58.079
A snowfall whisked ahead of her.

01:22:58.140 --> 01:23:00.539
She flapped her wings to catch up.

01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:01.979
Snowfall.

01:23:02.039 --> 01:23:03.479
What if they're dangerous?

01:23:03.600 --> 01:23:07.380
They'd better be dangerous, Snowfall

01:23:07.380 --> 01:23:07.680
said.

01:23:07.739 --> 01:23:09.180
That's the whole point.

01:23:09.239 --> 01:23:11.640
There's an invasion on its way here

01:23:11.640 --> 01:23:12.119
remember?

01:23:12.180 --> 01:23:13.979
We need all the protection we can get.

01:23:14.100 --> 01:23:16.680
This is why facing them with an army

01:23:16.680 --> 01:23:17.460
would be the best idea.

01:23:17.520 --> 01:23:20.880
I think you're just as scary as any army

01:23:20.880 --> 01:23:22.739
all on your own, Link said.

01:23:22.800 --> 01:23:24.359
Without any magic.

01:23:24.420 --> 01:23:27.060
Ha, Snowfall snorted.

01:23:27.119 --> 01:23:31.260
I only have like 7 non-magical weapons on

01:23:31.260 --> 01:23:31.380
me.

01:23:31.439 --> 01:23:33.899
We need 1000s of weapons to drive these

01:23:33.899 --> 01:23:34.619
dragons away.

01:23:34.680 --> 01:23:38.399
Lynx glanced down at her claws, as if

01:23:38.399 --> 01:23:40.439
she'd only just noticed that those were

01:23:40.439 --> 01:23:41.699
the only weapons she'd brought.

01:23:41.760 --> 01:23:43.020
Really?

01:23:43.079 --> 01:23:44.699
Seven weapons?

01:23:44.760 --> 01:23:46.260
Yes.

01:23:46.319 --> 01:23:48.779
Of course, Snowfall said.

01:23:48.840 --> 01:23:51.119
She pointed to the spear on her back.

01:23:51.180 --> 01:23:52.680
Spear.

01:23:52.739 --> 01:23:55.199
Then to the knives and the sheets at her

01:23:55.199 --> 01:23:55.560
wrists.

01:23:55.680 --> 01:23:59.520
Knife, knife, then to the sheaves under

01:23:59.520 --> 01:24:01.800
her wings, the concealed pockets of her

01:24:01.800 --> 01:24:03.840
chain mail armor, and the pouch around

01:24:03.840 --> 01:24:04.199
her neck.

01:24:04.260 --> 01:24:07.260
Knife, knife, throwing stars, poison.

01:24:07.319 --> 01:24:10.380
She didn't mention the other 3 hidden

01:24:10.380 --> 01:24:10.859
weapons.

01:24:10.920 --> 01:24:13.020
Just in case Links was actually working

01:24:13.020 --> 01:24:15.840
for Crystal, or the Night Wings, or had

01:24:15.840 --> 01:24:18.239
her own ulterior motives, and was maybe

01:24:18.239 --> 01:24:20.579
planning to attack snowfall as soon as

01:24:20.579 --> 01:24:21.840
she had her away from the castle

01:24:21.840 --> 01:24:22.560
unprotected.

01:24:22.619 --> 01:24:24.960
Well, ha, ha.

01:24:25.020 --> 01:24:27.180
Snowfall had foiled her with those 5

01:24:27.180 --> 01:24:27.600
guards.

01:24:27.720 --> 01:24:30.420
And the extra secret weaponry.

01:24:30.479 --> 01:24:33.000
And totally being on to her.

01:24:33.060 --> 01:24:35.220
Headache again?

01:24:35.279 --> 01:24:37.319
Ling said sympathetically.

01:24:37.380 --> 01:24:41.399
No, Snowball snapped. jerking her claws

01:24:41.399 --> 01:24:42.180
away from her temples.

01:24:42.239 --> 01:24:45.659
More like headache always, she thought.

01:24:45.720 --> 01:24:48.300
And you're not helping, potentially

01:24:48.300 --> 01:24:49.500
untrustworthy dragon.

01:24:49.560 --> 01:24:52.439
She spotted a cluster of ice structures

01:24:52.439 --> 01:24:54.359
below them, along the cliff that

01:24:54.359 --> 01:24:55.500
overlooked the ocean here.

01:24:55.619 --> 01:24:56.880
What's that?

01:24:56.939 --> 01:24:59.039
One of the outer villages.

01:24:59.100 --> 01:25:00.060
Link said.

01:25:00.119 --> 01:25:02.220
Where the turns fly, I think.

01:25:02.279 --> 01:25:05.460
I should royally decree that all ice

01:25:05.460 --> 01:25:07.500
swing villages must have one word names

01:25:07.500 --> 01:25:09.420
Snowfall said grumpily.

01:25:09.539 --> 01:25:12.180
Her claws still hurt from years of

01:25:12.180 --> 01:25:14.460
writing out the list of villages, over

01:25:14.460 --> 01:25:17.399
and over again, and labeling them on maps

01:25:17.399 --> 01:25:18.960
and writing essays about them.

01:25:19.020 --> 01:25:22.319
The time she could have saved, if Hamlet

01:25:22.319 --> 01:25:23.880
that worships the whales who sing at

01:25:23.880 --> 01:25:26.579
night, had just been called whales.

01:25:26.640 --> 01:25:29.340
Not to be confused with where the whales

01:25:29.340 --> 01:25:30.659
leave at dawn, of course.

01:25:30.720 --> 01:25:34.979
That would be a great royal decree, Lang

01:25:34.979 --> 01:25:37.739
said fervently, at least for maps and

01:25:37.739 --> 01:25:39.420
lists and essays by exhausted

01:25:39.420 --> 01:25:40.140
dragonettes.

01:25:40.199 --> 01:25:42.840
Your puny little estate is out here

01:25:42.840 --> 01:25:44.819
somewhere, Snowfall remembered.

01:25:44.880 --> 01:25:46.260
It is.

01:25:46.319 --> 01:25:49.500
Links cast a wistful glance to her left.

01:25:49.560 --> 01:25:51.960
It overlooks among the evergreens.

01:25:52.020 --> 01:25:55.260
My father lives there, but I haven't been

01:25:55.260 --> 01:25:55.859
back in a while.

01:25:55.920 --> 01:25:57.720
What is he?

01:25:57.779 --> 01:25:59.340
Fifth circle, sixth?

01:25:59.399 --> 01:26:02.640
Fifth for the last couple of years, Link

01:26:02.640 --> 01:26:02.939
said.

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:05.880
Because Lynx's success at court has

01:26:05.880 --> 01:26:06.420
raised him up.

01:26:06.539 --> 01:26:08.159
Snowfall guest.

01:26:08.760 --> 01:26:09.539
But hang on.

01:26:09.600 --> 01:26:12.060
Isn't there some kind of rule that no one

01:26:12.060 --> 01:26:13.560
is allowed to talk to the queen about the

01:26:13.560 --> 01:26:13.800
wall?

01:26:13.859 --> 01:26:16.859
It's fine if I bring it up.

01:26:16.979 --> 01:26:19.560
Snowfall said, bristling.

01:26:19.619 --> 01:26:22.020
But you can't ask me to change anything

01:26:22.020 --> 01:26:23.520
not that I would anyway.

01:26:23.579 --> 01:26:25.680
No one else makes my decisions for me.

01:26:25.739 --> 01:26:27.539
Oh, good.

01:26:27.600 --> 01:26:28.739
Link said.

01:26:28.800 --> 01:26:31.800
I was wondering why Tundra and permafrost

01:26:31.800 --> 01:26:33.659
had stayed up so high lately, when

01:26:33.659 --> 01:26:34.920
they're always so awful.

01:26:35.100 --> 01:26:37.199
But now that I know it's entirely your

01:26:37.199 --> 01:26:37.680
decision.

01:26:37.739 --> 01:26:39.420
I feel much better.

01:26:39.479 --> 01:26:41.520
Snowfall glared at her.

01:26:41.579 --> 01:26:44.460
That sounded like sarcasm.

01:26:44.520 --> 01:26:46.020
Did it?

01:26:46.079 --> 01:26:47.579
Links gasped.

01:26:47.640 --> 01:26:50.279
Your majesty, one of the guards

01:26:50.279 --> 01:26:52.380
interrupted, swooping back toward them.

01:26:52.439 --> 01:26:54.779
We think we see something.

01:26:54.840 --> 01:26:57.840
Snowfall pumped her wings to shoot ahead

01:26:57.840 --> 01:26:58.380
of links.

01:26:58.439 --> 01:27:00.239
Catching out to another guard who had

01:27:00.239 --> 01:27:01.079
been flying out in front.

01:27:01.140 --> 01:27:04.199
She squinted at the horizon, for the

01:27:04.199 --> 01:27:06.239
ocean took over from the snowy cliffs.

01:27:06.300 --> 01:27:08.699
At 1st she thought she was looking at

01:27:08.699 --> 01:27:09.180
clouds.

01:27:09.239 --> 01:27:12.899
Ordinary clouds, non-threatening puffs of

01:27:12.899 --> 01:27:15.479
fluff in the sky, and then she realized

01:27:15.479 --> 01:27:17.819
that the clouds were flickering and

01:27:17.819 --> 01:27:18.600
shivering with movement.

01:27:18.659 --> 01:27:22.260
Flashes of green and gold and rose and

01:27:22.260 --> 01:27:23.819
aquamarine caught the sunlight.

01:27:23.880 --> 01:27:28.020
They were clouds of wings, a whole fog of

01:27:28.020 --> 01:27:29.640
dragons descending on her kingdom.

01:27:29.699 --> 01:27:32.520
The jolt of terror that ran through

01:27:32.520 --> 01:27:34.500
snowfall's veins was like being stabbed

01:27:34.500 --> 01:27:35.520
with a sandwing tail.

01:27:35.579 --> 01:27:38.640
It was like 6 night wings attacking her

01:27:38.640 --> 01:27:39.000
at once.

01:27:39.060 --> 01:27:42.239
It was like the moment a cobalt blue

01:27:42.239 --> 01:27:44.220
hybrid dragon had bowed in front of her

01:27:44.279 --> 01:27:47.699
held out a garish earring and said, I am

01:27:47.699 --> 01:27:49.260
so sorry I didn't get here sooner, Queen

01:27:49.260 --> 01:27:49.859
Snowfall.

01:27:49.920 --> 01:27:52.560
I am too late for your mother, but I can

01:27:52.560 --> 01:27:54.600
at least save your life, if you put this

01:27:54.600 --> 01:27:54.779
on.

01:27:54.899 --> 01:27:57.659
This plague, it's a spell.

01:27:57.720 --> 01:28:00.659
It was sent by an animus night wing named

01:28:00.659 --> 01:28:03.359
Dark Stalker to wipe out the entire tribe

01:28:03.359 --> 01:28:04.260
of ice wings.

01:28:04.319 --> 01:28:07.140
They're coming to kill us, she said

01:28:07.140 --> 01:28:09.180
whisking around in the air and nearly

01:28:09.180 --> 01:28:10.140
colliding with links.

01:28:10.260 --> 01:28:13.140
Hearing her words, the closest guards

01:28:13.140 --> 01:28:14.220
faltered in the sky.

01:28:14.279 --> 01:28:16.260
They looked as scared as she felt.

01:28:16.319 --> 01:28:19.140
They're not coming to kill us.

01:28:19.199 --> 01:28:20.159
Link said.

01:28:20.220 --> 01:28:22.739
I mean, we don't know that they're coming

01:28:22.739 --> 01:28:23.340
to kill us.

01:28:23.399 --> 01:28:25.680
They're probably not coming to kill us.

01:28:25.739 --> 01:28:27.000
We're going to find out.

01:28:27.060 --> 01:28:29.760
This is a terrible way to find out.

01:28:29.819 --> 01:28:32.939
Snowfall protested, as Lynx turned her

01:28:32.939 --> 01:28:33.180
around.

01:28:33.239 --> 01:28:36.000
It would be much smarter to attack them

01:28:36.000 --> 01:28:37.800
with my whole army the moment they land.

01:28:37.859 --> 01:28:42.300
No, no, Links objected, alarmed.

01:28:42.359 --> 01:28:44.399
That would start things off on completely

01:28:44.399 --> 01:28:45.420
the wrong talent.

01:28:45.479 --> 01:28:48.000
Listen, it won't take long to get your

01:28:48.000 --> 01:28:48.840
army if we need it.

01:28:48.899 --> 01:28:51.960
If these dragons do seem dangerous, we

01:28:51.960 --> 01:28:54.239
can retreat to my father's estate and use

01:28:54.239 --> 01:28:55.979
the mirror signal system to summon

01:28:55.979 --> 01:28:56.399
backup.

01:28:56.460 --> 01:28:57.300
See?

01:28:57.359 --> 01:28:58.859
No need to panic.

01:28:58.979 --> 01:29:01.739
Snowball hissed at her.

01:29:01.859 --> 01:29:03.420
Yes, fine.

01:29:03.479 --> 01:29:06.000
She should probably act less terrified in

01:29:06.000 --> 01:29:06.600
front of the guards.

01:29:06.659 --> 01:29:09.180
Queens weren't supposed to freak out

01:29:09.180 --> 01:29:09.539
about anything.

01:29:09.600 --> 01:29:11.819
Queens never panicked.

01:29:11.880 --> 01:29:14.220
Mother was never scared.

01:29:14.279 --> 01:29:18.000
Not once, not during the war, and not

01:29:18.000 --> 01:29:19.079
even when the plague came.

01:29:19.140 --> 01:29:21.359
But why not?

01:29:21.359 --> 01:29:22.500
is my question.

01:29:22.560 --> 01:29:25.260
There are so many things to be scared

01:29:25.260 --> 01:29:25.619
of.

01:29:25.680 --> 01:29:28.500
Was she secretly this close to falling

01:29:28.500 --> 01:29:30.539
apart all the time, like I am?

01:29:30.659 --> 01:29:33.060
Did she wonder how she was going to hold

01:29:33.060 --> 01:29:35.399
the whole tribe together in this large

01:29:35.399 --> 01:29:38.460
cold kingdom after a war with so many

01:29:38.460 --> 01:29:39.060
deaths?

01:29:39.119 --> 01:29:41.640
Didn't she spend all her time worrying

01:29:41.640 --> 01:29:43.800
about how we could possibly survive

01:29:43.800 --> 01:29:46.079
against a tribe of dragons who hate us

01:29:46.079 --> 01:29:49.439
and who, by the way, have all the magic

01:29:49.439 --> 01:29:49.859
powers?

01:29:49.920 --> 01:29:52.739
Stop thinking about night wings.

01:29:52.859 --> 01:29:55.560
Deal with the brand new mysterious scary

01:29:55.560 --> 01:29:55.859
thing.

01:29:55.920 --> 01:30:00.300
Nobody is panicking, she said, flicking

01:30:00.300 --> 01:30:00.600
her tail.

01:30:00.659 --> 01:30:03.000
You're an impertinent net.

01:30:03.060 --> 01:30:03.960
Stop annoying me.

01:30:04.020 --> 01:30:06.479
She pushed links aside and flew on

01:30:06.479 --> 01:30:06.840
ahead.

01:30:06.899 --> 01:30:09.420
There was an alarming heartbeat of

01:30:09.420 --> 01:30:11.760
stillness from the guards, but then she

01:30:11.760 --> 01:30:13.500
sensed them moving into place around her

01:30:13.500 --> 01:30:16.500
flying in formation, just as though she

01:30:16.500 --> 01:30:18.420
were exactly the right queen doing

01:30:18.420 --> 01:30:19.319
exactly the right thing.

01:30:19.380 --> 01:30:22.859
Instead of making this all up as I go.

01:30:22.979 --> 01:30:26.699
She led them to a cliff. that overlooked

01:30:26.699 --> 01:30:28.920
a grove of snow covered pines and a rocky

01:30:28.920 --> 01:30:29.340
beach.

01:30:29.340 --> 01:30:32.699
Below them, dragons were swooping down to

01:30:32.699 --> 01:30:32.939
land.

01:30:33.000 --> 01:30:35.760
They were not night wings.

01:30:35.819 --> 01:30:37.380
The scout was right about that.

01:30:37.500 --> 01:30:40.680
They were not sea wings or rain wings

01:30:40.680 --> 01:30:40.979
either.

01:30:41.039 --> 01:30:44.699
The green dragons, actually green and

01:30:44.699 --> 01:30:46.560
brown and sometimes flecked with gold

01:30:46.560 --> 01:30:48.359
scales, snowfall noticed.

01:30:48.420 --> 01:30:51.060
Headwings elegantly shaped like leaves.

01:30:51.180 --> 01:30:54.539
No phosphorescent markings, and no webs

01:30:54.539 --> 01:30:55.500
between their claws.

01:30:55.560 --> 01:30:58.380
The other tribe was much stranger.

01:30:58.439 --> 01:31:01.020
Their scales were all over the color

01:31:01.020 --> 01:31:04.439
spectrum, shimmering pinks, dark violets

01:31:04.439 --> 01:31:07.500
pale lavenders, blues, and oranges, and

01:31:07.500 --> 01:31:08.579
summery yellows.

01:31:08.640 --> 01:31:12.359
They each had 4 wings instead of 2, and

01:31:12.359 --> 01:31:14.699
even at a distance, snowfall could see

01:31:14.699 --> 01:31:16.439
delicate antennae curling from their

01:31:16.439 --> 01:31:16.859
foreheads.

01:31:16.920 --> 01:31:21.239
Weird, creepy dragons, she hissed

01:31:21.239 --> 01:31:23.520
crouching close to the ground and peering

01:31:23.520 --> 01:31:24.359
over the cliff edge.

01:31:24.420 --> 01:31:26.039
They must be evil.

01:31:26.100 --> 01:31:27.960
They look totally different from us.

01:31:28.020 --> 01:31:30.300
So do sandwings.

01:31:30.359 --> 01:31:32.819
Could we manage to ally with a bunch of

01:31:32.819 --> 01:31:33.600
them during the war?

01:31:33.659 --> 01:31:35.640
Links pointed out from beside her.

01:31:35.699 --> 01:31:38.939
Every tribe looks a little different, but

01:31:38.939 --> 01:31:40.199
none of them are completely evil.

01:31:40.319 --> 01:31:43.500
Wrong, Snowfall snapped.

01:31:43.560 --> 01:31:44.520
Objectively wrong.

01:31:44.579 --> 01:31:47.640
Nightwings are 9000% evil.

01:31:47.760 --> 01:31:50.880
Thanksgiver that curious sideways look

01:31:50.880 --> 01:31:51.119
again.

01:31:51.180 --> 01:31:53.939
Didn't that empathy spell work on you at

01:31:53.939 --> 01:31:54.119
all?

01:31:54.180 --> 01:31:54.960
she asked.

01:31:55.079 --> 01:31:57.539
Didn't you feel what they were feeling?

01:31:57.600 --> 01:31:59.220
during our battle with them.

01:31:59.279 --> 01:32:01.800
It made the rest of us ice wings hate

01:32:01.800 --> 01:32:02.399
them way less.

01:32:02.460 --> 01:32:03.779
Why not you?

01:32:03.840 --> 01:32:06.359
Snowfall didn't answer.

01:32:06.479 --> 01:32:09.840
That moment, in the middle of the battle

01:32:09.840 --> 01:32:12.060
when an animus dragon had connected all

01:32:12.060 --> 01:32:14.520
the minds of the fighting dragons, ice

01:32:14.520 --> 01:32:17.399
wings and night wings together, that had

01:32:17.399 --> 01:32:18.659
been one of the worst moments of her

01:32:18.659 --> 01:32:18.899
life.

01:32:18.960 --> 01:32:21.899
Because threaded through the ice wing

01:32:21.899 --> 01:32:25.199
sphere, in dragon after dragon, she'd

01:32:25.199 --> 01:32:28.079
found one particular whisper, what are we

01:32:28.079 --> 01:32:29.640
going to do without Queen Glacier?

01:32:29.699 --> 01:32:32.880
How can snowfall possibly save us from

01:32:32.880 --> 01:32:33.060
this?

01:32:33.119 --> 01:32:34.680
She's not ready.

01:32:34.739 --> 01:32:37.020
She's a smug little monster.

01:32:37.140 --> 01:32:40.500
Our new queen is a spoiled dragonette. who

01:32:40.500 --> 01:32:41.460
has no idea what to do.

01:32:41.520 --> 01:32:44.220
Why would Glacier pick her?

01:32:44.279 --> 01:32:47.819
Up until then, she thought maybe the

01:32:47.819 --> 01:32:48.659
tribe was proud of her.

01:32:48.720 --> 01:32:51.600
Maybe they were glad she was the sister

01:32:51.600 --> 01:32:52.380
who'd been chosen.

01:32:52.439 --> 01:32:54.779
Maybe they knew how fiercely she would

01:32:54.779 --> 01:32:55.260
fight for them.

01:32:55.319 --> 01:32:58.020
Maybe when Glacier chose her.

01:32:58.079 --> 01:33:00.300
It had convinced everyone that she was

01:33:00.300 --> 01:33:01.439
truly a worthy queen.

01:33:01.560 --> 01:33:03.659
Apparently not.

01:33:03.720 --> 01:33:07.260
And over on the other side, she felt the

01:33:07.260 --> 01:33:08.520
night wings triumph too.

01:33:08.579 --> 01:33:10.199
Look at their queen.

01:33:10.260 --> 01:33:12.000
She's barely old enough to fly.

01:33:12.060 --> 01:33:13.079
She doesn't know anything.

01:33:13.140 --> 01:33:15.359
We can destroy her easily.

01:33:15.420 --> 01:33:18.420
It wasn't the biggest feeling the

01:33:18.420 --> 01:33:19.739
battling dragons were all having.

01:33:19.800 --> 01:33:21.180
That was fear.

01:33:21.300 --> 01:33:23.880
And now that fear was all anyone talked

01:33:23.880 --> 01:33:24.180
about.

01:33:24.239 --> 01:33:27.600
Night Wings, hey, maybe they're just like

01:33:27.600 --> 01:33:27.840
us.

01:33:27.899 --> 01:33:30.000
Maybe they're scared of stuff too.

01:33:30.060 --> 01:33:31.859
We can totally understand them.

01:33:31.920 --> 01:33:35.159
Snowfalls seem to be the only one who

01:33:35.159 --> 01:33:38.039
remembered, those layers of doubt under

01:33:38.039 --> 01:33:38.460
everything else.

01:33:38.520 --> 01:33:41.819
At least no one had ever dared to ask

01:33:41.819 --> 01:33:42.000
her.

01:33:42.060 --> 01:33:44.520
Hey, did you happen to hear me thinking

01:33:44.520 --> 01:33:46.260
about what a terrible queen you'll be?

01:33:46.380 --> 01:33:49.079
And she was still afraid of night wings.

01:33:49.140 --> 01:33:51.539
The other ice wings were delusional not

01:33:51.539 --> 01:33:51.840
to be.

01:33:51.899 --> 01:33:54.960
Do you want me to go talk to them first?

01:33:55.020 --> 01:33:56.220
Length asked.

01:33:56.279 --> 01:33:59.399
Snowfall realized the other dragon had

01:33:59.399 --> 01:34:01.079
been studying her face for the last few

01:34:01.079 --> 01:34:01.319
minutes.

01:34:01.380 --> 01:34:04.560
No, Snowfall growled.

01:34:04.619 --> 01:34:05.819
I'll go.

01:34:05.880 --> 01:34:08.220
We'll leave 2 guards here in case they

01:34:08.220 --> 01:34:08.939
have to fly for help.

01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:11.579
She flicked her tail at the 3 biggest

01:34:11.579 --> 01:34:13.560
guards to signal them to follow her.

01:34:13.619 --> 01:34:17.579
The closer they got, the more Snowfall

01:34:17.579 --> 01:34:19.619
noticed how bedraggled all the invaders

01:34:19.619 --> 01:34:20.220
looked.

01:34:20.279 --> 01:34:24.000
Some of them had singed tails or wings.

01:34:24.060 --> 01:34:25.800
All of them were wet and crusted with

01:34:25.800 --> 01:34:26.699
salt from the spray.

01:34:26.760 --> 01:34:28.979
Most of them were very thin.

01:34:29.039 --> 01:34:32.460
Almost all the colorful dragons had heavy

01:34:32.460 --> 01:34:34.439
looking metal wrist cuffs around their

01:34:34.439 --> 01:34:35.579
front talons.

01:34:35.640 --> 01:34:38.100
Why would anyone wear something like that

01:34:38.100 --> 01:34:39.119
for a long flight?

01:34:39.180 --> 01:34:41.880
Snowfall wondered suspiciously.

01:34:41.939 --> 01:34:44.220
They drag you down the whole time.

01:34:44.279 --> 01:34:46.739
They must be some kind of powerful

01:34:46.739 --> 01:34:47.279
weapon.

01:34:47.340 --> 01:34:50.699
Some of the green dragons lived oddly

01:34:50.699 --> 01:34:53.340
lumpy until they realized they were each

01:34:53.340 --> 01:34:55.020
wearing several woven pouches.

01:34:55.079 --> 01:34:58.079
And what's in those, she wondered.

01:34:58.140 --> 01:34:59.880
Car stop checks?

01:34:59.939 --> 01:35:01.739
What if they have something that can

01:35:01.739 --> 01:35:03.300
enchant us to hand over our whole

01:35:03.300 --> 01:35:03.720
kingdom?

01:35:03.779 --> 01:35:07.260
She touched the diamonds in her armband

01:35:07.260 --> 01:35:08.939
sharp edged and cold.

01:35:09.000 --> 01:35:12.000
It was comforting to know she had magic

01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:12.420
of her own.

01:35:12.479 --> 01:35:15.720
Most of the dragons looked up wearily as

01:35:15.720 --> 01:35:18.119
Snowfall and the others landed, pebbles

01:35:18.119 --> 01:35:19.500
and dice crunching under her claws.

01:35:19.619 --> 01:35:22.500
One of the green dragons stood up

01:35:22.500 --> 01:35:25.560
frowning, but then another grain dragon

01:35:25.560 --> 01:35:27.779
tugged her back down, and a 3rd grain

01:35:27.779 --> 01:35:29.819
dragon climbed to her feet, and came to

01:35:29.819 --> 01:35:30.600
face snowfall.

01:35:30.659 --> 01:35:33.180
Who are you?

01:35:33.239 --> 01:35:34.380
Snowfall demanded.

01:35:34.500 --> 01:35:36.899
What are you doing in my kingdom?

01:35:36.960 --> 01:35:39.960
The green dragon sat down and spread her

01:35:39.960 --> 01:35:40.260
wings.

01:35:40.319 --> 01:35:43.319
With her front talons raised, palms up.

01:35:43.380 --> 01:35:47.760
I am pre, um, Queen Hazel of the Leaf

01:35:47.760 --> 01:35:48.180
Wings.

01:35:48.239 --> 01:35:50.880
The other dragons traveling with us are

01:35:50.880 --> 01:35:51.720
silkwings.

01:35:51.779 --> 01:35:55.020
We come from the land of Pantala across

01:35:55.020 --> 01:35:55.560
the sea.

01:35:55.619 --> 01:35:58.439
Seems like a lot of dragons to bring with

01:35:58.439 --> 01:35:59.880
you for a neighborly visit.

01:35:59.939 --> 01:36:00.960
Snowfall said.

01:36:01.020 --> 01:36:03.119
I'm afraid we need help.

01:36:03.180 --> 01:36:06.600
Hazel said, sorrow flickering across her

01:36:06.600 --> 01:36:06.899
face.

01:36:06.960 --> 01:36:10.500
We were forced to flee our home very

01:36:10.500 --> 01:36:11.100
suddenly.

01:36:11.159 --> 01:36:14.100
Our jungle was burning, and our queen was

01:36:14.100 --> 01:36:14.340
gone.

01:36:14.399 --> 01:36:17.460
There is a terrible danger back on our

01:36:17.460 --> 01:36:20.579
continent, and if we hadn't escaped, it

01:36:20.579 --> 01:36:21.600
would have destroyed us all.

01:36:21.720 --> 01:36:26.039
Snowfall could feel the waves of sympathy

01:36:26.039 --> 01:36:28.619
radiating off links, who was standing a

01:36:28.619 --> 01:36:29.640
little too close to her left.

01:36:29.699 --> 01:36:32.819
No surprise that she would fall for any

01:36:32.819 --> 01:36:34.619
sad snout story she heard.

01:36:34.680 --> 01:36:36.659
But snowfall was smarter than that.

01:36:36.720 --> 01:36:38.880
She had a kingdom to protect.

01:36:39.000 --> 01:36:42.000
It sounds like you should have stayed and

01:36:42.000 --> 01:36:43.739
fought for your land, she said.

01:36:43.800 --> 01:36:46.199
We don't have any room for you anyway.

01:36:46.260 --> 01:36:48.420
You're going to have to leave, right

01:36:48.420 --> 01:36:48.899
now.

01:36:48.960 --> 01:36:51.420
Hazel's face fell.

01:36:51.479 --> 01:36:53.640
Just wait.

01:36:53.699 --> 01:36:54.180
Please.

01:36:54.239 --> 01:36:56.279
Let me tell you the whole story.

01:36:56.340 --> 01:36:59.760
Something suddenly charged at them across

01:36:59.760 --> 01:37:02.520
the sand, shrieking alien syllables.

01:37:02.579 --> 01:37:05.520
Snowballs bun toward it, drawing her

01:37:05.520 --> 01:37:07.680
knives, and was a tail flick away from

01:37:07.680 --> 01:37:10.079
throwing them, when she realized the

01:37:10.079 --> 01:37:11.760
attacker was a tiny dragonette.

01:37:11.819 --> 01:37:14.699
Like, really tiny.

01:37:14.760 --> 01:37:17.279
Let's get it to a stop with a terrified

01:37:17.279 --> 01:37:19.560
yelp, staring up at her glittering

01:37:19.560 --> 01:37:20.039
weaponry.

01:37:20.100 --> 01:37:23.699
Big, black rimmed eyes blinked in a warm

01:37:23.699 --> 01:37:24.539
golden face.

01:37:24.600 --> 01:37:27.300
Her 4 wings were a little more shimmery

01:37:27.300 --> 01:37:29.579
and thinner than most of the others, and

01:37:29.579 --> 01:37:31.500
her scales alternated in black and yellow

01:37:31.500 --> 01:37:32.340
stripes.

01:37:32.399 --> 01:37:34.800
The dragonette burst into tears.

01:37:34.859 --> 01:37:38.640
Oh, well done, Your Majesty.

01:37:38.699 --> 01:37:40.619
Links whispered to Snowfall.

01:37:40.680 --> 01:37:42.600
Excellent self-defense.

01:37:42.659 --> 01:37:45.779
Another yellow and black dragon came

01:37:45.779 --> 01:37:47.760
hurrying over and wrapped her wings

01:37:47.760 --> 01:37:48.239
around the baby.

01:37:48.300 --> 01:37:51.600
She wore crooked spectacles, and she

01:37:51.600 --> 01:37:52.979
looked absolutely exhausted.

01:37:53.100 --> 01:37:56.699
It's all right, she murmured.

01:37:56.760 --> 01:37:58.380
Don't cry, Bumblebee.

01:37:58.439 --> 01:38:00.359
Look, we made it to the distant

01:38:00.359 --> 01:38:00.899
kingdoms.

01:38:00.960 --> 01:38:02.939
Can you believe it's real?

01:38:03.000 --> 01:38:04.020
Isn't this amazing?

01:38:04.079 --> 01:38:04.979
We're here.

01:38:05.039 --> 01:38:06.300
We're safe now.

01:38:06.359 --> 01:38:09.000
Length, shot, snowfall, uh.

01:38:09.060 --> 01:38:11.220
You're going to crush this moment, aren't

01:38:11.220 --> 01:38:11.399
you?

01:38:11.460 --> 01:38:12.060
Look.

01:38:12.119 --> 01:38:14.279
Pibishimmy?

01:38:14.340 --> 01:38:16.439
Bumblebee sniffled into the other

01:38:16.439 --> 01:38:17.399
dragon's shoulder.

01:38:17.460 --> 01:38:20.340
Boutique, awar.

01:38:20.460 --> 01:38:23.699
The spectacled dragon looked up and met

01:38:23.699 --> 01:38:24.720
Snowfall's gaze.

01:38:24.779 --> 01:38:27.899
Her eyes flew wide, and suddenly she

01:38:27.899 --> 01:38:28.800
didn't look tired at all.

01:38:28.859 --> 01:38:32.279
Oh, wow, she cried.

01:38:32.340 --> 01:38:34.800
Our 1st new dragon in the distant

01:38:34.800 --> 01:38:35.399
kingdoms?

01:38:35.460 --> 01:38:37.800
Isn't she beyond amazing?

01:38:37.859 --> 01:38:40.020
Oh my gosh, she looks like she's made of

01:38:40.020 --> 01:38:40.439
ice.

01:38:40.500 --> 01:38:42.060
I had no idea.

01:38:42.119 --> 01:38:43.439
Hello, hi.

01:38:43.500 --> 01:38:45.180
Are you actually made of ice?

01:38:45.239 --> 01:38:46.979
I mean, you can't be right?

01:38:47.039 --> 01:38:49.979
No, you're clearly biological, but how

01:38:49.979 --> 01:38:51.300
are you so shiny?

01:38:51.359 --> 01:38:53.340
It is very cold here.

01:38:53.399 --> 01:38:55.859
Is this some kind of Arctic adaptation?

01:38:55.920 --> 01:38:57.840
Cricket?

01:38:57.899 --> 01:39:00.239
The one called Hazel said in a warning

01:39:00.239 --> 01:39:00.659
tone.

01:39:00.720 --> 01:39:03.420
I am trying to negotiate with this dragon

01:39:03.420 --> 01:39:03.840
queen.

01:39:03.899 --> 01:39:06.420
She is the queen.

01:39:06.539 --> 01:39:09.119
Cricket burst out, so excited.

01:39:09.180 --> 01:39:11.220
Her words started tumbling over each

01:39:11.220 --> 01:39:12.239
other even faster.

01:39:12.300 --> 01:39:14.100
Of the whole continent?

01:39:14.220 --> 01:39:15.000
Wow.

01:39:15.060 --> 01:39:16.500
How many dragons is that?

01:39:16.560 --> 01:39:18.180
Do you think this place is as big as

01:39:18.180 --> 01:39:18.720
Pantala?

01:39:18.779 --> 01:39:20.939
Of the Ice Kingdom.

01:39:21.000 --> 01:39:23.460
Snowball interrupted coldly.

01:39:23.520 --> 01:39:26.760
I am Queen Snowfall of the Ice Wings.

01:39:26.819 --> 01:39:30.479
But no, we're not actually made of ice.

01:39:30.539 --> 01:39:32.220
Links whispered to Cricket.

01:39:32.279 --> 01:39:34.619
Snowfall glared at her.

01:39:34.680 --> 01:39:38.159
Beyond Cricket and Hazel and Bumblebee

01:39:38.159 --> 01:39:39.960
Snowfall could see even more dragons

01:39:39.960 --> 01:39:41.880
arriving, staggering onto the beach.

01:39:41.939 --> 01:39:44.880
There really were 100s of them.

01:39:44.939 --> 01:39:48.779
And they landed with such relieved

01:39:48.779 --> 01:39:51.000
expressions, as though this was exactly

01:39:51.000 --> 01:39:53.760
where they wanted to be, as though it

01:39:53.760 --> 01:39:55.439
were just the kind of territory they'd

01:39:55.439 --> 01:39:56.159
been hoping to steal.

01:39:56.220 --> 01:39:59.939
One of them collapsed, digging his claws

01:39:59.939 --> 01:40:01.380
into the snow dusted soil.

01:40:01.439 --> 01:40:03.119
Is he sick?

01:40:03.180 --> 01:40:06.479
Snowfall wondered, is he contagious?

01:40:06.600 --> 01:40:09.239
Another movement made her spin to her

01:40:09.239 --> 01:40:11.399
right, but it was only a pair of young

01:40:11.399 --> 01:40:13.920
strong leaf wings, helping to drag a silk

01:40:13.920 --> 01:40:14.579
wing out of the water.

01:40:14.640 --> 01:40:16.500
Do they have magic?

01:40:16.560 --> 01:40:19.199
Are they going to suddenly turn violent?

01:40:19.260 --> 01:40:23.699
You must leave, she said to Hazel.

01:40:23.760 --> 01:40:26.399
She realized she was still holding the

01:40:26.399 --> 01:40:28.020
knives she'd brandished to the

01:40:28.020 --> 01:40:28.739
dragonette.

01:40:28.800 --> 01:40:31.260
She lifted her head regally and sheathed

01:40:31.260 --> 01:40:31.500
them.

01:40:31.619 --> 01:40:33.600
You are not welcome here.

01:40:33.720 --> 01:40:36.539
Go invade Thorn's kingdom instead.

01:40:36.600 --> 01:40:39.539
We have several dragons who can't

01:40:39.539 --> 01:40:42.840
possibly fly any further right now, Hazel

01:40:42.840 --> 01:40:43.260
pleaded.

01:40:43.319 --> 01:40:46.739
They're injured, or elderly, or too small

01:40:46.739 --> 01:40:48.720
and we've been traveling for days.

01:40:48.779 --> 01:40:50.100
Please.

01:40:50.220 --> 01:40:51.960
They need to rest.

01:40:52.079 --> 01:40:55.920
That's not my problem, Snowfall said.

01:40:55.979 --> 01:40:57.960
They're not my dragons.

01:40:58.020 --> 01:41:01.859
Snowfall, Link said meaningfully.

01:41:01.920 --> 01:41:04.979
They're not, Snowball protested.

01:41:05.039 --> 01:41:07.260
I have a tribe to protect.

01:41:07.319 --> 01:41:09.060
We are no threat to you.

01:41:09.119 --> 01:41:10.500
I promise.

01:41:10.560 --> 01:41:11.819
Hazel said.

01:41:11.880 --> 01:41:15.420
Snowfall realized the leaf wing queen was

01:41:15.420 --> 01:41:15.779
shivering.

01:41:15.840 --> 01:41:19.260
Was that fear or exhaustion or cold?

01:41:19.319 --> 01:41:21.119
Hopefully cold.

01:41:21.180 --> 01:41:23.640
Maybe the temperatures would drive them

01:41:23.640 --> 01:41:25.500
out of the ice kingdom even faster than

01:41:25.500 --> 01:41:25.979
she could.

01:41:26.100 --> 01:41:30.000
If so, maybe letting them stay for one

01:41:30.000 --> 01:41:31.439
night would be all right.

01:41:31.500 --> 01:41:34.560
If they promised to stay on the beach, and

01:41:34.560 --> 01:41:35.699
left 1st thing in the morning.

01:41:35.819 --> 01:41:40.260
That's everybody, a brash, familiar voice

01:41:40.260 --> 01:41:40.859
announced.

01:41:40.920 --> 01:41:44.399
Someone large and blue bounded out of the

01:41:44.399 --> 01:41:44.760
ocean.

01:41:44.819 --> 01:41:47.939
I mean, except Turtle, but he'll come

01:41:47.939 --> 01:41:48.840
wheezing up soon.

01:41:48.899 --> 01:41:49.560
Don't worry.

01:41:49.619 --> 01:41:51.779
Snowfall gasped.

01:41:51.899 --> 01:41:54.899
You, she spat.

01:41:54.960 --> 01:41:59.279
It was that awful sea wing dragonette of

01:41:59.279 --> 01:42:01.319
destiny who ran the Jade Mountain

01:42:01.319 --> 01:42:01.739
Academy.

01:42:01.800 --> 01:42:04.859
So this was a sea wing invasion.

01:42:04.920 --> 01:42:06.119
Somehow.

01:42:06.239 --> 01:42:08.399
And wasn't she friends with glory?

01:42:08.520 --> 01:42:10.920
The night wings were probably lurking

01:42:10.920 --> 01:42:13.199
nearby, waiting for snowfall to be

01:42:13.199 --> 01:42:15.180
distracted by the weird looking dragons

01:42:15.180 --> 01:42:16.560
and then they would pounce.

01:42:16.680 --> 01:42:20.279
An ambush, an attack, just as she'd

01:42:20.279 --> 01:42:20.640
suspected.

01:42:20.699 --> 01:42:22.800
Oh no.

01:42:22.859 --> 01:42:26.579
Tsunami said, wrinkling her snout and

01:42:26.579 --> 01:42:28.380
giving Snowfall a disgruntled book.

01:42:28.439 --> 01:42:30.300
We hit the ice kingdom?

01:42:30.359 --> 01:42:32.939
I thought we were way farther south.

01:42:33.000 --> 01:42:35.399
She sighed and shook out her wings.

01:42:35.460 --> 01:42:37.920
Scattering salt water and kelp and tiny

01:42:37.920 --> 01:42:39.119
sea snails everywhere.

01:42:39.119 --> 01:42:41.819
What are you doing here?

01:42:41.939 --> 01:42:44.460
Snowfall demanded furiously.

01:42:44.520 --> 01:42:47.340
How dare you come into my kingdom

01:42:47.340 --> 01:42:50.159
bringing an enormous throng of suspicious

01:42:50.159 --> 01:42:51.300
weird looking strangers.

01:42:51.359 --> 01:42:52.859
Get out at once.

01:42:52.920 --> 01:42:56.520
We're not suspicious, the one named

01:42:56.520 --> 01:42:57.600
Cricket protested.

01:42:57.659 --> 01:43:00.479
We're just tired and scared, and running

01:43:00.479 --> 01:43:02.520
away from a really scary bad thing.

01:43:02.579 --> 01:43:04.319
What do you think we could possibly do?

01:43:04.380 --> 01:43:08.100
It's all right, Cricket, Hazel said

01:43:08.100 --> 01:43:10.319
taking a step back toward her other green

01:43:10.319 --> 01:43:10.920
dragons.

01:43:10.979 --> 01:43:14.100
Snowfall noticed that the 1st one who'd

01:43:14.100 --> 01:43:16.260
moved was standing up again, frowning

01:43:16.260 --> 01:43:16.920
menacingly.

01:43:17.039 --> 01:43:19.859
I'd be alarmed if this many dragons

01:43:19.859 --> 01:43:21.899
suddenly showed up in my jungle too.

01:43:21.960 --> 01:43:25.199
You wouldn't be super rude to them though

01:43:25.199 --> 01:43:25.680
I bet.

01:43:25.800 --> 01:43:27.119
Tsunami snapped.

01:43:27.180 --> 01:43:30.359
Oh, I know, Cricket said.

01:43:30.420 --> 01:43:33.239
Wait, Queen Snowfall, we're not total

01:43:33.239 --> 01:43:33.720
strangers.

01:43:33.840 --> 01:43:36.300
Bumblebee and I had an ancestor from your

01:43:36.300 --> 01:43:37.979
continent 100s of years ago.

01:43:38.039 --> 01:43:39.720
Doesn't that help to know?

01:43:39.779 --> 01:43:41.159
You must have heard of her.

01:43:41.220 --> 01:43:43.619
We are descendants of Clearsight.

01:43:43.739 --> 01:43:47.460
Out of the corner of her eye, Snowfall

01:43:47.460 --> 01:43:48.779
saw tsunami wins.

01:43:48.899 --> 01:43:52.020
Snowfall had a strange moment of vertigo

01:43:52.140 --> 01:43:53.880
as though the ground under her had

01:43:53.880 --> 01:43:56.279
suddenly cracked and sent her sliding

01:43:56.279 --> 01:43:57.000
into the dark ocean.

01:43:57.060 --> 01:44:00.119
A pulse of fury stabbed through her

01:44:00.119 --> 01:44:02.159
temples and out to the tips of her

01:44:02.159 --> 01:44:02.399
wings.

01:44:02.460 --> 01:44:04.739
The black scales.

01:44:04.800 --> 01:44:07.739
The secretive, smarter than you

01:44:07.739 --> 01:44:08.279
expressions.

01:44:08.340 --> 01:44:10.199
She should have seen it.

01:44:10.260 --> 01:44:13.560
These dragons were part Nightwing.

01:44:13.619 --> 01:44:16.920
And worse than that, they were related to

01:44:16.920 --> 01:44:17.939
clear sight.

01:44:18.000 --> 01:44:21.119
Clearside, the dragon who'd helped Dark

01:44:21.119 --> 01:44:23.279
Stalker rise to power in the 1st place.

01:44:23.340 --> 01:44:26.579
The true love of that mass murderer.

01:44:26.640 --> 01:44:28.979
Seething with rage.

01:44:29.039 --> 01:44:32.100
Snowfall lifted her wrists and smashed

01:44:32.100 --> 01:44:33.060
the diamonds together.

01:44:33.119 --> 01:44:37.680
Once, twice, 3 times, just as the

01:44:37.680 --> 01:44:38.640
instructions had said.

01:44:38.699 --> 01:44:42.300
Behind her, along the top of the cliff

01:44:42.300 --> 01:44:45.060
the entire ice wing army appeared.

01:44:45.119 --> 01:44:49.500
Chapter 5.

01:44:49.859 --> 01:44:53.460
Lynx jumped away from her, startled.

01:44:53.520 --> 01:44:56.880
The other dragons, Hazel, Cricket

01:44:56.880 --> 01:45:00.119
Bumblebee, Tsunami, and 100s of invaders

01:45:00.119 --> 01:45:02.520
Frozen Place, staring up at the

01:45:02.520 --> 01:45:06.239
glittering ranks of soldiers, 3 moons.

01:45:06.300 --> 01:45:07.680
How did you do that?

01:45:07.800 --> 01:45:09.600
Links hissed.

01:45:09.659 --> 01:45:12.420
Snowfall tipped the wristbands toward her

01:45:12.420 --> 01:45:15.720
smirking the gift of stealth, she said.

01:45:15.779 --> 01:45:18.359
According to the notes in the forbidden

01:45:18.359 --> 01:45:20.159
treasury, she could use it to hide

01:45:20.159 --> 01:45:22.380
herself or anything else she wanted to.

01:45:22.439 --> 01:45:25.020
So she'd gathered her army in the night

01:45:25.020 --> 01:45:27.779
and prepared them to fly, weapons at the

01:45:27.779 --> 01:45:28.140
ready.

01:45:28.140 --> 01:45:31.319
She'd tested her new magic toy to make

01:45:31.319 --> 01:45:33.000
sure she could hide them, soaring along

01:45:33.000 --> 01:45:33.420
behind her.

01:45:33.479 --> 01:45:35.220
And there they were.

01:45:35.279 --> 01:45:37.800
As though she had pulled them from thin

01:45:37.800 --> 01:45:38.100
air.

01:45:38.159 --> 01:45:40.560
Now she felt strong.

01:45:40.619 --> 01:45:42.960
She felt like a queen.

01:45:43.020 --> 01:45:46.800
The strange dragons all look terrified of

01:45:46.800 --> 01:45:47.579
her.

01:45:47.640 --> 01:45:49.439
So brilliant.

01:45:49.500 --> 01:45:52.739
Everything she'd hoped for between the

01:45:52.739 --> 01:45:55.020
army and the magic, she'd proven her

01:45:55.020 --> 01:45:55.380
power.

01:45:55.439 --> 01:45:57.720
They wouldn't dare argue with her

01:45:57.720 --> 01:45:58.020
anymore.

01:45:58.079 --> 01:46:02.100
Why did mother ever dig these out, she

01:46:02.100 --> 01:46:02.460
wondered.

01:46:02.579 --> 01:46:05.159
We could have used some impressive ice

01:46:05.159 --> 01:46:06.359
wing magic during the war.

01:46:06.420 --> 01:46:09.779
She could have hidden her army, or spies

01:46:09.779 --> 01:46:12.060
or an assassin to go after burn and

01:46:12.060 --> 01:46:12.479
blister.

01:46:12.539 --> 01:46:15.060
The gift of stealth could have made us

01:46:15.060 --> 01:46:16.680
the most dangerous tribe in the war.

01:46:16.739 --> 01:46:20.579
Well, it's time for an ice wing queen

01:46:20.579 --> 01:46:22.199
who's not afraid to use all her

01:46:22.199 --> 01:46:22.619
resources.

01:46:22.680 --> 01:46:26.340
She lowered her voice to its coldest

01:46:26.340 --> 01:46:27.180
iciest tone.

01:46:27.300 --> 01:46:28.979
I said.

01:46:29.100 --> 01:46:31.079
She hissed softly.

01:46:31.140 --> 01:46:33.899
Get out.

01:46:33.960 --> 01:46:37.319
Hazel's gaze flickered hesitantly from

01:46:37.319 --> 01:46:39.479
her to the army to lynx.

01:46:39.600 --> 01:46:41.880
Of course, she said.

01:46:41.939 --> 01:46:44.159
Well, we'll go.

01:46:44.220 --> 01:46:46.140
She took another step back.

01:46:46.199 --> 01:46:49.199
There was one dragon who didn't look

01:46:49.199 --> 01:46:50.819
terrified, Snowfall realized.

01:46:50.880 --> 01:46:53.819
The frowning leaf wing behind Hazel was

01:46:53.819 --> 01:46:56.460
bristling, like an angry polar bear about

01:46:56.460 --> 01:46:56.880
to charge.

01:46:56.939 --> 01:46:59.939
Her tail lashed as she glared back at

01:46:59.939 --> 01:47:00.600
snowfall.

01:47:00.659 --> 01:47:03.359
The sooner Snowfall got that one out of

01:47:03.359 --> 01:47:04.739
the ice kingdom. the better.

01:47:04.859 --> 01:47:08.279
What was that?

01:47:08.399 --> 01:47:11.579
Cricket breathed, adjusting her glasses

01:47:11.579 --> 01:47:12.840
to squint up at the army.

01:47:12.899 --> 01:47:15.899
Can all dragons here turn invisible?

01:47:15.960 --> 01:47:16.439
What else can you do?

01:47:16.560 --> 01:47:18.359
Bumblebee, did you see that?

01:47:18.420 --> 01:47:20.880
Sparkle, toothie.

01:47:20.939 --> 01:47:24.000
Bumblebee murmured, burying her head in

01:47:24.000 --> 01:47:24.720
cricket's shoulder.

01:47:24.779 --> 01:47:27.119
All right, all right.

01:47:27.180 --> 01:47:28.800
Tsunami grumbled.

01:47:28.920 --> 01:47:30.659
She spread her wings.

01:47:30.720 --> 01:47:33.119
I might have known we'd land in a worst

01:47:33.119 --> 01:47:35.279
kingdom, and the 1st dragon weed sea

01:47:35.279 --> 01:47:36.539
would be the queen of grumps.

01:47:36.659 --> 01:47:40.020
Before snowfall could bite Tsunami's head

01:47:40.020 --> 01:47:41.880
off, Links unexpectedly spoke up.

01:47:41.939 --> 01:47:45.720
She is not grumpy, Link said.

01:47:45.779 --> 01:47:48.840
She's a great queen, and this is the best

01:47:48.840 --> 01:47:51.119
kingdom and nobody invited you here to

01:47:51.119 --> 01:47:51.659
insult us.

01:47:51.779 --> 01:47:54.899
Hazel had been giving quiet orders in the

01:47:54.899 --> 01:47:57.300
background, sending dragons to gather

01:47:57.300 --> 01:47:59.819
everyone, but now she paused and touched

01:47:59.819 --> 01:48:02.220
tsunami's shoulder before the sing wing

01:48:02.220 --> 01:48:03.060
could argue with links.

01:48:03.119 --> 01:48:05.460
Can you lead us somewhere else?

01:48:05.520 --> 01:48:06.479
She asked.

01:48:06.539 --> 01:48:10.140
Yeah, south to the kingdom of sand

01:48:10.140 --> 01:48:11.340
tsunami said.

01:48:11.399 --> 01:48:13.680
We'll find Luna and Moon there.

01:48:13.739 --> 01:48:16.079
And I'm sure Queen Thorn.

01:48:16.140 --> 01:48:17.939
We'll know how to treat a group of

01:48:17.939 --> 01:48:20.279
harmless tired, sad dragons who've lost

01:48:20.279 --> 01:48:21.060
their home.

01:48:21.180 --> 01:48:23.100
She's welcome to keep you.

01:48:23.220 --> 01:48:25.859
Snowfall snapped. throwing her wings

01:48:25.859 --> 01:48:26.100
back.

01:48:26.159 --> 01:48:29.460
Tsunami tossed her a disgusted look, and

01:48:29.460 --> 01:48:31.140
turned to help organize the dragons for

01:48:31.140 --> 01:48:31.500
departure.

01:48:31.560 --> 01:48:35.460
South, Snowfall thought suddenly.

01:48:35.520 --> 01:48:38.520
If they follow the coast, which they

01:48:38.520 --> 01:48:40.680
probably will, so they can rest often.

01:48:40.800 --> 01:48:42.720
They might end up flying within range

01:48:42.720 --> 01:48:44.220
with a great ice cliff.

01:48:44.279 --> 01:48:46.500
Which will promptly shoot them all with

01:48:46.500 --> 01:48:48.779
ice beers, even though they'll be flying

01:48:48.779 --> 01:48:49.680
over it from the other side.

01:48:49.739 --> 01:48:52.140
She hesitated.

01:48:52.199 --> 01:48:54.300
That would get rid of the problem

01:48:54.300 --> 01:48:54.899
completely.

01:48:54.960 --> 01:48:58.020
Those descendants of Clear Sight would be

01:48:58.020 --> 01:48:59.939
gone, and she wouldn't have to worry

01:48:59.939 --> 01:49:01.979
about any of this anymore, and her

01:49:01.979 --> 01:49:03.420
kingdom would be safe again.

01:49:03.479 --> 01:49:05.520
She would be safe again.

01:49:05.579 --> 01:49:09.300
But sending them off to be massacred was

01:49:09.300 --> 01:49:11.460
exactly the kind of thing Dark Stalker

01:49:11.460 --> 01:49:11.699
would do.

01:49:11.760 --> 01:49:14.159
Snowfall was about to speak.

01:49:14.220 --> 01:49:16.739
She was pretty sure she was about to say

01:49:16.739 --> 01:49:17.100
something.

01:49:17.159 --> 01:49:19.140
When Lynx got there first.

01:49:19.260 --> 01:49:21.779
You have to be careful.

01:49:21.840 --> 01:49:23.399
She said to Hazel.

01:49:23.460 --> 01:49:25.560
There's an ice cliff at our southern

01:49:25.560 --> 01:49:27.659
border that attacks dragons who fly over

01:49:27.659 --> 01:49:29.279
it if they're not ice wings.

01:49:29.340 --> 01:49:31.680
He'll have to circle out to sea to avoid

01:49:31.680 --> 01:49:31.859
it.

01:49:31.920 --> 01:49:34.560
Pretty far out to sea, I think.

01:49:34.619 --> 01:49:39.060
This news made Hazel look so tired, and

01:49:39.060 --> 01:49:41.640
Cricket so fascinated, the snowfall

01:49:41.640 --> 01:49:44.340
almost almost melted.

01:49:44.399 --> 01:49:46.319
But she couldn't.

01:49:46.380 --> 01:49:47.939
She had to be strong.

01:49:48.060 --> 01:49:50.579
Outside dragons were dangerous.

01:49:50.640 --> 01:49:52.260
That was all there was to it.

01:49:52.319 --> 01:49:56.699
We'll fly with you, Lang said, with

01:49:56.699 --> 01:49:59.279
absolutely no effort to run this plan by

01:49:59.279 --> 01:50:02.039
snowfall at all, we'll take you to the

01:50:02.039 --> 01:50:03.899
southern border of the ice kingdom, and

01:50:03.899 --> 01:50:05.159
make sure you get across safely.

01:50:05.220 --> 01:50:07.199
All of you?

01:50:07.260 --> 01:50:09.960
Hazel asked, glancing up at the army

01:50:09.960 --> 01:50:10.199
again.

01:50:10.260 --> 01:50:14.039
Just me and Queen Snowfall, Link said.

01:50:14.100 --> 01:50:19.260
Snowfall interjected, and 10 of my

01:50:19.260 --> 01:50:20.220
personal gar.

01:50:20.279 --> 01:50:23.039
She wasn't quite sure why she was

01:50:23.039 --> 01:50:24.180
agrained to go along at all.

01:50:24.239 --> 01:50:26.699
Perhaps she just wanted to make sure they

01:50:26.699 --> 01:50:27.300
were really gone.

01:50:27.359 --> 01:50:29.399
Yes, that made sense.

01:50:29.460 --> 01:50:32.399
Best to see them well over the border and

01:50:32.399 --> 01:50:34.020
definitely out of her life forever.

01:50:34.079 --> 01:50:37.680
Should she recloak her army and have them

01:50:37.680 --> 01:50:38.039
follow?

01:50:38.100 --> 01:50:40.500
Or would that be overkill?

01:50:40.560 --> 01:50:43.319
A sign of fear instead of strength?

01:50:43.380 --> 01:50:44.520
Hmm.

01:50:44.579 --> 01:50:47.640
She considered her options while she sat

01:50:47.640 --> 01:50:49.439
up on the cliff and watched the dragons

01:50:49.439 --> 01:50:50.939
below prepare to leave.

01:50:51.000 --> 01:50:54.180
They moved very slowly.

01:50:54.239 --> 01:50:57.359
If it was true that they'd been fleeing

01:50:57.359 --> 01:50:59.760
some enemy, Snowfall thought it must have

01:50:59.760 --> 01:51:02.220
been a rather lethargic one, or else it

01:51:02.220 --> 01:51:03.000
could have caught them easily.

01:51:03.060 --> 01:51:05.640
An enormous sloth perhaps.

01:51:05.760 --> 01:51:08.039
An elephant seal on land?

01:51:08.100 --> 01:51:10.439
A malevolent glacier?

01:51:10.500 --> 01:51:12.659
Lynx was down there trying to help.

01:51:12.720 --> 01:51:15.359
Snowfall could see her moving between the

01:51:15.359 --> 01:51:17.640
dragons, bringing them bowls of melted

01:51:17.640 --> 01:51:18.239
snow to drink.

01:51:18.300 --> 01:51:21.060
She'd also asked one of the soldiers to

01:51:21.060 --> 01:51:22.979
fly to the nearest gift of subsistence

01:51:22.979 --> 01:51:25.560
and bring back a few seals to share among

01:51:25.560 --> 01:51:26.100
the dragons.

01:51:26.159 --> 01:51:28.920
Snowfall had considered ordering him not

01:51:28.920 --> 01:51:31.800
to, but she decided it would be queenlier

01:51:31.800 --> 01:51:32.460
not to get involved.

01:51:32.520 --> 01:51:35.939
And after all, the gift of subsistence

01:51:35.939 --> 01:51:38.819
was magic, producing as many seals as the

01:51:38.819 --> 01:51:40.920
dragons needed, so they couldn't exactly

01:51:40.920 --> 01:51:41.340
run out.

01:51:41.399 --> 01:51:44.520
Apparently, the silk wings didn't eat

01:51:44.520 --> 01:51:47.100
meat though, which added to Snowfall's

01:51:47.100 --> 01:51:47.640
suspicions.

01:51:47.760 --> 01:51:50.220
Because wasn't that true of rain wings as

01:51:50.220 --> 01:51:50.340
well?

01:51:50.460 --> 01:51:53.279
Was anyone sure that these weird dragons

01:51:53.279 --> 01:51:54.600
weren't working for Queen Glory?

01:51:54.659 --> 01:51:57.420
Anyway, there was nothing growing in the

01:51:57.420 --> 01:51:58.439
pine grove that they could eat.

01:51:58.500 --> 01:51:59.760
See.

01:51:59.880 --> 01:52:01.920
The Ice Kingdom would be all wrong for

01:52:01.920 --> 01:52:02.159
them.

01:52:02.220 --> 01:52:05.579
Snowfall told herself, freezing over any

01:52:05.579 --> 01:52:07.199
twinges of guilt inside her.

01:52:07.260 --> 01:52:11.039
Too cold, no plants, dragons who want

01:52:11.039 --> 01:52:11.579
them gone.

01:52:11.640 --> 01:52:13.680
They should move right along and become

01:52:13.680 --> 01:52:15.539
some other queen's problem.

01:52:15.600 --> 01:52:18.600
The strange dragons had some kind of

01:52:18.600 --> 01:52:20.819
large makeshift thing that floated on the

01:52:20.819 --> 01:52:23.520
ocean, made of palm trees lashed together

01:52:23.520 --> 01:52:25.560
with vines as far as snowfall could

01:52:25.560 --> 01:52:25.800
tell.

01:52:25.920 --> 01:52:28.439
Tsunami had left it out at sea when she

01:52:28.439 --> 01:52:31.020
came crashing in, but she swam back out

01:52:31.020 --> 01:52:32.760
to get it, and a few of the healthier

01:52:32.760 --> 01:52:35.520
dragons, plus links, helped her drag it

01:52:35.520 --> 01:52:36.000
onto the shore.

01:52:36.060 --> 01:52:39.239
Snowfall watched them narrowly as they

01:52:39.239 --> 01:52:41.939
guided some of the oldest, weakest, and

01:52:41.939 --> 01:52:43.800
smallest dragons to climb on top of it.

01:52:43.920 --> 01:52:46.680
Evidently, the idea was to haul them over

01:52:46.680 --> 01:52:48.779
the top of the ocean, because they were

01:52:48.779 --> 01:52:50.460
incapable of flying that distance on

01:52:50.460 --> 01:52:50.760
their own.

01:52:50.819 --> 01:52:54.000
Then they shouldn't have left their own

01:52:54.000 --> 01:52:55.739
stupid continent, she thought.

01:52:55.800 --> 01:52:57.420
What did you call it?

01:52:57.479 --> 01:52:58.859
Pintala?

01:52:58.979 --> 01:53:01.020
They should have stayed there and dealt

01:53:01.020 --> 01:53:02.880
with their own problems, instead of

01:53:02.880 --> 01:53:03.539
bringing them to me.

01:53:03.600 --> 01:53:06.720
She flipped her tail to summon her

01:53:06.720 --> 01:53:07.380
favorite general.

01:53:07.439 --> 01:53:11.279
Ivory came over immediately, bowing with

01:53:11.279 --> 01:53:13.319
exactly the amount of respect Snowfall

01:53:13.319 --> 01:53:13.739
was looking for.

01:53:13.800 --> 01:53:16.920
Ivory had been in that battle with the

01:53:16.920 --> 01:53:17.340
night wings.

01:53:17.399 --> 01:53:20.880
But she hadn't thought, Queen Snowfall.

01:53:20.939 --> 01:53:23.460
Ugh, what a terrible choice, like so many

01:53:23.460 --> 01:53:24.720
of the dragons in her army.

01:53:24.779 --> 01:53:27.720
Her thoughts had been more alike, I hope

01:53:27.720 --> 01:53:28.439
she can do this.

01:53:28.500 --> 01:53:30.779
If we survive this, I'm going to help our

01:53:30.779 --> 01:53:32.220
new queen, however I can.

01:53:32.279 --> 01:53:34.260
It wasn't exactly.

01:53:34.380 --> 01:53:35.640
Hooray, Snow Fault.

01:53:35.699 --> 01:53:36.239
She's the best.

01:53:36.300 --> 01:53:38.640
But it was one of the only supportive

01:53:38.640 --> 01:53:40.500
things Snowfall had heard in the chaos.

01:53:40.619 --> 01:53:43.260
That's why she was Snowfall's favorite

01:53:43.260 --> 01:53:45.539
and would stay in the 1st circle forever

01:53:45.539 --> 01:53:47.579
as far as Snowfall was concerned.

01:53:47.640 --> 01:53:50.340
I am putting you in charge while I'm away

01:53:50.340 --> 01:53:50.939
from the kingdom.

01:53:51.000 --> 01:53:52.380
Snowfall said.

01:53:52.439 --> 01:53:53.760
Me?

01:53:53.819 --> 01:53:56.039
General Ivory looked surprised for a

01:53:56.039 --> 01:53:56.279
moment.

01:53:56.340 --> 01:53:58.500
Yes, your majesty.

01:53:58.619 --> 01:54:01.920
May I ask, what if Tundra objects?

01:54:02.039 --> 01:54:05.760
Then she can eat her own tail, Snowfall

01:54:05.760 --> 01:54:06.239
snapped.

01:54:06.300 --> 01:54:08.640
Tell her if she complains, I'll be happy

01:54:08.640 --> 01:54:10.140
to move her down to a different circle.

01:54:10.199 --> 01:54:14.220
Oh, she thought, with a sudden surge of

01:54:14.220 --> 01:54:15.779
something almost like joy.

01:54:15.840 --> 01:54:19.739
If I escort the invaders out of here, I

01:54:19.739 --> 01:54:21.060
definitely won't make it back to the

01:54:21.060 --> 01:54:22.500
palace by nightfall tonight.

01:54:22.619 --> 01:54:25.020
I'll have to camp overnight somewhere.

01:54:25.079 --> 01:54:27.300
Which means I won't have to do the wall.

01:54:27.420 --> 01:54:30.600
Perhaps it was a bad sign that this

01:54:30.600 --> 01:54:33.119
moment was literally the happiest she'd

01:54:33.119 --> 01:54:34.260
felt since becoming queen.

01:54:34.319 --> 01:54:37.979
Lynx waved up to her, and the dragons

01:54:37.979 --> 01:54:40.079
below rose from the beach in a whirlwind

01:54:40.079 --> 01:54:41.100
of wing beats.

01:54:41.399 --> 01:54:43.920
Snowfall summoned the 10 guards she'd

01:54:43.920 --> 01:54:45.960
chosen, and leaped into the sky to join

01:54:45.960 --> 01:54:46.199
them.

01:54:46.260 --> 01:54:50.279
Not with them, obviously, more like off

01:54:50.279 --> 01:54:52.619
to the side, where she could see them, but

01:54:52.619 --> 01:54:53.819
not get bummed by any of them.

01:54:53.880 --> 01:54:56.880
Her plan to stay apart was thwarted

01:54:56.880 --> 01:54:59.220
though, when Queen Hazel soared over to

01:54:59.220 --> 01:54:59.939
fly next to her.

01:55:00.000 --> 01:55:02.100
What are you doing?

01:55:02.159 --> 01:55:04.979
Snowfall asked, banking away slightly.

01:55:05.039 --> 01:55:08.760
We'll be out of your kingdom soon, Hazel

01:55:08.760 --> 01:55:09.000
said.

01:55:09.060 --> 01:55:10.800
I was just hoping.

01:55:11.100 --> 01:55:13.859
You're the only queen I've ever met.

01:55:13.920 --> 01:55:17.100
Besides my great grandmother, and you're

01:55:17.100 --> 01:55:17.939
not at all ancient.

01:55:18.000 --> 01:55:21.840
I mean, you seem about my age, and I just

01:55:21.840 --> 01:55:24.420
I'd love to know how you do everything.

01:55:24.539 --> 01:55:27.420
Because it's really new for me and it's a

01:55:27.420 --> 01:55:30.239
lot, a lot harder than I thought it would

01:55:30.239 --> 01:55:30.420
be.

01:55:30.539 --> 01:55:31.739
You know?

01:55:31.800 --> 01:55:34.619
My great grandmother has been queen for

01:55:34.619 --> 01:55:37.500
the longest ever time, and I thought I'd

01:55:37.500 --> 01:55:39.300
have so much longer before I'd have to do

01:55:39.300 --> 01:55:39.539
this.

01:55:39.659 --> 01:55:43.140
Snowfall was certainly not going to feel

01:55:43.140 --> 01:55:45.420
sympathy for a weird invasive dragon from

01:55:45.420 --> 01:55:46.020
across the sea.

01:55:46.079 --> 01:55:49.020
They were not the same at all.

01:55:49.140 --> 01:55:52.199
How long have you been, queen?

01:55:52.199 --> 01:55:53.399
Hazel asked.

01:55:53.460 --> 01:55:56.880
Less than half a year, but if she told

01:55:56.880 --> 01:55:59.399
Hazel that, the invading dragons wouldn't

01:55:59.399 --> 01:56:00.000
take her seriously.

01:56:00.060 --> 01:56:02.640
She needed them to stay afraid of her.

01:56:02.699 --> 01:56:04.979
A long time.

01:56:05.039 --> 01:56:06.180
She answered.

01:56:06.239 --> 01:56:09.060
It actually felt very true as she said

01:56:09.060 --> 01:56:09.359
it.

01:56:09.420 --> 01:56:11.699
Maybe when you barely slept.

01:56:11.760 --> 01:56:13.920
All the days and nights seemed a 1000

01:56:13.920 --> 01:56:14.520
times longer.

01:56:14.579 --> 01:56:17.640
Oh, Hazel said.

01:56:17.699 --> 01:56:20.399
So you must find it really easy by now.

01:56:20.460 --> 01:56:23.460
Snowfall hoped her face didn't give her

01:56:23.460 --> 01:56:23.699
away.

01:56:23.760 --> 01:56:28.859
There are Challenges, of course, she

01:56:28.859 --> 01:56:29.039
said.

01:56:29.100 --> 01:56:31.020
But the ice wings have a lot of

01:56:31.020 --> 01:56:33.300
traditions in place, that are responsible

01:56:33.300 --> 01:56:33.899
for upholding.

01:56:33.960 --> 01:56:36.300
They help keep the kingdom safe and

01:56:36.300 --> 01:56:38.340
orderly, so as long as I follow them

01:56:38.340 --> 01:56:40.739
everything stays in its place, and

01:56:40.739 --> 01:56:41.579
everyone will be safe.

01:56:41.640 --> 01:56:44.279
Safe would be so great.

01:56:44.399 --> 01:56:46.199
Hazel said sadly.

01:56:46.260 --> 01:56:49.439
We lost our home and our trees before I

01:56:49.439 --> 01:56:50.039
even hatched.

01:56:50.100 --> 01:56:52.859
If we had traditions like that once

01:56:52.859 --> 01:56:54.180
they're gone now.

01:56:54.300 --> 01:56:57.659
She paused for a moment, gazing off west

01:56:57.659 --> 01:56:59.640
as if the horizon was lined with the

01:56:59.640 --> 01:57:01.500
ghosts of everything her tribe had lost.

01:57:01.619 --> 01:57:05.220
After a few heartbeats, she asked, how

01:57:05.220 --> 01:57:06.420
did your last queen die?

01:57:06.479 --> 01:57:10.020
Evil magic plague, Snowfall said.

01:57:10.079 --> 01:57:11.100
Yours?

01:57:11.159 --> 01:57:12.840
Hazel hesitated.

01:57:12.899 --> 01:57:13.920
Well?

01:57:14.340 --> 01:57:16.199
I don't think she's dead.

01:57:16.260 --> 01:57:17.939
But I don't know for sure.

01:57:18.000 --> 01:57:20.939
We were fighting this enemy who can take

01:57:20.939 --> 01:57:23.819
over dragon minds and control them, and

01:57:23.819 --> 01:57:25.560
it got control of Queen Sequoia.

01:57:25.560 --> 01:57:28.739
So it might have killed her, I guess, but

01:57:28.739 --> 01:57:30.840
I think it would keep her alive. to use

01:57:30.840 --> 01:57:31.500
her against us.

01:57:31.560 --> 01:57:34.859
She sighed, and then noticed the way

01:57:34.859 --> 01:57:36.060
Snowfall was staring at her.

01:57:36.119 --> 01:57:37.199
What?

01:57:37.260 --> 01:57:40.619
An enemy who can take over dragon mines?

01:57:40.680 --> 01:57:41.939
Snowfall asked.

01:57:42.000 --> 01:57:44.279
Was his name Dark Stalker?

01:57:44.340 --> 01:57:48.300
No, Hazel said cautiously.

01:57:48.359 --> 01:57:51.300
That is, we always thought it was Queen

01:57:51.300 --> 01:57:53.939
Wasp, but it turns out maybe it's a

01:57:53.939 --> 01:57:54.359
plant?

01:57:54.479 --> 01:57:56.880
Snowfall narrowed her eyes.

01:57:56.939 --> 01:57:58.560
A plant.

01:57:58.619 --> 01:58:02.880
A very evil plant, Hazel added.

01:58:03.000 --> 01:58:05.340
What was more likely?

01:58:05.399 --> 01:58:06.960
An evil plant?

01:58:07.020 --> 01:58:09.600
Or that dark soccer's terrible nightwing

01:58:09.600 --> 01:58:11.939
powers somehow reached across the ocean

01:58:11.939 --> 01:58:14.880
to ensnare a mythical continent full of

01:58:14.880 --> 01:58:16.079
clear sight's descendants?

01:58:16.199 --> 01:58:18.899
Snowfall pondered this for a moment.

01:58:19.020 --> 01:58:21.960
Nothing really seemed beyond Dark

01:58:21.960 --> 01:58:24.119
Stalker's magic or malevolence in her

01:58:24.119 --> 01:58:24.359
opinion.

01:58:24.420 --> 01:58:27.180
Or maybe it was some other magic

01:58:27.180 --> 01:58:28.500
malevolent night wing.

01:58:28.619 --> 01:58:30.600
There could definitely be others.

01:58:30.659 --> 01:58:34.140
So, if she is still alive.

01:58:34.199 --> 01:58:35.939
Are you going back to save her?

01:58:36.000 --> 01:58:37.260
Snowball asked.

01:58:37.319 --> 01:58:39.000
Definitely.

01:58:39.060 --> 01:58:39.659
Yes.

01:58:39.720 --> 01:58:42.720
If I can figure out how, Hazel said.

01:58:42.840 --> 01:58:45.239
How to stop the mind control, I mean.

01:58:45.300 --> 01:58:48.420
But then, wouldn't you have to give your

01:58:48.420 --> 01:58:49.439
throne back to her?

01:58:49.500 --> 01:58:53.100
I do that in a heartbeat, Hazel said

01:58:53.100 --> 01:58:53.640
fervently.

01:58:53.699 --> 01:58:55.439
Would I?

01:58:55.500 --> 01:58:56.880
Snowfall thought.

01:58:57.000 --> 01:58:59.039
In exchange for my mother back.

01:58:59.100 --> 01:59:00.840
Yes.

01:59:00.899 --> 01:59:03.000
But they still weren't the same.

01:59:03.060 --> 01:59:06.060
Hazel, for instance, probably didn't have

01:59:06.060 --> 01:59:08.039
a nefarious missing sister lurking

01:59:08.039 --> 01:59:08.220
around.

01:59:08.279 --> 01:59:11.460
Is there anyone else who wants to be

01:59:11.460 --> 01:59:11.880
queen?

01:59:11.939 --> 01:59:13.079
Snowfall asked.

01:59:13.199 --> 01:59:16.140
I mean, someone who might take the throne

01:59:16.140 --> 01:59:16.439
from you?

01:59:16.560 --> 01:59:20.579
Hazel cast a glance over her shoulder, and

01:59:20.579 --> 01:59:22.619
snowfall followed her gaze to the leaf

01:59:22.619 --> 01:59:24.000
wing who'd been frowning at her before.

01:59:24.060 --> 01:59:27.119
She was flying close to her green friend

01:59:27.119 --> 01:59:29.579
almost close enough to twine their tails

01:59:29.579 --> 01:59:31.380
together, and it looked like they were

01:59:31.380 --> 01:59:31.800
arguing.

01:59:31.859 --> 01:59:34.859
No, Hazel said.

01:59:34.920 --> 01:59:37.560
I mean, there are dragons who would

01:59:37.560 --> 01:59:40.020
probably be better queens than me, but

01:59:40.020 --> 01:59:40.859
they don't want it.

01:59:40.920 --> 01:59:42.359
Ha!

01:59:42.420 --> 01:59:44.100
They say they don't want it.

01:59:44.159 --> 01:59:45.899
Snowfall burst out.

01:59:45.960 --> 01:59:48.420
You want some advice on being a queen?

01:59:48.479 --> 01:59:49.560
Watch your back.

01:59:49.619 --> 01:59:51.239
Don't trust anyone.

01:59:51.300 --> 01:59:54.239
Someone is always plotting to take your

01:59:54.239 --> 01:59:56.699
throne or murder your subjects or steal

01:59:56.699 --> 01:59:57.239
your territory.

01:59:57.300 --> 01:59:59.100
Hazel blinked.

01:59:59.220 --> 02:00:00.960
Shading her eyes from the bright

02:00:00.960 --> 02:00:02.819
reflection off the snowy cliffs to their

02:00:02.819 --> 02:00:03.060
left.

02:00:03.119 --> 02:00:04.500
Always?

02:00:04.619 --> 02:00:05.819
She said faintly.

02:00:05.939 --> 02:00:08.279
Even here in the distant kingdoms?

02:00:08.340 --> 02:00:10.380
Snowfall snorted.

02:00:10.439 --> 02:00:14.100
Especially here, and especially the night

02:00:14.100 --> 02:00:14.880
wing tribe.

02:00:14.939 --> 02:00:17.279
Watch out for any dragons with black and

02:00:17.279 --> 02:00:17.939
silver scales.

02:00:18.000 --> 02:00:19.859
They can read your mind and see the

02:00:19.859 --> 02:00:22.079
future, and they want to wipe out all the

02:00:22.079 --> 02:00:24.060
other tribes so they can be the only ones

02:00:24.060 --> 02:00:24.600
left.

02:00:24.659 --> 02:00:28.920
That sounds like clear sight, Hazel said

02:00:28.920 --> 02:00:29.399
thoughtfully.

02:00:29.460 --> 02:00:31.979
I mean, not the mind rating.

02:00:32.039 --> 02:00:33.899
I've never heard that she could do that.

02:00:33.960 --> 02:00:36.300
Can dragons here really do that?

02:00:36.359 --> 02:00:38.640
But she could see the future.

02:00:38.699 --> 02:00:41.699
And her descendants nearly wiped out my

02:00:41.699 --> 02:00:42.420
tribe.

02:00:42.479 --> 02:00:43.859
See?

02:00:43.920 --> 02:00:46.560
Snowfall batted a seagull away from her

02:00:46.560 --> 02:00:46.979
with her tail.

02:00:47.100 --> 02:00:51.539
Night wings, evil, untrustworthy, and yes

02:00:51.539 --> 02:00:53.220
totally mind readers.

02:00:53.279 --> 02:00:56.520
She doesn't sound evil in her book

02:00:56.520 --> 02:00:56.699
though.

02:00:56.760 --> 02:00:58.199
Hazel offered.

02:00:58.260 --> 02:01:01.079
I read it a few times on the journey, and

02:01:01.079 --> 02:01:03.960
she sounds much kinder than, say, Queen

02:01:03.960 --> 02:01:04.560
Wasp.

02:01:04.680 --> 02:01:06.899
I don't think she would have wiped out a

02:01:06.899 --> 02:01:08.579
tribe or hurt anyone if she could help

02:01:08.579 --> 02:01:08.819
it.

02:01:08.880 --> 02:01:11.399
Snowfall rolled her eyes.

02:01:11.460 --> 02:01:14.279
This green dragon wasn't going to rule

02:01:14.279 --> 02:01:16.439
much longer, if she kept trying to see

02:01:16.439 --> 02:01:18.180
the best in dragons like Clearsight.

02:01:18.300 --> 02:01:21.779
I'd better go check on the raft, Hazel

02:01:21.779 --> 02:01:22.079
said.

02:01:22.140 --> 02:01:24.600
Squinting down at the dragons towing

02:01:24.600 --> 02:01:25.739
their contraption through the waves.

02:01:25.800 --> 02:01:28.380
I hope we can talk more later.

02:01:28.439 --> 02:01:31.560
She whisked away, leaving snowfall to her

02:01:31.560 --> 02:01:33.180
unending circle of anxious thoughts.

02:01:33.239 --> 02:01:36.659
It was a much longer flight than Snowfall

02:01:36.659 --> 02:01:38.579
had anticipated, partly because the

02:01:38.579 --> 02:01:41.039
strange dragons had to stop to rest, like

02:01:41.039 --> 02:01:44.760
all the time, and partly because they had

02:01:44.760 --> 02:01:47.579
to detour so far out over the ocean to

02:01:47.579 --> 02:01:49.739
stay out of range of the ice cliff, and

02:01:49.739 --> 02:01:51.960
partly because the raft was unwieldy and

02:01:51.960 --> 02:01:54.300
awkward, and the dragon's towing it kept

02:01:54.300 --> 02:01:56.760
switching places, and once a surprise

02:01:56.760 --> 02:01:59.100
wave flipped the whole thing over, and

02:01:59.100 --> 02:02:01.260
everyone had a massive panic attack, and

02:02:01.260 --> 02:02:02.880
dove into the water to rescue the

02:02:02.880 --> 02:02:03.899
floundering swimmers.

02:02:03.960 --> 02:02:06.300
Even though tsunami and turtle were right

02:02:06.300 --> 02:02:08.279
there, and everything was totally fine

02:02:08.279 --> 02:02:10.800
and all the overreacting was completely

02:02:10.800 --> 02:02:11.520
unnecessary.

02:02:11.579 --> 02:02:14.819
But by late afternoon, they finally

02:02:14.819 --> 02:02:17.100
reached the far side of the tundra that

02:02:17.100 --> 02:02:19.079
was the disputed territory between the

02:02:19.079 --> 02:02:21.119
Ice Kingdom and the Kingdom of Sand.

02:02:21.239 --> 02:02:24.659
Territory that was definitely snowfalls.

02:02:24.720 --> 02:02:27.300
As far as snowfall was concerned, the

02:02:27.300 --> 02:02:29.520
land belonged to the ice kingdom, and

02:02:29.520 --> 02:02:31.920
Queen Thorn could stick a cactus upper

02:02:31.920 --> 02:02:33.420
nose if she thought she had any right to

02:02:33.420 --> 02:02:33.720
it.

02:02:33.779 --> 02:02:36.960
The pebbly beaches gave way slowly to a

02:02:36.960 --> 02:02:39.479
coastline of yellow white sand, and the

02:02:39.479 --> 02:02:41.340
temperature grew warmer and warmer as

02:02:41.340 --> 02:02:41.760
they flew.

02:02:41.819 --> 02:02:44.819
Just as the sun brushed the western edge

02:02:44.819 --> 02:02:47.699
of the orange flooded sky, tsunami came

02:02:47.699 --> 02:02:50.279
flying out of the water, waved at Hazel

02:02:50.279 --> 02:02:51.720
and pointed to something down below.

02:02:51.779 --> 02:02:56.460
A hut with a palm frond roof, tucked into

02:02:56.460 --> 02:02:58.619
a small cove where the water was calm and

02:02:58.619 --> 02:02:58.859
clear.

02:02:58.979 --> 02:03:02.579
And standing outside the hut, on the sand

02:03:02.579 --> 02:03:05.220
4 dragons, gazing up at the sky.

02:03:05.279 --> 02:03:09.180
Snowfall narrowed her eyes, wishing again

02:03:09.180 --> 02:03:10.920
that the stupid gift of vision ring

02:03:10.920 --> 02:03:12.060
actually worked.

02:03:12.119 --> 02:03:14.939
I swing eyesight was sharper than that of

02:03:14.939 --> 02:03:17.220
most other tribes, but she couldn't see

02:03:17.220 --> 02:03:19.020
their faces clearly from this distance

02:03:19.020 --> 02:03:20.100
like she wanted to.

02:03:20.159 --> 02:03:23.399
She could see, though, that one of the

02:03:23.399 --> 02:03:25.859
dragons down there was pale green, with

02:03:25.859 --> 02:03:28.439
bits of blue and gold and white, and that

02:03:28.439 --> 02:03:30.720
it had 4 wings, like some of the strange

02:03:30.720 --> 02:03:33.539
dragons from across the sea, the silk

02:03:33.539 --> 02:03:35.220
wings, Hazel had called them.

02:03:35.279 --> 02:03:38.579
Also, it was standing next to what was

02:03:38.579 --> 02:03:40.619
clearly a night wing.

02:03:40.680 --> 02:03:42.119
A night wing.

02:03:42.180 --> 02:03:44.760
With one of the weird rainbow dragons.

02:03:44.819 --> 02:03:46.920
They were working together.

02:03:46.979 --> 02:03:49.380
Snowfall was right all along.

02:03:49.439 --> 02:03:53.039
She felt a shiver of fear run along her

02:03:53.039 --> 02:03:55.079
scales, and tried to tamp it down.

02:03:55.140 --> 02:03:58.380
There were 10 well armed ice wing

02:03:58.380 --> 02:03:58.859
soldiers with her.

02:03:58.920 --> 02:04:02.039
She had the gift of stealth and the gift

02:04:02.039 --> 02:04:02.460
of strength.

02:04:02.579 --> 02:04:05.100
That night wing was the one who should be

02:04:05.100 --> 02:04:05.460
scared.

02:04:05.520 --> 02:04:09.659
The other 2 were sandwings, boring

02:04:09.659 --> 02:04:10.199
nothing to...

02:04:10.199 --> 02:04:11.579
Wait.

02:04:11.699 --> 02:04:15.060
Snowfall swooped lower and let out a

02:04:15.060 --> 02:04:15.420
hiss.

02:04:15.479 --> 02:04:19.739
One of the sand wings was jerboa.

02:04:19.800 --> 02:04:23.399
Jerboa, her animus dragon.

02:04:23.460 --> 02:04:26.279
Her animus, who was supposed to live in a

02:04:26.279 --> 02:04:28.859
hut all alone, and never talked to anyone

02:04:28.859 --> 02:04:30.119
but the ice wing queen.

02:04:30.180 --> 02:04:33.060
Maybe that wasn't exactly what Queen

02:04:33.060 --> 02:04:34.859
Glacier had said, but something like

02:04:34.859 --> 02:04:35.100
that.

02:04:35.159 --> 02:04:38.279
She wasn't supposed to help other sand

02:04:38.279 --> 02:04:40.560
wings and weird dragons from across the

02:04:40.560 --> 02:04:42.720
sea, and she definitely shouldn't be

02:04:42.720 --> 02:04:44.220
hanging out with a night wing.

02:04:44.279 --> 02:04:47.159
Nightwings had their own animus dragons.

02:04:47.220 --> 02:04:48.960
They didn't need Jerboa too.

02:04:49.020 --> 02:04:50.880
Why was she helping one of them?

02:04:50.939 --> 02:04:53.760
Or all of them, maybe actually?

02:04:53.819 --> 02:04:58.020
So maybe Turboa was lying about animus

02:04:58.020 --> 02:05:00.060
magic being broken, because she didn't

02:05:00.060 --> 02:05:01.920
want to help ice wings anymore, because

02:05:01.920 --> 02:05:04.079
now she was working with Snowfall's

02:05:04.079 --> 02:05:04.500
enemies.

02:05:04.560 --> 02:05:07.920
Snowfall's wings were vibrating with

02:05:07.920 --> 02:05:10.380
stress and anger and nerves as she

02:05:10.380 --> 02:05:11.939
crashed onto the beach ahead of the other

02:05:11.939 --> 02:05:12.420
dragons.

02:05:12.479 --> 02:05:15.840
The Silkwing bounded toward her with her

02:05:15.840 --> 02:05:16.859
whole face alight.

02:05:16.920 --> 02:05:18.539
Is blue with you?

02:05:18.600 --> 02:05:19.859
And sore tail?

02:05:19.920 --> 02:05:21.960
Wait, you're not a Silkwing?

02:05:22.020 --> 02:05:24.720
Sorry, but, oh, Sundu.

02:05:24.779 --> 02:05:27.420
She hurried past snowfall and threw her

02:05:27.420 --> 02:05:30.359
wings around the frowny leaf wing, who, it

02:05:30.359 --> 02:05:32.699
turned out, had other expressions besides

02:05:32.699 --> 02:05:34.800
menacing, such as startled.

02:05:34.920 --> 02:05:36.659
Sundew.

02:05:36.720 --> 02:05:39.000
The silk wing cried again, letting her

02:05:39.000 --> 02:05:39.180
go.

02:05:39.239 --> 02:05:41.819
I can't believe you all made it here.

02:05:41.939 --> 02:05:43.500
We're sore tail and blue.

02:05:43.619 --> 02:05:47.579
Sundews, pleased look, fell away, and she

02:05:47.579 --> 02:05:49.560
dug grooves in the sand with her claws.

02:05:49.619 --> 02:05:51.420
They're not here, Lena.

02:05:51.539 --> 02:05:53.340
I'm so sorry.

02:05:53.399 --> 02:05:56.159
Luna pressed her talons to her face.

02:05:56.159 --> 02:05:58.560
But before she could burst into tears

02:05:58.560 --> 02:06:00.720
Sundew's companion jumped in.

02:06:00.720 --> 02:06:04.319
They're still alive, as far as we know.

02:06:04.380 --> 02:06:05.399
She said.

02:06:05.460 --> 02:06:07.739
The Queen Wasp has them.

02:06:07.800 --> 02:06:09.600
It's a long story.

02:06:09.720 --> 02:06:12.359
We're going to get them back.

02:06:12.539 --> 02:06:14.039
Sundu said fiercely.

02:06:14.100 --> 02:06:15.600
I promise you that.

02:06:15.659 --> 02:06:18.479
Even at slugs for brains, sword tail.

02:06:18.539 --> 02:06:20.220
We'll figure out how to save them.

02:06:20.279 --> 02:06:22.439
Yes, Luna said.

02:06:22.500 --> 02:06:23.939
I'm so ready.

02:06:24.000 --> 02:06:26.039
If you know how to cross the ocean, I'll

02:06:26.039 --> 02:06:26.520
do it right now.

02:06:26.579 --> 02:06:29.939
Crossing the ocean isn't the hard part

02:06:29.939 --> 02:06:30.899
unfortunately.

02:06:30.960 --> 02:06:32.460
Sundew said.

02:06:32.520 --> 02:06:35.880
Luna's eyes drifted to cricket, standing

02:06:35.880 --> 02:06:37.380
behind the leaf wings and holding

02:06:37.380 --> 02:06:38.039
Bumblebee.

02:06:38.100 --> 02:06:40.619
She beckoned the yellow and black dragon

02:06:40.619 --> 02:06:41.819
forward and hugged her too.

02:06:41.880 --> 02:06:46.260
Come, tell me all about it, she said, and

02:06:46.260 --> 02:06:48.239
the 5 of them went up the beach into the

02:06:48.239 --> 02:06:48.539
hut.

02:06:48.600 --> 02:06:51.659
Snowfall had only been half listening.

02:06:51.779 --> 02:06:55.260
Her focus was on Jerboa, and if she could

02:06:55.260 --> 02:06:57.420
freeze dragons with her eyeballs, the

02:06:57.420 --> 02:06:59.399
anima sandwing would have turned to ice

02:06:59.399 --> 02:07:00.720
all the way to her bones.

02:07:00.779 --> 02:07:04.199
The voice of the rage in her glare was so

02:07:04.199 --> 02:07:06.659
strong, she couldn't believe how long it

02:07:06.659 --> 02:07:08.819
took Jerboa to finally turn and meet her

02:07:08.819 --> 02:07:09.060
eyes.

02:07:09.119 --> 02:07:11.880
And then Treboa didn't even look guilty.

02:07:11.939 --> 02:07:13.260
She looked.

02:07:13.260 --> 02:07:14.520
Annoyed?

02:07:14.579 --> 02:07:15.659
Tired?

02:07:15.720 --> 02:07:17.640
Something aggravating.

02:07:17.699 --> 02:07:20.220
Snowfall stormed up to her.

02:07:20.279 --> 02:07:22.859
The night wing and the other sand wing

02:07:22.859 --> 02:07:24.779
had gone down to the water to help the

02:07:24.779 --> 02:07:27.180
sea wings drag the raft ashore, with lots

02:07:27.180 --> 02:07:29.520
of yelps and chirps and gleeful reunion

02:07:29.520 --> 02:07:29.819
noises.

02:07:29.880 --> 02:07:32.819
There was a small oasis of silence around

02:07:32.819 --> 02:07:34.800
her boa and her little patch of sand.

02:07:34.920 --> 02:07:38.520
What are you doing here?

02:07:38.579 --> 02:07:40.859
Snowfall growled at her.

02:07:40.920 --> 02:07:43.020
Treboa arched one eyebrow.

02:07:43.079 --> 02:07:45.300
I live here.

02:07:45.359 --> 02:07:47.699
What are you doing here?

02:07:47.760 --> 02:07:50.460
Are you working with these dragons?

02:07:50.520 --> 02:07:52.020
Snowfall demanded.

02:07:52.079 --> 02:07:54.600
Did you give them some magic to help them

02:07:54.600 --> 02:07:56.220
invade my kingdom?

02:07:56.279 --> 02:07:58.199
Treboa gave her a withering look.

02:07:58.260 --> 02:08:01.079
As I am quite sure, I have mentioned

02:08:01.079 --> 02:08:02.520
before, she said.

02:08:02.640 --> 02:08:05.460
No one wants to invade your kingdom.

02:08:05.579 --> 02:08:07.199
Wrong.

02:08:07.319 --> 02:08:08.699
Snowfall snapped.

02:08:08.760 --> 02:08:11.880
These dragons tried to, and I have driven

02:08:11.880 --> 02:08:12.180
them out.

02:08:12.239 --> 02:08:15.960
By myself, I might add, without any help

02:08:15.960 --> 02:08:16.439
from you.

02:08:16.500 --> 02:08:18.000
See?

02:08:18.119 --> 02:08:20.100
Turboa said flatly.

02:08:20.159 --> 02:08:21.779
I knew you could do it.

02:08:21.840 --> 02:08:24.180
You just had to believe in yourself.

02:08:24.239 --> 02:08:26.100
Raw, raw.

02:08:26.159 --> 02:08:29.399
Why are you helping a night wing instead

02:08:29.399 --> 02:08:29.880
of me?

02:08:29.939 --> 02:08:32.159
Snowfall asked in a low hiss.

02:08:32.220 --> 02:08:35.880
I'm not helping anyone, Treboa said.

02:08:35.939 --> 02:08:37.800
I fulfilled my purpose.

02:08:37.859 --> 02:08:41.159
All I did here is provide some shelter

02:08:41.159 --> 02:08:43.560
and make an introduction, although

02:08:43.560 --> 02:08:45.539
providing shelter to 3 dragons is quite

02:08:45.539 --> 02:08:45.840
different.

02:08:45.899 --> 02:08:48.479
From sharing my cove with 2 entire

02:08:48.479 --> 02:08:49.140
tribes.

02:08:49.199 --> 02:08:52.920
She wrinkled her snout slightly, as she

02:08:52.920 --> 02:08:54.600
looked around at the chaos of dragons

02:08:54.600 --> 02:08:55.500
engulfing her beach.

02:08:55.560 --> 02:08:58.380
Tales and talons were churning up the

02:08:58.380 --> 02:08:58.560
sand.

02:08:58.619 --> 02:09:01.260
Several dragons were wading in the

02:09:01.260 --> 02:09:03.539
shallows of the cove, catching fish and

02:09:03.539 --> 02:09:05.760
crabs and clouding the water with silt.

02:09:05.819 --> 02:09:09.180
Others had collapsed all along the beach

02:09:09.180 --> 02:09:11.520
wings flung out to either side, soaking

02:09:11.520 --> 02:09:12.000
up the sun.

02:09:12.060 --> 02:09:15.119
The relieved expressions were back on

02:09:15.119 --> 02:09:17.699
most of their faces, and some of the silk

02:09:17.699 --> 02:09:19.439
wings were already gathering coconuts to

02:09:19.439 --> 02:09:21.840
eat, and debating placidly about how to

02:09:21.840 --> 02:09:22.260
open them.

02:09:22.319 --> 02:09:25.260
The night wing came floundering back of

02:09:25.260 --> 02:09:27.239
the beach, and snowfall finally

02:09:27.239 --> 02:09:28.380
recognized her.

02:09:28.439 --> 02:09:30.840
It was that interfering little one with

02:09:30.840 --> 02:09:33.300
the visions, the one Winter liked so much

02:09:33.300 --> 02:09:36.060
Moonface or something like that.

02:09:36.119 --> 02:09:38.579
The one who had been Dark Stalker's very

02:09:38.579 --> 02:09:40.800
best friend when he 1st came out of the

02:09:40.800 --> 02:09:41.100
mountain.

02:09:41.159 --> 02:09:43.319
According to Winter.

02:09:43.380 --> 02:09:45.600
She'd also been instrumental in stopping

02:09:45.600 --> 02:09:47.760
Dark Stalker, but given the lack of

02:09:47.760 --> 02:09:51.420
actual evidence, or a body, specifically

02:09:51.420 --> 02:09:53.699
Snowfall would have liked a specifically

02:09:53.699 --> 02:09:57.239
clearly dead body to examine and yell at

02:09:57.239 --> 02:09:58.199
and stomp on.

02:09:58.260 --> 02:10:00.960
Snowfall couldn't help but still find her

02:10:00.960 --> 02:10:02.939
very suspicious.

02:10:03.000 --> 02:10:06.300
This was a particularly bad nightwing

02:10:06.300 --> 02:10:07.920
defined with her animus.

02:10:07.979 --> 02:10:11.819
Hello, Moonface said breathlessly.

02:10:11.880 --> 02:10:13.979
You are Queen Snowfall, aren't you?

02:10:14.039 --> 02:10:16.680
You know perfectly well that I am?

02:10:16.739 --> 02:10:18.659
Snowfall said coldly.

02:10:18.720 --> 02:10:20.220
Mind reader.

02:10:20.279 --> 02:10:22.979
The black dragon had the grace to look a

02:10:22.979 --> 02:10:23.640
little abashed.

02:10:23.699 --> 02:10:27.060
It's moon actually, she said.

02:10:27.119 --> 02:10:29.880
Just moon, not moonface.

02:10:29.939 --> 02:10:32.880
Snowfall wished one of the ice wing

02:10:32.880 --> 02:10:34.920
animus gifts had been an invulnerability

02:10:34.920 --> 02:10:35.880
to night wing powers.

02:10:35.939 --> 02:10:39.060
That would have been extremely useful.

02:10:39.119 --> 02:10:41.640
Why didn't anyone ever think of that?

02:10:41.699 --> 02:10:44.939
Because they weren't our mortal enemies

02:10:44.939 --> 02:10:47.220
until they stole Arctic, she remembered.

02:10:47.279 --> 02:10:50.460
And after that, there were no more animus

02:10:50.460 --> 02:10:50.819
gifts.

02:10:50.880 --> 02:10:54.000
Moon winced and touched her temples.

02:10:54.060 --> 02:10:58.260
This is a lot of noisy dragons, she said

02:10:58.260 --> 02:10:59.039
to Jerboa.

02:10:59.100 --> 02:11:03.119
It certainly is, Treboa said, eyeing a

02:11:03.119 --> 02:11:04.739
pair of leaf winged dragonettes as they

02:11:04.739 --> 02:11:06.479
tumbled and wrestled along the beach with

02:11:06.479 --> 02:11:07.260
squeals of joy.

02:11:07.380 --> 02:11:10.140
Is this what your vision showed you?

02:11:10.260 --> 02:11:12.779
Sort of, Moon said.

02:11:12.899 --> 02:11:15.119
But it's only the beginning, I think.

02:11:15.180 --> 02:11:17.279
Only the beginning.

02:11:17.340 --> 02:11:20.220
Treboa looked nearly as annoyed with Moon

02:11:20.220 --> 02:11:21.479
as she was with Snowfall.

02:11:21.539 --> 02:11:23.819
Are there a lot more coming?

02:11:23.880 --> 02:11:27.000
Here, to this beach in particular?

02:11:27.060 --> 02:11:28.500
No.

02:11:28.560 --> 02:11:33.239
Wait, actually, I don't know, Moon said.

02:11:33.359 --> 02:11:37.800
They can stay for now, Treboa said with a

02:11:37.800 --> 02:11:38.039
sigh.

02:11:38.159 --> 02:11:41.699
Until they're ready to move on, which had

02:11:41.699 --> 02:11:42.779
better be soon.

02:11:42.840 --> 02:11:45.420
But where do you expect them to end up?

02:11:45.539 --> 02:11:49.739
I know, cried the other sandwing, jumping

02:11:49.739 --> 02:11:51.119
over the dunes toward them in little

02:11:51.119 --> 02:11:52.199
flying, hopping leaps.

02:11:52.319 --> 02:11:54.300
I have an idea.

02:11:54.359 --> 02:11:56.039
We can take them to sanctuary.

02:11:56.100 --> 02:11:57.420
Yes.

02:11:57.479 --> 02:12:01.319
Of course, the night wing said, her whole

02:12:01.319 --> 02:12:02.159
phase relaxing.

02:12:02.220 --> 02:12:03.659
That's perfect.

02:12:03.720 --> 02:12:05.340
They'll be safe there.

02:12:05.399 --> 02:12:08.340
That's where winter is, right?

02:12:08.399 --> 02:12:09.899
Length aft.

02:12:09.960 --> 02:12:11.939
Moon gave her a curious look.

02:12:12.000 --> 02:12:13.560
Have we met?

02:12:13.619 --> 02:12:16.680
I'm lynx, the ice wing offered.

02:12:16.800 --> 02:12:18.359
A friend of Winter's.

02:12:18.479 --> 02:12:21.420
But an even more loyal subject, my

02:12:21.420 --> 02:12:23.460
excellent one true queen snowfall right

02:12:23.460 --> 02:12:24.119
here, of course.

02:12:24.180 --> 02:12:25.560
She added quickly.

02:12:25.619 --> 02:12:28.859
Snowfall flicked sand in her face with

02:12:28.859 --> 02:12:30.539
her tail, and Lynx sneezed.

02:12:30.659 --> 02:12:33.000
Do you want to come with us?

02:12:33.119 --> 02:12:34.619
To sanctuary?

02:12:34.680 --> 02:12:35.699
Moon asked.

02:12:35.760 --> 02:12:38.279
I'm sure Winter would be happy to see you

02:12:38.279 --> 02:12:40.619
and we could use a few more strong wings

02:12:40.619 --> 02:12:41.880
to help these dragons get there.

02:12:41.939 --> 02:12:45.119
Links gave Snowfall a hopeful look.

02:12:45.180 --> 02:12:48.359
We can't sit here for days and days

02:12:48.359 --> 02:12:49.859
Snowfall pointed out.

02:12:49.920 --> 02:12:54.239
It won't be that long, Moon said, catching

02:12:54.239 --> 02:12:55.739
a look on Jaboa's face.

02:12:55.800 --> 02:12:58.920
Maybe one day to rest, and we leave the

02:12:58.920 --> 02:12:59.760
day after tomorrow?

02:12:59.819 --> 02:13:02.279
Or tomorrow, maybe tomorrow?

02:13:02.340 --> 02:13:06.359
Night was falling swiftly around them, but

02:13:06.359 --> 02:13:06.960
for once.

02:13:07.020 --> 02:13:09.359
Snowfall could watch the stars come out

02:13:09.359 --> 02:13:11.279
without a sense of suffocating dread.

02:13:11.340 --> 02:13:14.520
For once, her scales weren't crawling

02:13:14.520 --> 02:13:16.500
with the knowledge that Tundra was tip

02:13:16.500 --> 02:13:18.779
tapping toward her on cold judgmental

02:13:18.779 --> 02:13:19.140
claws.

02:13:19.199 --> 02:13:23.579
The wall was far, far away, and Snowfall

02:13:23.579 --> 02:13:25.079
did not have to worry about it for one

02:13:25.079 --> 02:13:26.460
blissful night.

02:13:26.520 --> 02:13:30.420
Which could be 2 nights, maybe three.

02:13:30.479 --> 02:13:34.319
Maybe even 4 if sanctuary required

02:13:34.319 --> 02:13:35.699
inspecting or anything like that.

02:13:35.760 --> 02:13:38.279
The wall wasn't going anywhere.

02:13:38.340 --> 02:13:41.039
Snowfall would face it again when she

02:13:41.039 --> 02:13:42.300
returned to the ice palace.

02:13:42.359 --> 02:13:44.520
There was no need to rush back.

02:13:44.579 --> 02:13:46.920
Queen Glacier had often gone on

02:13:46.920 --> 02:13:49.020
diplomatic trips or battle missions for

02:13:49.020 --> 02:13:51.000
days, and the kingdom didn't collapse.

02:13:51.060 --> 02:13:54.060
Maybe that was why she'd gone away so

02:13:54.060 --> 02:13:55.439
often, come to think of it.

02:13:55.500 --> 02:13:59.100
Fine, Snowfall said to Length.

02:13:59.159 --> 02:14:00.840
We'll go to sanctuary.

02:14:00.899 --> 02:14:03.420
But only so I can make sure my weird

02:14:03.420 --> 02:14:05.699
scavenger obsessed cousin isn't up to

02:14:05.699 --> 02:14:07.859
anything with all his new other tribe

02:14:07.859 --> 02:14:08.460
friends.

02:14:08.699 --> 02:14:11.880
Snowfall shot a glare at Moon, just to

02:14:11.880 --> 02:14:13.380
clarify exactly who she meant.

02:14:13.439 --> 02:14:16.739
The tribes settle down to sleep early.

02:14:16.800 --> 02:14:19.800
The silk wings, it turned out, could

02:14:19.800 --> 02:14:21.720
produce some kind of strange silvery

02:14:21.720 --> 02:14:23.880
stuff from their wrists, and several of

02:14:23.880 --> 02:14:25.319
them made little hammocks out of it to

02:14:25.319 --> 02:14:27.899
hang from the trees, then slept in them.

02:14:27.960 --> 02:14:30.420
It was very weird, and didn't seem like a

02:14:30.420 --> 02:14:32.159
normal dragon ability to snowfall at

02:14:32.159 --> 02:14:32.340
all.

02:14:32.399 --> 02:14:35.760
Snowfall ordered the other ice wings to

02:14:35.760 --> 02:14:37.979
choose their own section of beach, some

02:14:37.979 --> 02:14:40.319
ways off from the other tribes, but still

02:14:40.319 --> 02:14:40.800
within sight.

02:14:40.859 --> 02:14:43.800
She set a rotating guard schedule and

02:14:43.800 --> 02:14:45.659
gave them instructions to keep an eye out

02:14:45.659 --> 02:14:47.220
for the night wing especially.

02:14:47.279 --> 02:14:50.640
It was mercifully cooler after the sun

02:14:50.640 --> 02:14:52.800
went down, but still a little too warm

02:14:52.800 --> 02:14:54.060
for snowfall's comfort.

02:14:54.119 --> 02:14:56.939
She stabbed her claws into the sand

02:14:56.939 --> 02:14:59.579
digging down and down until she found a

02:14:59.579 --> 02:15:02.100
cold layer of sand far below the sun

02:15:02.100 --> 02:15:03.239
warmed layers on top.

02:15:03.300 --> 02:15:04.859
This was better.

02:15:04.920 --> 02:15:07.979
It was no slab of ice, but it would cool

02:15:07.979 --> 02:15:08.880
her off enough to sleep.

02:15:08.939 --> 02:15:12.000
She curled into the hole and felt her

02:15:12.000 --> 02:15:13.380
weapons jabber in the side.

02:15:13.439 --> 02:15:16.380
The animus touched wristbands weighed

02:15:16.380 --> 02:15:18.720
down her talons, and the tiara was quite

02:15:18.720 --> 02:15:19.800
uncomfortable to sleep in.

02:15:19.859 --> 02:15:22.260
But she wasn't about to take any of it

02:15:22.260 --> 02:15:22.800
off, of course.

02:15:22.859 --> 02:15:25.859
She might need those knives, or throwing

02:15:25.859 --> 02:15:28.619
stars, or other knives, or magic strength

02:15:28.619 --> 02:15:30.600
if someone attacked her in the middle of

02:15:30.600 --> 02:15:30.899
the night.

02:15:30.960 --> 02:15:34.020
She was surrounded by enemies here after

02:15:34.020 --> 02:15:34.260
all.

02:15:34.319 --> 02:15:37.319
Well, technically, she was surrounded by

02:15:37.319 --> 02:15:40.319
10 ice wing soldiers, and then a bunch of

02:15:40.319 --> 02:15:40.859
enemies.

02:15:40.920 --> 02:15:42.000
Still.

02:15:42.119 --> 02:15:44.819
But she could take off the gift of vision

02:15:44.819 --> 02:15:46.739
at least, since the stupid thing didn't

02:15:46.739 --> 02:15:47.159
work at all.

02:15:47.220 --> 02:15:50.340
She tugged on the opal ring to slide it

02:15:50.340 --> 02:15:50.939
off her claw.

02:15:51.060 --> 02:15:52.800
It didn't move.

02:15:52.859 --> 02:15:54.600
Which was odd.

02:15:54.720 --> 02:15:57.060
Hadn't it felt loose when she 1st put it

02:15:57.060 --> 02:15:57.239
on?

02:15:57.300 --> 02:15:59.819
Snowfall frowned at it.

02:15:59.880 --> 02:16:02.340
The opal caught the starlight and

02:16:02.340 --> 02:16:03.899
twinkled cheerfully at her.

02:16:03.960 --> 02:16:05.819
She tugged on it again.

02:16:05.880 --> 02:16:08.159
It was definitely stuck.

02:16:08.220 --> 02:16:11.279
Weird and annoying.

02:16:11.340 --> 02:16:13.380
With a sigh, she gave up.

02:16:13.439 --> 02:16:16.319
She was too tired for a wrestling match

02:16:16.319 --> 02:16:17.399
with an accessory tonight.

02:16:17.460 --> 02:16:20.340
Tomorrow she'd rubbed palm oil all over

02:16:20.340 --> 02:16:22.439
it or something, and then it would slide

02:16:22.439 --> 02:16:23.100
off easily.

02:16:23.159 --> 02:16:25.920
Stupid, useless, frustrating stupid

02:16:25.920 --> 02:16:26.399
thing.

02:16:26.460 --> 02:16:29.819
She tucked her nose under her tail, and

02:16:29.819 --> 02:16:32.219
for the 1st time in months, she fell

02:16:32.219 --> 02:16:33.239
asleep within moments.

02:16:33.299 --> 02:16:37.739
Chapter 6.

02:16:37.799 --> 02:16:42.299
She is flying, although her wings feel so

02:16:42.299 --> 02:16:42.539
heavy.

02:16:42.600 --> 02:16:44.819
She thinks they might drag her down into

02:16:44.819 --> 02:16:46.200
the ocean any moment.

02:16:46.260 --> 02:16:49.260
She has been flying for days and days.

02:16:49.319 --> 02:16:51.659
And below her, there is nothing but

02:16:51.659 --> 02:16:53.940
treacherous water in every direction

02:16:53.940 --> 02:16:56.159
restlessly waiting to swallow her up.

02:16:56.219 --> 02:17:00.359
Each island is so far away, and some of

02:17:00.359 --> 02:17:02.519
them are so tiny, it's a miracle anyone

02:17:02.519 --> 02:17:03.299
spotted them at all.

02:17:03.360 --> 02:17:05.639
There was one island that was big

02:17:05.639 --> 02:17:06.000
enough.

02:17:06.059 --> 02:17:08.219
She'd hoped it was the distant kingdoms

02:17:08.219 --> 02:17:11.039
but it was empty, and the map said it was

02:17:11.039 --> 02:17:12.899
only halfway to the other continent.

02:17:13.020 --> 02:17:16.200
Every morning she lifts into the sky on a

02:17:16.200 --> 02:17:18.899
new wave of terror, afraid that this will

02:17:18.899 --> 02:17:21.239
be the day they run out of islands, and

02:17:21.239 --> 02:17:22.139
everyone will drown.

02:17:22.260 --> 02:17:24.540
They can't turn back.

02:17:24.600 --> 02:17:25.920
Nobody can.

02:17:25.979 --> 02:17:27.780
There's only one map.

02:17:27.840 --> 02:17:30.420
She wouldn't know how to follow the chain

02:17:30.420 --> 02:17:32.219
of islands all the way back home on her

02:17:32.219 --> 02:17:32.340
own.

02:17:32.459 --> 02:17:34.979
And what's behind them is even worse than

02:17:34.979 --> 02:17:35.219
this.

02:17:35.340 --> 02:17:38.579
The burning jungle, the white eyed

02:17:38.579 --> 02:17:41.100
dragons, the mind control you can catch

02:17:41.100 --> 02:17:43.739
as easily as breathing in the wrong smoke

02:17:43.739 --> 02:17:44.280
someone said.

02:17:44.340 --> 02:17:46.860
Her wings shiver with terror.

02:17:46.920 --> 02:17:49.620
She thought she was joining an army.

02:17:49.680 --> 02:17:52.379
She thought the time for rebellion had

02:17:52.379 --> 02:17:53.100
finally come.

02:17:53.159 --> 02:17:55.799
That it was time to be brave and heroic.

02:17:55.860 --> 02:17:59.159
Io said the chrysalis was going to rise

02:17:59.159 --> 02:18:02.040
up, join the leaf wings, and fight Queen

02:18:02.040 --> 02:18:03.959
Wasp for freedom and a better future.

02:18:04.020 --> 02:18:06.420
But they never had a chance.

02:18:06.479 --> 02:18:09.120
Aren't we going to fight them?

02:18:09.180 --> 02:18:10.200
She'd asked.

02:18:10.260 --> 02:18:11.940
No.

02:18:12.059 --> 02:18:14.579
By the time they reached the poison

02:18:14.579 --> 02:18:16.319
jungle, everything had changed.

02:18:16.379 --> 02:18:19.799
Queen Wasp could control silk wings and

02:18:19.799 --> 02:18:20.819
leaf wings now.

02:18:20.879 --> 02:18:23.699
They'd lost before lifting even a single

02:18:23.699 --> 02:18:24.239
claw.

02:18:24.360 --> 02:18:26.819
All they could do was run.

02:18:26.879 --> 02:18:29.519
She couldn't even stop to get her little

02:18:29.519 --> 02:18:31.979
brother or her placid, perpetually

02:18:31.979 --> 02:18:33.479
confused grandparents.

02:18:33.659 --> 02:18:36.059
She'd left them in Yellow Jacket Hive

02:18:36.059 --> 02:18:38.100
thinking she'd be home within a day or 2

02:18:38.100 --> 02:18:40.559
to free them with a triumphant leaf wing

02:18:40.559 --> 02:18:40.920
army.

02:18:40.920 --> 02:18:42.959
She didn't even say goodbye.

02:18:43.079 --> 02:18:45.120
Where are they now?

02:18:45.180 --> 02:18:47.819
Have their minds been taken by the hive

02:18:47.819 --> 02:18:48.479
wing queen?

02:18:48.540 --> 02:18:51.540
Are they even less free now than they'd

02:18:51.540 --> 02:18:51.899
been before?

02:18:51.959 --> 02:18:54.779
And will she ever see them again?

02:18:54.840 --> 02:18:58.379
Her tears blur the shapes of the dragons

02:18:58.379 --> 02:19:00.659
around her before they're swept away by

02:19:00.659 --> 02:19:01.260
the cold wind.

02:19:01.319 --> 02:19:04.500
Two more days until we reach the distant

02:19:04.500 --> 02:19:07.020
kingdoms, says a leaf wing flying beside

02:19:07.020 --> 02:19:07.200
her.

02:19:07.319 --> 02:19:08.639
His voice kind.

02:19:08.700 --> 02:19:10.739
Gentle leaf wings.

02:19:10.799 --> 02:19:13.259
She'd had no idea such a thing had ever

02:19:13.259 --> 02:19:14.699
existed before all this.

02:19:14.760 --> 02:19:16.559
We're almost there.

02:19:16.620 --> 02:19:18.959
Then we can rest and be safe.

02:19:19.020 --> 02:19:21.059
Safety.

02:19:21.120 --> 02:19:22.319
Rest.

02:19:22.379 --> 02:19:24.839
Those both sound impossible.

02:19:24.959 --> 02:19:28.259
All she wants is to lie down on solid

02:19:28.259 --> 02:19:31.559
ground and feel for even a moment that

02:19:31.559 --> 02:19:32.699
she doesn't have to be completely

02:19:32.699 --> 02:19:33.539
terrified.

02:19:33.600 --> 02:19:37.680
She rubs her face dry and flies on.

02:19:37.739 --> 02:19:42.120
Snowfall jolted awake, her heart

02:19:42.120 --> 02:19:42.780
pounding.

02:19:42.840 --> 02:19:45.840
Her wings flared up and flung sand in all

02:19:45.840 --> 02:19:46.620
directions.

02:19:46.680 --> 02:19:49.139
Her wings, her own wings.

02:19:49.200 --> 02:19:53.159
White and curved, and only 2 of them as

02:19:53.159 --> 02:19:54.059
they were supposed to be.

02:19:54.059 --> 02:19:56.579
She touched her claws to her skull.

02:19:56.639 --> 02:19:59.159
Nothing strange growing out of her head.

02:19:59.219 --> 02:20:02.280
She checked her wings again, but they

02:20:02.280 --> 02:20:03.959
definitely hadn't turned peach orange

02:20:03.959 --> 02:20:05.940
with sapphire spots during the night.

02:20:06.000 --> 02:20:07.860
She was on a beach.

02:20:07.920 --> 02:20:11.100
A beach with waves pounding nearby

02:20:11.100 --> 02:20:13.860
everything pale and pearly gray in the

02:20:13.860 --> 02:20:14.579
early morning light.

02:20:14.700 --> 02:20:17.340
Dragons slept all around her.

02:20:17.399 --> 02:20:19.920
I'm Queen Snowfall.

02:20:19.979 --> 02:20:21.600
She reassured herself.

02:20:21.659 --> 02:20:24.420
I am Queen Snowfall.

02:20:24.479 --> 02:20:27.299
She said out loud, because the universe

02:20:27.299 --> 02:20:29.219
had a whole skeptical vibe about it that

02:20:29.219 --> 02:20:30.360
was very aggravating.

02:20:30.420 --> 02:20:33.239
Length lifted her head from a nearby

02:20:33.239 --> 02:20:35.280
sandpile, squinting blearily.

02:20:35.340 --> 02:20:37.620
Who said you weren't?

02:20:37.680 --> 02:20:38.639
She mumbled.

02:20:38.700 --> 02:20:40.920
I'm a kill him.

02:20:40.979 --> 02:20:41.700
Sure, yes.

02:20:41.819 --> 02:20:43.920
Later, ish.

02:20:43.979 --> 02:20:45.840
Now it's too early.

02:20:45.899 --> 02:20:48.239
No stabbing before breakfast.

02:20:48.360 --> 02:20:51.239
Her voice rambled off into nonsense as

02:20:51.239 --> 02:20:52.319
she slid back down to sleep.

02:20:52.379 --> 02:20:56.040
Snowfall considered making her wake up

02:20:56.040 --> 02:20:58.319
which was a thing a queen could certainly

02:20:58.319 --> 02:21:01.139
do, except then the queen would have to

02:21:01.139 --> 02:21:03.299
explain that she'd been freaked out by a

02:21:03.299 --> 02:21:05.700
bad dream and just wanted company, which

02:21:05.700 --> 02:21:07.559
didn't seem very regal at all, really.

02:21:07.620 --> 02:21:10.799
It wasn't so much the content of the

02:21:10.799 --> 02:21:13.079
dream, although it had been unsettling.

02:21:13.139 --> 02:21:15.780
But she'd spent the whole day with that

02:21:15.780 --> 02:21:18.420
nervous, forlorn tribe of meek rainbow

02:21:18.420 --> 02:21:19.020
dragons.

02:21:19.079 --> 02:21:21.299
It wasn't all that weird that she might

02:21:21.299 --> 02:21:22.680
dream about their situation.

02:21:22.739 --> 02:21:25.860
The freaky part was that she'd really

02:21:25.860 --> 02:21:28.500
felt like she was someone else.

02:21:28.559 --> 02:21:31.620
In the dream, she'd completely been one

02:21:31.620 --> 02:21:34.200
of those homeless silk wings, completely

02:21:34.200 --> 02:21:36.059
inside another dragon.

02:21:36.120 --> 02:21:39.000
Not even a thought of the Ice Kingdom.

02:21:39.059 --> 02:21:42.180
No hint of snowfall left at all.

02:21:42.299 --> 02:21:45.659
She did not like that?

02:21:45.719 --> 02:21:46.260
No, sir.

02:21:46.319 --> 02:21:49.620
And now there were all these lingering

02:21:49.620 --> 02:21:51.059
feelings.

02:21:51.120 --> 02:21:54.299
The terror skittering along her scales

02:21:54.299 --> 02:21:54.959
was one thing.

02:21:55.020 --> 02:21:57.420
She was used to worrying about dangerous

02:21:57.420 --> 02:21:57.959
things out there.

02:21:58.020 --> 02:22:02.280
Not these specific dangerous things, but

02:22:02.280 --> 02:22:03.600
she could slide that all into one

02:22:03.600 --> 02:22:04.139
compartment.

02:22:04.200 --> 02:22:09.360
It was the boring, exhausting, sadness

02:22:09.360 --> 02:22:10.680
she didn't like.

02:22:10.739 --> 02:22:13.559
How could she be feeling this depressed

02:22:13.559 --> 02:22:16.620
about a continent and a few dragons she'd

02:22:16.620 --> 02:22:16.920
never seen?

02:22:16.979 --> 02:22:20.219
Dragons who didn't exist, mind you

02:22:20.219 --> 02:22:21.719
because her brain had conjured them out

02:22:21.719 --> 02:22:22.020
of nothing?

02:22:22.079 --> 02:22:24.780
Snap out of it.

02:22:24.840 --> 02:22:25.979
I'm fine.

02:22:26.040 --> 02:22:28.680
It's just these stupid, pathetic dragons

02:22:28.680 --> 02:22:29.520
messing with my head.

02:22:29.639 --> 02:22:33.299
She glared balefully up the beach at the

02:22:33.299 --> 02:22:35.459
slumbering forms around Jerboa's hut.

02:22:35.520 --> 02:22:38.639
Wait, what if that was literally true?

02:22:38.760 --> 02:22:41.700
Maybe this was some kind of sinister

02:22:41.700 --> 02:22:43.500
dragon magic from across the sea.

02:22:43.620 --> 02:22:46.799
Maybe they've given her a sappy nightmare

02:22:46.799 --> 02:22:48.299
to trick her into feeling sorry for

02:22:48.299 --> 02:22:48.540
them.

02:22:48.600 --> 02:22:52.680
Which was an unimpressive bit of magic, if

02:22:52.680 --> 02:22:53.579
that was all they could do.

02:22:53.639 --> 02:22:56.459
If she had the power to give dragons

02:22:56.459 --> 02:22:58.739
specific dreams, she'd make them all

02:22:58.739 --> 02:23:00.959
dream about how strong and amazing she

02:23:00.959 --> 02:23:01.319
was.

02:23:01.379 --> 02:23:04.739
So they'd be totally in awe of her and do

02:23:04.739 --> 02:23:06.840
everything she said, and never have any

02:23:06.840 --> 02:23:07.799
doubts about her ever.

02:23:07.860 --> 02:23:11.520
Snowfall leaned over and poked the links

02:23:11.520 --> 02:23:11.940
in the shoulder.

02:23:12.000 --> 02:23:14.219
Hey, she said.

02:23:14.280 --> 02:23:15.360
Links.

02:23:15.420 --> 02:23:16.680
Lynx.

02:23:16.739 --> 02:23:18.120
Lynx.

02:23:18.180 --> 02:23:18.899
Wake up.

02:23:18.959 --> 02:23:20.159
I have an important question.

02:23:20.219 --> 02:23:22.020
Did you have any weird dreams?

02:23:22.079 --> 02:23:28.139
Wing said in a muffled voice, trying to

02:23:28.139 --> 02:23:30.000
roll away from Snowfall's claw.

02:23:30.059 --> 02:23:31.500
Go away.

02:23:31.559 --> 02:23:34.680
You can't tell your queen to go away

02:23:34.680 --> 02:23:36.360
Snowfall pointed out.

02:23:36.420 --> 02:23:38.879
Your queen demands that you answer her

02:23:38.879 --> 02:23:39.239
question.

02:23:39.299 --> 02:23:40.979
It's a royal command.

02:23:41.040 --> 02:23:43.680
What?

02:23:43.799 --> 02:23:46.620
Things protested without opening her

02:23:46.620 --> 02:23:46.860
eyes.

02:23:46.920 --> 02:23:49.799
Did you have any weird dreams last

02:23:49.799 --> 02:23:50.100
night?

02:23:50.159 --> 02:23:52.020
Snowfall said impatiently.

02:23:52.079 --> 02:23:55.079
No, Lynx mumbled.

02:23:55.139 --> 02:23:56.700
Slept great.

02:23:56.760 --> 02:23:58.920
Would still be sleeping great if it were

02:23:58.920 --> 02:23:59.340
up to me?

02:23:59.399 --> 02:24:01.680
Unless I'm dreaming that my queen is

02:24:01.680 --> 02:24:04.200
waking me up at a horrifying hour to ask

02:24:04.200 --> 02:24:07.319
about my dreams, in which case, yes, this

02:24:07.319 --> 02:24:08.100
one is a bit weird.

02:24:08.159 --> 02:24:11.100
You are a useless minion.

02:24:11.159 --> 02:24:12.719
Snowfall observed.

02:24:12.780 --> 02:24:18.120
Friend, length enunciated clearly, before

02:24:18.120 --> 02:24:20.280
edging away and burying herself farther

02:24:20.280 --> 02:24:20.819
into the sand.

02:24:20.879 --> 02:24:23.700
Her voice came sleepily over the dune.

02:24:23.760 --> 02:24:26.280
The word you're looking for.

02:24:26.399 --> 02:24:28.079
His friend.

02:24:28.200 --> 02:24:30.239
Humph.

02:24:30.299 --> 02:24:32.760
Snow falls down to hole in the beach and

02:24:32.760 --> 02:24:34.620
shoved a passing crab into it.

02:24:34.680 --> 02:24:37.500
Come to think of it, Sheep slept well

02:24:37.500 --> 02:24:37.680
too.

02:24:37.739 --> 02:24:40.139
Really, truly slept.

02:24:40.200 --> 02:24:43.799
Despite the dream, she felt rested for

02:24:43.799 --> 02:24:45.120
the 1st time in forever.

02:24:45.180 --> 02:24:48.959
Okay, so shake it off.

02:24:49.020 --> 02:24:50.520
It was just a dream.

02:24:50.579 --> 02:24:53.399
Time to get these dragons to sanctuary

02:24:53.399 --> 02:24:55.319
and make them some other queen's problem

02:24:55.319 --> 02:24:56.219
so I can go home.

02:24:56.280 --> 02:24:59.399
Two of her guards jumped to their feet

02:24:59.399 --> 02:25:01.200
and followed her as she marched up the

02:25:01.200 --> 02:25:01.559
beach.

02:25:01.620 --> 02:25:04.079
Most of the Pentalan dragons were still

02:25:04.079 --> 02:25:05.819
asleep, but the one who'd been here

02:25:05.819 --> 02:25:08.579
before the rest, waiting with Treboa, was

02:25:08.579 --> 02:25:10.559
gathering wood into a pile, and a few

02:25:10.559 --> 02:25:11.340
others were helping her.

02:25:11.399 --> 02:25:14.520
Snowfall slowed down as she approached

02:25:14.520 --> 02:25:16.860
her eyes drifting over the strangers.

02:25:16.920 --> 02:25:19.620
She knew her brain had simply jumbled

02:25:19.620 --> 02:25:21.299
together a bunch of ideas from her

02:25:21.299 --> 02:25:25.440
subconscious, but She felt her heart do a

02:25:25.440 --> 02:25:27.180
startled little spasm in her chest.

02:25:27.239 --> 02:25:28.799
There.

02:25:28.860 --> 02:25:31.440
Asleep with her back pressed against one

02:25:31.440 --> 02:25:34.379
of the green dragons, peach orange scales

02:25:34.379 --> 02:25:37.620
sapphire blue spots, and the leaf wing

02:25:37.620 --> 02:25:38.040
beside her?

02:25:38.100 --> 02:25:40.860
Wasn't he the one who'd spoken to her in

02:25:40.860 --> 02:25:41.219
the sky?

02:25:41.280 --> 02:25:44.280
Except I made that up.

02:25:44.399 --> 02:25:47.579
In my head, in a random dream.

02:25:47.639 --> 02:25:50.940
She must have seen the 2 dragons flying

02:25:50.940 --> 02:25:53.280
together yesterday, even if she hadn't

02:25:53.280 --> 02:25:54.120
thought about it consciously.

02:25:54.180 --> 02:25:57.360
Her subconscious brain probably saw them

02:25:57.360 --> 02:25:59.459
being friendly, and stuffed that image

02:25:59.459 --> 02:26:02.579
into a box labeled, gross, intertribe

02:26:02.579 --> 02:26:03.719
flirting, not okay.

02:26:03.780 --> 02:26:04.979
Dream about this later.

02:26:05.040 --> 02:26:08.579
And if it did turn out that the Silk

02:26:08.579 --> 02:26:11.040
Wings name was Atala, that was also

02:26:11.040 --> 02:26:13.200
definitely a coincidence, with a

02:26:13.200 --> 02:26:15.479
reasonable explanation, and so she did

02:26:15.479 --> 02:26:16.620
not at all need to find that out.

02:26:16.680 --> 02:26:20.100
Snowfall sat down and watched the dragons

02:26:20.100 --> 02:26:21.120
building the fire instead.

02:26:21.180 --> 02:26:24.540
As far as she'd seen yesterday, neither

02:26:24.540 --> 02:26:26.459
silk wings nor leaf wings could breathe

02:26:26.459 --> 02:26:28.860
fire, so she expected the night wing or

02:26:28.860 --> 02:26:30.659
one of the sand wings to emerge and light

02:26:30.659 --> 02:26:31.079
it for them.

02:26:31.139 --> 02:26:33.899
But once the wood pile was high enough

02:26:33.899 --> 02:26:36.540
the 1st silk wings stepped forward and

02:26:36.540 --> 02:26:37.920
held out her front talons.

02:26:37.979 --> 02:26:41.340
Their peculiar dragon silk started

02:26:41.340 --> 02:26:42.719
spiraling out from her wrists.

02:26:42.840 --> 02:26:45.479
Except...

02:26:45.479 --> 02:26:48.420
Snowfall shot to her feet and paced

02:26:48.420 --> 02:26:49.020
closer.

02:26:49.079 --> 02:26:51.959
This dragon's silk was the color of

02:26:51.959 --> 02:26:52.260
gold.

02:26:52.319 --> 02:26:55.500
And where it touched the wood, licks of

02:26:55.500 --> 02:26:56.819
flame growled to life.

02:26:56.879 --> 02:26:58.860
Whoa.

02:26:58.920 --> 02:27:01.559
What is that?

02:27:01.680 --> 02:27:04.500
Snowfall demanded of the nearest silk

02:27:04.500 --> 02:27:04.739
wing.

02:27:04.799 --> 02:27:08.040
He was smaller than her, all pale gray

02:27:08.040 --> 02:27:09.360
and brown with hints of purple.

02:27:09.420 --> 02:27:13.620
He blinked, yawned, stretched, yawned

02:27:13.620 --> 02:27:16.559
again, and finally, about 300 years later

02:27:16.559 --> 02:27:17.520
answered her question.

02:27:17.579 --> 02:27:20.340
Oh, he said.

02:27:20.399 --> 02:27:21.299
Right.

02:27:21.360 --> 02:27:22.920
Balloon is a flame silk.

02:27:23.040 --> 02:27:26.100
He started to yawn again, and Snowfall

02:27:26.100 --> 02:27:27.719
was tempted to throw lobster at his

02:27:27.719 --> 02:27:27.899
face.

02:27:27.959 --> 02:27:29.879
That means nothing to me.

02:27:30.000 --> 02:27:31.260
She snapped.

02:27:31.319 --> 02:27:34.020
Use more words that convey actual

02:27:34.020 --> 02:27:34.799
information.

02:27:34.860 --> 02:27:35.700
If you please.

02:27:35.760 --> 02:27:40.020
Um, he said. swallowing his yawn

02:27:40.020 --> 02:27:40.620
nervously.

02:27:40.680 --> 02:27:44.639
Like her silk can be fire, if she wants

02:27:44.639 --> 02:27:45.059
it to be?

02:27:45.120 --> 02:27:47.760
Snowfall narrowed her eyes at him.

02:27:47.819 --> 02:27:49.500
Can you all do that?

02:27:49.559 --> 02:27:52.500
No, no, no, he said.

02:27:52.559 --> 02:27:55.020
He shook his head and flicked his tail

02:27:55.020 --> 02:27:55.620
toward Luna.

02:27:55.739 --> 02:27:57.780
Flame silks are very rare.

02:27:57.840 --> 02:28:00.719
That's why she ran away, you know, before

02:28:00.719 --> 02:28:03.479
any of us, because Queen Wasp keeps them

02:28:03.479 --> 02:28:06.479
all trapped, and she escaped, and okay

02:28:06.479 --> 02:28:09.840
that's enough words, Snowfall said, waving

02:28:09.840 --> 02:28:10.079
him away.

02:28:10.139 --> 02:28:13.079
He blinked a few times, and then resumed

02:28:13.079 --> 02:28:13.739
his stretching.

02:28:13.799 --> 02:28:16.559
The sound of clanking drew Snowball's

02:28:16.559 --> 02:28:17.520
attention back to the fire.

