vigorously, Lang said.

02:36:52.260 --> 02:36:55.379
So I wondered, you know, a whole lot of

02:36:55.379 --> 02:36:56.760
vigorous nothing before breakfast.

02:36:56.819 --> 02:37:00.360
Maybe I have had breakfast, Snowball

02:37:00.360 --> 02:37:00.840
observed.

02:37:00.899 --> 02:37:03.479
You would know, since you've been asleep

02:37:03.479 --> 02:37:03.899
half the morning.

02:37:03.959 --> 02:37:06.600
I do know that you have not.

02:37:06.719 --> 02:37:09.719
Link said, because I asked your guards

02:37:09.719 --> 02:37:11.219
and they said you've been out here for

02:37:11.219 --> 02:37:13.680
ages, doing battle with either your own

02:37:13.680 --> 02:37:15.659
claws or an invisible shark.

02:37:15.719 --> 02:37:19.139
Snowfall bristled and shot a dark look at

02:37:19.139 --> 02:37:21.000
her guards, who were lined up on the

02:37:21.000 --> 02:37:22.680
beach with concerned expressions.

02:37:22.739 --> 02:37:24.239
Is that what they said?

02:37:24.299 --> 02:37:26.940
No, Links admitted.

02:37:27.000 --> 02:37:28.799
They just said you haven't had breakfast

02:37:28.799 --> 02:37:29.159
yet.

02:37:29.280 --> 02:37:31.500
I interpreted the rest by watching you

02:37:31.500 --> 02:37:32.100
for a few minutes.

02:37:32.159 --> 02:37:36.959
I am having a swim, Snowfall said, lifting

02:37:36.959 --> 02:37:37.379
her chin.

02:37:37.440 --> 02:37:39.719
There is nothing unusual about that.

02:37:39.780 --> 02:37:43.559
I've seen you swim, Link said.

02:37:43.620 --> 02:37:45.659
You don't usually look quite so much like

02:37:45.659 --> 02:37:46.739
an agitated squid.

02:37:46.799 --> 02:37:49.500
I'm just going to start making a mental

02:37:49.500 --> 02:37:52.079
list, Snowfall informed her, so that when

02:37:52.079 --> 02:37:54.120
we get home, I can execute you for all

02:37:54.120 --> 02:37:55.079
your treason at once.

02:37:55.200 --> 02:37:59.340
Once would probably be enough, Lang said

02:37:59.340 --> 02:37:59.579
laughing.

02:37:59.700 --> 02:38:02.159
She flicked a spray of water at snowfall

02:38:02.159 --> 02:38:02.639
with her tail.

02:38:02.700 --> 02:38:04.860
Come on, Snowfall.

02:38:04.920 --> 02:38:06.360
Even queens need someone to talk to.

02:38:06.420 --> 02:38:07.559
Tell me what's wrong.

02:38:07.620 --> 02:38:11.459
Nothing is wrong, Snowfall protested.

02:38:11.520 --> 02:38:14.579
I'm just having a small problem with this

02:38:14.579 --> 02:38:16.680
ring, I can't get off, but it's not

02:38:16.680 --> 02:38:16.920
important.

02:38:16.979 --> 02:38:19.979
I mean, not compared to what are we going

02:38:19.979 --> 02:38:22.079
to do with all these homeless dragons and

02:38:22.079 --> 02:38:23.280
the bad things they're running away

02:38:23.280 --> 02:38:24.059
from?

02:38:24.120 --> 02:38:25.200
Like, seriously?

02:38:25.260 --> 02:38:28.079
Length tilted her head and studied

02:38:28.079 --> 02:38:30.479
snowfall for a moment, as though she were

02:38:30.479 --> 02:38:32.639
a palm tree that had suddenly sprouted in

02:38:32.639 --> 02:38:33.840
the middle of the ice palace.

02:38:33.899 --> 02:38:36.719
They'll be all right now that they're

02:38:36.719 --> 02:38:38.219
here, she said finally.

02:38:38.280 --> 02:38:40.260
Let me see that ring.

02:38:40.319 --> 02:38:43.979
Snowfall grudgingly held out her talons

02:38:43.979 --> 02:38:45.840
and links gripped the ring between her

02:38:45.840 --> 02:38:46.260
claws.

02:38:46.319 --> 02:38:49.500
She pulled and wiggled it, and tried

02:38:49.500 --> 02:38:51.840
sliding her claws under it, and yanked

02:38:51.840 --> 02:38:54.420
some more, until Snowfall finally got fed

02:38:54.420 --> 02:38:55.680
up and snatched her arm back.

02:38:55.739 --> 02:39:00.479
Well, you're no use, Snowfall hissed.

02:39:00.540 --> 02:39:02.159
No surprise there.

02:39:02.280 --> 02:39:04.319
She dunked her claws in the water again.

02:39:04.379 --> 02:39:07.739
But now Links looked worried, which meant

02:39:07.739 --> 02:39:10.200
she was about to get very annoying.

02:39:10.260 --> 02:39:13.379
It's really not moving at all, she said.

02:39:13.500 --> 02:39:15.000
Snowfall.

02:39:15.059 --> 02:39:17.219
Was that ring from the forbidden

02:39:17.219 --> 02:39:17.819
treasury?

02:39:17.879 --> 02:39:19.799
Is it animus touched?

02:39:19.860 --> 02:39:22.440
Snowfall frowned and took a piece of

02:39:22.440 --> 02:39:23.399
seaweed off her tail.

02:39:23.459 --> 02:39:25.620
Yes, but it doesn't work.

02:39:25.680 --> 02:39:27.420
Are you sure?

02:39:27.479 --> 02:39:29.040
Lengx asked.

02:39:29.100 --> 02:39:30.600
What is it supposed to do?

02:39:30.659 --> 02:39:34.680
It's, Supposed to make your eyesight

02:39:34.680 --> 02:39:36.479
sharper, Snowfall said.

02:39:36.540 --> 02:39:38.700
But it didn't make any difference at all

02:39:38.700 --> 02:39:40.200
which is why I want it off.

02:39:40.260 --> 02:39:42.540
Were there any notes?

02:39:42.600 --> 02:39:46.260
Links pressed. about how to use it, or

02:39:46.260 --> 02:39:48.840
what it did for other queens, or who made

02:39:48.840 --> 02:39:49.020
it?

02:39:49.079 --> 02:39:51.899
No, Snowfall said.

02:39:51.959 --> 02:39:54.840
Nobody wrote an encyclopedia about it.

02:39:54.959 --> 02:39:56.520
It's not that complicated.

02:39:56.579 --> 02:39:58.500
Put on the ring, get better vision.

02:39:58.620 --> 02:40:02.040
But that isn't what happened, Link said.

02:40:02.159 --> 02:40:05.340
Wait, were there any notes?

02:40:05.459 --> 02:40:07.920
Her expression shifted to the most

02:40:07.920 --> 02:40:10.739
absolutely irritating, wide-eyed alarm.

02:40:10.860 --> 02:40:13.440
Did you just put it on without knowing

02:40:13.440 --> 02:40:14.100
anything about it?

02:40:14.159 --> 02:40:16.020
Why not?

02:40:16.079 --> 02:40:17.459
Snowfall snapped.

02:40:17.520 --> 02:40:18.899
Better Vision would be helpful.

02:40:18.959 --> 02:40:21.479
But what if there's a catch?

02:40:21.600 --> 02:40:22.739
Langs cried.

02:40:22.799 --> 02:40:25.200
What if there's a secret downside to the

02:40:25.200 --> 02:40:25.500
spell?

02:40:25.559 --> 02:40:27.959
What are the animus dragon who made it

02:40:27.959 --> 02:40:29.159
added a curse to the magic?

02:40:29.219 --> 02:40:32.399
Or what if it does something entirely

02:40:32.399 --> 02:40:33.899
different than I thought it did?

02:40:33.959 --> 02:40:36.420
Snowfall shoved that thought away.

02:40:36.479 --> 02:40:40.020
Then we wouldn't have kept it, she

02:40:40.020 --> 02:40:41.040
snarled at length.

02:40:41.100 --> 02:40:43.680
It wouldn't still be in our treasury if

02:40:43.680 --> 02:40:44.280
it was evil.

02:40:44.340 --> 02:40:46.860
Some cursed queen before us would have

02:40:46.860 --> 02:40:47.340
destroyed it.

02:40:47.399 --> 02:40:50.399
Unless it was enchanted so it could never

02:40:50.399 --> 02:40:51.059
be destroyed.

02:40:51.180 --> 02:40:54.000
Length yelped, sounding uncomfortably

02:40:54.000 --> 02:40:55.799
like snowfall's inner monologue.

02:40:55.860 --> 02:40:58.440
Maybe it magically shows up in the

02:40:58.440 --> 02:41:00.719
forbidden treasury once every 100 years

02:41:00.719 --> 02:41:03.180
to ensnare some new hapless queen.

02:41:03.239 --> 02:41:07.200
I'm not hapless, Snowfall shouted.

02:41:07.260 --> 02:41:09.180
Who's being paranoid now?

02:41:09.239 --> 02:41:12.120
It was a gift for ice wing queens.

02:41:12.180 --> 02:41:14.459
So it's supposed to make us stronger and

02:41:14.459 --> 02:41:17.340
safer, like the wall, and the ice cliff.

02:41:17.399 --> 02:41:20.340
Personally, I don't think it makes our

02:41:20.340 --> 02:41:22.440
tribe stronger for us all to be

02:41:22.440 --> 02:41:23.879
constantly pitted against each other.

02:41:23.940 --> 02:41:25.260
Langs cried.

02:41:25.319 --> 02:41:27.719
And I don't think cutting us off from the

02:41:27.719 --> 02:41:29.520
other tribes makes us safer either.

02:41:29.579 --> 02:41:31.139
Wow.

02:41:31.200 --> 02:41:34.680
Snowfall said with a hiss. questioning

02:41:34.680 --> 02:41:36.659
the most fundamental gifts that hold our

02:41:36.659 --> 02:41:37.260
tribe together?

02:41:37.319 --> 02:41:39.719
You really don't belong in the 1st

02:41:39.719 --> 02:41:40.139
circle.

02:41:40.200 --> 02:41:42.000
What kind of ice wing are you?

02:41:42.059 --> 02:41:44.879
The kind who actually thinks for herself

02:41:44.879 --> 02:41:48.180
sometimes, Link said, flinging up her

02:41:48.180 --> 02:41:49.979
wings and accidentally splashing a small

02:41:49.979 --> 02:41:51.600
fish into snowfall's face.

02:41:51.719 --> 02:41:53.879
The kind who wants you to be a better

02:41:53.879 --> 02:41:55.379
queen than the ones we've had before

02:41:55.379 --> 02:41:58.079
because I know you, and I know you can

02:41:58.079 --> 02:41:58.379
be.

02:41:58.440 --> 02:42:01.319
But feel free to keep living your life by

02:42:01.319 --> 02:42:03.540
the rules of that oppressive wall, if

02:42:03.540 --> 02:42:05.700
that's all you want, and feel free to

02:42:05.700 --> 02:42:07.260
move me down to the bottom of the list

02:42:07.260 --> 02:42:07.979
when we get home.

02:42:08.040 --> 02:42:11.100
She took a step toward the beach, then

02:42:11.100 --> 02:42:12.420
turned back for one more shot.

02:42:12.479 --> 02:42:16.260
If that mysterious magic ring even lets

02:42:16.260 --> 02:42:16.739
you get home.

02:42:16.799 --> 02:42:19.559
After everything animus magic has done to

02:42:19.559 --> 02:42:22.139
us, I can't believe you'd throw yourself

02:42:22.139 --> 02:42:23.100
into its talent again.

02:42:23.219 --> 02:42:26.280
She splashed away furiously.

02:42:26.340 --> 02:42:28.860
Snowfall threw herself under the water

02:42:28.860 --> 02:42:32.159
and screamed out her rage in a flurry of

02:42:32.159 --> 02:42:32.520
bubbles.

02:42:32.639 --> 02:42:35.459
This was why she didn't tell anyone her

02:42:35.459 --> 02:42:35.940
problems.

02:42:36.059 --> 02:42:38.280
Because they would definitely make them

02:42:38.280 --> 02:42:38.579
worse.

02:42:38.639 --> 02:42:41.459
Lynx was not right.

02:42:41.579 --> 02:42:44.399
It was just a stupid broken ring.

02:42:44.459 --> 02:42:47.100
Snowfall had definitely not

02:42:47.100 --> 02:42:49.680
misinterpreted what a gift of vision

02:42:49.680 --> 02:42:51.959
might mean, and this had nothing to do

02:42:51.959 --> 02:42:53.159
with her dream last night.

02:42:53.219 --> 02:42:54.540
No.

02:42:54.600 --> 02:42:56.940
She would not stand for it.

02:42:57.000 --> 02:42:59.459
When she surfaced again.

02:42:59.520 --> 02:43:02.040
Lynx was with the strangers by the fire

02:43:02.040 --> 02:43:04.559
where some of the littlest dragonettes

02:43:04.559 --> 02:43:07.200
were building a kind of tree like termite

02:43:07.200 --> 02:43:08.340
mound out of the sand.

02:43:08.399 --> 02:43:11.579
Snowfall squinted at them, as 2 young

02:43:11.579 --> 02:43:13.200
leaf wings pounced on the shape and

02:43:13.200 --> 02:43:13.979
stomped it flat.

02:43:14.040 --> 02:43:17.819
The opal ring winked gold blue lavender

02:43:17.819 --> 02:43:18.600
in the morning light.

02:43:18.659 --> 02:43:22.739
I'm not afraid of you, Snowfall thought

02:43:22.739 --> 02:43:23.340
fiercely.

02:43:23.399 --> 02:43:26.399
I am getting rid of you today, even if I

02:43:26.399 --> 02:43:28.260
have to cut off my own claw to do it.

02:43:28.319 --> 02:43:31.920
She would get this ring off and throw it

02:43:31.920 --> 02:43:34.079
into the ocean, and then she would make

02:43:34.079 --> 02:43:35.879
sure the strange dragons went to

02:43:35.879 --> 02:43:38.700
sanctuary, and then she would go home, and

02:43:38.700 --> 02:43:40.680
everything would go back to the normal

02:43:40.680 --> 02:43:43.020
everyday anxiety festival her life was

02:43:43.020 --> 02:43:43.440
supposed to be.

02:43:43.500 --> 02:43:46.680
Snowball splashed her way back onto the

02:43:46.680 --> 02:43:48.959
beach, waving regally at her guards.

02:43:49.020 --> 02:43:50.940
Nothing to see here.

02:43:51.000 --> 02:43:54.180
No queens losing their royal minds.

02:43:54.360 --> 02:43:55.319
Certainly not.

02:43:55.379 --> 02:43:58.739
She waited until she was sure Lynx wasn't

02:43:58.739 --> 02:44:00.299
watching her, and then she tried

02:44:00.299 --> 02:44:02.639
smothering her claws and palm oil from

02:44:02.639 --> 02:44:04.739
one of the jars outside Jerboa's hut.

02:44:04.799 --> 02:44:06.540
That didn't work either.

02:44:06.600 --> 02:44:09.239
It only left snowfall's talons feeling

02:44:09.239 --> 02:44:09.899
greasy.

02:44:09.959 --> 02:44:12.000
Oh, please.

02:44:12.120 --> 02:44:14.879
Treboa said acidly from the doorway.

02:44:14.940 --> 02:44:16.559
Help yourself.

02:44:16.620 --> 02:44:19.260
My stuff is everybody's stuff, evidently.

02:44:19.379 --> 02:44:23.100
This is your fault, Snowfall said

02:44:23.100 --> 02:44:25.319
brandishing the now extremely shiny

02:44:25.319 --> 02:44:25.680
ring.

02:44:25.799 --> 02:44:28.860
That you're wearing too much hideous

02:44:28.860 --> 02:44:30.360
jewelry, Turboa said.

02:44:30.420 --> 02:44:31.500
Make sense.

02:44:31.559 --> 02:44:33.780
I do have that effect on dragons.

02:44:33.840 --> 02:44:36.959
I wouldn't need this if your stupid magic

02:44:36.959 --> 02:44:39.299
worked, Snowfall said with a flick of her

02:44:39.299 --> 02:44:39.540
wings.

02:44:39.600 --> 02:44:41.399
Have you checked today?

02:44:41.459 --> 02:44:42.600
Is it working now?

02:44:42.659 --> 02:44:45.600
The frown lines in Jerboa's face

02:44:45.600 --> 02:44:46.139
deepened.

02:44:46.260 --> 02:44:47.280
No.

02:44:47.399 --> 02:44:49.139
It's not working for anyone.

02:44:49.200 --> 02:44:51.899
She glanced back into the hut.

02:44:51.959 --> 02:44:53.459
Snowfall wasn't sure why.

02:44:53.520 --> 02:44:56.040
Really definitely?

02:44:56.219 --> 02:44:57.299
Snowfall asked.

02:44:57.360 --> 02:44:59.760
She held out her front talons.

02:44:59.819 --> 02:45:01.020
Let's test it.

02:45:01.079 --> 02:45:03.600
Tell this ring to slide off my claw.

02:45:03.659 --> 02:45:06.420
Turboa's side and cast another glance

02:45:06.420 --> 02:45:06.840
around.

02:45:06.959 --> 02:45:09.120
But no other dragons were close enough to

02:45:09.120 --> 02:45:09.840
pay attention to them.

02:45:09.899 --> 02:45:13.200
The sand wing reached out and tapped the

02:45:13.200 --> 02:45:13.739
ring twice.

02:45:13.799 --> 02:45:16.860
Come off the queen's claw this instant

02:45:16.860 --> 02:45:17.639
she said.

02:45:17.760 --> 02:45:19.860
The ring didn't move.

02:45:19.920 --> 02:45:23.579
Snowfall tried pulling on it again, but

02:45:23.579 --> 02:45:24.959
it was just as stuck as before.

02:45:25.020 --> 02:45:27.479
She growled softly.

02:45:27.540 --> 02:45:29.399
Is it?

02:45:29.399 --> 02:45:30.659
Anna's touch?

02:45:30.780 --> 02:45:34.139
Treboa asked, finally sounding curious.

02:45:34.200 --> 02:45:37.319
I thought so, Snowfall said, but it seems

02:45:37.319 --> 02:45:38.399
to be flipping broken.

02:45:38.459 --> 02:45:40.739
Animas touched by who?

02:45:40.799 --> 02:45:42.479
Jaboa frowned again.

02:45:42.540 --> 02:45:43.500
When?

02:45:43.559 --> 02:45:47.879
Like 1000s of years ago, Snowfall said

02:45:47.879 --> 02:45:48.420
with a sigh.

02:45:48.540 --> 02:45:51.719
By the worst ice wing animus in history

02:45:51.719 --> 02:45:54.239
I'm guessing, some kind of worm brained

02:45:54.239 --> 02:45:55.260
fan snorter.

02:45:55.319 --> 02:45:58.079
Why would anyone enchant a ring to stay

02:45:58.079 --> 02:45:59.280
on someone's claw?

02:45:59.340 --> 02:46:01.559
What kind of stupid waste of magic is

02:46:01.559 --> 02:46:01.739
that?

02:46:01.799 --> 02:46:05.579
Treboa scratched her jaw thoughtfully, but

02:46:05.579 --> 02:46:06.959
her tense expression had relaxed.

02:46:07.079 --> 02:46:08.760
Maybe.

02:46:08.819 --> 02:46:10.920
It's enchanted to frustrate easily

02:46:10.920 --> 02:46:12.719
annoyed queens into learning some

02:46:12.719 --> 02:46:13.079
patience.

02:46:13.139 --> 02:46:15.659
Boo, hiss.

02:46:15.719 --> 02:46:17.219
Snowfall shouted.

02:46:17.280 --> 02:46:20.219
Several of the silk wings jumped and

02:46:20.219 --> 02:46:21.420
turned to see what the noise was.

02:46:21.479 --> 02:46:23.459
She lowered her voice again.

02:46:23.520 --> 02:46:26.520
I don't need an ancient accessory to

02:46:26.520 --> 02:46:27.299
teach me anything.

02:46:27.360 --> 02:46:28.979
I'm very patient.

02:46:29.100 --> 02:46:31.920
I've been queen for months without

02:46:31.920 --> 02:46:33.719
stabbing anybody in the face with an

02:46:33.719 --> 02:46:36.600
icicle, despite lots of dragons highly

02:46:36.600 --> 02:46:37.260
deserving it.

02:46:37.319 --> 02:46:42.420
Well, Treboa said, if my magic comes back

02:46:42.420 --> 02:46:45.000
I'll make removing your ring my top

02:46:45.000 --> 02:46:45.840
priority.

02:46:45.899 --> 02:46:46.799
How about that?

02:46:46.860 --> 02:46:49.920
No need, Snowfall said.

02:46:49.979 --> 02:46:51.600
I have another plan.

02:46:51.659 --> 02:46:54.420
She narrowed her eyes at your boa and

02:46:54.420 --> 02:46:56.819
added in a whisper, But if it does come

02:46:56.819 --> 02:46:58.200
back, tell me right away.

02:46:58.319 --> 02:47:01.680
Turbo's expression was quite far from

02:47:01.680 --> 02:47:04.020
reassuring, but she ducked into her hut

02:47:04.020 --> 02:47:05.159
without saying anything else.

02:47:05.219 --> 02:47:07.860
Snowfall caught a glimpse of the night

02:47:07.860 --> 02:47:10.139
wing inside, still fast asleep.

02:47:10.200 --> 02:47:12.479
She moved away as quickly as she could.

02:47:12.540 --> 02:47:15.059
The last thing she needed was that dragon

02:47:15.059 --> 02:47:16.500
poking around inside her head.

02:47:16.620 --> 02:47:19.379
It was bad enough to have links making

02:47:19.379 --> 02:47:20.879
worried eyes at her all the time.

02:47:20.940 --> 02:47:23.159
She didn't need any night wings thinking

02:47:23.159 --> 02:47:26.280
she was weak or cursed by weird jewelry.

02:47:26.340 --> 02:47:28.379
Over by the fire.

02:47:28.440 --> 02:47:31.079
Luna was finally alone more or less

02:47:31.079 --> 02:47:33.600
surrounded by a mound of discarded wrist

02:47:33.600 --> 02:47:34.020
cuffs.

02:47:34.079 --> 02:47:36.659
Most of the other silk wings had gone off

02:47:36.659 --> 02:47:39.000
to gather coconuts or lie quietly on the

02:47:39.000 --> 02:47:41.579
warm sand, and lynx was up in the sky

02:47:41.579 --> 02:47:43.319
flying with one of the leaf wings.

02:47:43.379 --> 02:47:46.559
Snowfall sidled up to Luna.

02:47:46.620 --> 02:47:49.139
The Silkwing dropped the cuff she'd been

02:47:49.139 --> 02:47:51.299
holding, and eyed Snowfall with alarm.

02:47:51.360 --> 02:47:54.780
Hey, Snowfall said gruffly.

02:47:54.840 --> 02:47:56.639
That fire thread thing?

02:47:56.700 --> 02:47:58.139
Can you try that on my ring?

02:47:58.200 --> 02:48:00.299
It's stuck, and it's annoying me.

02:48:00.360 --> 02:48:02.639
You're that queen of the ice wings

02:48:02.639 --> 02:48:02.819
right?

02:48:02.879 --> 02:48:04.920
Luna said, lifting her chin.

02:48:05.040 --> 02:48:07.559
The one who kicked my tribe out of your

02:48:07.559 --> 02:48:08.280
kingdom yesterday?

02:48:08.340 --> 02:48:10.319
Lucky for you?

02:48:10.379 --> 02:48:13.680
Snowfall pointed out, or they wouldn't be

02:48:13.680 --> 02:48:13.860
here.

02:48:13.920 --> 02:48:16.200
Having this touching reunion with you.

02:48:16.260 --> 02:48:18.899
Luna rolled her eyes and held out her

02:48:18.899 --> 02:48:19.440
claws.

02:48:19.500 --> 02:48:20.459
Show me.

02:48:20.520 --> 02:48:23.879
Snowfall gingerly offered the talon with

02:48:23.879 --> 02:48:24.360
a ring on it.

02:48:24.420 --> 02:48:27.239
Luna picked up a filament of fire from

02:48:27.239 --> 02:48:29.399
the sand beside her and bent over their

02:48:29.399 --> 02:48:30.600
twined claws.

02:48:30.659 --> 02:48:33.600
The burning filament brushed the silver

02:48:33.600 --> 02:48:36.899
curve of the ring once, twice, 3 times

02:48:36.899 --> 02:48:38.879
without even leaving a trace on the

02:48:38.879 --> 02:48:39.180
metal.

02:48:39.239 --> 02:48:41.639
Luna frowned and tried again.

02:48:41.700 --> 02:48:45.059
The heat was enormously uncomfortable

02:48:45.059 --> 02:48:47.040
that close to snowfalls scales.

02:48:47.100 --> 02:48:49.680
And she didn't like the feel of this silk

02:48:49.680 --> 02:48:50.879
wing gripping her talons either.

02:48:50.940 --> 02:48:53.879
But she held still, glaring into the

02:48:53.879 --> 02:48:56.159
opal's shimmering depths, until Luna

02:48:56.159 --> 02:48:58.440
finally said, That's so weird.

02:48:58.500 --> 02:49:01.680
Sorry, your majesty, it's not working.

02:49:01.739 --> 02:49:04.920
Snowfall lifted the opal to eye level and

02:49:04.920 --> 02:49:05.639
hissed at it.

02:49:05.700 --> 02:49:07.979
How could fire not work?

02:49:08.040 --> 02:49:11.340
Don't tell links, she said to Luna.

02:49:11.399 --> 02:49:15.059
Uh, sure, Luna agreed.

02:49:15.120 --> 02:49:16.260
You're welcome.

02:49:16.379 --> 02:49:18.059
For what?

02:49:18.120 --> 02:49:20.639
Snowfall snapped and stomped away.

02:49:20.700 --> 02:49:23.760
She found a large boulder in a shaded

02:49:23.760 --> 02:49:25.799
spot near the tree line, and perched on

02:49:25.799 --> 02:49:26.819
it to brood for a while.

02:49:26.940 --> 02:49:29.700
Her guards fanned out in a discreet

02:49:29.700 --> 02:49:31.680
circle around her, and one of them

02:49:31.680 --> 02:49:33.420
brought her a fish to eat, and she even

02:49:33.420 --> 02:49:34.500
remembered to thank him for it.

02:49:34.559 --> 02:49:37.920
So, at least I did one excellently

02:49:37.920 --> 02:49:39.059
queenly ding today.

02:49:39.120 --> 02:49:42.180
The other animus touched things came off

02:49:42.180 --> 02:49:42.659
easily.

02:49:42.719 --> 02:49:43.799
No problem.

02:49:43.860 --> 02:49:46.979
The stealth wristbands, and the tiara of

02:49:46.979 --> 02:49:48.479
strength, off and back on.

02:49:48.540 --> 02:49:50.399
Nothing sinister about them at all.

02:49:50.520 --> 02:49:53.879
Snowfall had always assumed that if

02:49:53.879 --> 02:49:55.979
something was made by an ice wing animus

02:49:55.979 --> 02:49:57.000
it would be something great.

02:49:57.059 --> 02:50:00.899
Something good and helpful and smart and

02:50:00.899 --> 02:50:01.319
clever.

02:50:01.440 --> 02:50:03.299
Like an ice wing.

02:50:03.360 --> 02:50:05.760
An ice wing animus would make a secret

02:50:05.760 --> 02:50:09.059
evil spell like a night wing would, surely

02:50:09.059 --> 02:50:10.200
right?

02:50:10.260 --> 02:50:13.200
The ring was not a big deal, she told

02:50:13.200 --> 02:50:13.559
herself.

02:50:13.680 --> 02:50:16.139
It was Linx's fault that she was even

02:50:16.139 --> 02:50:17.100
worrying about it at all.

02:50:17.219 --> 02:50:18.780
But really?

02:50:18.840 --> 02:50:21.360
If she thought about it, she felt fine.

02:50:21.420 --> 02:50:23.159
Better than usual in fact.

02:50:23.280 --> 02:50:25.739
Probably because she hadn't had to see

02:50:25.739 --> 02:50:28.200
Aunt Tundra's smug face for a whole day.

02:50:28.260 --> 02:50:32.459
Moreover, if there was a secret spell on

02:50:32.459 --> 02:50:34.440
the ring, it hadn't given her a terrible

02:50:34.440 --> 02:50:37.139
illness yet, or turned her into a

02:50:37.139 --> 02:50:37.920
different dragon.

02:50:37.979 --> 02:50:39.180
Ha!

02:50:39.239 --> 02:50:40.319
It could try.

02:50:40.379 --> 02:50:43.260
She was always snowfall and always would

02:50:43.260 --> 02:50:43.559
be.

02:50:43.620 --> 02:50:46.020
It hadn't tricked her into letting

02:50:46.020 --> 02:50:47.819
strange invader dragons into her

02:50:47.819 --> 02:50:48.239
kingdom.

02:50:48.299 --> 02:50:50.579
She was the same as always.

02:50:50.639 --> 02:50:53.040
Everything was normal.

02:50:53.100 --> 02:50:56.700
Even the lingering sadness from the dream

02:50:56.700 --> 02:50:58.260
lifted a little as the day went on.

02:50:58.319 --> 02:51:01.620
She could see Atala from her spot, and

02:51:01.620 --> 02:51:03.059
the Silk Queen didn't look totally

02:51:03.059 --> 02:51:04.920
miserable, so that helped.

02:51:04.979 --> 02:51:08.459
Atala got her wrist cuff burned off, ate

02:51:08.459 --> 02:51:10.799
a talon full of dates, laughed at a leaf

02:51:10.799 --> 02:51:12.420
wing when he tried to catch a crab, and

02:51:12.420 --> 02:51:14.520
it tweaked his nose, and took several

02:51:14.520 --> 02:51:14.940
naps.

02:51:15.000 --> 02:51:18.059
The silk wing also spent a while staring

02:51:18.059 --> 02:51:18.659
out of the ocean.

02:51:18.719 --> 02:51:22.020
Thinking about the family she left behind

02:51:22.020 --> 02:51:23.399
snowfall guest.

02:51:23.459 --> 02:51:24.780
I hope they're safe.

02:51:24.840 --> 02:51:26.819
No, I don't.

02:51:26.940 --> 02:51:28.079
I don't care at all.

02:51:28.139 --> 02:51:30.059
She shook herself vigorously.

02:51:30.120 --> 02:51:31.500
I don't know them.

02:51:31.559 --> 02:51:32.760
Why would I care?

02:51:32.819 --> 02:51:34.559
Stupid dream.

02:51:34.620 --> 02:51:36.360
Or vision or whatever.

02:51:36.420 --> 02:51:40.440
Shortly before sunset, Snowfall heard the

02:51:40.440 --> 02:51:42.479
cracks and snaps of talent steps in the

02:51:42.479 --> 02:51:43.139
trees behind her.

02:51:43.200 --> 02:51:46.020
She turned and spotted the frowning weaf

02:51:46.020 --> 02:51:48.239
wing pacing between the palms, throwing

02:51:48.239 --> 02:51:49.680
fallen coconuts into a sack.

02:51:49.739 --> 02:51:52.260
Another green dragon followed her.

02:51:52.379 --> 02:51:54.479
This one with pinkish streaks on her

02:51:54.479 --> 02:51:55.200
wings and horns.

02:51:55.260 --> 02:51:57.959
We jazz.

02:51:58.079 --> 02:52:01.079
Just got here, said the pink tinted leaf

02:52:01.079 --> 02:52:02.040
wing languidly.

02:52:02.100 --> 02:52:05.399
Why are you acting like such a frustrated

02:52:05.399 --> 02:52:06.420
panther already?

02:52:06.479 --> 02:52:08.399
Wasn't this the goal?

02:52:08.520 --> 02:52:12.239
But we can't stay, Cobra Lily, cried the

02:52:12.239 --> 02:52:12.540
other one.

02:52:12.600 --> 02:52:15.479
We can't just find a nice, safe spot to

02:52:15.479 --> 02:52:16.799
settle down and get comfortable.

02:52:16.860 --> 02:52:18.000
That's not the plan.

02:52:18.059 --> 02:52:20.760
I won't give up on our whole continent

02:52:20.760 --> 02:52:21.420
and everyone there.

02:52:21.540 --> 02:52:23.879
Cobra Lily shrugged.

02:52:23.940 --> 02:52:26.159
An elegant lift and fall of her wings.

02:52:26.219 --> 02:52:29.940
You can be that upset about losing nettle

02:52:29.940 --> 02:52:32.520
and belladonna, and if you use silly silk

02:52:32.520 --> 02:52:33.719
wings, she said.

02:52:33.780 --> 02:52:36.059
Seems like an upside to me.

02:52:36.120 --> 02:52:38.579
No more nettle annoying us.

02:52:38.639 --> 02:52:41.219
No more belladonna telling you what to

02:52:41.219 --> 02:52:41.340
do.

02:52:41.459 --> 02:52:44.340
The scowly one fixed her with a

02:52:44.340 --> 02:52:45.959
particularly ferocious scowl.

02:52:46.020 --> 02:52:49.260
Queen Sequoia is back there, plus half

02:52:49.260 --> 02:52:51.659
the dragons we grew up with, a monster

02:52:51.659 --> 02:52:52.920
has stolen our home.

02:52:52.979 --> 02:52:56.340
And by the way, those silly silk wings

02:52:56.340 --> 02:52:57.780
risked a lot to help us.

02:52:57.840 --> 02:53:02.399
Don't get excited, Cobra Lily said.

02:53:02.459 --> 02:53:06.120
I'm just saying, this place is already

02:53:06.120 --> 02:53:09.120
significantly nicer than a jungle full of

02:53:09.120 --> 02:53:12.959
carnivorous plants, or a land full of

02:53:12.959 --> 02:53:15.360
mind controlled bug dragons.

02:53:15.420 --> 02:53:17.639
Maybe we could stay here.

02:53:17.700 --> 02:53:19.440
Make a new home.

02:53:19.500 --> 02:53:23.459
One queen over both the silk wings and

02:53:23.459 --> 02:53:24.600
the leaf wings.

02:53:24.659 --> 02:53:28.079
I bet most of these dragons wouldn't mind

02:53:28.079 --> 02:53:30.899
following a queen's sundew.

02:53:31.020 --> 02:53:34.440
No sundew growled.

02:53:34.500 --> 02:53:36.000
Stop saying that.

02:53:36.059 --> 02:53:37.979
Hazel is our queen.

02:53:38.040 --> 02:53:40.379
She half turned and finally spotted

02:53:40.379 --> 02:53:42.059
snowfall lying on her boulder.

02:53:42.120 --> 02:53:45.180
Her tail lashed for a moment, and then

02:53:45.180 --> 02:53:47.100
she spread her wings and lifted off into

02:53:47.100 --> 02:53:47.399
the sky.

02:53:47.459 --> 02:53:51.479
That's interesting, Snowfall thought.

02:53:51.540 --> 02:53:53.040
Sundew.

02:53:53.159 --> 02:53:55.680
She is a threat to Hazel's rule.

02:53:55.739 --> 02:53:58.620
Even if she doesn't mean to be, other

02:53:58.620 --> 02:53:59.819
dragons want her to be.

02:53:59.940 --> 02:54:02.639
Just like the dragons who probably still

02:54:02.639 --> 02:54:04.680
want Crystal to be queen instead of me.

02:54:04.799 --> 02:54:06.239
How many of them are there?

02:54:06.299 --> 02:54:07.860
Are they hiding her?

02:54:07.920 --> 02:54:09.780
Are they planning something?

02:54:09.840 --> 02:54:11.520
Gathering an army?

02:54:11.579 --> 02:54:13.680
Conspiring with night wings?

02:54:13.739 --> 02:54:15.899
Where is she?

02:54:15.959 --> 02:54:19.559
Snowfall brooded about this until one of

02:54:19.559 --> 02:54:21.719
her guards came over to inform her that

02:54:21.719 --> 02:54:23.579
the strange tribes had decided to stay

02:54:23.579 --> 02:54:25.680
one more night before setting out for

02:54:25.680 --> 02:54:26.700
sanctuary in the morning.

02:54:26.760 --> 02:54:29.520
Snowfall could tell that Hazel would have

02:54:29.520 --> 02:54:30.299
liked to stay longer.

02:54:30.360 --> 02:54:33.059
The leaf winged queen kept leaning

02:54:33.059 --> 02:54:35.579
wistfully on the palm trees, and gazing

02:54:35.579 --> 02:54:36.719
up at their swaying leaves.

02:54:36.780 --> 02:54:39.840
But moon was bustling around, reassuring

02:54:39.840 --> 02:54:41.459
everyone that sanctuary would be even

02:54:41.459 --> 02:54:44.340
better, with more trees and lots of space

02:54:44.340 --> 02:54:45.120
and food for them.

02:54:45.180 --> 02:54:47.940
Highly suspicious.

02:54:48.000 --> 02:54:51.120
Possibly some kind of nefarious plan at

02:54:51.120 --> 02:54:52.920
work if a night wing was all excited

02:54:52.920 --> 02:54:53.459
about it.

02:54:53.520 --> 02:54:57.360
As the sun set, Snowfall dug her sleeping

02:54:57.360 --> 02:54:59.639
hole with extra vigor, throwing all the

02:54:59.639 --> 02:55:01.620
excess sand in Lynx's direction.

02:55:01.680 --> 02:55:03.899
She was not going to worry about this

02:55:03.899 --> 02:55:04.799
ridiculous ring.

02:55:04.860 --> 02:55:09.059
She refused to have another vision of

02:55:09.059 --> 02:55:10.680
mystery dragons she didn't know.

02:55:10.799 --> 02:55:14.399
She was the queen, and she would simply

02:55:14.399 --> 02:55:16.500
order her brain to have an ordinary night

02:55:16.500 --> 02:55:18.899
with perfectly ordinary dreams.

02:55:19.020 --> 02:55:20.340
Yes.

02:55:20.399 --> 02:55:24.840
She curled up, closed her eyes, and

02:55:24.840 --> 02:55:26.940
dropped almost instantly into another

02:55:26.940 --> 02:55:28.139
dragon's scales.

02:55:28.200 --> 02:55:32.579
Chapter 8.

02:55:32.639 --> 02:55:36.299
She is alone in the kitchen, rolling

02:55:36.299 --> 02:55:38.459
antelope meatballs, trying to keep her

02:55:38.459 --> 02:55:39.120
claws busy.

02:55:39.180 --> 02:55:42.479
She's trying not to think about cinnabar

02:55:42.479 --> 02:55:44.700
or how she should be with the rest of the

02:55:44.700 --> 02:55:46.979
chrysalis, finally trying to change the

02:55:46.979 --> 02:55:47.280
world.

02:55:47.340 --> 02:55:51.420
She is trying not to hate her misshapen

02:55:51.420 --> 02:55:51.780
wing.

02:55:51.840 --> 02:55:55.559
I'm sorry, Tal, Cinnabar had whispered.

02:55:55.620 --> 02:55:57.540
Clasping her front talons between her

02:55:57.540 --> 02:55:57.780
own.

02:55:57.840 --> 02:56:00.059
We talked about this.

02:56:00.120 --> 02:56:01.739
You knew if there was fighting.

02:56:01.799 --> 02:56:03.180
You wouldn't be able to join us.

02:56:03.239 --> 02:56:05.280
It would be too dangerous for you.

02:56:05.340 --> 02:56:08.340
You mean, I couldn't keep up with you.

02:56:08.459 --> 02:56:10.319
Tao had answered ruefully.

02:56:10.379 --> 02:56:12.840
Think about who we're fighting, though

02:56:12.840 --> 02:56:14.459
Cinnabar had pressed.

02:56:14.520 --> 02:56:16.799
What if you saw tree hopper on the

02:56:16.799 --> 02:56:17.280
battlefield?

02:56:17.399 --> 02:56:19.739
All wide eyes and zombie brain?

02:56:19.799 --> 02:56:21.059
What if he attacked you?

02:56:21.120 --> 02:56:22.079
Or me?

02:56:22.139 --> 02:56:24.420
You're better off not having to face him

02:56:24.420 --> 02:56:24.780
like that.

02:56:24.840 --> 02:56:27.659
You'll be safe here until we win and come

02:56:27.659 --> 02:56:28.139
back for you.

02:56:28.200 --> 02:56:30.780
You'd better win.

02:56:30.840 --> 02:56:33.360
Tao had hugged her, her heart beating

02:56:33.360 --> 02:56:33.959
Biercely.

02:56:34.020 --> 02:56:37.079
Being left behind was worse than she'd

02:56:37.079 --> 02:56:37.620
expected, though.

02:56:37.739 --> 02:56:39.719
Not knowing what was happening?

02:56:39.780 --> 02:56:42.479
All her friends all fighting a battle

02:56:42.479 --> 02:56:42.959
without her?

02:56:43.020 --> 02:56:46.200
Wondering if they really did find an

02:56:46.200 --> 02:56:47.280
antidote to the mind control.

02:56:47.399 --> 02:56:50.879
Is Tree Hopper finally free of Queen

02:56:50.879 --> 02:56:51.540
Wasp?

02:56:51.600 --> 02:56:54.600
Or is he killing silk wings right now

02:56:54.600 --> 02:56:56.219
dead eyed and soulless?

02:56:56.280 --> 02:56:58.260
She shivers.

02:56:58.319 --> 02:57:02.219
How will he ever forgive himself if Wasp

02:57:02.219 --> 02:57:04.020
forces him to hurt his cow's friends?

02:57:04.079 --> 02:57:07.200
There hasn't been any sign of the hive

02:57:07.200 --> 02:57:09.299
wings since every single one of them

02:57:09.299 --> 02:57:11.579
suddenly froze, pivoted to the nearest

02:57:11.579 --> 02:57:13.500
window, and flew away north.

02:57:13.559 --> 02:57:16.920
It's peaceful, with all of Jewel Hive

02:57:16.920 --> 02:57:19.379
nearly empty, but also unsettling.

02:57:19.440 --> 02:57:21.600
Tow.

02:57:21.659 --> 02:57:23.280
Right.

02:57:23.340 --> 02:57:25.920
Not every hive wing.

02:57:26.040 --> 02:57:29.340
Lady Scarab marches into the kitchen and

02:57:29.340 --> 02:57:31.260
eyes the meatballs so intently.

02:57:31.319 --> 02:57:33.299
She practically sticks her nose into one

02:57:33.299 --> 02:57:33.540
of them.

02:57:33.600 --> 02:57:36.180
What is this?

02:57:36.299 --> 02:57:37.260
She demands.

02:57:37.319 --> 02:57:39.959
What herbs are you using?

02:57:40.020 --> 02:57:42.479
Why does it smell like that?

02:57:42.540 --> 02:57:45.059
Antelope meatballs?

02:57:45.180 --> 02:57:46.680
Tao says patiently.

02:57:46.739 --> 02:57:51.000
I have the only good recipe for antelope

02:57:51.000 --> 02:57:53.280
meatballs, Lady Scarab announces.

02:57:53.340 --> 02:57:56.819
If you didn't put chives in it, these

02:57:56.819 --> 02:57:58.139
won't be worth eating.

02:57:58.139 --> 02:58:01.920
I did put chives in it, Tao says.

02:58:01.979 --> 02:58:04.500
Probably too many.

02:58:04.559 --> 02:58:06.659
Lady Scarab sniffs.

02:58:06.719 --> 02:58:09.540
Something crashes in the hall behind them

02:58:09.540 --> 02:58:11.520
and they both turn toward the sound of

02:58:11.520 --> 02:58:12.719
galloping talon steps.

02:58:12.780 --> 02:58:16.139
Lady Jewel bursts into the kitchen, and

02:58:16.139 --> 02:58:18.479
the sight of her face sends Tao straight

02:58:18.479 --> 02:58:19.440
into full-blown panic.

02:58:19.559 --> 02:58:22.139
Cinnabar was just here.

02:58:22.200 --> 02:58:23.340
Joel gasps.

02:58:23.399 --> 02:58:24.719
With a message.

02:58:24.840 --> 02:58:26.579
The hive wings won.

02:58:26.639 --> 02:58:28.500
They're burning the poison jungle.

02:58:28.559 --> 02:58:30.719
And when they're done, they'll come here

02:58:30.719 --> 02:58:33.479
and now they can mind control silk wings

02:58:33.479 --> 02:58:34.260
as well.

02:58:34.319 --> 02:58:35.819
What?

02:58:35.879 --> 02:58:38.879
Tao clutches the counter, her talon

02:58:38.879 --> 02:58:39.719
slippery with grease.

02:58:39.840 --> 02:58:42.360
She can't process any piece of that

02:58:42.360 --> 02:58:44.520
information, let alone all of it.

02:58:44.579 --> 02:58:46.920
She latches on to the 1st thing.

02:58:46.979 --> 02:58:49.020
Cinnabar is here?

02:58:49.079 --> 02:58:49.920
Is she all right?

02:58:49.979 --> 02:58:52.979
She only had time to give me the message

02:58:52.979 --> 02:58:53.819
Jules says.

02:58:53.879 --> 02:58:56.940
They have to get to the other hives as

02:58:56.940 --> 02:58:59.639
fast as they can to warn the rest of the

02:58:59.639 --> 02:59:00.540
silk wings.

02:59:00.600 --> 02:59:02.940
I told her we'd get everyone here to

02:59:02.940 --> 02:59:03.540
safety.

02:59:03.600 --> 02:59:07.200
She glances around the room wildly, as

02:59:07.200 --> 02:59:08.760
though she's considering trying to fit

02:59:08.760 --> 02:59:10.920
every silk wing in the hive into one of

02:59:10.920 --> 02:59:11.879
her potato barrels.

02:59:11.940 --> 02:59:13.500
But how?

02:59:13.860 --> 02:59:14.579
Tao asks.

02:59:14.639 --> 02:59:16.079
Where can we go?

02:59:16.139 --> 02:59:18.899
Her heart feels like it's squeezing

02:59:18.899 --> 02:59:21.840
inward, shrinking into a nest of fear and

02:59:21.840 --> 02:59:22.319
spikes.

02:59:22.379 --> 02:59:24.719
They weren't supposed to lose.

02:59:24.780 --> 02:59:27.420
It wasn't supposed to get worse.

02:59:27.479 --> 02:59:31.440
Well, this is a fine mess.

02:59:31.500 --> 02:59:33.059
Lady scarab hisses.

02:59:33.120 --> 02:59:36.600
Now, who's going to take down my dreadful

02:59:36.600 --> 02:59:37.139
niece?

02:59:37.260 --> 02:59:40.920
Certainly would be nice if I had a

02:59:40.920 --> 02:59:43.200
daughter, willing to fight for the throne

02:59:43.200 --> 02:59:44.879
that should actually be ours.

02:59:45.000 --> 02:59:49.260
Not now, mother, Jules says.

02:59:49.319 --> 02:59:51.959
Cinnabar said to bring everyone to Lake

02:59:51.959 --> 02:59:52.739
Scorpion.

02:59:52.799 --> 02:59:54.659
There's somewhere we can go from there

02:59:54.659 --> 02:59:56.819
she said, but we have to all go

02:59:56.819 --> 02:59:57.299
together.

02:59:57.360 --> 03:00:00.180
She presses her claws to her temples for

03:00:00.180 --> 03:00:00.479
a moment.

03:00:00.540 --> 03:00:03.299
We need messengers to check every level

03:00:03.299 --> 03:00:04.020
of the hive.

03:00:04.079 --> 03:00:06.000
Someone to go to the webs.

03:00:06.059 --> 03:00:08.399
Dragons to carry the cocoons of any silk

03:00:08.399 --> 03:00:10.920
wings and metamorphosis right now, others

03:00:10.920 --> 03:00:13.260
to carry all the silk wing and hive wing

03:00:13.260 --> 03:00:14.280
eggs in the hatcheries.

03:00:14.399 --> 03:00:16.920
No, Scarab says.

03:00:16.979 --> 03:00:19.260
Not the hive wing eggs, jewel.

03:00:19.379 --> 03:00:22.440
We can't leave them behind, Joel

03:00:22.440 --> 03:00:23.040
protests.

03:00:23.100 --> 03:00:25.500
Oh, those tiny dragonettes.

03:00:25.620 --> 03:00:27.899
They're already infected.

03:00:28.020 --> 03:00:29.879
Scarab says bluntly.

03:00:29.940 --> 03:00:32.700
As soon as they hatch.

03:00:32.760 --> 03:00:34.979
Wasp will be able to see through their

03:00:34.979 --> 03:00:37.319
eyes, and then she'll find us.

03:00:37.379 --> 03:00:41.159
You can't bring them along, or you doom

03:00:41.159 --> 03:00:41.940
everyone else.

03:00:42.000 --> 03:00:45.360
Joel curls her talons and takes a deep

03:00:45.360 --> 03:00:45.659
breath.

03:00:45.719 --> 03:00:48.600
Tao knows she is thinking of her own

03:00:48.600 --> 03:00:50.579
children, who are out of reach now

03:00:50.579 --> 03:00:52.500
summoned along with everyone else.

03:00:52.559 --> 03:00:55.379
Jewel had thought they were free of the

03:00:55.379 --> 03:00:57.780
mind control, until they flew away with

03:00:57.780 --> 03:00:59.040
all the other hive wings.

03:00:59.100 --> 03:01:02.579
Maybe Scarab must guess Jules' thoughts

03:01:02.579 --> 03:01:02.819
too.

03:01:02.879 --> 03:01:05.819
Because she says, with unaccustomed

03:01:05.819 --> 03:01:08.040
gentleness, I miss them too.

03:01:08.100 --> 03:01:10.920
But it's better that we know at least.

03:01:11.040 --> 03:01:13.559
She could have used them against us if

03:01:13.559 --> 03:01:14.459
she'd left them here.

03:01:14.520 --> 03:01:18.600
She still can, Jules says quietly.

03:01:18.659 --> 03:01:21.600
Only if she can find you to threaten

03:01:21.600 --> 03:01:21.899
you.

03:01:21.959 --> 03:01:23.520
Scarab points out.

03:01:23.579 --> 03:01:26.639
They'll be safer if you vanish.

03:01:26.700 --> 03:01:30.659
Jewel doesn't answer, but her tail lashes

03:01:30.659 --> 03:01:32.700
across the floor, knocking over a stack

03:01:32.700 --> 03:01:33.239
of lemons.

03:01:33.299 --> 03:01:36.780
Maybe we can bring some of the hive wing

03:01:36.780 --> 03:01:38.520
eggs, Tao suggests.

03:01:38.579 --> 03:01:40.620
The ones who have only been stabbed

03:01:40.620 --> 03:01:40.860
once.

03:01:40.979 --> 03:01:42.000
Remember?

03:01:42.059 --> 03:01:44.219
Cricket said that wasp has to inject each

03:01:44.219 --> 03:01:46.020
egg twice to be able to control them.

03:01:46.139 --> 03:01:48.420
That was her theory.

03:01:48.540 --> 03:01:50.459
Scarab growls.

03:01:50.520 --> 03:01:52.079
She could be wrong.

03:01:52.139 --> 03:01:53.760
It's too risky.

03:01:53.819 --> 03:01:56.280
But if we can save some of them.

03:01:56.340 --> 03:01:58.440
We have to, Joel says.

03:01:58.500 --> 03:02:00.000
I'll think about it.

03:02:00.059 --> 03:02:03.120
In the meanwhile, you 2 go bring as many

03:02:03.120 --> 03:02:04.500
silk wings here as you can.

03:02:04.559 --> 03:02:06.180
And then we'll split into teams.

03:02:06.239 --> 03:02:08.879
She hurries out of the kitchen again

03:02:08.879 --> 03:02:11.280
murmuring lists of tasks to herself.

03:02:11.340 --> 03:02:14.579
Tao doesn't stop to hear any more of

03:02:14.579 --> 03:02:16.139
scarab's grim warnings.

03:02:16.200 --> 03:02:18.959
She runs out of the kitchen, through

03:02:18.959 --> 03:02:21.479
Jules mansion, her talons skidding on the

03:02:21.479 --> 03:02:21.659
floor.

03:02:21.719 --> 03:02:24.780
She'll start with the other servants and

03:02:24.780 --> 03:02:26.340
the prisoners and jewels dungeon.

03:02:26.399 --> 03:02:28.860
How many silk wings are there in the

03:02:28.860 --> 03:02:29.399
whole hive?

03:02:29.459 --> 03:02:31.440
Will they all listen to her?

03:02:31.500 --> 03:02:32.940
Or to Lady Jewel?

03:02:33.000 --> 03:02:35.159
How fast can they escape?

03:02:35.219 --> 03:02:38.639
Only as fast as our slowest dragons.

03:02:38.700 --> 03:02:40.559
Which includes me.

03:02:40.680 --> 03:02:44.159
The terror drives her onward, calling

03:02:44.159 --> 03:02:45.840
dragon after dragon to the ballroom.

03:02:45.959 --> 03:02:48.479
She can't get the images out of her

03:02:48.479 --> 03:02:48.719
head.

03:02:48.780 --> 03:02:52.139
Images of her friends, with white eyes

03:02:52.139 --> 03:02:54.840
like the mind controlled hive wings

03:02:54.840 --> 03:02:57.479
images of tree hopper slicing ruthlessly

03:02:57.479 --> 03:02:59.040
through any silk wing who tries to stop

03:02:59.040 --> 03:03:01.920
him, images of Queen Wasp, burning the

03:03:01.920 --> 03:03:04.379
jungle, killing all the leaf wings

03:03:04.379 --> 03:03:06.659
laughing her merciless laugh.

03:03:06.719 --> 03:03:09.420
But Cinnabar got away from her.

03:03:09.479 --> 03:03:12.479
So it's possible, if we can move fast

03:03:12.479 --> 03:03:12.840
enough.

03:03:12.959 --> 03:03:15.059
We have to escape.

03:03:15.120 --> 03:03:18.959
We have to, or none of us will ever be

03:03:18.959 --> 03:03:19.500
free again.

03:03:19.620 --> 03:03:24.959
Snowfall woke up, extremely grumpy.

03:03:25.020 --> 03:03:28.680
That is, first, she woke up in a state of

03:03:28.680 --> 03:03:31.379
heart pounding panic, confused and

03:03:31.379 --> 03:03:33.540
terrified about how she was suddenly

03:03:33.540 --> 03:03:35.459
asleep on a beach when she should be

03:03:35.459 --> 03:03:37.680
gathering dragons to escape jewel hive.

03:03:37.739 --> 03:03:40.319
But as her heart rate gradually slowed to

03:03:40.319 --> 03:03:42.299
normal, and she remembered who she

03:03:42.299 --> 03:03:45.360
actually was, her natural grumpiness

03:03:45.360 --> 03:03:46.739
returned to the power of 10.

03:03:46.979 --> 03:03:48.959
What?

03:03:48.959 --> 03:03:51.239
The moons was that.

03:03:51.299 --> 03:03:54.360
She glanced down and saw that her claws

03:03:54.360 --> 03:03:54.780
were shaking.

03:03:54.840 --> 03:03:57.780
She shoved them as far into the sand as

03:03:57.780 --> 03:03:58.920
she could until they stopped.

03:03:58.979 --> 03:04:02.819
I said, no more visions.

03:04:02.879 --> 03:04:04.920
She hissed the ring under her breath.

03:04:05.040 --> 03:04:08.399
And this time, she couldn't even pretend

03:04:08.399 --> 03:04:10.440
she'd just happened to dream about

03:04:10.440 --> 03:04:11.760
someone she'd seen.

03:04:11.819 --> 03:04:14.399
She'd never laid eyes on Tao in her life

03:04:14.399 --> 03:04:15.899
and probably never would.

03:04:15.959 --> 03:04:18.840
So either she had conjured an entire

03:04:18.840 --> 03:04:21.959
imaginary dragon with a forbidden love

03:04:21.959 --> 03:04:24.659
and revolutionary friends, and an entire

03:04:24.659 --> 03:04:27.719
hive, and about a 1000000 more dragons to

03:04:27.719 --> 03:04:30.780
worry about, where the stupid magic had

03:04:30.780 --> 03:04:33.059
dragged her brain all the way across the

03:04:33.059 --> 03:04:35.639
ocean, to torture her with scary things

03:04:35.639 --> 03:04:36.959
she could do nothing about.

03:04:37.020 --> 03:04:39.780
What is the point of this?

03:04:39.899 --> 03:04:43.020
Snowfall heard someone floundering

03:04:43.020 --> 03:04:43.979
through the sand toward her.

03:04:44.040 --> 03:04:47.040
She lifted her head out of her hole, and

03:04:47.040 --> 03:04:49.260
of course, it was lynx, looking all kinds

03:04:49.260 --> 03:04:50.040
of wound up.

03:04:50.100 --> 03:04:52.260
I have a theory.

03:04:52.319 --> 03:04:53.459
Length cried.

03:04:53.520 --> 03:04:55.799
As soon as she spotted Snowfall's face.

03:04:55.860 --> 03:04:59.520
No, good morning, or hello, Your Majesty

03:04:59.520 --> 03:05:02.520
or sorry for being a judgmental walrus

03:05:02.520 --> 03:05:02.940
yesterday.

03:05:03.000 --> 03:05:06.000
Snowfall shook out her wings irritably.

03:05:06.059 --> 03:05:08.399
Marvelous, she said.

03:05:08.459 --> 03:05:11.159
Let me guess, it involves me doing

03:05:11.159 --> 03:05:11.639
something wrong.

03:05:11.700 --> 03:05:14.940
You woke me up to ask me about weird

03:05:14.940 --> 03:05:16.139
dreams yesterday.

03:05:16.200 --> 03:05:18.180
Link said, pointing at her.

03:05:18.239 --> 03:05:20.819
Because you had a weird dream.

03:05:20.879 --> 03:05:23.579
And that ring you can't get off is called

03:05:23.579 --> 03:05:25.799
The Gift of Vision, isn't it?

03:05:25.860 --> 03:05:27.659
That's why you thought it was about

03:05:27.659 --> 03:05:29.459
eyesight, but it's not.

03:05:29.520 --> 03:05:32.340
I think it's giving you weird dreams

03:05:32.340 --> 03:05:34.020
because they're not dreams.

03:05:34.079 --> 03:05:36.479
They're visions.

03:05:36.540 --> 03:05:37.440
Get it?

03:05:37.500 --> 03:05:38.520
See what I mean?

03:05:38.579 --> 03:05:40.860
Gift of vision.

03:05:40.979 --> 03:05:43.799
Great eye spirits.

03:05:43.860 --> 03:05:45.059
Stop talking already.

03:05:45.120 --> 03:05:46.920
Snowfall growled.

03:05:46.979 --> 03:05:49.440
I figured that out about a 100 years ago

03:05:49.440 --> 03:05:52.500
but even if that's the case, it does not

03:05:52.500 --> 03:05:55.079
explain why the ring is stuck on my claw

03:05:55.079 --> 03:05:56.520
I still think it's broken.

03:05:56.579 --> 03:05:59.340
But it is doing something.

03:05:59.459 --> 03:06:02.340
Leng flicked her tail, and now her

03:06:02.340 --> 03:06:04.079
expression was definitely veering toward

03:06:04.079 --> 03:06:04.500
excited.

03:06:04.559 --> 03:06:06.780
Maybe it's important.

03:06:06.840 --> 03:06:08.280
Did you have another vision last night?

03:06:08.340 --> 03:06:09.659
What was it about?

03:06:09.719 --> 03:06:12.780
I thought you didn't trust animus magic

03:06:12.780 --> 03:06:14.940
and wearing this was a terrible idea

03:06:14.940 --> 03:06:16.920
Snowfall said accusingly.

03:06:16.979 --> 03:06:20.819
I'm still right about that, Ling said, but

03:06:20.819 --> 03:06:21.899
as long as you're stuck with it?

03:06:21.959 --> 03:06:23.399
We should figure out what it's trying to

03:06:23.399 --> 03:06:23.700
tell us.

03:06:23.819 --> 03:06:26.520
It's not trying to tell me anything

03:06:26.520 --> 03:06:28.139
Snowfall protested.

03:06:28.200 --> 03:06:31.920
It's a ring, an inanimate object, with no

03:06:31.920 --> 03:06:32.879
agenda or feelings.

03:06:32.940 --> 03:06:35.040
Except maybe smugness.

03:06:35.100 --> 03:06:36.780
You're very smug.

03:06:36.899 --> 03:06:38.520
She snapped at the opal.

03:06:38.579 --> 03:06:41.340
Snowball.

03:06:41.399 --> 03:06:42.600
Tell me what you saw.

03:06:42.719 --> 03:06:46.200
Links lashed her tail. sending up gusts

03:06:46.200 --> 03:06:46.680
of sand.

03:06:46.739 --> 03:06:49.020
Something happening back in the ice

03:06:49.020 --> 03:06:51.239
kingdom, something that's going to

03:06:51.239 --> 03:06:51.540
happen.

03:06:51.600 --> 03:06:54.659
No, Snowfall barked.

03:06:54.719 --> 03:06:56.040
Nothing useful.

03:06:56.159 --> 03:06:58.620
Nothing about my tribe or my problems.

03:06:58.680 --> 03:07:00.299
Nothing important at all.

03:07:00.420 --> 03:07:03.899
If this is stupid magic, then it's really

03:07:03.899 --> 03:07:05.219
stupid magic.

03:07:05.280 --> 03:07:09.659
Why would I, queen of the ice wings, need

03:07:09.659 --> 03:07:11.760
to know about all the inner emotions, of

03:07:11.760 --> 03:07:13.920
a bunch of rainbow dragons from a

03:07:13.920 --> 03:07:16.079
completely irrelevant continent that I'll

03:07:16.079 --> 03:07:16.319
never see?

03:07:16.440 --> 03:07:18.479
Inner emotions?

03:07:18.540 --> 03:07:19.860
Links asked.

03:07:19.920 --> 03:07:23.760
Like, you could feel what the silk wings

03:07:23.760 --> 03:07:24.180
were feeling.

03:07:24.239 --> 03:07:27.899
First, I was one of those stats now

03:07:27.899 --> 03:07:30.059
Snowball said, pointing up the beach.

03:07:30.120 --> 03:07:33.600
Her name is Atala, total tragedy vase.

03:07:33.659 --> 03:07:36.000
And then last night, I was some random

03:07:36.000 --> 03:07:39.120
dragon named Tao, who was stuck back over

03:07:39.120 --> 03:07:40.260
there and freaking out.

03:07:40.319 --> 03:07:42.059
Why would I need to see that?

03:07:42.180 --> 03:07:43.979
It's not like I can do anything to help

03:07:43.979 --> 03:07:44.219
her.

03:07:44.280 --> 03:07:47.760
Not that she would have, even if she

03:07:47.760 --> 03:07:48.000
could.

03:07:48.059 --> 03:07:51.540
She wasn't going to invite more invasive

03:07:51.540 --> 03:07:52.799
strange looking dragons here.

03:07:52.920 --> 03:07:56.340
Hmm, Lang said.

03:07:56.399 --> 03:07:57.899
Maybe you can.

03:07:58.020 --> 03:07:59.100
Somehow.

03:07:59.159 --> 03:08:02.100
Maybe, we just need to lay out everything

03:08:02.100 --> 03:08:04.260
you learned from your visions and figure

03:08:04.260 --> 03:08:05.159
out what to do about them.

03:08:05.219 --> 03:08:07.200
That's not a gift.

03:08:07.260 --> 03:08:10.020
That's homework. snowfall snapped.

03:08:10.079 --> 03:08:11.819
I've had quite enough of that.

03:08:11.879 --> 03:08:12.239
Thank you.

03:08:12.299 --> 03:08:13.979
I'm queen now.

03:08:14.040 --> 03:08:16.020
Other dragons should have to do the

03:08:16.020 --> 03:08:17.340
things I don't want to do.

03:08:17.399 --> 03:08:21.120
So tell me about it, Lang said eagerly.

03:08:21.180 --> 03:08:23.760
And everything about the 1st one before

03:08:23.760 --> 03:08:25.979
you forget it, and I'll figure out what

03:08:25.979 --> 03:08:26.280
they mean.

03:08:26.399 --> 03:08:29.219
Snowfall pointed one claw at her.

03:08:29.280 --> 03:08:30.540
No.

03:08:30.600 --> 03:08:32.940
I am going to ignore this nonsense.

03:08:33.000 --> 03:08:36.000
Are these slow slug dragons ready to fly

03:08:36.000 --> 03:08:36.899
to sanctuary yet?

03:08:36.959 --> 03:08:39.719
Lanx looked as if she wanted to keep

03:08:39.719 --> 03:08:40.200
arguing.

03:08:40.260 --> 03:08:42.780
But she stayed quiet as she followed

03:08:42.780 --> 03:08:44.520
Snowfall up the beach to investigate.

03:08:44.579 --> 03:08:48.180
And no, of course nobody was ready to

03:08:48.180 --> 03:08:48.360
go.

03:08:48.420 --> 03:08:51.299
Of course, it took the foreign tribes the

03:08:51.299 --> 03:08:52.739
entire morning to get organized.

03:08:52.799 --> 03:08:55.500
And then they decided to leave half the

03:08:55.500 --> 03:08:57.719
dragons behind, so the stronger ones

03:08:57.719 --> 03:08:59.819
could go ahead and make sure there was a

03:08:59.819 --> 03:09:00.299
place for everyone.

03:09:00.420 --> 03:09:03.120
So then they had to resettle the ones

03:09:03.120 --> 03:09:05.219
they were leaving behind, and then they

03:09:05.219 --> 03:09:06.360
decided to take a break to eat

03:09:06.360 --> 03:09:06.659
something.

03:09:06.719 --> 03:09:09.780
By the time their wings finally lifted

03:09:09.780 --> 03:09:11.940
into the sky, the sun was high above

03:09:11.940 --> 03:09:12.239
them.

03:09:12.360 --> 03:09:15.780
Snowfall was stalking back to summon the

03:09:15.780 --> 03:09:16.500
rest of her guards.

03:09:16.559 --> 03:09:19.379
When she heard someone say Queen Thorn's

03:09:19.379 --> 03:09:19.559
name.

03:09:19.620 --> 03:09:22.799
Her ears pricked, and she turned to see

03:09:22.799 --> 03:09:24.780
Moon talking to the sandwing who wasn't

03:09:24.780 --> 03:09:25.440
Jerboa.

03:09:25.500 --> 03:09:28.799
I'll fly ahead and visit Thorn on the way

03:09:28.799 --> 03:09:29.700
he said.

03:09:29.760 --> 03:09:32.280
You know, in case she wants to know why

03:09:32.280 --> 03:09:33.840
there's a flood of unusual looking

03:09:33.840 --> 03:09:35.399
dragons flying over her kingdom.

03:09:35.459 --> 03:09:37.860
Seems like something she might want to

03:09:37.860 --> 03:09:38.459
heads up about.

03:09:38.520 --> 03:09:40.500
Tell her where they're going.

03:09:40.559 --> 03:09:42.120
Moon suggested.

03:09:42.180 --> 03:09:45.059
Sanctuary is technically on the border of

03:09:45.059 --> 03:09:48.180
Sandwing and Skywing territory, so she

03:09:48.180 --> 03:09:49.139
should know that they're there.

03:09:49.139 --> 03:09:51.239
Ha!

03:09:51.299 --> 03:09:53.639
Snowfall thought to herself, pacing

03:09:53.639 --> 03:09:54.120
forward again.

03:09:54.180 --> 03:09:56.760
Let's see how she likes it.

03:09:56.819 --> 03:09:59.760
If Thorn lets all these dragons flap

03:09:59.760 --> 03:10:01.620
around over her desert and settle on her

03:10:01.620 --> 03:10:01.979
border.

03:10:02.040 --> 03:10:04.680
Maybe she isn't as strong a queen as

03:10:04.680 --> 03:10:05.340
everyone thinks.

03:10:05.399 --> 03:10:09.000
She wondered how Queen Ruby would feel

03:10:09.000 --> 03:10:11.280
about these new dragons living on the

03:10:11.280 --> 03:10:12.840
edge of Sky Wing territory.

03:10:12.899 --> 03:10:15.420
Sanctuary was supposed to be a small

03:10:15.420 --> 03:10:17.819
enclave, where dragons who couldn't go

03:10:17.819 --> 03:10:19.319
home to their own kingdoms could live.

03:10:19.379 --> 03:10:23.280
Dragons like Snowfall's cousin, Winter

03:10:23.280 --> 03:10:25.680
who'd been banished, or the remaining

03:10:25.680 --> 03:10:28.079
talons of peace, who wanted to stay with

03:10:28.079 --> 03:10:29.579
one another more than they wanted to

03:10:29.579 --> 03:10:30.479
return to their tribes.

03:10:30.600 --> 03:10:33.840
Snowfall didn't think Ruby or Thorn had

03:10:33.840 --> 03:10:36.719
ever imagined it, as a refuge for 100s of

03:10:36.719 --> 03:10:39.059
strange dragons, when they agreed to let

03:10:39.059 --> 03:10:40.440
the talons of peace build it.

03:10:40.500 --> 03:10:43.680
And what happens if even more dragons

03:10:43.680 --> 03:10:45.120
follow them here from Pantala?

03:10:45.180 --> 03:10:47.940
Is Cinnabar trying to bring all the rest

03:10:47.940 --> 03:10:49.379
of the silk wings over too?

03:10:49.440 --> 03:10:51.000
All of them?

03:10:51.000 --> 03:10:52.319
From all the hives?

03:10:52.379 --> 03:10:54.180
Where else can they go?

03:10:54.239 --> 03:10:57.000
With Queen Wasp and her brain washed hive

03:10:57.000 --> 03:10:58.799
wings controlling all of Pentala.

03:10:58.860 --> 03:11:01.559
Snowfall cut off that train of thought

03:11:01.559 --> 03:11:02.459
with a hiss.

03:11:02.520 --> 03:11:04.440
That's their problem.

03:11:04.500 --> 03:11:06.420
Not my problem.

03:11:06.479 --> 03:11:08.520
I have ice wings to take care of.

03:11:08.579 --> 03:11:11.100
I'm not responsible for anyone else, and

03:11:11.100 --> 03:11:12.120
I don't care about them.

03:11:12.180 --> 03:11:16.020
The terrors seemed to still be lingering

03:11:16.020 --> 03:11:18.120
in her veins though, and she couldn't

03:11:18.120 --> 03:11:20.819
shake the urgent, panicked feeling that

03:11:20.819 --> 03:11:22.860
she had to get an entire city of dragons

03:11:22.860 --> 03:11:24.600
to safety before it was too late.

03:11:24.659 --> 03:11:27.420
She wondered how old the vision was.

03:11:27.479 --> 03:11:30.840
Had that scene happened last night, while

03:11:30.840 --> 03:11:32.040
Snowfall dreamt it?

03:11:32.100 --> 03:11:34.319
Or days earlier, like her vision of

03:11:34.319 --> 03:11:34.860
Atala?

03:11:34.920 --> 03:11:39.959
If it happened days ago, Where were Tao

03:11:39.959 --> 03:11:41.700
and Duel, and Scarab now?

03:11:41.760 --> 03:11:44.219
Safely hidden or captured?

03:11:44.280 --> 03:11:48.000
Don't care, stop thinking about them.

03:11:48.059 --> 03:11:51.659
Let's go, she ordered her guards.

03:11:51.780 --> 03:11:54.479
They took up their positions in formation

03:11:54.479 --> 03:11:56.760
around her, and followed the silk wings

03:11:56.760 --> 03:11:59.040
and leaf wings away from the ocean, east

03:11:59.040 --> 03:12:00.540
into the desert sky.

03:12:00.600 --> 03:12:04.020
Snowfall glanced back and saw Jerboa

03:12:04.020 --> 03:12:06.000
sitting outside her hut, watching them

03:12:06.000 --> 03:12:06.239
leave.

03:12:06.299 --> 03:12:09.840
Why doesn't she seem to care more that

03:12:09.840 --> 03:12:10.920
her magic isn't working?

03:12:10.979 --> 03:12:12.719
Snowfall wondered.

03:12:12.780 --> 03:12:16.079
If she'd been an animus dragon, and then

03:12:16.079 --> 03:12:17.280
suddenly her power was gone.

03:12:17.340 --> 03:12:19.559
She'd have absolutely freaked out.

03:12:19.620 --> 03:12:23.219
Jerboa, on the other talent, seemed

03:12:23.219 --> 03:12:25.200
mostly amused by how much that annoyed

03:12:25.200 --> 03:12:25.799
Snowfall.

03:12:25.860 --> 03:12:28.860
It was still possible she was lying to

03:12:28.860 --> 03:12:29.399
Snowfall.

03:12:29.459 --> 03:12:32.760
But if animus magic was working, wouldn't

03:12:32.760 --> 03:12:34.739
tsunami's gang of righteous do-gooders

03:12:34.739 --> 03:12:36.540
have used it to bring all the Pentalin

03:12:36.540 --> 03:12:39.180
dragons to safety, or to stop Queen

03:12:39.180 --> 03:12:39.780
Wasp?

03:12:39.899 --> 03:12:42.299
They definitely would.

03:12:42.360 --> 03:12:44.399
They used it to end the plague and stop

03:12:44.399 --> 03:12:45.180
Dark Stalker.

03:12:45.239 --> 03:12:47.520
They could solve all the Bental and

03:12:47.520 --> 03:12:49.620
Dragon's problems with a snap of their

03:12:49.620 --> 03:12:51.120
claws if they had magic right now.

03:12:51.180 --> 03:12:53.100
So why don't they?

03:12:53.159 --> 03:12:55.500
Why would magic just?

03:12:55.920 --> 03:12:57.299
Stop working.

03:12:57.360 --> 03:13:00.600
Snowfall, eyeball, the oval ring.

03:13:00.659 --> 03:13:02.579
Do you know anything about this?

03:13:02.639 --> 03:13:04.200
She growled at it.

03:13:04.260 --> 03:13:07.799
Why do you work and actual useful magic

03:13:07.799 --> 03:13:08.219
doesn't?

03:13:08.340 --> 03:13:11.159
She shook out her talons grumpily and

03:13:11.159 --> 03:13:12.000
glared at it again.

03:13:12.059 --> 03:13:13.379
You know what?

03:13:13.500 --> 03:13:15.959
How about instead of filling my head with

03:13:15.959 --> 03:13:18.360
sympathy and nonsense, you give me some

03:13:18.360 --> 03:13:19.559
information I really need.

03:13:19.620 --> 03:13:21.959
Like a vision that explains what happened

03:13:21.959 --> 03:13:22.620
to magic.

03:13:22.739 --> 03:13:25.559
Maybe that's what she was doing wrong.

03:13:25.620 --> 03:13:28.559
Maybe she needed to tell the ring what

03:13:28.559 --> 03:13:29.340
vision she wanted.

03:13:29.399 --> 03:13:32.879
Oh, that would be simple and so great.

03:13:32.940 --> 03:13:35.040
Visions of anything she wanted.

03:13:35.100 --> 03:13:37.139
Why hadn't she thought of this earlier?

03:13:37.200 --> 03:13:39.239
Yes.

03:13:39.299 --> 03:13:40.559
She said firmly.

03:13:40.620 --> 03:13:42.180
You hear me, Ring?

03:13:42.239 --> 03:13:43.079
Tonight?

03:13:43.139 --> 03:13:45.000
No more silkwing nightmares.

03:13:45.059 --> 03:13:48.239
Just a nice, uncomplicated scene where I

03:13:48.239 --> 03:13:50.399
find out why animus magic isn't working.

03:13:50.520 --> 03:13:52.799
This is a good plan.

03:13:52.860 --> 03:13:56.280
Theopal caught the light and sparkled

03:13:56.280 --> 03:13:57.180
rainbows at her.

03:13:57.239 --> 03:13:59.819
Snowfall couldn't tell if those were

03:13:59.819 --> 03:14:02.399
absolutely, Your Majesty, anything you

03:14:02.399 --> 03:14:05.700
say, rainbows, or, ha, ha, ha.

03:14:05.760 --> 03:14:07.500
I'll give you whatever I want to give you

03:14:07.500 --> 03:14:09.000
and there's nothing you can do about it.

03:14:09.059 --> 03:14:09.959
Ha ha.

03:14:10.020 --> 03:14:10.860
Rainbows.

03:14:10.920 --> 03:14:13.079
I guess I'll find out tonight.

03:14:13.200 --> 03:14:16.500
She flew after the ribbon of dragons

03:14:16.500 --> 03:14:18.899
stretched across the sky. trying to feel

03:14:18.899 --> 03:14:20.579
confident that she'd solved her problem.

03:14:20.700 --> 03:14:23.639
But it was hard to shake the ominous

03:14:23.639 --> 03:14:27.239
feeling that maybe, just perhaps, she'd

03:14:27.239 --> 03:14:29.459
stumbled into a more dangerous magic than

03:14:29.459 --> 03:14:30.180
she'd expected.

03:14:30.239 --> 03:14:34.739
Chapter 9.

03:14:34.799 --> 03:14:38.579
The ice wings, leaf wings, and silk wings

03:14:38.579 --> 03:14:40.799
flew in their weird, mismatched crowd

03:14:40.799 --> 03:14:43.500
over the desert, which, incidentally, was

03:14:43.500 --> 03:14:44.879
a dreadful place.

03:14:45.239 --> 03:14:48.420
The sun beat down mercilessly, trying the

03:14:48.420 --> 03:14:50.700
scales on snowfalls back until she felt

03:14:50.700 --> 03:14:51.840
as if they might crack off.

03:14:51.899 --> 03:14:54.659
How could anyone live in a place like

03:14:54.659 --> 03:14:54.899
this?

03:14:54.959 --> 03:14:57.540
It was so hot.

03:14:57.600 --> 03:14:59.399
Blech.

03:14:59.520 --> 03:15:02.280
The leaf wings looked almost as unhappy

03:15:02.280 --> 03:15:03.420
about the heat as she was.

03:15:03.479 --> 03:15:06.180
Their wing beats slowed as they flew

03:15:06.180 --> 03:15:08.639
farther and farther from the ocean. and a

03:15:08.639 --> 03:15:10.799
vast treeless landscape spread out below

03:15:10.799 --> 03:15:10.979
them.

03:15:11.100 --> 03:15:15.299
Rocks and sand, and sand and rocks, and a

03:15:15.299 --> 03:15:16.200
whole lot of nothing.

03:15:16.260 --> 03:15:19.200
Trubella kept saying that nobody would

03:15:19.200 --> 03:15:21.239
want the ice kingdom, but who would

03:15:21.239 --> 03:15:21.899
prefer this?

03:15:21.959 --> 03:15:25.139
Of course, dragons would rather live in a

03:15:25.139 --> 03:15:27.899
cool, beautiful, snowy, crystalline place

03:15:27.899 --> 03:15:30.239
full of polar bears and walruses.

03:15:30.239 --> 03:15:32.219
What did they have to eat here?

03:15:32.280 --> 03:15:36.180
Tiny, brittle lizards, bony, gross

03:15:36.180 --> 03:15:37.079
smelling camels?

03:15:37.200 --> 03:15:39.959
It made much more sense the dragons would

03:15:39.959 --> 03:15:41.459
want to invade the ice kingdom than

03:15:41.459 --> 03:15:41.700
here.

03:15:41.760 --> 03:15:44.879
Snowfall was absolutely right to worry

03:15:44.879 --> 03:15:45.840
about defending it.

03:15:45.899 --> 03:15:49.200
Moon had some kind of map from her

03:15:49.200 --> 03:15:51.360
sandwing friend that showed each oasis

03:15:51.360 --> 03:15:53.340
along their route, so they were able to

03:15:53.340 --> 03:15:54.360
stop twice for water.

03:15:54.420 --> 03:15:57.600
Snowfall waded all the way into the tiny

03:15:57.600 --> 03:16:00.479
springs, trying to soak every drop into

03:16:00.479 --> 03:16:01.020
her scales.

03:16:01.079 --> 03:16:04.319
It suddenly seemed slightly insane to her

03:16:04.319 --> 03:16:06.600
that her tribe had ever fought with the

03:16:06.600 --> 03:16:07.319
sand wings.

03:16:07.379 --> 03:16:09.479
When this territory was the absolute

03:16:09.479 --> 03:16:11.579
worst, and they couldn't possibly want

03:16:11.579 --> 03:16:12.239
anything here.

03:16:12.299 --> 03:16:15.360
It was late in the afternoon when they

03:16:15.360 --> 03:16:17.040
caught their 1st glimpse of the mountains

03:16:17.040 --> 03:16:20.340
ahead, like a long giant dragon's spine

03:16:20.340 --> 03:16:21.659
curled across the horizon.

03:16:21.719 --> 03:16:24.719
They were mostly green and brown, but

03:16:24.719 --> 03:16:26.760
dappled with glorious snow at the peaks.

03:16:26.819 --> 03:16:30.780
Tao has never seen mountains, Snowfall

03:16:30.780 --> 03:16:32.520
thought, and then caught herself thinking

03:16:32.520 --> 03:16:33.780
that and was furious.

03:16:33.840 --> 03:16:35.819
So what?

03:16:35.879 --> 03:16:37.559
She demanded of her brain.

03:16:37.620 --> 03:16:41.100
I've never seen one of these hive cities

03:16:41.100 --> 03:16:42.600
and I'm perfectly happy about it.

03:16:42.659 --> 03:16:46.079
She put on a burst of speed to catch up

03:16:46.079 --> 03:16:48.420
to Hazel, who looked a little surprised

03:16:48.420 --> 03:16:50.700
to be approached, but too tired to have

03:16:50.700 --> 03:16:51.899
much more of a reaction.

03:16:51.959 --> 03:16:54.659
Hello, question for you.

03:16:54.719 --> 03:16:55.979
Snowfall said.

03:16:56.100 --> 03:16:58.319
How many dragons did you leave behind?

03:16:58.379 --> 03:17:00.899
On Jerboa's beach?

03:17:00.959 --> 03:17:01.920
Hazel asked.

03:17:01.979 --> 03:17:06.059
About, no, no, Snowfall interrupted.

03:17:06.120 --> 03:17:09.360
Back on Pantala, how many dragons did you

03:17:09.360 --> 03:17:09.719
leave there?

03:17:09.780 --> 03:17:12.719
Oh, Hazel blinked.

03:17:12.780 --> 03:17:16.860
Well, the, the leaf wing army, I guess

03:17:16.860 --> 03:17:17.520
you'd call it?

03:17:17.579 --> 03:17:20.159
Everyone who went with Queen Sequoia to

03:17:20.159 --> 03:17:20.459
fight.

03:17:20.520 --> 03:17:22.979
They must have been exposed to the breath

03:17:22.979 --> 03:17:23.940
of evil right away.

03:17:24.000 --> 03:17:27.479
They're probably under wasps' power now.

03:17:27.540 --> 03:17:31.079
She bit her lip and burrowed her brow and

03:17:31.079 --> 03:17:32.760
did some more odd things with her face

03:17:32.760 --> 03:17:35.579
which Snowfall eventually realized were

03:17:35.579 --> 03:17:37.079
all Hazel tried not to cry.

03:17:37.139 --> 03:17:40.079
I hope some of them managed to escape

03:17:40.079 --> 03:17:40.319
though.

03:17:40.379 --> 03:17:42.899
And then there's the rest of the silk

03:17:42.899 --> 03:17:43.979
wings and all the hives.

03:17:44.100 --> 03:17:46.739
Hundreds of them, but I don't know

03:17:46.739 --> 03:17:47.760
exactly how many.

03:17:47.819 --> 03:17:50.639
The ones who flew over with us are only

03:17:50.639 --> 03:17:53.399
from 3 of the hives, and they were in a

03:17:53.399 --> 03:17:54.659
group called the chrysalis.

03:17:54.719 --> 03:17:56.819
They'd come to the jungle to help us

03:17:56.819 --> 03:17:57.959
fight the hive wings.

03:17:58.020 --> 03:18:01.440
But that went horribly wrong, Snowfall

03:18:01.440 --> 03:18:01.680
said.

03:18:01.739 --> 03:18:04.020
And now all the silk wings you left

03:18:04.020 --> 03:18:05.100
behind are in danger.

03:18:05.159 --> 03:18:06.600
Yes?

03:18:06.719 --> 03:18:10.260
Hazel trailed off and gave her a sideways

03:18:10.260 --> 03:18:11.219
confused expression.

03:18:11.280 --> 03:18:13.739
You sound kind of worried about them?

03:18:13.860 --> 03:18:16.799
I'm not, Snowball cried.

03:18:16.860 --> 03:18:18.180
I'm definitely not.

03:18:18.239 --> 03:18:21.780
Maybe just a little worried about Tao, but

03:18:21.780 --> 03:18:22.200
not really.

03:18:22.260 --> 03:18:24.959
Only because of a dopey magic spell

03:18:24.959 --> 03:18:26.100
giving me weird dreams.

03:18:26.159 --> 03:18:29.040
No, she added firmly.

03:18:29.100 --> 03:18:32.579
If I am at all worried, it is because I

03:18:32.579 --> 03:18:34.860
am wondering whether all those dragons

03:18:34.860 --> 03:18:36.780
are going to end up floundering into my

03:18:36.780 --> 03:18:38.159
kingdom sometime soon as well.

03:18:38.219 --> 03:18:41.760
It is very hard to get across the ocean

03:18:41.760 --> 03:18:43.020
Hazel said.

03:18:43.079 --> 03:18:46.200
I I mean, we hope they'll try.

03:18:46.260 --> 03:18:49.559
But I can't predict how many, or if

03:18:49.559 --> 03:18:52.440
they'll succeed, or when, if that's what

03:18:52.440 --> 03:18:52.860
you're asking.

03:18:52.920 --> 03:18:55.200
Nightwing!

03:18:55.260 --> 03:18:58.319
Snowfall bellowed, startling Hazel into

03:18:58.319 --> 03:18:59.819
losing her flight rhythm for a moment.

03:18:59.879 --> 03:19:03.120
Up ahead, Moon twisted around, looking

03:19:03.120 --> 03:19:03.719
puzzled.

03:19:03.780 --> 03:19:05.879
Snowfall beckoned to her.

03:19:05.940 --> 03:19:08.280
And Moon came soaring back to fly on the

03:19:08.280 --> 03:19:09.180
other side of Hazel.

03:19:09.239 --> 03:19:11.040
Yes?

03:19:11.159 --> 03:19:12.719
Moon said cautiously.

03:19:12.780 --> 03:19:15.600
You can see the future, can't you?

03:19:15.659 --> 03:19:17.040
Snowfall demanded.

03:19:17.100 --> 03:19:19.860
Winter told me you had some prophecy

03:19:19.860 --> 03:19:22.200
about Dark Stalker, not that it helped

03:19:22.200 --> 03:19:22.739
anyone at all.

03:19:22.799 --> 03:19:24.420
Are you ever useful?

03:19:24.479 --> 03:19:27.120
Can you predict if the other silk wings

03:19:27.120 --> 03:19:28.379
are going to make it to this continent?

03:19:28.440 --> 03:19:33.719
I, that's not, Moon stammered. flustered.

03:19:33.780 --> 03:19:37.020
My visions aren't specific like that.

03:19:37.079 --> 03:19:39.479
I caught a glimpse of this group arriving

03:19:39.479 --> 03:19:42.360
but I haven't seen any other Pentalon

03:19:42.360 --> 03:19:42.840
dragons.

03:19:42.899 --> 03:19:45.540
That doesn't mean they won't make it

03:19:45.540 --> 03:19:45.659
though.

03:19:45.780 --> 03:19:49.139
And we can't poke your head to find out?

03:19:49.200 --> 03:19:50.520
Snowfall asked.

03:19:50.579 --> 03:19:53.520
Like summon a vision or whatever.

03:19:53.579 --> 03:19:56.879
I thought you could, Hazel admitted.

03:19:56.940 --> 03:19:59.819
I mean, I thought Clearside could.

03:19:59.879 --> 03:20:00.959
From what I've read.

03:20:01.020 --> 03:20:03.420
So I thought you all could see whatever

03:20:03.420 --> 03:20:04.139
you wanted.

03:20:04.200 --> 03:20:06.180
Moon shook her head.

03:20:06.239 --> 03:20:09.000
Clearsight's power was unusual.

03:20:09.059 --> 03:20:12.120
All I get is flashes whenever the

03:20:12.120 --> 03:20:14.700
universe feels like giving them to me, and

03:20:14.700 --> 03:20:16.500
the occasional cryptic prophecy.

03:20:16.559 --> 03:20:19.620
She shut her mouth quickly, but Snowfall

03:20:19.620 --> 03:20:20.760
had already caught the shift in her

03:20:20.760 --> 03:20:20.940
eyes.

03:20:21.059 --> 03:20:23.760
Aha, she said.

03:20:23.819 --> 03:20:27.000
You had a cryptic prophecy about all this

03:20:27.000 --> 03:20:27.659
didn't you?

03:20:27.719 --> 03:20:29.280
That's right.

03:20:29.340 --> 03:20:31.079
Tsunami said you did.

03:20:31.200 --> 03:20:33.059
Hazel's eyes lit up.

03:20:33.180 --> 03:20:35.159
Did it mention the breath of evil?

03:20:35.219 --> 03:20:37.500
Did it tell you how we can rescue

03:20:37.500 --> 03:20:39.299
everyone and save Pantala?

03:20:39.360 --> 03:20:41.579
Not exactly.

03:20:41.639 --> 03:20:43.799
Moon admitted reluctantly.

03:20:43.860 --> 03:20:47.819
I mean, the key word here is cryptic

03:20:47.819 --> 03:20:48.299
remember?

03:20:48.360 --> 03:20:52.139
Tell us anyway, Snowfall commanded.

03:20:52.260 --> 03:20:54.600
We will uncrypticate for you.

03:20:54.719 --> 03:20:57.899
Moonside, and then recited.

03:20:57.959 --> 03:21:01.860
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire. to

03:21:01.860 --> 03:21:04.559
the land across the sea, where dragons

03:21:04.559 --> 03:21:07.319
are poisoned and dragons are dying, and

03:21:07.319 --> 03:21:08.760
no one can ever be free.

03:21:08.819 --> 03:21:11.639
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

03:21:11.700 --> 03:21:14.159
A secret hides within their book.

03:21:14.159 --> 03:21:18.360
A secret buried far below may save those

03:21:18.360 --> 03:21:19.379
brave enough to look.

03:21:19.440 --> 03:21:23.399
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

03:21:23.399 --> 03:21:25.739
to the dragons who flee from the hive.

03:21:25.799 --> 03:21:29.879
Face a great evil with talent united, or

03:21:29.879 --> 03:21:31.440
none of the tribes will survive.

03:21:31.559 --> 03:21:35.100
There was silence for several wing beats

03:21:35.100 --> 03:21:36.059
after she finished.

03:21:36.120 --> 03:21:38.760
Hazel stared off into the sky ahead of

03:21:38.760 --> 03:21:41.520
them, her brow furrowed, her mouth moving

03:21:41.520 --> 03:21:43.739
as she repeated the prophecy quietly to

03:21:43.739 --> 03:21:43.979
herself.

03:21:44.100 --> 03:21:48.120
Well, Snowfall said finally.

03:21:48.180 --> 03:21:49.799
I do not like that.

03:21:49.860 --> 03:21:51.360
No, I do not.

03:21:51.420 --> 03:21:54.059
Dark soccer was quiet enough great evil

03:21:54.059 --> 03:21:54.360
for me.

03:21:54.479 --> 03:21:57.540
She saw Moon flinch when she said Dark

03:21:57.540 --> 03:21:59.579
Stalker's name, which was interesting.

03:21:59.639 --> 03:22:02.100
Did the Nightwing feel guilty about

03:22:02.100 --> 03:22:03.420
everything that had happened with him?

03:22:03.479 --> 03:22:06.239
Or did she feel guilty because she was

03:22:06.239 --> 03:22:08.219
totally lying about him actually being

03:22:08.219 --> 03:22:08.579
gone?

03:22:08.639 --> 03:22:12.780
Wasn't it possible that he was the great

03:22:12.780 --> 03:22:13.319
evil?

03:22:13.379 --> 03:22:16.680
After all, how many great evils could

03:22:16.680 --> 03:22:17.399
there possibly be?

03:22:17.459 --> 03:22:22.020
Hang on, she said, her thoughts swerving

03:22:22.020 --> 03:22:22.739
onto a new track.

03:22:22.799 --> 03:22:26.459
Did you say none of the tribes will

03:22:26.459 --> 03:22:26.760
survive?

03:22:26.879 --> 03:22:29.100
That's the prophecy.

03:22:29.159 --> 03:22:32.399
Moon said, spreading her front talons in

03:22:32.399 --> 03:22:34.559
an, I have no idea gesture.

03:22:34.620 --> 03:22:38.159
But you mean none of the Pentalan

03:22:38.159 --> 03:22:38.760
tribes.

03:22:38.819 --> 03:22:41.579
Snowfall clarified, right?

03:22:41.639 --> 03:22:42.959
Just those three?

03:22:43.020 --> 03:22:45.479
Not the 7 tribes on this continent.

03:22:45.600 --> 03:22:47.639
It has nothing to do with us, right?

03:22:47.700 --> 03:22:51.479
I think it might mean all of us, Link

03:22:51.479 --> 03:22:51.840
said.

03:22:51.899 --> 03:22:54.239
Suddenly and very unwelcomely.

03:22:54.299 --> 03:22:57.059
Snowfall hadn't even noticed her pop up

03:22:57.059 --> 03:22:57.420
below them.

03:22:57.479 --> 03:23:00.659
I mean, it starts off talking to us.

03:23:00.719 --> 03:23:03.899
Turn your eyes to the land across the sea

03:23:03.959 --> 03:23:04.620
right?

03:23:04.680 --> 03:23:08.520
And then face a great evil with talons

03:23:08.520 --> 03:23:08.940
united.

03:23:09.000 --> 03:23:11.340
That sounds like it's talking about all

03:23:11.340 --> 03:23:13.739
the tribes here and there.

03:23:13.799 --> 03:23:16.799
Bosh. said Snowfall.

03:23:16.860 --> 03:23:19.799
We can't unite to face an evil that's all

03:23:19.799 --> 03:23:21.780
the way across the ocean, even if we

03:23:21.780 --> 03:23:24.659
wanted to, which, to be clear, the ice

03:23:24.659 --> 03:23:26.040
wing tribe does not.

03:23:26.100 --> 03:23:28.920
There are 7 tribes here?

03:23:29.040 --> 03:23:30.659
Hazel asked Moon.

03:23:30.719 --> 03:23:32.579
Each with its own queen?

03:23:32.700 --> 03:23:34.500
Moon nodded.

03:23:34.559 --> 03:23:35.639
Yes.

03:23:35.700 --> 03:23:38.459
We should call a council and see if

03:23:38.459 --> 03:23:40.079
they'll all come, she said.

03:23:40.139 --> 03:23:43.020
They should know about you and Pentala

03:23:43.020 --> 03:23:44.340
and everything happening over there.

03:23:44.399 --> 03:23:48.840
Oh, marvelous, Snowfall thought

03:23:48.840 --> 03:23:49.440
gradually.

03:23:49.500 --> 03:23:52.260
All the queens who annoy me in one place

03:23:52.260 --> 03:23:54.479
arguing and telling me what to do.

03:23:54.600 --> 03:23:57.899
On the plus side, staying in sanctuary

03:23:57.899 --> 03:24:00.299
for a queen council would mean avoiding

03:24:00.299 --> 03:24:01.979
the wall for a few more days.

03:24:02.040 --> 03:24:05.100
But listening to Thorn, and Ruby, and

03:24:05.100 --> 03:24:07.739
Morehen, and Coral, and worst of all

03:24:07.739 --> 03:24:11.879
glory, go on and on about unity, and

03:24:11.879 --> 03:24:14.940
working together, and mutual trust, and

03:24:14.940 --> 03:24:17.399
all that sort of nonsense, was basically

03:24:17.399 --> 03:24:19.260
Snowfall's nightmare.

03:24:19.319 --> 03:24:20.459
Blur.

03:24:20.579 --> 03:24:24.840
I'll tell Tsunami, Moon said, tilting her

03:24:24.840 --> 03:24:25.200
wings.

03:24:25.260 --> 03:24:27.780
I'm sure she can organize some dragons

03:24:27.780 --> 03:24:29.760
from sanctuary. to take messages to the

03:24:29.760 --> 03:24:30.180
queens.

03:24:30.239 --> 03:24:32.700
She flew off toward the pair of sea

03:24:32.700 --> 03:24:33.000
wings.

03:24:33.059 --> 03:24:35.940
It's amazing that all your queens get

03:24:35.940 --> 03:24:38.700
along so well, Hazel said wistfully.

03:24:38.760 --> 03:24:41.760
I wish we could have 3 tribes peacefully

03:24:41.760 --> 03:24:43.379
coexisting on Pentala.

03:24:43.440 --> 03:24:45.120
Ha!

03:24:45.180 --> 03:24:46.260
Snowfall said.

03:24:46.319 --> 03:24:48.239
Peacefully coexisting?

03:24:48.299 --> 03:24:49.979
We just got out of a war.

03:24:50.040 --> 03:24:53.459
Two, technically, if you count the ice

03:24:53.459 --> 03:24:55.920
wing night wing war, I tried to have

03:24:55.920 --> 03:24:58.860
before that busybody animus interfered.

03:24:58.920 --> 03:25:00.479
You did?

03:25:00.540 --> 03:25:02.879
Hazel said, wide-eyed.

03:25:02.940 --> 03:25:04.860
Long story.

03:25:04.979 --> 03:25:07.139
Snowfall added with a snort.

03:25:07.139 --> 03:25:08.700
I'll explain it.

03:25:08.760 --> 03:25:11.459
Links offered, and then spent the rest of

03:25:11.459 --> 03:25:13.200
the flight telling Hazel about the War of

03:25:13.200 --> 03:25:15.479
Sandwing succession, and how it started

03:25:15.479 --> 03:25:17.879
and all about the prophecy, and how the

03:25:17.879 --> 03:25:19.920
shiny heroic dragonettes finally ended

03:25:19.920 --> 03:25:20.159
it.

03:25:20.219 --> 03:25:23.760
Personally, Snowfall thought they got an

03:25:23.760 --> 03:25:25.979
awful lot of credit considering the real

03:25:25.979 --> 03:25:28.440
heroes were a deadly snake, and an old

03:25:28.440 --> 03:25:29.340
enchanted orb.

03:25:29.459 --> 03:25:31.799
If there'd been an ice wing in the

03:25:31.799 --> 03:25:33.840
prophecy, she probably would have ended

03:25:33.840 --> 03:25:35.700
the war way sooner and more neatly.

03:25:35.819 --> 03:25:38.940
But whatever, not snowfall's problem.

03:25:39.059 --> 03:25:41.639
As they started their descent into

03:25:41.639 --> 03:25:44.280
sanctuary, Snowfall was startled to see

03:25:44.280 --> 03:25:46.020
how much bigger it was than she'd

03:25:46.020 --> 03:25:46.440
imagined.

03:25:46.500 --> 03:25:49.500
The new Dragon Village was built along a

03:25:49.500 --> 03:25:52.079
stream, trickling downhill from a lake in

03:25:52.079 --> 03:25:54.059
the foothills of the Claws of the Clouds

03:25:54.059 --> 03:25:54.540
Mountains.

03:25:54.600 --> 03:25:57.360
Some of the new dragon buildings were in

03:25:57.360 --> 03:25:59.520
the wildflower meadows, while some were

03:25:59.520 --> 03:26:01.020
under the trees of the forest.

03:26:01.079 --> 03:26:03.600
It was very disorganized.

03:26:03.659 --> 03:26:05.340
As far as snowfall could see.

03:26:05.399 --> 03:26:07.739
Each dragon home looked completely

03:26:07.739 --> 03:26:08.819
different from the next.

03:26:08.879 --> 03:26:12.659
Here there was a weird mound of clay, with

03:26:12.659 --> 03:26:13.319
a hole at the top.

03:26:13.440 --> 03:26:16.139
Then right beside it, there'd be a rough

03:26:16.139 --> 03:26:17.760
cabin made of logs and leaves.

03:26:17.879 --> 03:26:20.459
While over by the lake, there were a

03:26:20.459 --> 03:26:22.440
couple of crooked structures poking half

03:26:22.440 --> 03:26:24.120
in and half out of the water.

03:26:24.180 --> 03:26:27.959
Upon landing, Snowfall noticed that there

03:26:27.959 --> 03:26:30.000
were also more dragonettes than she'd

03:26:30.000 --> 03:26:31.860
expected, and some of them were really

03:26:31.860 --> 03:26:32.639
odd looking.

03:26:32.700 --> 03:26:35.760
The 1st one she saw was a tiny thing

03:26:35.760 --> 03:26:38.280
playing in the stream, pouncing on fish.

03:26:38.340 --> 03:26:41.819
Its scales were a deep mahogany brown

03:26:41.819 --> 03:26:42.959
like a mud wings.

03:26:43.020 --> 03:26:45.840
But speckled with phosphorescent bluish

03:26:45.840 --> 03:26:48.479
scales along its spine and wings, and as

03:26:48.479 --> 03:26:50.700
far as she could tell, its talons were

03:26:50.700 --> 03:26:52.260
webbed like a sea wings.

03:26:52.379 --> 03:26:55.799
Nearby, a little cluster of orange and

03:26:55.799 --> 03:26:57.600
red dragonettes were gathered around a

03:26:57.600 --> 03:26:59.700
sky wing, listening as he read them a

03:26:59.700 --> 03:27:00.000
scroll.

03:27:00.059 --> 03:27:03.899
But 2 of the red dragonettes had scorpion

03:27:03.899 --> 03:27:06.299
like tail barbs, and one of the orange

03:27:06.299 --> 03:27:08.040
ones had a scattering of black scales

03:27:08.040 --> 03:27:08.940
across its nose.

03:27:09.000 --> 03:27:12.239
Snowfall's brain was still contorting

03:27:12.239 --> 03:27:14.520
itself around this information when a sky

03:27:14.520 --> 03:27:16.799
blue sea wing came bounding out of the

03:27:16.799 --> 03:27:17.819
trees toward them.

03:27:17.879 --> 03:27:22.020
Tsunami, he cried, as though the sun

03:27:22.020 --> 03:27:23.760
itself had arrived to visit him.

03:27:23.819 --> 03:27:27.780
His whole face was full of joy, which

03:27:27.780 --> 03:27:30.540
made no sense, because who could possibly

03:27:30.540 --> 03:27:33.420
be that excited to see the very absolute

03:27:33.420 --> 03:27:35.579
most annoying member of the Dragonette

03:27:35.579 --> 03:27:36.059
prophecy.

03:27:36.120 --> 03:27:40.319
Hey, riptide, she said, in a voice that

03:27:40.319 --> 03:27:43.020
sounded as confident as she usually did

03:27:43.020 --> 03:27:45.659
but didn't quite match the funny look on

03:27:45.659 --> 03:27:46.020
her face.

03:27:46.079 --> 03:27:49.739
The 2 sea wings awkwardly tried to hug

03:27:49.739 --> 03:27:51.420
and their wings all went in the wrong

03:27:51.420 --> 03:27:53.700
directions, and they ended up bonking

03:27:53.700 --> 03:27:56.159
heads and then jumping back and flapping

03:27:56.159 --> 03:27:56.700
about for a bit.

03:27:56.760 --> 03:27:59.879
Snowfall guessed, there was something she

03:27:59.879 --> 03:28:01.260
could infer from their strange

03:28:01.260 --> 03:28:01.979
interaction.

03:28:02.100 --> 03:28:03.959
She wasn't all that interested.

03:28:04.020 --> 03:28:06.239
She was looking around for her cousin

03:28:06.239 --> 03:28:06.780
Winter.

03:28:06.899 --> 03:28:10.139
Was that a flash of white scales in the

03:28:10.139 --> 03:28:10.500
trees?

03:28:10.559 --> 03:28:13.739
Snowfall squinted, but whoever it was had

03:28:13.739 --> 03:28:14.399
vanished again.

03:28:14.459 --> 03:28:16.680
Or maybe it had been a trick of the

03:28:16.680 --> 03:28:16.860
light.

03:28:16.920 --> 03:28:21.000
It's so great to see you, Riptide was

03:28:21.000 --> 03:28:21.840
saying to tsunami.

03:28:21.899 --> 03:28:24.239
I was hoping you'd come see all the

03:28:24.239 --> 03:28:25.739
changes we.

03:28:26.940 --> 03:28:28.979
His voice trailed off as his eyes

03:28:28.979 --> 03:28:30.959
followed the line of dragons behind her

03:28:30.959 --> 03:28:33.540
up into the sky, where more and more

03:28:33.540 --> 03:28:35.700
dragons were arriving as the slowpokes

03:28:35.700 --> 03:28:36.059
caught up.

03:28:36.120 --> 03:28:37.500
What?

03:28:37.620 --> 03:28:39.420
Riptide tried.

03:28:39.479 --> 03:28:40.739
What?

03:28:40.799 --> 03:28:45.780
Um, Surprise, tsunami said buoyantly.

03:28:45.840 --> 03:28:48.059
New dragons for sanctuary.

03:28:48.180 --> 03:28:49.979
New.

03:28:50.040 --> 03:28:53.700
All these, but Riptide sputtered.

03:28:53.760 --> 03:28:55.799
Are those rain wings?

03:28:55.860 --> 03:28:58.079
asked a new voice from Snowfall's right.

03:28:58.139 --> 03:29:00.719
She turned and saw Winters flashing

03:29:00.719 --> 03:29:02.579
through the stream, staring up at the

03:29:02.579 --> 03:29:03.600
arriving silk wings.

03:29:03.719 --> 03:29:07.500
Hmm, So that couldn't have been him in

03:29:07.500 --> 03:29:07.860
the woods.

03:29:07.979 --> 03:29:11.760
Winter, Lynx cried with delight.

03:29:11.819 --> 03:29:15.360
He jumped and dropped his gaze to her, and

03:29:15.360 --> 03:29:17.100
then to snowfall standing right next to

03:29:17.100 --> 03:29:17.280
her.

03:29:17.340 --> 03:29:21.000
Lynx, he said in a wondering voice.

03:29:21.120 --> 03:29:22.860
Snowfall?

03:29:22.920 --> 03:29:24.540
What are you doing here?

03:29:24.659 --> 03:29:27.600
Length cleared her throat and bobbed her

03:29:27.600 --> 03:29:29.280
head meaningfully in Snowfall's

03:29:29.280 --> 03:29:29.520
direction.

03:29:29.579 --> 03:29:32.639
I mean, apologies.

03:29:32.700 --> 03:29:35.520
Your majesty, he said to Snowfall.

03:29:35.639 --> 03:29:37.440
Welcome to Sanctuary.

03:29:37.500 --> 03:29:40.260
He even bowed properly, which was

03:29:40.260 --> 03:29:40.739
mollifying.

03:29:40.860 --> 03:29:43.979
I have come to inspect this new city

03:29:43.979 --> 03:29:45.600
Snowfall informed him.

03:29:45.659 --> 03:29:49.020
And to make sure these peculiar dragons

03:29:49.020 --> 03:29:51.360
settle here, and don't try to come back

03:29:51.360 --> 03:29:52.139
into the ice kingdom.

03:29:52.260 --> 03:29:56.639
Not that they can, Links observed, given

03:29:56.639 --> 03:29:57.719
the cliff and everything.

03:29:57.780 --> 03:30:00.360
Are they hybrids?

03:30:00.420 --> 03:30:03.180
Winter asked, tilting his head at a leaf

03:30:03.180 --> 03:30:04.680
wing who was burying her snout in the

03:30:04.680 --> 03:30:04.860
stream.

03:30:04.920 --> 03:30:06.899
We have a lot of those here.

03:30:06.959 --> 03:30:09.120
Suing rain wing maybe?

03:30:09.180 --> 03:30:10.799
But there's so many.

03:30:10.920 --> 03:30:13.979
His eyes widened as a silk wing landed

03:30:13.979 --> 03:30:15.780
stumbling beside tsunami.

03:30:15.840 --> 03:30:19.979
That dragon has 4 wings, he whispered to

03:30:19.979 --> 03:30:20.399
Lynx.

03:30:20.520 --> 03:30:21.420
Wait.

03:30:21.479 --> 03:30:23.579
So does that one, and that one.

03:30:23.639 --> 03:30:26.399
They're from the other continent.

03:30:26.459 --> 03:30:28.139
Links burst out.

03:30:28.200 --> 03:30:30.360
Flinging excitement in all directions.

03:30:30.420 --> 03:30:32.459
It's real winter.

03:30:32.520 --> 03:30:34.979
It's full of dragons, totally different

03:30:34.979 --> 03:30:35.520
tribes.

03:30:35.579 --> 03:30:38.520
The colorful ones are silk wings, and the

03:30:38.520 --> 03:30:40.860
green ones are leaf wings, and there are

03:30:40.860 --> 03:30:41.760
also two...

03:30:41.760 --> 03:30:43.920
There, see the yellow and black ones.

03:30:43.979 --> 03:30:45.840
Those are hive wings.

03:30:45.899 --> 03:30:49.680
Snowfall had almost never seen her cousin

03:30:49.680 --> 03:30:52.079
look confused, let alone this

03:30:52.079 --> 03:30:53.219
discombobulated.

03:30:53.280 --> 03:30:55.379
It kind of made the whole trip to

03:30:55.379 --> 03:30:56.579
sanctuary worthwhile.

03:30:56.700 --> 03:30:59.100
Something caught her eye in the trees

03:30:59.100 --> 03:30:59.399
again.

03:30:59.459 --> 03:31:02.459
A flash of reflected light in the bushes

03:31:02.459 --> 03:31:04.799
a shimmer of scales behind the leaves.

03:31:04.860 --> 03:31:07.979
But when she turned toward it, there was

03:31:07.979 --> 03:31:10.079
nothing but wind aimlessly stirring the

03:31:10.079 --> 03:31:10.620
forest floor.

03:31:10.680 --> 03:31:13.319
She trusted her instincts though.

03:31:13.440 --> 03:31:16.319
Another ice wing was hidden over there

03:31:16.319 --> 03:31:17.280
watching her.

03:31:17.340 --> 03:31:20.819
And whoever it was, they did not want to

03:31:20.819 --> 03:31:21.239
be seen.

03:31:21.299 --> 03:31:25.799
Chapter 10.

03:31:26.100 --> 03:31:29.819
Are there other ice wings here?

03:31:29.879 --> 03:31:31.559
Snowfall asked Winter.

03:31:31.620 --> 03:31:34.319
A few, he said, with a guarded

03:31:34.319 --> 03:31:34.920
expression.

03:31:34.979 --> 03:31:36.360
Didn't you know that?

03:31:36.420 --> 03:31:39.120
She looked down her snout at him.

03:31:39.180 --> 03:31:41.340
Of course, I know that.

03:31:41.399 --> 03:31:44.340
I merely wish to know how many, and who

03:31:44.340 --> 03:31:44.819
exactly.

03:31:44.879 --> 03:31:48.899
I think I shouldn't be the one to tell

03:31:48.899 --> 03:31:49.260
you that.

03:31:49.379 --> 03:31:51.360
Your Majesty, he said.

03:31:51.420 --> 03:31:53.399
I don't know their reasons for being

03:31:53.399 --> 03:31:53.639
here.

03:31:53.760 --> 03:31:56.340
But I'm sure they'll tell you, if you

03:31:56.340 --> 03:31:57.000
want to ask them.

03:31:57.059 --> 03:32:00.180
Snowfall considered finding this

03:32:00.180 --> 03:32:01.799
irritating enough to yell at him.

03:32:01.860 --> 03:32:04.079
She could do that now that she was the

03:32:04.079 --> 03:32:06.299
queen, and he wouldn't be able to argue

03:32:06.299 --> 03:32:08.340
back at her or run away the way he

03:32:08.340 --> 03:32:09.239
sometimes did when they were

03:32:09.239 --> 03:32:10.020
dragonettes.

03:32:10.079 --> 03:32:13.020
She missed her chance, though, because

03:32:13.020 --> 03:32:15.239
while she was thinking, that awful night

03:32:15.239 --> 03:32:17.520
wing landed and sucked up all the air

03:32:17.520 --> 03:32:18.479
around Winter's head.

03:32:18.600 --> 03:32:23.040
Moon, he said, in a quiet, wondering

03:32:23.040 --> 03:32:23.520
voice.

03:32:23.639 --> 03:32:27.239
Hey, Winter, Moon said nervously.

03:32:27.299 --> 03:32:29.700
She batted one of her wings at him

03:32:29.700 --> 03:32:31.020
without actually touching him.

03:32:31.079 --> 03:32:33.659
We really miss you at Jade Mountain.

03:32:33.719 --> 03:32:36.540
I miss you too, he said.

03:32:36.600 --> 03:32:37.799
All of you.

03:32:37.860 --> 03:32:39.420
I mean, everything, I miss.

03:32:39.659 --> 03:32:40.920
I miss everyone.

03:32:40.979 --> 03:32:43.739
So why aren't you still there?

03:32:43.799 --> 03:32:44.940
Links asked.

03:32:45.000 --> 03:32:48.000
For some reason, they all looked at

03:32:48.000 --> 03:32:48.420
snowfall.

03:32:48.479 --> 03:32:51.059
She waited a beat to see if that was a

03:32:51.059 --> 03:32:53.219
mistake, and then when everyone kept

03:32:53.219 --> 03:32:55.860
looking at her, she said, what?

03:32:55.920 --> 03:32:58.739
You're the one who said he couldn't go

03:32:58.739 --> 03:33:00.899
back to the academy, Moon offered.

03:33:00.959 --> 03:33:02.159
I did?

03:33:02.219 --> 03:33:04.739
Snowfall considered this news for a

03:33:04.739 --> 03:33:04.979
moment.

03:33:05.040 --> 03:33:07.860
She couldn't remember making a royal

03:33:07.860 --> 03:33:10.079
decree like that, or even thinking about

03:33:10.079 --> 03:33:10.620
it at all.

03:33:10.680 --> 03:33:14.399
She knew 2 new ice wing dragonettes had

03:33:14.399 --> 03:33:16.620
been chosen to go to the academy, and now

03:33:16.620 --> 03:33:18.600
that she thought about it, Those were

03:33:18.600 --> 03:33:20.819
probably replacing icicle and winter.

03:33:20.879 --> 03:33:23.399
But she had no recollection of anyone

03:33:23.399 --> 03:33:25.319
asking her whether Winter could keep

03:33:25.319 --> 03:33:26.760
being a student there or not.

03:33:26.819 --> 03:33:29.459
She had decided he was still banished

03:33:29.459 --> 03:33:31.440
from the ice kingdom, but she didn't

03:33:31.440 --> 03:33:33.420
particularly care what he did outside the

03:33:33.420 --> 03:33:34.260
ice kingdom.

03:33:34.319 --> 03:33:36.719
I don't actually care.

03:33:36.780 --> 03:33:38.579
She informed Winter.

03:33:38.639 --> 03:33:41.159
You can go ahead and study hugs and

03:33:41.159 --> 03:33:42.899
whatever nonsense happens at that school

03:33:42.899 --> 03:33:43.500
if you want to.

03:33:43.559 --> 03:33:46.079
I have much more important things to deal

03:33:46.079 --> 03:33:48.600
with, like these homeless dragons and all

03:33:48.600 --> 03:33:49.559
the ones they left behind.

03:33:49.680 --> 03:33:52.260
She waved her wings of the tribes that

03:33:52.260 --> 03:33:53.459
were still landing around them.

03:33:53.520 --> 03:33:55.920
The meadow was starting to get a bit

03:33:55.920 --> 03:33:56.399
crowded.

03:33:56.459 --> 03:33:59.159
Riptide was starting to look slightly

03:33:59.159 --> 03:34:00.000
panic stricken.

03:34:00.059 --> 03:34:02.520
The ones they left behind?

03:34:02.520 --> 03:34:05.579
Links echoed, giving her almost the exact

03:34:05.579 --> 03:34:07.739
same puzzled look Hazel had given her

03:34:07.739 --> 03:34:08.340
earlier.

03:34:08.700 --> 03:34:12.899
As if it was so weird for snowfall to

03:34:12.899 --> 03:34:15.000
feel even a hint of concern for all the

03:34:15.000 --> 03:34:17.579
silk wings, still trapped with a creepy

03:34:17.579 --> 03:34:18.479
evil thing over there.

03:34:18.540 --> 03:34:21.659
I'm not saying they should come here.

03:34:21.719 --> 03:34:23.819
Snowfall snapped at her.

03:34:23.940 --> 03:34:26.579
But I don't expect these dragons to just

03:34:26.579 --> 03:34:27.899
give up on them.

03:34:27.959 --> 03:34:30.479
One of the leaf wings by the stream

03:34:30.479 --> 03:34:33.239
looked up, and gave her a fierce, intense

03:34:33.239 --> 03:34:33.719
stare.

03:34:33.780 --> 03:34:36.479
Snowfall recognized her from the day

03:34:36.479 --> 03:34:36.780
before.

03:34:36.899 --> 03:34:39.719
She was the one who might be a threat to

03:34:39.719 --> 03:34:40.680
Hazel's crown.

03:34:40.739 --> 03:34:42.360
Sun something.

03:34:42.420 --> 03:34:45.059
The one who was always frowning and

03:34:45.059 --> 03:34:46.979
glaring and looking ready for a fight.

03:34:47.100 --> 03:34:48.719
What?

03:34:48.840 --> 03:34:50.100
Snowfall demanded.

03:34:50.159 --> 03:34:54.059
We are not giving up on them, the leaf

03:34:54.059 --> 03:34:55.139
wing said with a hiss.

03:34:55.200 --> 03:34:57.000
We won't abandon them.

03:34:57.120 --> 03:35:00.059
The leaf wing beside her brushed her wing

03:35:00.059 --> 03:35:00.540
gently.

03:35:00.600 --> 03:35:03.600
No one is saying we will, she said.

03:35:03.659 --> 03:35:07.319
This pile of icicles just did, snapped

03:35:07.319 --> 03:35:08.280
the 1st leaf wing.

03:35:08.399 --> 03:35:09.780
No, love.

03:35:09.840 --> 03:35:11.520
The 2nd one said calmly.

03:35:11.639 --> 03:35:14.340
Actually, if you were listening, Queen

03:35:14.340 --> 03:35:16.079
Snowfall is saying exactly what you've

03:35:16.079 --> 03:35:18.659
been saying for the last 3 days, that we

03:35:18.659 --> 03:35:20.340
need to make a plan to go back and save

03:35:20.340 --> 03:35:20.760
everyone.

03:35:20.819 --> 03:35:23.639
Yes, exactly.

03:35:23.700 --> 03:35:25.200
That is what I meant.

03:35:25.260 --> 03:35:26.579
Snowfall thought.

03:35:26.639 --> 03:35:28.920
Not because I care about any of those

03:35:28.920 --> 03:35:29.819
dragons over there.

03:35:29.879 --> 03:35:32.520
Just because I want all of these ones to

03:35:32.520 --> 03:35:33.659
be able to go away again.

03:35:33.719 --> 03:35:35.940
I'm Willow.

03:35:36.000 --> 03:35:38.159
The 2nd Leaf Wing said to Winter.

03:35:38.219 --> 03:35:39.840
And this is Sundew.

03:35:39.959 --> 03:35:42.059
We're very worried about the dragons who

03:35:42.059 --> 03:35:43.620
are still stuck back on Pentala.

03:35:43.680 --> 03:35:47.399
We should go back now, right away, Sundu

03:35:47.399 --> 03:35:47.639
said.

03:35:47.700 --> 03:35:50.040
Even if it's just you and me and Cricket

03:35:50.040 --> 03:35:52.440
we should take them by surprise before

03:35:52.440 --> 03:35:54.059
the breath of evil gets any stronger.

03:35:54.120 --> 03:35:56.100
Moon shuddered.

03:35:56.159 --> 03:35:57.780
And Winter turned to her quickly.

03:35:57.840 --> 03:36:02.219
No, not a vision, she said, before he

03:36:02.219 --> 03:36:02.520
could ask.

03:36:02.579 --> 03:36:06.360
Just those words, breath of evil.

03:36:06.420 --> 03:36:08.399
They scare me every time.

03:36:08.520 --> 03:36:10.739
Imagine how you'd feel.

03:36:10.860 --> 03:36:12.479
If you were stuck on the same continent

03:36:12.479 --> 03:36:14.219
with it, Snowfall said.

03:36:14.340 --> 03:36:16.739
And then half of them gave her the weird

03:36:16.739 --> 03:36:18.180
look, again.

03:36:18.299 --> 03:36:21.120
Maybe the ring was also turning her

03:36:21.120 --> 03:36:22.799
horn's bright pink or something?

03:36:22.860 --> 03:36:25.739
Otherwise, it made no sense that everyone

03:36:25.739 --> 03:36:27.840
kept reacting as though she'd vomited

03:36:27.840 --> 03:36:29.639
miniature caribou each time she spoke.

03:36:29.760 --> 03:36:33.540
Fortunately, tsunami and ribtide and

03:36:33.540 --> 03:36:35.520
Hazel arrived to create a distraction.

03:36:35.639 --> 03:36:39.780
Riptide has plenty of room here, Tsunami

03:36:39.780 --> 03:36:40.799
announced briskly.

03:36:40.860 --> 03:36:42.299
Everyone can stay.

03:36:42.360 --> 03:36:44.520
That's not what I said.

03:36:44.579 --> 03:36:46.379
Riptide objected.

03:36:46.440 --> 03:36:48.899
I said, I don't know where we can

03:36:48.899 --> 03:36:50.760
possibly put them all, but they can stay

03:36:50.760 --> 03:36:52.200
for a few nights while we figure this

03:36:52.200 --> 03:36:52.379
out.

03:36:52.440 --> 03:36:54.299
Ha!

03:36:54.360 --> 03:36:56.819
Snowfall flicked her tail at tsunami.

03:36:56.879 --> 03:37:00.180
C, even your precious friend and his

03:37:00.180 --> 03:37:01.920
heartwarming togetherness project.

03:37:01.979 --> 03:37:04.079
Don't want all these sad snouts.

03:37:04.139 --> 03:37:05.819
I'm not the bad guy.

03:37:05.879 --> 03:37:07.979
My reaction is the normal one.

03:37:08.040 --> 03:37:10.860
No offense, she added to Hazel.

03:37:10.920 --> 03:37:14.100
Tsunami shot a glare at riptide, and he

03:37:14.100 --> 03:37:15.059
backpedaled quickly.

03:37:15.120 --> 03:37:17.879
Of course, I want them, he said.

03:37:17.940 --> 03:37:19.559
We can make this work.

03:37:19.620 --> 03:37:22.440
I mean, this more than quadruples the

03:37:22.440 --> 03:37:25.020
number of dragons living here, but, but

03:37:25.020 --> 03:37:28.559
um, I just have to, and maybe if we...

03:37:29.100 --> 03:37:29.579
But then the.

03:37:30.659 --> 03:37:32.280
I mean, yes, yes, of course, they can

03:37:32.280 --> 03:37:32.459
stay.

03:37:32.520 --> 03:37:35.579
Great, tsunami said.

03:37:35.639 --> 03:37:36.840
Now beaming at him.

03:37:36.899 --> 03:37:38.879
I knew we could count on you.

03:37:38.940 --> 03:37:42.299
We can help, Hazel promised.

03:37:42.360 --> 03:37:45.239
Leave wings prefer to build our homes in

03:37:45.239 --> 03:37:48.239
the trees anyway, so we won't take up any

03:37:48.239 --> 03:37:51.239
extra ground space, and the silk wings

03:37:51.239 --> 03:37:52.379
can make their own webs.

03:37:52.440 --> 03:37:55.260
Maybe their silk could be useful.

03:37:55.319 --> 03:37:58.079
Snowfall could tell that Hazel was trying

03:37:58.079 --> 03:38:01.020
really hard, not to glance pointedly at

03:38:01.020 --> 03:38:03.059
some of the more ram shackle buildings

03:38:03.059 --> 03:38:03.299
around them.

03:38:03.360 --> 03:38:06.180
Besides, we're not staying long.

03:38:06.239 --> 03:38:07.860
Sundew cut in.

03:38:07.920 --> 03:38:10.920
We're going back to Pentala, just as soon

03:38:10.920 --> 03:38:12.479
as we figure out how to defeat the breath

03:38:12.479 --> 03:38:13.020
of evil.

03:38:13.079 --> 03:38:17.219
Hazel and Willow exchanged a glance that

03:38:17.219 --> 03:38:19.559
made even snowfall feel all bristly.

03:38:19.620 --> 03:38:22.020
She wasn't surprised when sundew let out

03:38:22.020 --> 03:38:24.120
a hiss and stalked off toward the lake.

03:38:24.180 --> 03:38:27.780
Clean snowfall, Hazel said.

03:38:27.840 --> 03:38:30.420
Would you be able to stay with us a few

03:38:30.420 --> 03:38:30.840
more days?

03:38:30.899 --> 03:38:32.520
Me?

03:38:32.579 --> 03:38:35.459
Snowfall said, fluffing out her wings.

03:38:35.520 --> 03:38:37.739
Here, why?

03:38:37.799 --> 03:38:40.620
So we can summon the other queens, of

03:38:40.620 --> 03:38:44.100
course. tsunami said, for a big old queen

03:38:44.100 --> 03:38:44.700
summit.

03:38:44.760 --> 03:38:46.559
Not because we want you around.

03:38:46.620 --> 03:38:47.520
Don't worry.

03:38:47.579 --> 03:38:51.659
Don't be rude to my queen, Link said

03:38:51.659 --> 03:38:52.260
sharply.

03:38:52.319 --> 03:38:55.680
I'd really appreciate it, Your Majesty

03:38:55.680 --> 03:38:58.440
Hazel interjected, her eyes wide.

03:38:58.500 --> 03:39:00.659
You're the only one I know.

03:39:00.719 --> 03:39:03.479
I'd feel so much better if I had a friend

03:39:03.479 --> 03:39:04.620
among the queens.

03:39:04.680 --> 03:39:07.559
Three moon, Snowfall.

03:39:07.620 --> 03:39:09.959
Tell me you are not melting into a puddle

03:39:09.959 --> 03:39:12.840
just because this strange green dragon

03:39:12.840 --> 03:39:13.559
called you a friend.

03:39:13.620 --> 03:39:16.319
She doesn't know you at all. and vice

03:39:16.319 --> 03:39:16.739
versa.

03:39:16.799 --> 03:39:19.500
Why would I even want a friend from

03:39:19.500 --> 03:39:20.100
another tribe?

03:39:20.159 --> 03:39:22.799
What good can she possibly do for the ice

03:39:22.799 --> 03:39:23.340
wings?

03:39:23.459 --> 03:39:25.680
It's not like an alliance with her would

03:39:25.680 --> 03:39:26.340
make us stronger.

03:39:26.399 --> 03:39:30.000
But there are other perfectly logical

03:39:30.000 --> 03:39:31.559
queenly reasons to stay.

03:39:31.680 --> 03:39:34.620
I mean, I don't want all the other queens

03:39:34.620 --> 03:39:35.399
meeting without me.

03:39:35.459 --> 03:39:37.979
Who knows what they would say about me if

03:39:37.979 --> 03:39:38.579
I wasn't here.

03:39:38.639 --> 03:39:42.420
They might plot and scheme, and make smug

03:39:42.420 --> 03:39:42.959
faces.

03:39:43.020 --> 03:39:45.540
Staying is the right thing to do for the

03:39:45.540 --> 03:39:46.440
ice wing tribe.

03:39:46.500 --> 03:39:48.360
I need to know what everyone is up to

03:39:48.360 --> 03:39:48.719
anyway.

03:39:48.780 --> 03:39:53.579
Very well, Snowfall said, trying to sound

03:39:53.579 --> 03:39:54.299
bored.

03:39:54.360 --> 03:39:56.819
We can stay until the other queens arrive

03:39:56.819 --> 03:39:58.739
but tell them to make it snappy.

03:39:58.799 --> 03:40:01.200
I can't be gone from my palace for too

03:40:01.200 --> 03:40:01.440
long.

03:40:01.500 --> 03:40:05.280
Let's go choose the messengers, Riptide

03:40:05.280 --> 03:40:07.500
said to tsunami, tugging her away before

03:40:07.500 --> 03:40:09.719
she could say whatever snarky thing was

03:40:09.719 --> 03:40:11.100
building up inside her snout.

03:40:11.159 --> 03:40:12.959
Show me around.

03:40:13.020 --> 03:40:14.579
Leng said to Winter.

03:40:14.639 --> 03:40:16.020
I want to see everything.

03:40:16.079 --> 03:40:18.899
Of course, he said.

03:40:18.959 --> 03:40:20.760
And then after a moment of hesitation

03:40:20.760 --> 03:40:23.219
added, Moon, do you want to come too?

03:40:23.280 --> 03:40:26.340
The Nightwing nodded a little vaguely.

03:40:26.399 --> 03:40:29.219
She had a kind of distracted air about

03:40:29.219 --> 03:40:31.620
her most of the time, as though invisible

03:40:31.620 --> 03:40:33.479
dragons were whispering in her ears while

03:40:33.479 --> 03:40:34.200
everyone was talking.

03:40:34.260 --> 03:40:38.159
Oh, Snowfall realized.

03:40:38.219 --> 03:40:40.680
Because she's listening to our thoughts.

03:40:40.739 --> 03:40:44.340
I know you can hear my thoughts

03:40:44.340 --> 03:40:44.879
Nightwing.

03:40:44.940 --> 03:40:45.899
Here's one for you.

03:40:45.959 --> 03:40:48.600
I think your entire tribe is a bunch of

03:40:48.600 --> 03:40:50.579
malevolent fire snorting toads.

03:40:50.639 --> 03:40:55.020
Moon jumped slightly, gave Snowfall a

03:40:55.020 --> 03:40:57.180
wounded look, and followed winter and

03:40:57.180 --> 03:40:58.319
lynx off into the meadow.

03:40:58.379 --> 03:41:00.899
Hazel and Willow stood around for a

03:41:00.899 --> 03:41:02.819
moment, as though they weren't sure that

03:41:02.819 --> 03:41:04.860
Snowfall was done with them, and then

03:41:04.860 --> 03:41:06.239
finally went off in the same direction

03:41:06.239 --> 03:41:07.440
Sundew had gone.

03:41:07.500 --> 03:41:11.399
Snowfall waded into the stream, which was

03:41:11.399 --> 03:41:13.979
brilliantly cold, like melted snow.

03:41:14.040 --> 03:41:17.340
She stood there, letting her scales cool

03:41:17.340 --> 03:41:20.100
down, as she studied the dragon scattered

03:41:20.100 --> 03:41:20.879
across sanctuary.

03:41:20.940 --> 03:41:23.639
From where she stood, she could see

03:41:23.639 --> 03:41:25.379
dragons from almost every tribe.

03:41:25.440 --> 03:41:29.760
Sand wings, sky wings, sea wings, mud

03:41:29.760 --> 03:41:31.979
wings, even a couple of rain wings.

03:41:32.040 --> 03:41:34.559
Although at 1st glance, she mistook them

03:41:34.559 --> 03:41:35.399
for silk wings.

03:41:35.459 --> 03:41:38.700
But no ice wings, as far as she could

03:41:38.700 --> 03:41:38.879
see.

03:41:38.940 --> 03:41:42.479
She was about to think, well, ha.

03:41:42.540 --> 03:41:45.299
That makes sense because our kingdom is

03:41:45.299 --> 03:41:46.139
so amazing.

03:41:46.200 --> 03:41:47.940
Why would anyone want to leave it?

03:41:48.000 --> 03:41:51.059
But then she had to admit, she didn't see

03:41:51.059 --> 03:41:53.340
any night wings either, which sort of

03:41:53.340 --> 03:41:54.299
undercut her theory.

03:41:54.360 --> 03:41:57.360
And Winter said there were other ice

03:41:57.360 --> 03:41:57.899
wings here.

03:41:58.020 --> 03:41:59.819
So where were they?

03:41:59.879 --> 03:42:02.520
Why hadn't they come out to see the giant

03:42:02.520 --> 03:42:03.780
throng of new visitors?

03:42:03.899 --> 03:42:07.620
The sanctuary dragons seemed curious

03:42:07.620 --> 03:42:09.299
rather than afraid of the strange

03:42:09.299 --> 03:42:09.899
tribes.

03:42:09.959 --> 03:42:12.360
Snowfall wondered if that was because

03:42:12.360 --> 03:42:14.280
some of them were so odd looking

03:42:14.280 --> 03:42:16.500
themselves, or because they were used to

03:42:16.500 --> 03:42:17.940
living with other kinds of dragons

03:42:17.940 --> 03:42:18.299
already.

03:42:18.360 --> 03:42:21.360
She watched the little brown dragon with

03:42:21.360 --> 03:42:23.700
phosphorescent blue scales dart up to a

03:42:23.700 --> 03:42:26.879
silk wing, circle his talons slowly, and

03:42:26.879 --> 03:42:29.639
then sit down to gulp up at his 4 indigo

03:42:29.639 --> 03:42:30.360
and orange wings.

03:42:30.479 --> 03:42:33.840
And then another flicker of white caught

03:42:33.840 --> 03:42:34.319
her gaze.

03:42:34.440 --> 03:42:36.780
Moving through the trees on the other

03:42:36.780 --> 03:42:37.799
side of the meadow.

03:42:37.860 --> 03:42:40.440
That was definitely an ice wing.

03:42:40.500 --> 03:42:43.860
Snowfall bounded out of the water and

03:42:43.860 --> 03:42:46.440
charged across the grass, scattering

03:42:46.440 --> 03:42:47.819
clumsy dragonettes in her wake.

03:42:47.879 --> 03:42:50.040
In the shadows of the trees.

03:42:50.100 --> 03:42:52.680
There was a whirl of white wings as the

03:42:52.680 --> 03:42:53.819
ice wing turned and fled.

03:42:53.940 --> 03:42:56.579
Fled from her.

03:42:56.639 --> 03:42:59.399
Queen Snowfall, the indignity.

03:42:59.459 --> 03:43:02.819
Snowfall doubled her pace as she plunged

03:43:02.819 --> 03:43:03.360
into the trees.

03:43:03.420 --> 03:43:07.020
Pine needles slipped under her talons, and

03:43:07.020 --> 03:43:08.940
the smell of damp leaves filled her

03:43:08.940 --> 03:43:09.239
snout.

03:43:09.360 --> 03:43:12.659
Squirrels shouted angry chirpy things at

03:43:12.659 --> 03:43:14.879
her as she raced past, dodging tree

03:43:14.879 --> 03:43:15.360
trunks.

03:43:15.420 --> 03:43:16.739
Ahead.

03:43:16.799 --> 03:43:18.899
She could see her praise white tail

03:43:18.899 --> 03:43:19.500
flickering.

03:43:19.559 --> 03:43:22.979
The shady forest at twilight wasn't

03:43:22.979 --> 03:43:24.959
exactly the best place for an ice wing to

03:43:24.959 --> 03:43:25.500
hide.

03:43:25.559 --> 03:43:29.399
The best place is the Ice Kingdom

03:43:29.399 --> 03:43:31.079
Snowfall thought irritably.

03:43:31.139 --> 03:43:33.600
Why would any sensible dragon ever leave

03:43:33.600 --> 03:43:33.780
it?

03:43:33.840 --> 03:43:35.520
Because of me.

03:43:35.639 --> 03:43:38.219
Her brain offered with an awful jolt.

03:43:38.280 --> 03:43:40.860
Because they think I'm a terrible queen.

03:43:40.920 --> 03:43:43.139
Just like all the dragons in that night

03:43:43.139 --> 03:43:43.799
wing battle.

03:43:43.860 --> 03:43:46.979
Maybe ice wings are sneaking out of the

03:43:46.979 --> 03:43:49.260
kingdom in droves, because they're afraid

03:43:49.260 --> 03:43:51.840
I'm going to ruin the whole tribe, or do

03:43:51.840 --> 03:43:52.620
something dreadful.

03:43:52.680 --> 03:43:55.200
She shook her head fiercely.

03:43:55.260 --> 03:43:58.260
It was unlikely she'd catch this dragon

03:43:58.260 --> 03:44:00.479
with speed, since she was tired from

03:44:00.479 --> 03:44:01.260
flying all day.

03:44:01.319 --> 03:44:04.559
She could try throwing a spear or a knife

03:44:04.559 --> 03:44:06.959
although that would be kind of a violent

03:44:06.959 --> 03:44:08.280
way to find out who it was.

03:44:08.340 --> 03:44:09.840
But wait.

03:44:09.899 --> 03:44:11.700
She had magic.

03:44:11.760 --> 03:44:15.659
Snowfall skidded to a stop, and banged

03:44:15.659 --> 03:44:17.159
the wristbands of stealth together

03:44:17.159 --> 03:44:19.500
imagining herself invisible.

03:44:19.559 --> 03:44:21.000
And then she was.

03:44:21.059 --> 03:44:23.639
She couldn't even see her own talons.

03:44:23.700 --> 03:44:27.059
The bushes behind her seemed to shiver in

03:44:27.059 --> 03:44:29.520
a non-existent breeze as she flicked them

03:44:29.520 --> 03:44:29.940
with her tail.

03:44:30.059 --> 03:44:33.719
She carried on after the fleeing ice wing

03:44:33.719 --> 03:44:36.719
but now she moved more slowly, trying to

03:44:36.719 --> 03:44:38.459
sneak up on whoever it was.

03:44:38.520 --> 03:44:41.219
It was hard to be quiet in such a noisy

03:44:41.219 --> 03:44:43.920
crackly yippy place, but soon she heard

03:44:43.920 --> 03:44:45.899
someone gasping for air up ahead.

03:44:45.959 --> 03:44:48.600
The ice wing thought snowfall had lost

03:44:48.600 --> 03:44:49.079
its trail.

03:44:49.200 --> 03:44:52.860
It had stopped, panting, next to a giant

03:44:52.860 --> 03:44:54.840
boulder half covered in poison ivy.

03:44:54.959 --> 03:44:59.399
Snowfall crept toward it, one talon, then

03:44:59.399 --> 03:45:02.100
the next, keeping her eyes fixed on the

03:45:02.100 --> 03:45:03.659
shimmering white scales beyond the

03:45:03.659 --> 03:45:05.940
foliage, and then...

03:45:05.940 --> 03:45:07.739
She pounced.

03:45:07.799 --> 03:45:11.579
Debris flew up in all directions as she

03:45:11.579 --> 03:45:13.920
slammed into the ice wing, tumbling

03:45:13.920 --> 03:45:16.739
talons over wings until they both crashed

03:45:16.739 --> 03:45:18.299
into the bare side of the boulder.

03:45:18.360 --> 03:45:20.760
Snowfall were covered first.

03:45:20.819 --> 03:45:24.059
She shook out her wings and leaped to pin

03:45:24.059 --> 03:45:24.899
down the other dragon.

03:45:24.959 --> 03:45:28.500
Her captive shrieked.

03:45:28.620 --> 03:45:30.059
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

03:45:30.120 --> 03:45:33.479
Snowfall blinked down at the pale blue

03:45:33.479 --> 03:45:36.360
eyes, the long, graceful neck, and the

03:45:36.360 --> 03:45:39.120
unmistakable face of her missing sister.

03:45:39.180 --> 03:45:43.500
Part two.

03:45:43.559 --> 03:45:46.739
Sanctuary and scavengers.

03:45:46.799 --> 03:45:49.020
Chapter 11.

03:45:49.319 --> 03:45:51.719
Crystal?

03:45:51.780 --> 03:45:53.159
Snowfall blurted.

03:45:53.219 --> 03:45:56.159
She set up and used the bracelets to turn

03:45:56.159 --> 03:45:57.180
herself visible again.

03:45:57.239 --> 03:46:00.479
Her sister's eyes widened as snowfalls

03:46:00.479 --> 03:46:01.260
shimmered into view.

03:46:01.319 --> 03:46:03.420
Did you follow me here?

03:46:03.479 --> 03:46:05.280
Follow you?

03:46:05.399 --> 03:46:07.319
Crystal said indignantly.

03:46:07.379 --> 03:46:09.780
You're the one who chased me through the

03:46:09.780 --> 03:46:10.139
woods.

03:46:10.200 --> 03:46:14.459
Because you were lurking suspiciously

03:46:14.459 --> 03:46:15.180
Snowfall cried.

03:46:15.239 --> 03:46:17.760
How long have you been watching me?

03:46:17.879 --> 03:46:20.700
I have not been watching you.

03:46:20.819 --> 03:46:22.440
Crystal objected.

03:46:22.500 --> 03:46:24.780
I don't have any desire to watch you.

03:46:24.840 --> 03:46:27.059
I've been staying far away from you.

03:46:27.120 --> 03:46:30.299
You're the one who came to my nice, quiet

03:46:30.299 --> 03:46:30.659
place.

03:46:30.719 --> 03:46:33.059
What are you doing here?

03:46:33.120 --> 03:46:36.059
She pushed ineffectively at Snowfall's

03:46:36.059 --> 03:46:36.479
talons.

03:46:36.600 --> 03:46:39.360
Also, can you please get off already?

03:46:39.479 --> 03:46:40.920
Wait.

03:46:40.979 --> 03:46:44.100
Snowfall said, backing up so Crystal

03:46:44.100 --> 03:46:45.180
could climb to her feet.

03:46:45.239 --> 03:46:47.760
You mean, you've been here?

03:46:47.879 --> 03:46:49.559
In sanctuary?

03:46:49.620 --> 03:46:50.879
This whole time?

03:46:50.940 --> 03:46:54.360
She was having about 80,000 emotions at

03:46:54.360 --> 03:46:57.059
once, and it was very overwhelming.

03:46:57.120 --> 03:46:59.520
Did this mean Crystal hadn't been

03:46:59.520 --> 03:47:01.260
skulking around the ice palace at any

03:47:01.260 --> 03:47:01.500
point?

03:47:01.559 --> 03:47:04.260
But what about her nefarious plot?

03:47:04.379 --> 03:47:06.180
And why would she come here?

03:47:06.239 --> 03:47:08.520
Was snow fall in danger?

03:47:08.579 --> 03:47:10.200
Was this all a trap?

03:47:10.260 --> 03:47:13.920
Admittedly, even she couldn't quite

03:47:13.920 --> 03:47:16.319
imagine how Crystal could have engineered

03:47:16.319 --> 03:47:18.959
an invasion of mystery dragons just to

03:47:18.959 --> 03:47:20.639
get snowfall to visit sanctuary.

03:47:20.700 --> 03:47:24.000
But her pounding heart and shaking claws

03:47:24.000 --> 03:47:26.100
were having some trouble coming up with

03:47:26.100 --> 03:47:27.719
any other explanation for this.

03:47:27.780 --> 03:47:29.219
Crystal.

03:47:29.340 --> 03:47:30.420
Here.

03:47:30.479 --> 03:47:32.219
Lying in wait.

03:47:32.280 --> 03:47:35.459
Crystal glanced around as though she had

03:47:35.459 --> 03:47:36.719
never thought about where she was.

03:47:36.780 --> 03:47:40.319
I mean, I suppose I've been here since

03:47:40.319 --> 03:47:41.879
mother died, more or less.

03:47:41.940 --> 03:47:42.959
She said.

03:47:43.020 --> 03:47:44.879
Doing what?

03:47:44.940 --> 03:47:46.379
Snowfall demanded.

03:47:46.500 --> 03:47:49.739
Plotting, gathering an army, hiring

03:47:49.739 --> 03:47:50.579
assassins?

03:47:50.700 --> 03:47:53.040
Her sister looked faintly amused.

03:47:53.159 --> 03:47:56.399
If I wanted to hire an assassin, I

03:47:56.399 --> 03:47:57.840
wouldn't start in a community of

03:47:57.840 --> 03:47:59.100
scavenger huggers like this.

03:47:59.219 --> 03:48:01.979
I'd go straight to the Scorpion Den.

03:48:02.040 --> 03:48:04.319
So you have thought about it.

03:48:04.379 --> 03:48:06.360
Snowfall said accusingly.

03:48:06.420 --> 03:48:09.360
A sudden crashing in the undergrowth

03:48:09.360 --> 03:48:10.860
warned Snowfall just in time.

03:48:10.979 --> 03:48:14.819
She spun as a dragon threw himself out of

03:48:14.819 --> 03:48:15.840
the trees at her head.

03:48:15.899 --> 03:48:19.379
He flew past, clipping her on the nose

03:48:19.379 --> 03:48:21.659
with his wings and ricocheted off the

03:48:21.659 --> 03:48:21.959
boulder.

03:48:22.020 --> 03:48:25.139
She ducked again as he lunged back toward

03:48:25.139 --> 03:48:27.659
her, but this time, he was able to pivot

03:48:27.659 --> 03:48:28.920
and slam her into a tree.

03:48:28.979 --> 03:48:30.719
I knew it.

03:48:30.840 --> 03:48:33.059
I knew Crystal was planning to kill me.

03:48:33.120 --> 03:48:36.659
Crystal was shouting something, but

03:48:36.659 --> 03:48:38.340
Snowfall couldn't hear the words over the

03:48:38.340 --> 03:48:40.979
grunts and snarls of her opponent as she

03:48:40.979 --> 03:48:41.879
kicked him in the chest.

03:48:41.940 --> 03:48:45.659
He had brown scales, and a flat square

03:48:45.659 --> 03:48:48.840
head, and heavy talons, a mud wing.

03:48:48.899 --> 03:48:51.659
Crystal had formed an alliance with a mud

03:48:51.659 --> 03:48:52.079
wings.

03:48:52.139 --> 03:48:54.540
Did she have Queen Moorhen on her side?

03:48:54.600 --> 03:48:57.959
Snowfall had always found Moorhen the

03:48:57.959 --> 03:49:00.479
least annoying of the other queens, but

03:49:00.479 --> 03:49:02.700
maybe her quiet demeanor was all in act

03:49:02.700 --> 03:49:04.739
while she conspired with Crystal.

03:49:04.860 --> 03:49:08.819
With a hiss of rage, Snowfall summoned

03:49:08.819 --> 03:49:09.659
the strength magic.

03:49:09.780 --> 03:49:13.079
She sank her talons into the mud wing and

03:49:13.079 --> 03:49:14.940
threw him off into the forest.

03:49:15.000 --> 03:49:18.600
He hurtled out of sight, smashing a path

03:49:18.600 --> 03:49:19.379
through the branches.

03:49:19.500 --> 03:49:22.500
A moment later, there was a resounding

03:49:22.500 --> 03:49:23.459
bud in the distance.

03:49:23.520 --> 03:49:27.659
Crystal shrieked and pelted after him, and

03:49:27.659 --> 03:49:29.280
Snowfall chased her into the trees.

03:49:29.399 --> 03:49:33.180
That's what happens, she shouted at her

03:49:33.180 --> 03:49:33.479
sister.

03:49:33.540 --> 03:49:36.000
I'm not as easy to kill as you think.

03:49:36.059 --> 03:49:38.639
Crystal didn't even look back.

03:49:38.700 --> 03:49:41.399
She ran full tilt along the path of

03:49:41.399 --> 03:49:43.680
destruction until she found the mud wing

03:49:43.680 --> 03:49:45.840
lying flat on his back at the other end

03:49:45.840 --> 03:49:47.700
wings flung out to either side.

03:49:47.760 --> 03:49:51.959
Carry on, she cried, crouching beside

03:49:51.959 --> 03:49:52.139
him.

03:49:52.200 --> 03:49:54.360
Gary, are you all right?

03:49:54.420 --> 03:49:56.340
Saving.

03:49:56.340 --> 03:49:57.959
Ew.

03:49:58.020 --> 03:49:59.340
He wheezed.

03:49:59.399 --> 03:50:02.280
Not very well, you great hippo.

03:50:02.340 --> 03:50:03.600
Crystal scolded.

03:50:03.659 --> 03:50:05.639
She wasn't even attacking me.

03:50:05.700 --> 03:50:07.559
But...

03:50:07.559 --> 03:50:09.000
Dangerous.

03:50:09.059 --> 03:50:10.920
He managed to gasp.

03:50:10.979 --> 03:50:13.680
Crystal looked over her shoulder at

03:50:13.680 --> 03:50:16.139
Snowfall, who had paused the edge of the

03:50:16.139 --> 03:50:18.239
glade, puzzled by the tableau.

03:50:18.299 --> 03:50:21.059
Crystal was clutching the mud wings front

03:50:21.059 --> 03:50:22.979
talons in her own, and he had this

03:50:22.979 --> 03:50:26.340
bonkers moony expression on his face as

03:50:26.340 --> 03:50:27.600
he gazed up at her.

03:50:27.899 --> 03:50:30.600
He must have hit his head really hard to

03:50:30.600 --> 03:50:33.059
be making that face, especially a crystal

03:50:33.059 --> 03:50:34.020
of all dragons.

03:50:34.079 --> 03:50:36.659
Are you here to kill me?

03:50:36.719 --> 03:50:38.819
Crystal asked Snowfall.

03:50:38.879 --> 03:50:41.639
No, Snowfall said.

03:50:41.700 --> 03:50:44.280
I mean, not unless you're planning

03:50:44.280 --> 03:50:44.760
something.

03:50:44.819 --> 03:50:45.899
Should I?

03:50:45.959 --> 03:50:47.520
Kill me?

03:50:47.579 --> 03:50:50.219
No, thank you, Crystal said.

03:50:50.340 --> 03:50:53.159
Snowfall, how could I possibly be

03:50:53.159 --> 03:50:54.959
plotting against you or trying to kill

03:50:54.959 --> 03:50:55.139
you?

03:50:55.200 --> 03:50:58.319
We swore an oath to our mother, remember?

03:50:58.440 --> 03:51:01.079
I promised not to try to take the throne

03:51:01.079 --> 03:51:01.440
from you.

03:51:01.500 --> 03:51:05.579
Yes, Snowfall said, but...

03:51:05.579 --> 03:51:07.139
You...

03:51:07.319 --> 03:51:10.440
But still, what if you...

03:51:10.500 --> 03:51:11.700
She trailed off.

03:51:11.760 --> 03:51:14.700
Somehow it had never occurred to her that

03:51:14.700 --> 03:51:16.200
Crystal would take that oath so

03:51:16.200 --> 03:51:16.620
seriously.

03:51:16.739 --> 03:51:20.879
I mean, if you're not plotting something

03:51:20.879 --> 03:51:22.319
why did you disappear?

03:51:22.379 --> 03:51:23.459
She demanded.

03:51:23.579 --> 03:51:28.319
Well, Crystal said, to be honest, I was

03:51:28.319 --> 03:51:30.000
pretty sure you were going to kill me.

03:51:30.059 --> 03:51:32.579
The oath said not to fight for the

03:51:32.579 --> 03:51:33.239
throne.

03:51:33.299 --> 03:51:35.579
It didn't say anything about keeping your

03:51:35.579 --> 03:51:37.500
sisters and possible threats alive.

03:51:37.559 --> 03:51:40.799
Snowfall snorted.

03:51:40.860 --> 03:51:43.739
I'm not the kind of queen who kills all

03:51:43.739 --> 03:51:45.299
her heirs just to feel safe.

03:51:45.360 --> 03:51:47.399
That's pure stupidity.

03:51:47.459 --> 03:51:49.319
I also.

03:51:49.920 --> 03:51:51.959
I had somewhere else I wanted to be.

03:51:52.020 --> 03:51:54.659
Crystal said, looking down at the mud

03:51:54.659 --> 03:51:55.139
wing again.

03:51:55.200 --> 03:51:58.620
Or rather, someone else I wanted to be

03:51:58.620 --> 03:51:58.979
with.

03:51:59.040 --> 03:52:02.219
Snowfall tilted her head at them.

03:52:02.280 --> 03:52:04.860
This still made no sense to her.

03:52:04.920 --> 03:52:07.739
Where else would anyone want to be

03:52:07.739 --> 03:52:08.879
besides the Ice Kingdom?

03:52:08.940 --> 03:52:12.780
Here, in this noisy, fluttery forest full

03:52:12.780 --> 03:52:15.420
of dragons from other tribes?

03:52:15.479 --> 03:52:15.659
Why?

03:52:15.719 --> 03:52:17.879
Snowfall?

03:52:17.940 --> 03:52:19.020
This is Gariol.

03:52:19.139 --> 03:52:20.280
Crystal said.

03:52:20.340 --> 03:52:23.340
We met during the war, when his troop

03:52:23.340 --> 03:52:25.020
joined our army to fight blister.

03:52:25.139 --> 03:52:27.780
Once I was home again, I couldn't stop

03:52:27.780 --> 03:52:28.440
thinking about him.

03:52:28.500 --> 03:52:31.379
Oh, Snowfall said.

03:52:31.440 --> 03:52:33.120
Oh.

03:52:33.239 --> 03:52:36.959
Now Crystal was making the same schmoopy

03:52:36.959 --> 03:52:39.120
face as he had, and she didn't have a

03:52:39.120 --> 03:52:40.500
head injury as an excuse.

03:52:40.559 --> 03:52:43.559
Crystal was in love with this mud wing.

03:52:43.620 --> 03:52:46.559
Of all the absurd brain melt.

03:52:46.620 --> 03:52:50.280
This is the secret length guest she had.

03:52:50.399 --> 03:52:54.540
I think, I think mother knew, actually

03:52:54.540 --> 03:52:57.959
Crystal said, or guessed, at least.

03:52:58.020 --> 03:53:00.600
I think that might be partly why she

03:53:00.600 --> 03:53:01.799
didn't give me the crown.

03:53:01.860 --> 03:53:04.500
Because she was so horrified.

03:53:04.559 --> 03:53:06.299
Snowfall supplied.

03:53:06.360 --> 03:53:09.000
Crystal whipped her head up and frowned

03:53:09.000 --> 03:53:09.360
at her.

03:53:09.420 --> 03:53:12.840
No, because she knew it would tear me

03:53:12.840 --> 03:53:15.360
apart if I had to choose between the ice

03:53:15.360 --> 03:53:17.700
wing throne and the dragon I love.

03:53:17.760 --> 03:53:20.280
He could never come to the ice palace.

03:53:20.340 --> 03:53:23.399
If I were queen, there'd be no future for

03:53:23.399 --> 03:53:23.579
us.

03:53:23.700 --> 03:53:27.479
This was the silliest thing Snowfall had

03:53:27.479 --> 03:53:27.840
ever heard.

03:53:27.899 --> 03:53:31.860
Choosing a romance over being queen of an

03:53:31.860 --> 03:53:32.639
entire kingdom?

03:53:32.700 --> 03:53:35.520
A romance with a mud wing?

03:53:35.579 --> 03:53:36.239
No less.

03:53:36.299 --> 03:53:39.180
For the 1st time since the Battle with

03:53:39.180 --> 03:53:39.959
the Night Wings.

03:53:40.020 --> 03:53:43.739
Snowfall felt a brief, shining moment of

03:53:43.739 --> 03:53:44.700
you know what?

03:53:44.819 --> 03:53:47.760
My mother did pick the right dragon to be

03:53:47.760 --> 03:53:48.000
queen.

03:53:48.059 --> 03:53:50.040
All that worrying.

03:53:50.100 --> 03:53:53.219
The endless nightmares and stress, and

03:53:53.219 --> 03:53:55.920
peering around corners, thinking crystal

03:53:55.920 --> 03:53:57.360
was lurking in every shadow with

03:53:57.360 --> 03:54:00.059
murderous intent, and the whole time

03:54:00.059 --> 03:54:02.940
crystal was here, throwing away her

03:54:02.940 --> 03:54:05.040
kingdom, and being a total sap about

03:54:05.040 --> 03:54:08.040
someone who was, frankly, a very ordinary

03:54:08.040 --> 03:54:09.180
looking brown dragon.

03:54:09.239 --> 03:54:14.579
Well, Snowfall said, sitting down, folding

03:54:14.579 --> 03:54:16.559
her wings neatly and letting out a yawn.

03:54:16.620 --> 03:54:19.680
You could have told me instead of

03:54:19.680 --> 03:54:21.659
sneaking off and giving me a month long

03:54:21.659 --> 03:54:22.559
panic attack.

03:54:22.620 --> 03:54:24.299
Could I have told you?

03:54:24.360 --> 03:54:26.280
Crystal said skeptically.

03:54:26.340 --> 03:54:28.260
Wouldn't you have made that exact

03:54:28.260 --> 03:54:30.959
disgusted face and tried to forbid me

03:54:30.959 --> 03:54:31.319
from leaving?

03:54:31.440 --> 03:54:34.799
Snowfall made an effort to rearrange her

03:54:34.799 --> 03:54:36.840
expression, but she could tell it wasn't

03:54:36.840 --> 03:54:37.079
working.

03:54:37.139 --> 03:54:39.659
Probably, she agreed.

03:54:39.719 --> 03:54:42.420
Because what are you thinking?

03:54:42.479 --> 03:54:44.159
A mudwing?

03:54:44.280 --> 03:54:46.020
I'm right.

03:54:46.139 --> 03:54:47.760
Here.

03:54:47.819 --> 03:54:49.739
Gary All said weakly.

03:54:49.799 --> 03:54:52.079
You don't know anything about love.

03:54:52.139 --> 03:54:55.020
Crystal said haughtily, flicking her tail

03:54:55.020 --> 03:54:55.680
at snowfall.

03:54:55.739 --> 03:54:58.020
Or mud wings, for that matter.

03:54:58.079 --> 03:55:01.799
Yeah, and I'm way better off that way

03:55:01.799 --> 03:55:03.479
Snowfall pointed out.

03:55:03.540 --> 03:55:05.879
She got up and turned back toward the

03:55:05.879 --> 03:55:06.840
center of sanctuary.

03:55:06.899 --> 03:55:08.579
Very well then.

03:55:08.639 --> 03:55:10.260
If you're really not planning to

03:55:10.260 --> 03:55:12.180
assassinate me, I'm going to bed.

03:55:12.239 --> 03:55:14.879
Nice to meet you.

03:55:14.940 --> 03:55:17.280
Gary old wheezed as she left.

03:55:17.340 --> 03:55:20.520
Snowfall's wings ached from flying all

03:55:20.520 --> 03:55:22.799
day, but she felt lighter than she could

03:55:22.799 --> 03:55:24.059
remember feeling in forever.

03:55:24.120 --> 03:55:26.579
As though her scales were made of

03:55:26.579 --> 03:55:27.239
moonlight.

03:55:27.299 --> 03:55:29.520
Shining to the dark clouds that had been

03:55:29.520 --> 03:55:29.940
around her.

03:55:30.000 --> 03:55:33.180
Mother knew I'd be a better choice than

03:55:33.180 --> 03:55:33.659
Crystal.

03:55:33.719 --> 03:55:36.059
Because I care about the kingdom more

03:55:36.059 --> 03:55:36.540
than anything.

03:55:36.600 --> 03:55:40.200
She glanced up at the 2 moons that were

03:55:40.200 --> 03:55:42.540
already visible in the twilight sky, and

03:55:42.540 --> 03:55:44.219
her talons stumbled over a fallen

03:55:44.219 --> 03:55:44.639
branch.

03:55:44.700 --> 03:55:49.920
Or, She knew Crystal's secret, so she was

03:55:49.920 --> 03:55:50.819
forced to choose me.

03:55:50.879 --> 03:55:53.760
Maybe she would have picked her, but she

03:55:53.760 --> 03:55:55.739
was stuck with me instead because she

03:55:55.739 --> 03:55:56.819
knew Crystal might leave.

03:55:56.879 --> 03:55:59.459
Snowfall sighed.

03:55:59.520 --> 03:56:02.100
That shining moment hadn't lasted very

03:56:02.100 --> 03:56:02.280
long.

03:56:02.340 --> 03:56:05.280
She found her way back to the sanctuary

03:56:05.280 --> 03:56:07.739
lake, and waded in to wash off all the

03:56:07.739 --> 03:56:09.719
dirt of the forest, and clean the

03:56:09.719 --> 03:56:11.280
scratches that Mudwing had given her.

03:56:11.340 --> 03:56:14.340
Her guards looked surprisingly pleased to

03:56:14.340 --> 03:56:16.920
see her, although she guessed that was

03:56:16.920 --> 03:56:18.000
because they'd have a hard time

03:56:18.000 --> 03:56:20.100
explaining how they'd lost the queen to

03:56:20.100 --> 03:56:21.059
everyone back home.

03:56:21.180 --> 03:56:23.280
They followed her to a spot on the lake

03:56:23.280 --> 03:56:25.559
shore, a fair distance away from all the

03:56:25.559 --> 03:56:28.020
other dragons, and formed a perimeter

03:56:28.020 --> 03:56:29.639
around her while she tried to scratch

03:56:29.639 --> 03:56:31.920
together enough moss for a comfortable

03:56:31.920 --> 03:56:32.760
sleeping spot.

03:56:32.819 --> 03:56:35.520
Snowfall wondered where Lynx was.

03:56:35.579 --> 03:56:38.280
Having a jolly, marvelous time with

03:56:38.280 --> 03:56:41.520
winter and moon, no doubt, romping around

03:56:41.520 --> 03:56:43.500
sanctuary, telling stories about

03:56:43.500 --> 03:56:45.180
everything Snowfall had already done

03:56:45.180 --> 03:56:47.280
wrong as queen, laughing at her.

03:56:47.340 --> 03:56:50.159
Can you believe she was dumb enough to

03:56:50.159 --> 03:56:52.139
get an animus touched ring stuck on her

03:56:52.139 --> 03:56:52.440
claw?

03:56:52.559 --> 03:56:54.120
That sort of thing.

03:56:54.239 --> 03:56:57.899
She tried once more to pull it off, and

03:56:57.899 --> 03:57:00.479
when that didn't work, of course, she lay

03:57:00.479 --> 03:57:02.399
down and stared gloomily at the ring in

03:57:02.399 --> 03:57:03.000
the darkness.

03:57:03.059 --> 03:57:05.159
It had nothing to say for itself.

03:57:05.219 --> 03:57:07.979
Not even a smug twinkle tonight.

03:57:08.100 --> 03:57:12.180
Remember what I told you, she thought

03:57:12.180 --> 03:57:12.959
added fiercely.

03:57:13.020 --> 03:57:15.540
I demand a specific vision.

03:57:15.600 --> 03:57:18.299
I want to know what happened to animus

03:57:18.299 --> 03:57:18.780
magic.

03:57:18.840 --> 03:57:21.180
If you must haunt my dreams tonight.

03:57:21.239 --> 03:57:23.700
That is the vision I choose to summon.

03:57:23.760 --> 03:57:27.479
I am your queen, and that is my command.

03:57:27.540 --> 03:57:29.100
You hear me?

03:57:29.159 --> 03:57:32.219
Impudent silence from the ring.

03:57:32.280 --> 03:57:36.780
Snowfall sighed, closed her eyes, and

03:57:36.780 --> 03:57:38.520
drifted uneasily towards sleep.

03:57:38.579 --> 03:57:42.840
Chapter 12.

03:57:43.200 --> 03:57:46.559
Her wings are green and they miss the

03:57:46.559 --> 03:57:46.799
sun.

03:57:46.920 --> 03:57:49.799
Her claws hurt from walking on stone

03:57:49.799 --> 03:57:51.360
instead of dirt for days.

03:57:51.420 --> 03:57:53.520
She is hungry.

03:57:53.579 --> 03:57:55.500
There is not enough food for all the

03:57:55.500 --> 03:57:56.760
dragons they are hiding.

03:57:56.819 --> 03:57:58.799
But every time someone goes out to get

03:57:58.799 --> 03:58:01.260
more, they fly back with terrifying

03:58:01.260 --> 03:58:03.659
stories of hive wing swarms hunting the

03:58:03.659 --> 03:58:04.079
savannah.

03:58:04.139 --> 03:58:07.559
For them, the dragons who burned

03:58:07.559 --> 03:58:08.520
bloodworm hive.

03:58:08.639 --> 03:58:10.979
Or for sundew and her allies.

03:58:11.040 --> 03:58:12.719
She's not sure.

03:58:12.780 --> 03:58:16.620
A gray dragon is curled beside her, asleep

03:58:16.620 --> 03:58:18.780
with his head resting on her shoulder, and

03:58:18.780 --> 03:58:20.340
his tail twined around hers.

03:58:20.399 --> 03:58:23.159
He is the sweetest dragon the world has

03:58:23.159 --> 03:58:23.940
ever seen.

03:58:24.059 --> 03:58:26.700
He thinks she's a hero for destroying his

03:58:26.700 --> 03:58:26.940
home.

03:58:27.000 --> 03:58:30.600
He loves her when she's angry, just as

03:58:30.600 --> 03:58:31.920
much as when she's cheerful.

03:58:31.979 --> 03:58:34.799
She has no idea how she fell in love with

03:58:34.799 --> 03:58:37.440
a gentle silk wing, but she will murder

03:58:37.440 --> 03:58:38.459
anyone who hurts him.

03:58:38.520 --> 03:58:42.120
Another leaf wing enters the cave, and

03:58:42.120 --> 03:58:44.040
she motions for him to whisper, so he

03:58:44.040 --> 03:58:45.180
won't wake Grayling.

03:58:45.239 --> 03:58:48.899
Strange happenings above, he says

03:58:48.899 --> 03:58:49.440
quietly.

03:58:49.500 --> 03:58:52.799
Pokeweed just got back, and he says he

03:58:52.799 --> 03:58:54.840
saw silk wings flying with the hive

03:58:54.840 --> 03:58:55.079
wings.

03:58:55.139 --> 03:58:57.000
What's strange about that?

03:58:57.000 --> 03:58:58.200
she asks.

03:58:58.260 --> 03:59:00.420
Silkwings have been working for hive

03:59:00.420 --> 03:59:01.200
wings for so long.

03:59:01.260 --> 03:59:03.780
I'm sure some have been forced to help

03:59:03.780 --> 03:59:04.799
with a hunt, that's all.

03:59:04.920 --> 03:59:08.639
No, Hemlock says with a sigh.

03:59:08.700 --> 03:59:12.719
All flying the same way, in formation.

03:59:12.780 --> 03:59:16.440
Exact wing movements, all in sync.

03:59:16.559 --> 03:59:18.360
He took a deep breath.

03:59:18.420 --> 03:59:21.000
And they had white eyes.

03:59:21.059 --> 03:59:23.340
She blinks at him.

03:59:23.399 --> 03:59:24.659
That's impossible.

03:59:24.719 --> 03:59:28.079
Wasp's power doesn't work on silk wings.

03:59:28.139 --> 03:59:30.659
I guess it does now.

03:59:30.780 --> 03:59:32.700
He rubs his face.

03:59:32.760 --> 03:59:34.860
Where's pokeweed?

03:59:34.920 --> 03:59:35.700
She asks.

03:59:35.760 --> 03:59:37.920
I want to know exactly what he saw.

03:59:37.979 --> 03:59:42.299
You went deeper into the caves, Hemlock

03:59:42.299 --> 03:59:42.719
answers.

03:59:42.780 --> 03:59:45.540
Still trying to catch those monkey

03:59:45.540 --> 03:59:46.500
looking creatures.

03:59:46.620 --> 03:59:49.739
They've seen the underground monkeys

03:59:49.739 --> 03:59:52.139
scurrying out of sight a few times, but

03:59:52.139 --> 03:59:54.120
none of the 3 leaf wings have managed to

03:59:54.120 --> 03:59:54.780
eat one yet.

03:59:54.840 --> 03:59:57.780
They're either faster than they look, or

03:59:57.780 --> 03:59:58.739
surprisingly clever.

03:59:58.860 --> 04:00:03.059
There's something worse, Hemlock says

04:00:03.059 --> 04:00:03.719
reluctantly.

04:00:03.780 --> 04:00:07.979
One of the silk wings said, she saw leaf

04:00:07.979 --> 04:00:08.700
wings up there too.

04:00:08.819 --> 04:00:12.719
She flinches so hard, she knocks Grayling

04:00:12.719 --> 04:00:12.959
awake.

04:00:13.020 --> 04:00:16.260
He sits up, yawning and brushing her

04:00:16.260 --> 04:00:16.860
wings with his.

04:00:16.920 --> 04:00:18.600
He's too thin.

04:00:18.659 --> 04:00:21.000
She wishes she could protect him better

04:00:21.000 --> 04:00:22.440
from the hunger.

04:00:22.500 --> 04:00:24.000
And from this news.

04:00:24.120 --> 04:00:28.680
That can't be right, she says to Hemlock

04:00:28.680 --> 04:00:29.459
with a low hiss.

04:00:29.520 --> 04:00:34.260
We saw all that smoke in the north, he

04:00:34.260 --> 04:00:35.100
says bleakly.

04:00:35.159 --> 04:00:39.120
Maybe Queen Wasp burned the poison jungle

04:00:39.120 --> 04:00:42.299
to punish us for burning bloodworm hive.

04:00:42.360 --> 04:00:45.360
Maybe our tribe lost and now.

04:00:46.139 --> 04:00:49.260
No, they're out there somewhere, Graham

04:00:49.260 --> 04:00:49.739
interrupts.

04:00:49.799 --> 04:00:52.440
He gives her a look with more trust in it

04:00:52.440 --> 04:00:54.299
than she's ever felt about anything.

04:00:54.360 --> 04:00:57.120
The leaf wings have survived terrible

04:00:57.120 --> 04:00:57.780
things before.

04:00:57.840 --> 04:00:58.979
They'll fight back.

04:00:59.100 --> 04:01:00.840
The hive wings won't win.

04:01:00.899 --> 04:01:01.860
They can't.

04:01:01.920 --> 04:01:05.340
She wants to feel that way so badly.

04:01:05.459 --> 04:01:07.739
She doesn't know what will hurt more.

04:01:07.799 --> 04:01:09.600
To believe the worst.

04:01:09.659 --> 04:01:12.059
So if it's true, she can't feel any

04:01:12.059 --> 04:01:12.479
lower.

04:01:12.540 --> 04:01:16.500
Or to hold on to hope, but run the risk

04:01:16.500 --> 04:01:17.219
of being crushed.

04:01:17.280 --> 04:01:21.059
I wish we could do something, she says.

04:01:21.120 --> 04:01:23.100
I wish we knew what was happening.

04:01:23.159 --> 04:01:25.559
I thought Belladonna would have sent us a

04:01:25.559 --> 04:01:26.159
message by now.

04:01:26.219 --> 04:01:29.159
Maybe we should go fight the hive wings

04:01:29.159 --> 04:01:30.719
Grayling suggests.

04:01:30.780 --> 04:01:33.299
With all the silk wings from bloodworm

04:01:33.299 --> 04:01:35.340
hive, there are so many of us down here

04:01:35.340 --> 04:01:36.899
couldn't we fight them?

04:01:36.959 --> 04:01:40.559
Not if Queen Wasp can control silk wings

04:01:40.559 --> 04:01:41.520
and leaf wings now.

04:01:41.639 --> 04:01:44.520
She doesn't add that silk wings are kind

04:01:44.520 --> 04:01:45.479
of useless fighters.

04:01:45.540 --> 04:01:48.659
She takes graylings, front talons as his

04:01:48.659 --> 04:01:49.500
face crumbles.

04:01:49.559 --> 04:01:50.940
Don't worry.

04:01:51.000 --> 04:01:52.979
Wasp is never getting you.

04:01:53.040 --> 04:01:55.680
Never, never, never.

04:01:55.739 --> 04:01:58.139
But what is she going to do?

04:01:58.200 --> 04:02:00.899
They can't hide underground for the rest

04:02:00.899 --> 04:02:01.500
of their lives.

04:02:01.559 --> 04:02:04.200
But if they can't go back to the poison

04:02:04.200 --> 04:02:05.040
jungle either.

04:02:05.159 --> 04:02:08.819
Is there anywhere they can possibly be

04:02:08.819 --> 04:02:09.180
safe?

04:02:09.239 --> 04:02:13.500
When Snowfall awoke, there was another

04:02:13.500 --> 04:02:16.139
dragon line close beside her, one wing

04:02:16.139 --> 04:02:18.479
resting on hers, and she had to stare at

04:02:18.479 --> 04:02:20.639
the dragon's soothing white scales for

04:02:20.639 --> 04:02:23.459
entirely too long before she realized it

04:02:23.459 --> 04:02:24.299
wasn't graming.

04:02:24.360 --> 04:02:26.879
Of course it wasn't graving.

04:02:26.940 --> 04:02:29.159
Gray Lane was stuck on the other side of

04:02:29.159 --> 04:02:29.819
the ocean.

04:02:29.879 --> 04:02:33.659
Grayling was a silk wing, in a cave, under

04:02:33.659 --> 04:02:35.280
a continent snowfall was never going to

04:02:35.280 --> 04:02:38.280
see, which was great news because that

04:02:38.280 --> 04:02:40.260
continent sounded more and more dreadful

04:02:40.260 --> 04:02:41.700
every time she visited it.

04:02:41.760 --> 04:02:45.000
No, the impertinent dragon sleeping next

04:02:45.000 --> 04:02:46.379
to her was lynx.

04:02:46.440 --> 04:02:49.799
Snowfall poked her face until Lynx's eyes

04:02:49.799 --> 04:02:50.520
fluttered open.

04:02:50.639 --> 04:02:54.180
Oh, length grumbled.

04:02:54.239 --> 04:02:55.500
Rude.

04:02:55.559 --> 04:02:58.200
She turned her face away and buried it

04:02:58.200 --> 04:02:58.920
under her other wing.

04:02:59.040 --> 04:03:02.100
What's rude is sleeping on the queen's

04:03:02.100 --> 04:03:04.139
tail, Snowfall barked.

04:03:04.200 --> 04:03:05.100
Get off.

04:03:05.219 --> 04:03:08.700
Links rolled away, still muttering, and

04:03:08.700 --> 04:03:10.260
then suddenly shook herself and sat up.

04:03:10.379 --> 04:03:12.420
What happened last night?

04:03:12.479 --> 04:03:14.100
she asked, blinking.

04:03:14.159 --> 04:03:16.020
Did you have another vision?

04:03:16.079 --> 04:03:17.340
Yes.

04:03:17.399 --> 04:03:20.459
Snowfall admitted reluctantly, even

04:03:20.459 --> 04:03:22.379
though this was exactly why she'd woken

04:03:22.379 --> 04:03:23.579
links in the 1st place.

04:03:23.639 --> 04:03:26.100
I was a stupid leaf wing this time.

04:03:26.159 --> 04:03:28.139
One of the ones here?

04:03:28.200 --> 04:03:29.700
No.

04:03:29.760 --> 04:03:31.500
Snowfall shook her head.

04:03:31.559 --> 04:03:33.299
Her name is Bryany.

04:03:33.360 --> 04:03:35.639
She knows that sundew dragon, though.

04:03:35.760 --> 04:03:38.280
Length slammed her talon down on

04:03:38.280 --> 04:03:39.840
something small and furry that was

04:03:39.840 --> 04:03:41.040
scurrying through the undergrowth.

04:03:41.100 --> 04:03:44.280
Ooh, maybe that means you're supposed to

04:03:44.280 --> 04:03:45.420
tell Sunu about your vision.

04:03:45.540 --> 04:03:50.700
No, I do not need a 1000 more dragons

04:03:50.700 --> 04:03:52.379
having opinions about my magic head

04:03:52.379 --> 04:03:52.860
trips.

04:03:52.920 --> 04:03:55.440
One is far more than enough.

04:03:55.559 --> 04:03:57.840
Snowfall glared at the ring.

04:03:57.959 --> 04:04:00.120
She was starting to feel a little more

04:04:00.120 --> 04:04:02.639
like herself, but the quiet, worried

04:04:02.639 --> 04:04:05.159
Briony personality was still shifting

04:04:05.159 --> 04:04:07.260
under her scales, and it was so

04:04:07.260 --> 04:04:08.219
unsettling.

04:04:08.340 --> 04:04:11.100
You stupid broken thing.

04:04:11.159 --> 04:04:13.799
She hissed balefully at the opal.

04:04:13.920 --> 04:04:16.440
That vision had nothing to do with animus

04:04:16.440 --> 04:04:16.860
magic.

04:04:16.920 --> 04:04:19.799
Shimmer, shimmer, shimmer.

04:04:19.860 --> 04:04:22.319
Theobal winked back serenely.

04:04:22.440 --> 04:04:25.799
Snowfall stood up and flapped her wings

04:04:25.799 --> 04:04:28.079
trying to shake off the lingering strands

04:04:28.079 --> 04:04:30.299
of affection for the adorable gray silk

04:04:30.299 --> 04:04:30.659
wing.

04:04:30.719 --> 04:04:32.760
He was different from the others.

04:04:32.819 --> 04:04:36.719
He was special and beloved, and what was

04:04:36.719 --> 04:04:37.379
happening to her?

04:04:37.440 --> 04:04:40.559
Melting like a snowball in the desert

04:04:40.559 --> 04:04:43.680
over a strange dragon she'd never met, who

04:04:43.680 --> 04:04:46.020
was definitely not her type, even if she

04:04:46.020 --> 04:04:46.260
did?

04:04:46.319 --> 04:04:49.440
Was this how Crystal felt about that

04:04:49.440 --> 04:04:50.100
mudwing?

04:04:50.159 --> 04:04:53.100
Snowball shot another suspicious glance

04:04:53.100 --> 04:04:53.579
at the ring.

04:04:53.639 --> 04:04:56.280
Was it trying to hit her over the head

04:04:56.280 --> 04:04:59.100
with a lesson about sympathy and

04:04:59.100 --> 04:05:00.479
understanding?

04:05:00.540 --> 04:05:02.040
Yuck.

04:05:02.100 --> 04:05:04.979
Am I going to have dreams like this for

04:05:04.979 --> 04:05:05.879
the rest of my life?

04:05:05.940 --> 04:05:08.159
Will I still be me?

04:05:08.159 --> 04:05:10.680
If I spend every night as an entirely

04:05:10.680 --> 04:05:11.520
different dragon?

04:05:11.579 --> 04:05:14.280
I saw a crystal yesterday?

04:05:14.399 --> 04:05:16.260
She informed Length abruptly.

04:05:16.319 --> 04:05:17.760
She lives here now.

04:05:17.819 --> 04:05:21.360
Lanx's eyes widened, and she put down her

04:05:21.360 --> 04:05:22.319
half eaten prey.

04:05:22.440 --> 04:05:23.940
No way.

04:05:24.000 --> 04:05:26.280
She was here the entire time?

04:05:26.340 --> 04:05:27.719
She grinned.

04:05:27.780 --> 04:05:30.479
There was a tuft of mouth for a caught in

04:05:30.479 --> 04:05:30.840
her teeth.

04:05:30.899 --> 04:05:32.760
So wait.

04:05:32.819 --> 04:05:36.299
Doesn't that mean she was not plotting

04:05:36.299 --> 04:05:36.959
against you after all?

04:05:37.079 --> 04:05:40.559
She ran away to be with a mudwing

04:05:40.559 --> 04:05:42.360
Snowfall said with a snort.

04:05:42.420 --> 04:05:45.360
Hmm, Lang said.

04:05:45.420 --> 04:05:47.459
Sounds like maybe you were being

04:05:47.459 --> 04:05:49.559
extremely paranoid and anxious about

04:05:49.559 --> 04:05:50.219
nothing then?

04:05:50.280 --> 04:05:53.520
And just possibly, that might apply to

04:05:53.520 --> 04:05:55.799
other things you are extremely paranoid

04:05:55.799 --> 04:05:56.040
about?

04:05:56.100 --> 04:05:59.940
You are the most aggravating dragon in

04:05:59.940 --> 04:06:00.299
the world.

04:06:00.420 --> 04:06:02.280
Snowball observed.

04:06:02.399 --> 04:06:05.040
She had a sense that normally she would

04:06:05.040 --> 04:06:07.200
be furious with links, and that she

04:06:07.200 --> 04:06:09.420
should be yelling, and perhaps throwing

04:06:09.420 --> 04:06:11.219
her in the lake, but it was hard to get

04:06:11.219 --> 04:06:13.500
worked up about a little insubordination

04:06:13.500 --> 04:06:16.620
when Briony was stuck underground, and

04:06:16.620 --> 04:06:18.299
Grayling was in danger of being mind

04:06:18.299 --> 04:06:21.120
controlled, and she had no idea if Tao

04:06:21.120 --> 04:06:23.520
had escaped Jewel Hive, or whether any of

04:06:23.520 --> 04:06:24.780
them would ever find one another.

04:06:24.840 --> 04:06:28.739
Lynx studied her for a moment, with a

04:06:28.739 --> 04:06:30.959
crease of worry along her forehead, and

04:06:30.959 --> 04:06:32.520
then she shook herself vigorously.

04:06:32.579 --> 04:06:35.579
Come see what our lunatic friend Winter

04:06:35.579 --> 04:06:35.819
has done.

04:06:35.879 --> 04:06:39.719
Friend seemed like a bit of a stretch. in

04:06:39.719 --> 04:06:41.760
Snowfall's opinion, but she was

04:06:41.760 --> 04:06:43.200
definitely up for a distraction.

04:06:43.319 --> 04:06:45.299
So she followed links along the lake

04:06:45.299 --> 04:06:47.159
shore, back through sanctuary.

04:06:47.219 --> 04:06:50.340
Not far from the water's edge in an area

04:06:50.340 --> 04:06:51.600
that had been cleared of trees.

04:06:51.659 --> 04:06:54.299
There was an odd space surrounded by a

04:06:54.299 --> 04:06:54.959
tall fence.

04:06:55.020 --> 04:06:58.139
The fence was made of entire tree trunks

04:06:58.139 --> 04:07:01.319
lashed together, so it was very high, and

04:07:01.319 --> 04:07:03.000
snowfall had to crane her neck to see

04:07:03.000 --> 04:07:03.299
over it.

04:07:03.420 --> 04:07:07.200
Inside, there was a dragon made pool of

04:07:07.200 --> 04:07:09.719
water, a pile of leaves and pine needles

04:07:09.719 --> 04:07:12.239
with a small leaf canopy over it, and

04:07:12.239 --> 04:07:13.620
something that darted around so

04:07:13.620 --> 04:07:15.780
energetically, it took snowfall a moment

04:07:15.780 --> 04:07:16.799
to figure out what it was.

04:07:16.860 --> 04:07:21.600
Great eye spirits, she said to Lynx.

04:07:21.659 --> 04:07:23.819
I thought he was over his scavenger

04:07:23.819 --> 04:07:24.299
obsession.

04:07:24.360 --> 04:07:27.120
Winter poked his head out of a hut near

04:07:27.120 --> 04:07:27.659
the fence.

04:07:27.719 --> 04:07:30.719
I'm not, he said huffily.

04:07:30.780 --> 04:07:32.159
Why would I be?

04:07:32.219 --> 04:07:34.079
Scavengers are fascinating.

04:07:34.139 --> 04:07:36.600
You are so weird.

04:07:36.719 --> 04:07:38.219
Snowball said.

04:07:38.280 --> 04:07:41.040
Nobody else keeps their lunch in a pretty

04:07:41.040 --> 04:07:42.959
cage for months to study it.

04:07:43.020 --> 04:07:48.000
She's not lunch, he said, outraged.

04:07:48.059 --> 04:07:51.479
My scavenger is a research subject.

04:07:51.540 --> 04:07:53.340
I'm learning so much about them.

04:07:53.459 --> 04:07:54.540
They're really smart.

04:07:54.600 --> 04:07:57.059
Snowfall rolled her eyes.

04:07:57.120 --> 04:07:59.700
What happened to that droopy one mother

04:07:59.700 --> 04:08:00.959
let you have when you went off to

04:08:00.959 --> 04:08:01.139
school?

04:08:01.200 --> 04:08:03.000
Bandit.

04:08:03.059 --> 04:08:06.600
I had to let him go, Winter said

04:08:06.600 --> 04:08:07.139
tragically.

04:08:07.200 --> 04:08:09.479
I have no idea what was wrong with him.

04:08:09.540 --> 04:08:11.159
But this one is different.

04:08:11.219 --> 04:08:14.700
This one has bitten him 5 times.

04:08:14.760 --> 04:08:16.979
Lynx whispered to Snowfall.

04:08:17.040 --> 04:08:20.819
She's very brave, he said, with a hint of

04:08:20.819 --> 04:08:21.180
pride.

04:08:21.239 --> 04:08:23.639
She's come up with all kinds of ways to

04:08:23.639 --> 04:08:23.940
escape.

04:08:24.000 --> 04:08:27.180
Snowfall peered over the top of the fence

04:08:27.180 --> 04:08:27.420
again.

04:08:27.479 --> 04:08:30.780
The scavenger had a long tail of dark fur

04:08:30.780 --> 04:08:33.000
on her head, tied up with a scrap of

04:08:33.000 --> 04:08:34.680
fabric that might have been bright yellow

04:08:34.680 --> 04:08:35.159
at some point.

04:08:35.219 --> 04:08:37.920
She was now marching up and down the

04:08:37.920 --> 04:08:40.139
length of the vents, shoving each of the

04:08:40.139 --> 04:08:42.299
logs and testing them for footholds.

04:08:42.360 --> 04:08:44.940
Moon says she's really mad.

04:08:45.000 --> 04:08:46.920
Ling told Snowfall.

04:08:47.040 --> 04:08:48.299
What?

04:08:48.360 --> 04:08:49.559
Snowfall said.

04:08:49.620 --> 04:08:51.659
Why would Moon be mad about this?

04:08:51.719 --> 04:08:54.959
No, I mean, the scavenger is mad.

04:08:55.020 --> 04:08:57.120
She really wants to get out of there.

04:08:57.180 --> 04:08:59.639
Snowfall frowned at length.

04:08:59.760 --> 04:09:03.420
Are you trying to suggest that that night

04:09:03.420 --> 04:09:05.639
wing can read scavenger minds as well?

04:09:05.700 --> 04:09:08.760
Not exactly, Winter answered.

04:09:08.819 --> 04:09:11.760
It's not as clear as reading Dragon Minds

04:09:11.760 --> 04:09:13.620
but she gets a sense of their emotions.

04:09:13.680 --> 04:09:16.559
She says, they're just as strong and

04:09:16.559 --> 04:09:18.959
complicated as dragon emotions, he added

04:09:18.959 --> 04:09:19.680
with a little smile.

04:09:19.739 --> 04:09:22.559
I'm not going to dignify this

04:09:22.559 --> 04:09:24.239
conversation with any more of my

04:09:24.239 --> 04:09:25.860
attention, Snowfall said.

04:09:25.920 --> 04:09:28.620
That is the most ridiculous thing I've

04:09:28.620 --> 04:09:28.920
ever heard.

04:09:28.979 --> 04:09:31.500
Winter's being ridiculous.

04:09:32.280 --> 04:09:33.420
A new voice suddenly chimed in.

04:09:33.479 --> 04:09:35.280
If so, that's me.

04:09:35.399 --> 04:09:36.360
I did that.

04:09:36.420 --> 04:09:37.559
All credit to me.

04:09:37.620 --> 04:09:39.659
I built his entire sense of humor from

04:09:39.659 --> 04:09:40.260
the ground up.

04:09:40.319 --> 04:09:43.500
The ice wings whirled around to find a

04:09:43.500 --> 04:09:45.120
pair of sand wings emerging from the

04:09:45.120 --> 04:09:45.360
trees.

04:09:45.420 --> 04:09:48.719
The one speaking was in front, bounding

04:09:48.719 --> 04:09:50.579
toward winter with an irrepressible grin

04:09:50.579 --> 04:09:51.120
on his face.

04:09:51.180 --> 04:09:53.399
He was the one from the beach.

04:09:53.459 --> 04:09:54.840
Snowfall was pretty sure.

04:09:54.899 --> 04:09:56.340
Moon's friend.

04:09:56.399 --> 04:09:58.139
Oh, no.

04:09:58.200 --> 04:10:00.120
Winter said dryly.

04:10:00.180 --> 04:10:01.860
There goes the neighborhood.

04:10:01.920 --> 04:10:04.979
Aw, I can see it in your eyes.

04:10:05.040 --> 04:10:07.620
You missed me so much said the sand

04:10:07.620 --> 04:10:08.040
wing.

04:10:08.100 --> 04:10:10.739
He threw one wing affectionately over

04:10:10.739 --> 04:10:13.200
Winter's shoulders, and nudged the side

04:10:13.200 --> 04:10:14.520
of his neck with his snout.

04:10:14.579 --> 04:10:16.559
I missed you too, best friend.

04:10:16.620 --> 04:10:19.799
Snowfall raised her eyebrows at Winter

04:10:19.799 --> 04:10:22.920
who said, I have no idea who this scruffy

04:10:22.920 --> 04:10:23.399
snout is.

04:10:23.459 --> 04:10:27.420
His favorite dragon in the world, the

04:10:27.420 --> 04:10:28.979
Sandwing said with genuine delight.

04:10:29.100 --> 04:10:31.319
Did we ever officially meet your

04:10:31.319 --> 04:10:31.860
majesty?

04:10:31.979 --> 04:10:33.360
He asked no fall.

04:10:33.420 --> 04:10:36.479
I'm Kibley, Queen Thorn's 2nd in command

04:10:36.479 --> 04:10:36.719
basically.

04:10:36.780 --> 04:10:40.680
Ha, said the other sandwing, and then

04:10:40.680 --> 04:10:42.540
started actually laughing as Kibley gave

04:10:42.540 --> 04:10:43.260
her an offended look.

04:10:43.319 --> 04:10:47.100
Link snudged Snowfall in the ribs, but

04:10:47.100 --> 04:10:48.840
she had already recognized the laughing

04:10:48.840 --> 04:10:49.260
dragon.

04:10:49.319 --> 04:10:52.020
Snowfall had made a diplomatic trip to

04:10:52.020 --> 04:10:54.299
each of the kingdoms soon after becoming

04:10:54.299 --> 04:10:57.239
queen, very much against her will, but

04:10:57.239 --> 04:10:58.799
apparently it was one of those things the

04:10:58.799 --> 04:11:00.059
queen was required to do.

04:11:00.059 --> 04:11:04.860
Queen Thorn, she said, inclining her head

04:11:04.860 --> 04:11:05.819
exactly the right amount.

04:11:05.879 --> 04:11:09.719
Queen Snowfall, Thorn replied, doing the

04:11:09.719 --> 04:11:09.899
same.

04:11:10.020 --> 04:11:11.700
I'm glad you're still here.

04:11:11.760 --> 04:11:14.700
Oh, Snowball said.

04:11:14.819 --> 04:11:17.819
The spikes along her spine ruffled up as

04:11:17.819 --> 04:11:19.440
she braced herself for a lecture about

04:11:19.440 --> 04:11:20.760
how real queens behaved.

04:11:20.819 --> 04:11:22.440
No, wait.

04:11:22.500 --> 04:11:24.600
That was more Queen Coral's style.

04:11:24.659 --> 04:11:27.479
Queen Thorn didn't care much for rules

04:11:27.479 --> 04:11:28.020
and traditions.

04:11:28.139 --> 04:11:31.020
But that also meant she could be horribly

04:11:31.020 --> 04:11:32.459
direct about sharing her opinions.

04:11:32.579 --> 04:11:35.399
I don't like the sound of that thing

04:11:35.399 --> 04:11:37.379
across the ocean, said Thorn.

04:11:37.440 --> 04:11:40.860
Thank the moon's pyreas and peace, so we

04:11:40.860 --> 04:11:42.120
can all talk about it together, like

04:11:42.120 --> 04:11:44.040
sensible dragons, instead of snarling

04:11:44.040 --> 04:11:44.639
hyenas.

04:11:44.700 --> 04:11:47.340
Pierre is at peace.

04:11:47.459 --> 04:11:49.860
Snowfall had never thought about it that

04:11:49.860 --> 04:11:50.040
way.

04:11:50.100 --> 04:11:53.340
Sure, the war of Sandwing's succession

04:11:53.340 --> 04:11:55.079
was over, but her mother had been

04:11:55.079 --> 04:11:57.719
murdered pretty recently by a night

04:11:57.719 --> 04:11:58.200
wing.

04:11:58.260 --> 04:12:00.540
Snowfall wouldn't describe her feelings

04:12:00.540 --> 04:12:02.639
about that tribe as exactly peaceful.

04:12:02.700 --> 04:12:06.239
That didn't make her a snarling hyena

04:12:06.239 --> 04:12:07.319
though, seriously.

04:12:07.379 --> 04:12:10.440
The other queens on their way?

04:12:10.500 --> 04:12:11.639
Snowball asked.

04:12:11.760 --> 04:12:14.159
Rooptide said they could be here by

04:12:14.159 --> 04:12:16.440
tonight, Kibley answered cheerfully.

04:12:16.500 --> 04:12:19.739
He gave Winter another hopeful smile, and

04:12:19.739 --> 04:12:21.180
his earring caught the light of a

04:12:21.180 --> 04:12:21.600
sunbeam.

04:12:21.659 --> 04:12:23.520
That earring.

04:12:23.639 --> 04:12:25.979
The earring.

04:12:26.040 --> 04:12:29.040
Or at least, it looked exactly like the

04:12:29.040 --> 04:12:30.959
earrings that had saved her tribe from

04:12:30.959 --> 04:12:32.700
Dark Stalker in the plague.

04:12:32.760 --> 04:12:34.440
She remembered them arriving.

04:12:34.500 --> 04:12:37.319
Sacks and sacks on them, brought by ice

04:12:37.319 --> 04:12:40.200
wings who lived in possibility. sent by

04:12:40.200 --> 04:12:41.700
Queen Thorn in the Sand Kingdom.

04:12:41.819 --> 04:12:45.479
Snowfall's very 1st task as queen, had

04:12:45.479 --> 04:12:47.520
been making sure that every ice wing in

04:12:47.520 --> 04:12:49.440
her kingdom received one to reverse the

04:12:49.440 --> 04:12:50.340
effects of the plague.

04:12:50.399 --> 04:12:53.940
For a long time, they weren't sure if it

04:12:53.940 --> 04:12:55.020
was safe to take them off again.

04:12:55.079 --> 04:12:57.899
Every ice wing had gone around for months

04:12:57.899 --> 04:13:00.059
wearing them, and then one day someone

04:13:00.059 --> 04:13:02.159
took theirs off to see what would happen

04:13:02.159 --> 04:13:04.079
and the plague didn't come back.

04:13:04.139 --> 04:13:06.600
So gradually they had disappeared off the

04:13:06.600 --> 04:13:07.260
dragons.

04:13:07.319 --> 04:13:10.020
But everyone kept theirs tucked away into

04:13:10.020 --> 04:13:11.579
safe spots just in case.

04:13:11.700 --> 04:13:14.159
Just in case they were needed again.

04:13:14.219 --> 04:13:18.000
Just in case, he wasn't really gone.

04:13:18.059 --> 04:13:21.600
Snowfall had been the last ice wing to

04:13:21.600 --> 04:13:22.379
remove her earring.

04:13:22.440 --> 04:13:25.260
She still carried it with her, and the

04:13:25.260 --> 04:13:26.100
pouch around her neck.

04:13:26.159 --> 04:13:29.579
It was so strange to see the exact same

04:13:29.579 --> 04:13:32.520
earring on this enthusiastic sand wing

04:13:32.520 --> 04:13:34.920
just a regular little accessory instead

04:13:34.920 --> 04:13:36.299
of the thing that had saved her entire

04:13:36.299 --> 04:13:36.780
tribe.

04:13:36.840 --> 04:13:39.120
Are you all right?

04:13:39.180 --> 04:13:41.040
Lynx whispered in her ear.

04:13:41.159 --> 04:13:44.340
Snowfall pulled herself up and folded her

04:13:44.340 --> 04:13:45.659
wings regally.

04:13:45.719 --> 04:13:47.639
Yes, always.

04:13:47.700 --> 04:13:50.819
And then something flashed behind her

04:13:50.819 --> 04:13:53.159
eyes like a bolt of lightning, and her

04:13:53.159 --> 04:13:55.440
head split in 2, and everything around

04:13:55.440 --> 04:13:58.739
her, sanctuary, the scavenger enclosure

04:13:58.739 --> 04:14:02.040
Queen Thorn, length, snowfall herself.

04:14:02.100 --> 04:14:04.860
All vanished into thin air.

04:14:04.920 --> 04:14:09.180
Chapter 13.

04:14:09.360 --> 04:14:12.000
His claws are shaking.

04:14:12.059 --> 04:14:15.540
They are his claws, and they are not his

04:14:15.540 --> 04:14:16.079
claws.

04:14:16.200 --> 04:14:19.260
His claws would never seize a fleeing

04:14:19.260 --> 04:14:21.299
dragonette from the webs and drag her

04:14:21.299 --> 04:14:21.840
into the hive.

04:14:21.899 --> 04:14:25.260
His voice would never shout orders at

04:14:25.260 --> 04:14:26.520
terrified silkwings.

04:14:26.579 --> 04:14:28.620
His talons would never threaten them with

04:14:28.620 --> 04:14:29.100
this spear.

04:14:29.159 --> 04:14:31.739
Where did this spear even come from?

04:14:31.799 --> 04:14:33.719
How long has he been like this?

04:14:33.840 --> 04:14:36.959
The days are blurring together, and he

04:14:36.959 --> 04:14:38.940
hasn't been his real self for so long.

04:14:39.000 --> 04:14:42.540
The queen is in his head, and his

04:14:42.540 --> 04:14:43.020
muscles.

04:14:43.079 --> 04:14:44.280
In his talons.

04:14:44.340 --> 04:14:48.000
It's worse than he ever imagined, any of

04:14:48.000 --> 04:14:49.799
the times he tried to imagine how the

04:14:49.799 --> 04:14:51.959
hive wings must feel as she takes over.

04:14:52.020 --> 04:14:54.899
If he pulls himself all the way back

04:14:54.899 --> 04:14:56.940
inside and stares inward.

04:14:57.000 --> 04:14:59.940
He can lose time, knowing his body is

04:14:59.940 --> 04:15:00.600
moving without him.

04:15:00.659 --> 04:15:03.780
But right now, he can't do that.

04:15:03.840 --> 04:15:05.879
He's in his own hive.

04:15:05.940 --> 04:15:08.879
The place he fled with cricket and sword

04:15:08.879 --> 04:15:10.139
tail not so long ago.

04:15:10.200 --> 04:15:12.899
He is storming through familiar hallways

04:15:12.899 --> 04:15:16.139
smashing displays in the market, rounding

04:15:16.139 --> 04:15:18.120
up all the silk wings who were peacefully

04:15:18.120 --> 04:15:20.040
lying in the sun in the mosaic garden.

04:15:20.100 --> 04:15:23.879
He sees dragons he knows from school, who

04:15:23.879 --> 04:15:25.799
stare at him in paralyzed terror.

04:15:25.860 --> 04:15:29.459
They know he would never do this, so this

04:15:29.459 --> 04:15:31.139
is how they discover the queen can

04:15:31.139 --> 04:15:33.719
control silk wings now, as well as hive

04:15:33.719 --> 04:15:34.139
wings.

04:15:34.200 --> 04:15:36.120
Except it's not the queen.

04:15:36.239 --> 04:15:37.979
It's even worse.

04:15:38.100 --> 04:15:40.079
But they don't know that yet.

04:15:40.139 --> 04:15:43.200
They look at their own talents, wondering

04:15:43.200 --> 04:15:45.239
when it will happen if they'll remember

04:15:45.239 --> 04:15:45.479
it.

04:15:45.600 --> 04:15:48.000
All the things Blue wondered too.

04:15:48.059 --> 04:15:50.219
But there's a process.

04:15:50.280 --> 04:15:54.420
The new, stronger breath of evil plant is

04:15:54.420 --> 04:15:55.500
needed for the process.

04:15:55.559 --> 04:15:57.600
And the dragons who were supposed to make

04:15:57.600 --> 04:15:59.340
it grow faster escaped.

04:15:59.399 --> 04:16:01.200
Sundew.

04:16:01.319 --> 04:16:04.620
No one has found her yet, or cricket, as

04:16:04.620 --> 04:16:05.399
far as Blue knows.

04:16:05.459 --> 04:16:07.020
She might be safe.

04:16:07.079 --> 04:16:09.540
Maybe they're even in the distant

04:16:09.540 --> 04:16:12.180
kingdoms now, far from all of this.

04:16:12.239 --> 04:16:14.700
Carelessness.

04:16:14.760 --> 04:16:17.579
Wasp's voice hisses in his head.

04:16:17.639 --> 04:16:20.700
This was a strange discovery, that

04:16:20.700 --> 04:16:23.100
although she can't read his thoughts, He

04:16:23.100 --> 04:16:25.620
can hear hers, sometimes very clearly.

04:16:25.680 --> 04:16:29.399
She's furious about the silk wings that

04:16:29.399 --> 04:16:30.899
have slipped through her claws already.

04:16:30.959 --> 04:16:33.659
Hundreds of them vanished during the 2

04:16:33.659 --> 04:16:36.180
days while her army was rescuing every

04:16:36.180 --> 04:16:38.579
last scrap of the breath of evil plant

04:16:38.579 --> 04:16:39.659
from the burning jungle.

04:16:39.719 --> 04:16:44.219
The jungle she made me burn, he thinks

04:16:44.219 --> 04:16:46.260
but has to stop himself from thinking.

04:16:46.319 --> 04:16:49.020
They were hunting for leaf wings at the

04:16:49.020 --> 04:16:50.700
same time, but found none.

04:16:50.760 --> 04:16:53.159
None.

04:16:53.219 --> 04:16:57.000
How did they all escape?

04:16:57.059 --> 04:16:59.100
Where could they have gone?

04:16:59.159 --> 04:17:03.659
I will find them and destroy them.

04:17:03.719 --> 04:17:07.079
At least I have their army and their

04:17:07.079 --> 04:17:07.559
queen.

