04:28:08.459 --> 04:28:10.799
I've been wondering about how she did

04:28:10.799 --> 04:28:11.459
that for days.

04:28:11.520 --> 04:28:14.700
It seems to be jewelry related?

04:28:14.760 --> 04:28:17.940
She studied Snowfall's bracelets and the

04:28:17.940 --> 04:28:19.920
ring that sat obstinately on her claw.

04:28:20.040 --> 04:28:23.040
Kibley gave her a surprised, approving

04:28:23.040 --> 04:28:23.280
look.

04:28:23.340 --> 04:28:25.979
He held out one talent to snowfall.

04:28:26.040 --> 04:28:27.420
May I see?

04:28:27.540 --> 04:28:30.719
Snowfall wasn't sure why she placed her

04:28:30.719 --> 04:28:33.239
talent in his, letting him bend down to

04:28:33.239 --> 04:28:34.260
peer at the oval ring.

04:28:34.319 --> 04:28:37.680
Maybe it was the smoky haze of Blue's

04:28:37.680 --> 04:28:39.719
brain inside hers, wanting to trust

04:28:39.719 --> 04:28:42.540
everyone, which was still better than the

04:28:42.540 --> 04:28:45.059
sharp teeth of wasp's brain that wanted

04:28:45.059 --> 04:28:46.079
her to bite him instead.

04:28:46.139 --> 04:28:48.360
Is that right?

04:28:48.420 --> 04:28:50.940
Am I being all snowfall right now?

04:28:51.000 --> 04:28:53.459
Would Snowfall normally want to bite him

04:28:53.459 --> 04:28:53.639
too?

04:28:53.700 --> 04:28:56.100
Are any of my feelings real?

04:28:56.159 --> 04:28:58.739
Invisible army?

04:28:58.799 --> 04:29:00.899
Winter murmured to Lynx.

04:29:01.020 --> 04:29:03.420
She tugged him a few steps away from the

04:29:03.420 --> 04:29:04.500
group and whispered in his ear.

04:29:04.559 --> 04:29:08.159
At the same time, Kibble was tapping on

04:29:08.159 --> 04:29:09.899
the opal and trying to wiggle the ring

04:29:09.899 --> 04:29:11.520
around Snowfall's claw.

04:29:11.579 --> 04:29:15.180
This isn't an ordinary stock ring, is

04:29:15.180 --> 04:29:15.360
it?

04:29:15.420 --> 04:29:16.139
He said.

04:29:16.200 --> 04:29:17.760
What's the spell on it?

04:29:17.819 --> 04:29:19.139
Do you know who cast it?

04:29:19.200 --> 04:29:22.079
Sundu drew in a sharp breath behind him?

04:29:22.200 --> 04:29:23.700
Spell?

04:29:23.819 --> 04:29:24.479
she echoed.

04:29:24.540 --> 04:29:27.180
You can cast actual magic spells?

04:29:27.239 --> 04:29:30.120
Part of snowfall, really?

04:29:30.120 --> 04:29:32.879
Really wanted to tell these other tribe

04:29:32.879 --> 04:29:33.959
dragons, nothing.

04:29:34.020 --> 04:29:36.360
This was ice wing business.

04:29:36.420 --> 04:29:38.639
Nothing to do with anyone else.

04:29:38.700 --> 04:29:42.239
There was cricket, and her curious face

04:29:42.239 --> 04:29:45.059
that Blue loved so much, and Blue would

04:29:45.059 --> 04:29:46.260
never hide anything from her.

04:29:46.319 --> 04:29:49.500
And even the parts of snowfall that

04:29:49.500 --> 04:29:50.940
weren't all blurry from being blue

04:29:50.940 --> 04:29:53.520
couldn't help thinking, she should know

04:29:53.520 --> 04:29:56.159
that he's still alive, or at least he was

04:29:56.159 --> 04:29:57.479
whenever that vision happened.

04:29:57.600 --> 04:29:59.579
Is going to happen?

04:29:59.639 --> 04:30:01.379
Arrr!

04:30:01.440 --> 04:30:04.559
It would be helpful to know things, you

04:30:04.559 --> 04:30:05.219
stupid ring.

04:30:05.280 --> 04:30:09.120
It's an old animus touched object from

04:30:09.120 --> 04:30:11.760
way back in ice wing history, she told

04:30:11.760 --> 04:30:12.360
Kibley.

04:30:12.420 --> 04:30:14.219
I found it in our treasury.

04:30:14.340 --> 04:30:17.760
It gives me visions of other dragons, like

04:30:17.760 --> 04:30:20.340
I'm inside them, thinking their thoughts

04:30:20.340 --> 04:30:22.079
feeling their feelings.

04:30:22.139 --> 04:30:23.940
She scowled.

04:30:24.059 --> 04:30:26.819
It's the worst, if you want to know the

04:30:26.819 --> 04:30:27.059
truth.

04:30:27.120 --> 04:30:30.479
Wow, Cricket breathed.

04:30:30.600 --> 04:30:32.879
Blue would love that.

04:30:33.000 --> 04:30:35.520
Snowfall rubbed her head.

04:30:35.579 --> 04:30:37.440
The one I just had.

04:30:37.500 --> 04:30:40.020
I was blue, actually.

04:30:40.079 --> 04:30:42.840
She didn't want to tell them the wasp

04:30:42.840 --> 04:30:43.319
part.

04:30:43.379 --> 04:30:46.440
Maybe she could keep that to herself, and

04:30:46.440 --> 04:30:48.659
by keeping it to herself, forget it ever

04:30:48.659 --> 04:30:49.020
happened.

04:30:49.079 --> 04:30:52.020
Cricket and Luna stared at her with a

04:30:52.020 --> 04:30:53.280
whole new light in their eyes.

04:30:53.340 --> 04:30:54.840
Blue?

04:30:54.899 --> 04:30:57.899
Luna gasped, and you saw him?

04:30:57.959 --> 04:30:58.979
He's all right?

04:30:59.100 --> 04:31:00.899
Cricket blurted at the same time.

04:31:00.959 --> 04:31:05.100
I didn't see him, Snowfall explained

04:31:05.100 --> 04:31:05.940
Snively.

04:31:06.000 --> 04:31:07.379
I was him.

04:31:07.440 --> 04:31:09.840
I was stuck inside him.

04:31:09.899 --> 04:31:12.479
He is the sappiest little butterfly of a

04:31:12.479 --> 04:31:12.899
dragon.

04:31:12.959 --> 04:31:14.520
I have ever encountered.

04:31:14.579 --> 04:31:16.319
That's blue.

04:31:16.379 --> 04:31:18.299
Luna said affectionately.

04:31:18.360 --> 04:31:21.120
Tiras were running down Cricket's face.

04:31:21.180 --> 04:31:22.680
What was he doing?

04:31:22.739 --> 04:31:24.180
Is he safe?

04:31:24.299 --> 04:31:28.559
Not even remotely, Snowfall said, and

04:31:28.559 --> 04:31:31.559
then, ow, as Lynx kicked her tail and

04:31:31.559 --> 04:31:33.180
gave her a significant look.

04:31:33.239 --> 04:31:35.340
I mean, he's alive.

04:31:35.399 --> 04:31:37.860
But that evil queen of yours is

04:31:37.860 --> 04:31:40.200
controlling his talons, and he's trapped

04:31:40.200 --> 04:31:42.239
with her army, and they were just forced

04:31:42.239 --> 04:31:44.280
to round up a bunch of silk wings in

04:31:44.280 --> 04:31:47.399
Cicada Hive, including his mother's, and

04:31:47.399 --> 04:31:49.020
he was feeling really guilty about that.

04:31:49.079 --> 04:31:50.459
What?

04:31:50.579 --> 04:31:53.219
She barked, as Lynx kicked her tail

04:31:53.219 --> 04:31:53.399
again.

04:31:53.459 --> 04:31:55.139
It's all right.

04:31:55.200 --> 04:31:58.020
Cricket said to Lynx, although her tears

04:31:58.020 --> 04:31:58.680
hadn't stopped.

04:31:58.799 --> 04:32:00.659
I want to know the truth.

04:32:00.719 --> 04:32:02.700
See?

04:32:02.700 --> 04:32:04.620
Snowfall glowered at length.

04:32:04.680 --> 04:32:07.500
Have you had visions of other penthal and

04:32:07.500 --> 04:32:08.040
dragons?

04:32:08.100 --> 04:32:09.360
Sunu interrupted.

04:32:09.420 --> 04:32:10.979
Any leaf wings?

04:32:11.040 --> 04:32:14.819
Yes, one named Bryony.

04:32:14.879 --> 04:32:16.079
Snowfall said.

04:32:16.139 --> 04:32:19.680
Sunday's eyes narrowed, but less like she

04:32:19.680 --> 04:32:21.899
was mad at snowfall, and more like she

04:32:21.899 --> 04:32:23.399
was trying not to have some other

04:32:23.399 --> 04:32:24.000
expression.

04:32:24.059 --> 04:32:25.620
Was she?

04:32:25.620 --> 04:32:27.780
Did Queen Wasp have her?

04:32:27.780 --> 04:32:29.459
and the other leaf wings with her?

04:32:29.520 --> 04:32:33.360
No, she's in hiding, Snowfall said.

04:32:33.479 --> 04:32:36.120
With hemlock and all the silk wings from

04:32:36.120 --> 04:32:37.079
Bloodworm Hive.

04:32:37.139 --> 04:32:40.379
All the silk wings from Bloodworm Hive

04:32:40.379 --> 04:32:43.139
Sundu echoed, confusion taking over her

04:32:43.139 --> 04:32:43.379
face.

04:32:43.440 --> 04:32:46.680
Yes, Snowfall snapped.

04:32:46.739 --> 04:32:49.260
I know your plan was to lead them all to

04:32:49.260 --> 04:32:51.540
die with the hive wings, but Briony

04:32:51.540 --> 04:32:52.260
didn't let that happen.

04:32:52.379 --> 04:32:55.920
Sundew blinked, and it was Cricket who

04:32:55.920 --> 04:32:56.879
jumped in to defend her.

04:32:56.940 --> 04:32:59.639
Sundew didn't want them to burn the hive

04:32:59.639 --> 04:33:00.840
at all, she said.

04:33:00.899 --> 04:33:03.360
And she's the one who made sure they

04:33:03.360 --> 04:33:05.040
contacted the chrysalis first.

04:33:05.159 --> 04:33:08.700
This is so weird, Link said.

04:33:08.759 --> 04:33:11.579
I mean, listening to you talk about all

04:33:11.579 --> 04:33:14.099
this Pantala stuff, and those dragons

04:33:14.099 --> 04:33:15.419
over there as if you know them.

04:33:15.540 --> 04:33:17.520
She added to Snowfall.

04:33:17.580 --> 04:33:21.240
As if you care about them, her puzzled

04:33:21.240 --> 04:33:22.319
eyebrows seemed to say.

04:33:22.380 --> 04:33:24.840
It's not great.

04:33:24.900 --> 04:33:27.119
Snowfall lashed her tail.

04:33:27.180 --> 04:33:29.520
It's pretty aggravating, in fact.

04:33:29.580 --> 04:33:31.799
I have enough problems to handle in the

04:33:31.799 --> 04:33:32.580
ice kingdom.

04:33:32.639 --> 04:33:35.040
I don't want to worry about problems on a

04:33:35.040 --> 04:33:36.180
whole other continent too.

04:33:36.299 --> 04:33:39.299
Thank you for telling us, though, cricket

04:33:39.299 --> 04:33:40.799
said. wiping her eyes.

04:33:40.860 --> 04:33:42.479
It means a lot.

04:33:42.599 --> 04:33:44.339
Who else?

04:33:44.459 --> 04:33:45.599
Sundew demanded.

04:33:45.659 --> 04:33:47.639
How long have you been having these

04:33:47.639 --> 04:33:48.720
visions without telling us?

04:33:48.840 --> 04:33:51.299
Snowfall hissed at her?

04:33:51.360 --> 04:33:54.180
Just since you came barging into my

04:33:54.180 --> 04:33:54.540
kingdom?

04:33:54.599 --> 04:33:55.679
she said.

04:33:55.740 --> 04:33:58.139
The other 2 times were silk wings.

04:33:58.139 --> 04:33:59.700
In the 1st vision?

04:33:59.759 --> 04:34:02.159
I was Atala while she flew over the ocean

04:34:02.159 --> 04:34:04.319
with you all, but she's here now and

04:34:04.319 --> 04:34:04.919
totally fine.

04:34:04.979 --> 04:34:07.259
The other is named Tao.

04:34:07.380 --> 04:34:09.659
She was trying to escape Jewel hive

04:34:09.659 --> 04:34:11.040
before the hive wings got there.

04:34:11.099 --> 04:34:14.039
Tell, Cricket said softly.

04:34:14.099 --> 04:34:15.839
Did she make it?

04:34:15.900 --> 04:34:17.819
I don't know.

04:34:17.880 --> 04:34:20.700
Snowfall threw her wings up in the air

04:34:20.700 --> 04:34:22.139
scattering pine needles.

04:34:22.200 --> 04:34:26.040
Wait, yes, I do, sort of, because Blue

04:34:26.040 --> 04:34:28.319
was thinking about how Wasp's army found

04:34:28.319 --> 04:34:29.759
Jewel Hive empty.

04:34:29.880 --> 04:34:32.520
So I think she did, but I can't be sure

04:34:32.520 --> 04:34:35.099
because I don't even know if I was seeing

04:34:35.099 --> 04:34:37.500
the past present or future.

04:34:37.560 --> 04:34:39.779
There is no reason for any of this.

04:34:39.840 --> 04:34:42.180
And now they're happening during the

04:34:42.180 --> 04:34:42.599
day?

04:34:42.659 --> 04:34:45.299
She growled low in her throat.

04:34:45.360 --> 04:34:48.779
I can be collapsing and getting infested

04:34:48.779 --> 04:34:51.900
with other dragon's emotions in the

04:34:51.900 --> 04:34:53.279
middle of a council of queens.

04:34:53.340 --> 04:34:55.139
Let's cut off my claw.

04:34:55.259 --> 04:34:57.479
She said abruptly to lynx.

04:34:57.599 --> 04:35:01.979
That might be a bit drastic, Kibley said

04:35:01.979 --> 04:35:04.439
and she realized he was still holding her

04:35:04.439 --> 04:35:05.999
talon, studying the ring.

04:35:06.060 --> 04:35:10.259
I mean, let's make that plan B or like

04:35:10.259 --> 04:35:13.860
plan F. What's plan A?

04:35:13.919 --> 04:35:15.899
Snowfall shouted at him.

04:35:15.959 --> 04:35:18.659
Can you communicate with the dragons in

04:35:18.659 --> 04:35:19.139
your visions?

04:35:19.200 --> 04:35:22.380
Kibley asked, like, to let them know

04:35:22.380 --> 04:35:24.060
where everyone is gone, or that they

04:35:24.060 --> 04:35:25.200
should come across the ocean too.

04:35:25.259 --> 04:35:26.879
No.

04:35:26.939 --> 04:35:28.319
Snowfall cried.

04:35:28.380 --> 04:35:31.259
What is wrong with your ears?

04:35:31.319 --> 04:35:33.900
I'm not snowfall when I'm inside them.

04:35:33.959 --> 04:35:35.639
Snowfall disappears.

04:35:35.700 --> 04:35:37.979
I have no way of telling them anything.

04:35:38.040 --> 04:35:40.860
I can't even remember what snowfall

04:35:40.860 --> 04:35:41.220
knows.

04:35:41.279 --> 04:35:43.919
It's like I never existed at all.

04:35:44.040 --> 04:35:46.680
She took a deep, shuddering breath.

04:35:46.740 --> 04:35:50.759
Queen Thorn nudged Kibli aside. and took

04:35:50.759 --> 04:35:52.080
his place beside Snowfall.

04:35:52.200 --> 04:35:55.680
The queen needs a moment, Thorn said with

04:35:55.680 --> 04:35:56.040
authority.

04:35:56.099 --> 04:35:59.039
Everyone who's not me, go away.

04:35:59.099 --> 04:36:03.419
But Kibli and Sundu both started to

04:36:03.419 --> 04:36:04.499
protest at the same time.

04:36:04.560 --> 04:36:08.700
Now, Thorn said with a forbidding look.

04:36:08.759 --> 04:36:11.699
The other dragons melted away like

04:36:11.699 --> 04:36:12.179
magic.

04:36:12.240 --> 04:36:15.419
Real queen magic, Snowfall thought

04:36:15.419 --> 04:36:16.020
wistfully.

04:36:16.080 --> 04:36:18.779
The magic of saying things and being

04:36:18.779 --> 04:36:19.740
instantly obeyed.

04:36:19.860 --> 04:36:22.860
The magic of being so queenly that

04:36:22.860 --> 04:36:25.259
everyone listens to you, because they

04:36:25.259 --> 04:36:27.840
trust you, and know your great queen.

04:36:27.900 --> 04:36:30.060
Woof!

04:36:30.119 --> 04:36:31.679
Thorn said when they were gone.

04:36:31.740 --> 04:36:34.439
Her voice suddenly surprisingly normal.

04:36:34.500 --> 04:36:37.020
Have you noticed that it's awfully hard

04:36:37.020 --> 04:36:38.819
to get any peace and quiet when you're

04:36:38.819 --> 04:36:39.060
queen?

04:36:39.119 --> 04:36:42.659
Snowfall thought of her empty, echoing

04:36:42.659 --> 04:36:45.359
palace, and the way dragons vanished when

04:36:45.359 --> 04:36:46.019
they saw her coming.

04:36:46.139 --> 04:36:50.639
The long, long nights that were too quiet

04:36:50.639 --> 04:36:53.220
and yet not peaceful at all.

04:36:53.279 --> 04:36:56.819
But also the constant pressure inside her

04:36:56.819 --> 04:36:59.219
head, knowing the wall was always waiting

04:36:59.219 --> 04:37:01.259
for her, and feeling as though dragons

04:37:01.259 --> 04:37:02.579
were watching her every move.

04:37:02.639 --> 04:37:06.299
I wonder if Tundra has changed any of

04:37:06.299 --> 04:37:07.799
their rankings while I've been gone.

04:37:07.860 --> 04:37:11.279
Narwhal used to, when Queen Glacier was

04:37:11.279 --> 04:37:11.459
away.

04:37:11.520 --> 04:37:14.099
Snowfall didn't think she'd officially

04:37:14.099 --> 04:37:16.799
authorized that, but maybe tundra would

04:37:16.799 --> 04:37:19.139
just assume that power because Snowfall

04:37:19.139 --> 04:37:20.459
hadn't told her not to.

04:37:20.520 --> 04:37:24.180
Let's go flying, Thorn suggested.

04:37:24.240 --> 04:37:26.520
We can figure out what we think before

04:37:26.520 --> 04:37:27.479
the other queens get here.

04:37:27.540 --> 04:37:30.299
I don't know how to figure out what I

04:37:30.299 --> 04:37:32.759
think Snowfall said, standing up.

04:37:32.880 --> 04:37:34.979
Should I get my guards?

04:37:35.040 --> 04:37:37.560
Nah, just you and me.

04:37:37.619 --> 04:37:38.579
Thorn said.

04:37:38.639 --> 04:37:41.279
I mean, who would dare attack us?

04:37:41.340 --> 04:37:43.860
Brain dead beetles who want to be crushed

04:37:43.860 --> 04:37:44.099
maybe?

04:37:44.159 --> 04:37:47.279
Snowfall laughed despite herself.

04:37:47.340 --> 04:37:50.099
Flying away from everyone was exactly

04:37:50.099 --> 04:37:52.020
what she wanted to do right now anyway.

04:37:52.080 --> 04:37:55.979
They lifted up into the sky, letting the

04:37:55.979 --> 04:37:58.080
late morning sun wash over them and

04:37:58.080 --> 04:37:59.279
soared toward the peaks.

04:37:59.400 --> 04:38:02.819
Snowfall inhaled the smell of distant

04:38:02.819 --> 04:38:03.240
snow.

04:38:03.299 --> 04:38:06.360
Along with a scent of not so distant

04:38:06.360 --> 04:38:07.259
scavengers.

04:38:07.319 --> 04:38:10.080
More than one scavenger?

04:38:10.139 --> 04:38:12.840
She glanced down at Winter's little

04:38:12.840 --> 04:38:13.319
enclosure.

04:38:13.380 --> 04:38:16.020
The creature in there was sprinting

04:38:16.020 --> 04:38:18.180
around the space again, making lots of

04:38:18.180 --> 04:38:20.220
funny squeaking noises.

04:38:20.279 --> 04:38:22.619
But Snowfall's nose told her that wasn't

04:38:22.619 --> 04:38:24.179
the only scavenger nearby.

04:38:24.240 --> 04:38:28.020
And were those tree branches moving in

04:38:28.020 --> 04:38:28.799
more than the wind?

04:38:28.860 --> 04:38:31.380
Snowfall shrugged?

04:38:31.439 --> 04:38:34.619
She had never cared about scavengers, and

04:38:34.619 --> 04:38:35.819
she wasn't about to start now.

04:38:35.880 --> 04:38:39.540
She tilted her wings and followed Queen

04:38:39.540 --> 04:38:40.799
Thorn into the clouds.

04:38:40.860 --> 04:38:45.540
Chapter 14.

04:38:45.779 --> 04:38:49.919
Queen Thorn didn't make Snowfall talk, or

04:38:49.919 --> 04:38:52.379
ask a bunch of questions, or lecture her

04:38:52.379 --> 04:38:53.219
on queenliness.

04:38:53.340 --> 04:38:56.520
They just flew and hunted when they got

04:38:56.520 --> 04:38:59.880
hungry, and flew some more, until the sun

04:38:59.880 --> 04:39:02.040
was high in the sky, warming their

04:39:02.040 --> 04:39:02.819
chilled wings.

04:39:02.939 --> 04:39:05.999
Snowfall felt her head clearing of the

04:39:05.999 --> 04:39:07.499
post vision blue haze.

04:39:07.560 --> 04:39:10.560
Her own thoughts sharpened and felt real

04:39:10.560 --> 04:39:10.799
again.

04:39:10.919 --> 04:39:14.639
Thoughts including, is that going to keep

04:39:14.639 --> 04:39:14.999
happening?

04:39:15.060 --> 04:39:17.340
Visions in the middle of the day?

04:39:17.400 --> 04:39:20.459
What if one happens while I'm flying?

04:39:20.580 --> 04:39:23.819
Will I just fall out of the sky and die?

04:39:23.880 --> 04:39:25.919
Will they ever stop?

04:39:25.979 --> 04:39:28.139
Or will they start coming more and more

04:39:28.139 --> 04:39:30.959
frequently until my mind is never my own

04:39:30.959 --> 04:39:31.380
anymore?

04:39:31.439 --> 04:39:33.659
She shivered.

04:39:33.720 --> 04:39:36.479
What was the point of this magic?

04:39:36.540 --> 04:39:39.119
Was it set to get worse and worse

04:39:39.119 --> 04:39:39.779
gradually?

04:39:39.900 --> 04:39:42.959
Maybe so the original animus would have

04:39:42.959 --> 04:39:44.939
had time to escape the kingdom before the

04:39:44.939 --> 04:39:45.599
queen went mad?

04:39:45.659 --> 04:39:48.659
And what was happening with Blue Now?

04:39:48.779 --> 04:39:51.360
Or Bryony, or Tao?

04:39:51.479 --> 04:39:54.240
If only she could compel the ring to give

04:39:54.240 --> 04:39:54.900
her visions.

04:39:54.959 --> 04:39:58.560
She actually wanted useful visions.

04:39:58.619 --> 04:40:00.659
Instead of walking nightmares, she

04:40:00.659 --> 04:40:01.439
couldn't do anything about.

04:40:01.500 --> 04:40:04.080
Ready to go back?

04:40:04.139 --> 04:40:06.479
Thorn asked, swooping up beside her.

04:40:06.540 --> 04:40:08.580
Snowfall made a phase.

04:40:08.700 --> 04:40:10.319
I can't wait.

04:40:10.380 --> 04:40:12.000
More interrogation.

04:40:12.060 --> 04:40:12.779
How thrilling.

04:40:12.840 --> 04:40:15.479
You just shut them down whenever you need

04:40:15.479 --> 04:40:17.040
to, Thorn suggested.

04:40:17.099 --> 04:40:18.479
You are a queen.

04:40:18.540 --> 04:40:21.060
But remember that, of course, they're

04:40:21.060 --> 04:40:23.159
curious and worried about their friends

04:40:23.159 --> 04:40:24.900
so that's why they want to know more.

04:40:24.959 --> 04:40:28.919
Yes, yes, Snowfall grumbled.

04:40:28.979 --> 04:40:32.220
If Blue had known snowfall was inside him

04:40:32.220 --> 04:40:34.919
he would have been over the moons to give

04:40:34.919 --> 04:40:36.000
her a message for cricket.

04:40:36.060 --> 04:40:38.520
The least she could do for that poor

04:40:38.520 --> 04:40:40.680
trapped dragon was reassured, the hive

04:40:40.680 --> 04:40:41.340
wing he loved.

04:40:41.459 --> 04:40:46.200
Another intertribal romance, she thought

04:40:46.200 --> 04:40:47.279
shaking her head.

04:40:47.340 --> 04:40:50.220
Were they more common than she realized?

04:40:50.279 --> 04:40:53.099
She'd always assumed Ice Wings would

04:40:53.099 --> 04:40:55.500
never choose to be with dragons outside

04:40:55.500 --> 04:40:56.159
their tribe.

04:40:56.220 --> 04:40:59.459
But then, the dragon had brought them the

04:40:59.459 --> 04:41:01.919
1st 2 earrings had been a hybrid ice wing

04:41:01.919 --> 04:41:02.939
sea wing from possibility.

04:41:03.000 --> 04:41:06.000
And now there was crystal and garial.

04:41:06.060 --> 04:41:08.159
So it did happen.

04:41:08.220 --> 04:41:10.380
Hybrids.

04:41:10.439 --> 04:41:12.060
Winter mentioned them.

04:41:12.119 --> 04:41:14.880
In the chaos yesterday, she hadn't really

04:41:14.880 --> 04:41:17.159
registered it, but now she remembered.

04:41:17.220 --> 04:41:21.119
He'd said, We have a lot of hybrids

04:41:21.119 --> 04:41:21.299
here.

04:41:21.360 --> 04:41:24.419
That meant dragonettes whose parents were

04:41:24.419 --> 04:41:26.700
from 2 different tribes, like the ones

04:41:26.700 --> 04:41:27.840
she'd spotted yesterday.

04:41:27.900 --> 04:41:31.619
Probably a mud wing sea wing, and at

04:41:31.619 --> 04:41:34.979
least 2 sky wing sand wings, and maybe a

04:41:34.979 --> 04:41:36.540
sky wing night wing?

04:41:36.599 --> 04:41:39.180
No wonder those dragons wanted a new city

04:41:39.180 --> 04:41:39.900
to live in.

04:41:39.959 --> 04:41:41.639
How could they ever return to their

04:41:41.639 --> 04:41:44.340
kingdoms, or choose one tribe while

04:41:44.340 --> 04:41:45.240
abandoning the other?

04:41:45.299 --> 04:41:48.959
Snowfall had to admit to herself that she

04:41:48.959 --> 04:41:50.639
would have forbidden crystal to see

04:41:50.639 --> 04:41:52.680
Garyel if she'd known about it when she

04:41:52.680 --> 04:41:53.639
1st became queen.

04:41:53.700 --> 04:41:56.040
And he wouldn't have been able to cross

04:41:56.040 --> 04:41:57.540
the great ice cliff alive.

04:41:57.599 --> 04:41:59.459
He still couldn't.

04:41:59.520 --> 04:42:01.979
So even if Snowfall gave them her

04:42:01.979 --> 04:42:04.139
blessing, they'd never be able to come to

04:42:04.139 --> 04:42:05.040
the ice palace.

04:42:05.099 --> 04:42:08.159
She followed Thorn as they descended into

04:42:08.159 --> 04:42:10.619
the central clearing of sanctuary, where

04:42:10.619 --> 04:42:12.419
sundew and tsunami were yelling at each

04:42:12.419 --> 04:42:14.700
other, surrounded by a wide eyed

04:42:14.700 --> 04:42:15.000
audience.

04:42:15.060 --> 04:42:18.959
You could save us, Sunday shouted.

04:42:19.020 --> 04:42:20.819
It would be so easy for you.

04:42:20.880 --> 04:42:24.779
I did save you, tsunami shouted back.

04:42:24.840 --> 04:42:26.459
You're here, aren't you?

04:42:26.520 --> 04:42:27.060
and alive.

04:42:27.180 --> 04:42:29.880
I mean, everyone back there.

04:42:29.939 --> 04:42:32.159
Sundu waved one wing at the Western

04:42:32.159 --> 04:42:32.580
Horizon.

04:42:32.639 --> 04:42:35.520
Oh, the mind controlled dragons.

04:42:35.580 --> 04:42:37.500
You could save them with one spell.

04:42:37.560 --> 04:42:39.599
That's what?

04:42:39.659 --> 04:42:41.340
tsunami sputtered.

04:42:41.400 --> 04:42:42.540
Oh what now?

04:42:42.659 --> 04:42:44.459
A spell.

04:42:44.520 --> 04:42:46.319
Sundu clenched her fists.

04:42:46.380 --> 04:42:48.900
The dragons on this continent have real

04:42:48.900 --> 04:42:51.360
magic, she announced to the leaf wings

04:42:51.360 --> 04:42:51.720
around her.

04:42:51.779 --> 04:42:54.419
It's not only seeing the future and

04:42:54.419 --> 04:42:57.659
invisible armies, they can cast any spell

04:42:57.659 --> 04:42:58.439
they want.

04:42:58.500 --> 04:43:01.080
They could make a spell to free all the

04:43:01.080 --> 04:43:03.119
dragons in Pantala, but they won't.

04:43:03.180 --> 04:43:05.580
They've been hiding their magic from us.

04:43:05.639 --> 04:43:07.380
All right.

04:43:07.439 --> 04:43:10.560
Hang on, tsunami said over the mutters

04:43:10.560 --> 04:43:11.099
from the crowd.

04:43:11.220 --> 04:43:14.099
That's a highly confused understanding of

04:43:14.099 --> 04:43:14.580
the situation.

04:43:14.639 --> 04:43:18.720
So, unconfuse it, Sundew barked.

04:43:18.779 --> 04:43:21.000
We don't all have magic.

04:43:21.060 --> 04:43:24.299
Tsunami turned to riptide, who had come

04:43:24.299 --> 04:43:25.979
up to stand supportively beside her.

04:43:26.040 --> 04:43:27.659
Back me up.

04:43:27.720 --> 04:43:29.099
Hardly any of us have magic.

04:43:29.159 --> 04:43:31.200
It's very rare.

04:43:31.259 --> 04:43:32.400
Riptide agreed.

04:43:32.459 --> 04:43:35.759
Once in a generation, often less, or at

04:43:35.759 --> 04:43:36.720
least it's supposed to be.

04:43:36.779 --> 04:43:39.840
So right now you have what?

04:43:39.900 --> 04:43:41.279
Sundu demanded.

04:43:41.340 --> 04:43:42.900
One magician?

04:43:42.900 --> 04:43:43.799
Two?

04:43:43.799 --> 04:43:46.439
Tsunami's grunge upper snout.

04:43:46.439 --> 04:43:49.740
We call them animus dragons, she said.

04:43:49.860 --> 04:43:54.299
And Four, we think, more or less.

04:43:54.360 --> 04:43:55.979
Four?

04:43:56.099 --> 04:43:58.139
Snowfall tried to think.

04:43:58.200 --> 04:43:59.759
Did she know about this?

04:43:59.819 --> 04:44:02.880
There was Jerboa, and there was some

04:44:02.880 --> 04:44:04.560
animus dragon at Jade Mountain.

04:44:04.619 --> 04:44:07.139
She assumed a sea wing, who'd cast the

04:44:07.139 --> 04:44:07.919
empathy spell.

04:44:07.979 --> 04:44:10.020
So who were the other two?

04:44:10.080 --> 04:44:12.180
What tribe did they work for?

04:44:12.240 --> 04:44:14.159
That was outrageous.

04:44:14.220 --> 04:44:17.639
Animus dragons all over the place, and

04:44:17.639 --> 04:44:18.900
none of them ice wings.

04:44:18.959 --> 04:44:20.520
No one was safe.

04:44:20.580 --> 04:44:23.459
So bring us one of them.

04:44:23.580 --> 04:44:27.240
Sundew said in a steely voice, and have

04:44:27.240 --> 04:44:29.580
them cast one spell for us.

04:44:29.639 --> 04:44:33.299
Tsunami's eyes slipped sideways into the

04:44:33.299 --> 04:44:33.599
crowd.

04:44:33.659 --> 04:44:35.819
The snowfall didn't catch who she was

04:44:35.819 --> 04:44:38.040
looking at, Whoa.

04:44:38.099 --> 04:44:40.860
Is there an animus dragon here right

04:44:40.860 --> 04:44:41.159
now?

04:44:41.220 --> 04:44:43.979
Here's the thing.

04:44:44.040 --> 04:44:45.840
Tsunami said slowly.

04:44:45.900 --> 04:44:48.540
Animus magic has stopped working.

04:44:48.599 --> 04:44:50.279
Nobody knows why.

04:44:50.340 --> 04:44:52.740
That's why I didn't tell you all about it

04:44:52.740 --> 04:44:55.740
because even though we want to help you

04:44:55.799 --> 04:44:57.119
We can't do it with magic.

04:44:57.180 --> 04:44:58.560
We just can't.

04:44:58.680 --> 04:45:02.220
That sounds like another lie, Sundu

04:45:02.220 --> 04:45:02.580
yelled.

04:45:02.639 --> 04:45:06.240
Snowfall saw Queen Hazel in the crowd of

04:45:06.240 --> 04:45:09.000
leaf wings, at the same moment, Hazel

04:45:09.000 --> 04:45:11.099
caught her eye, and gave a little start

04:45:11.099 --> 04:45:12.779
as though she'd forgotten she was a

04:45:12.779 --> 04:45:13.860
figure of authority around here.

04:45:13.919 --> 04:45:19.020
Hey, hey, she said, stepping in between

04:45:19.020 --> 04:45:21.959
sundu and tsunami, her green wings spread

04:45:21.959 --> 04:45:23.520
out like giant leaf curtains.

04:45:23.580 --> 04:45:25.919
It could be true, Sundoo.

04:45:25.979 --> 04:45:29.040
If their magic isn't working, why would

04:45:29.040 --> 04:45:29.759
they tell us about it?

04:45:29.819 --> 04:45:33.479
If their magic isn't working, Why is she

04:45:33.479 --> 04:45:35.819
making armies invisible and having

04:45:35.819 --> 04:45:37.619
visions of Pentalon dragons?

04:45:37.680 --> 04:45:40.560
Sandu asked, pointing at snowfall.

04:45:40.619 --> 04:45:42.840
Oh, great.

04:45:42.900 --> 04:45:45.900
Now, the 100s of puzzled eyes turned

04:45:45.900 --> 04:45:46.919
towards Snowfall.

04:45:46.979 --> 04:45:51.959
I'm using old magic, she answered, holding

04:45:51.959 --> 04:45:54.419
up her talon with a ring on it, and

04:45:54.419 --> 04:45:55.500
chanted a long time ago.

04:45:55.560 --> 04:45:57.540
Those still work.

04:45:57.599 --> 04:45:59.700
It's only new spells that don't.

04:45:59.759 --> 04:46:02.880
Apparently, if we take the animus

04:46:02.880 --> 04:46:03.900
dragon's word for it.

04:46:03.959 --> 04:46:07.439
Tsunami frowned at her, and Snowfall

04:46:07.439 --> 04:46:08.700
scowled right back.

04:46:08.759 --> 04:46:12.240
The queens are starting to arrive, Riptide

04:46:12.240 --> 04:46:14.340
said, brushing tsunami's wing with his

04:46:14.340 --> 04:46:14.520
own.

04:46:14.580 --> 04:46:17.880
A wing of dragons was soaring down toward

04:46:17.880 --> 04:46:20.819
them, and farther off in the sky, Snowfall

04:46:20.819 --> 04:46:22.020
could see another group approaching.

04:46:22.080 --> 04:46:24.540
Everyone turned to look at them

04:46:24.540 --> 04:46:27.299
whispering and murmuring, who would get

04:46:27.299 --> 04:46:27.900
here first?

04:46:27.959 --> 04:46:30.180
Would they come with any friends or

04:46:30.180 --> 04:46:32.040
family of the sanctuary dragons?

04:46:32.099 --> 04:46:35.700
Time to put on my super queen face?

04:46:35.759 --> 04:46:38.880
My, the Ice Kingdom is just fine, thank

04:46:38.880 --> 04:46:39.900
you, Bass.

04:46:39.959 --> 04:46:41.520
No advice needed.

04:46:41.580 --> 04:46:42.959
Don't tell me what to do.

04:46:43.020 --> 04:46:45.479
I am an excellent queen who can handle.

04:46:45.479 --> 04:46:47.099
Who can?

04:46:47.159 --> 04:46:47.639
What?

04:46:47.700 --> 04:46:48.779
Oh no.

04:46:48.900 --> 04:46:51.060
It was happening again.

04:46:51.119 --> 04:46:53.639
Darkness was crowding in around the

04:46:53.639 --> 04:46:54.779
corners of her eyes.

04:46:54.840 --> 04:46:58.020
Snowfall looked around wildly, spotted

04:46:58.020 --> 04:46:59.939
winter. and sank her claws into his

04:46:59.939 --> 04:47:00.180
tail.

04:47:00.240 --> 04:47:04.560
Yowch, he yelped, whipping around to look

04:47:04.560 --> 04:47:04.919
at her.

04:47:04.979 --> 04:47:08.400
Get me somewhere safe, she hissed.

04:47:08.459 --> 04:47:10.139
Don't let them see.

04:47:10.200 --> 04:47:11.819
He didn't argue.

04:47:11.880 --> 04:47:13.080
Didn't ask questions.

04:47:13.979 --> 04:47:15.540
Didn't stand there with a dopey

04:47:15.540 --> 04:47:16.680
bewildered look on his face.

04:47:16.740 --> 04:47:19.740
He grabbed Kibley, and the 2 of them

04:47:19.740 --> 04:47:21.659
spread their wings around snowfall

04:47:21.659 --> 04:47:23.880
hooking their arms under hers, and

04:47:23.880 --> 04:47:25.680
carrying her away from the circle of

04:47:25.680 --> 04:47:26.040
dragons.

04:47:26.099 --> 04:47:28.560
But everyone looking up at the sky.

04:47:28.619 --> 04:47:31.380
Snowfall had to hope they wouldn't notice

04:47:31.380 --> 04:47:34.380
her being spirited away, but she only had

04:47:34.380 --> 04:47:36.299
a moment to worry about it before.

04:47:36.299 --> 04:47:41.040
Tall grass brushes her wings and tickles

04:47:41.040 --> 04:47:41.520
her snout.

04:47:41.580 --> 04:47:44.819
She crouches lower, spreading her long

04:47:44.819 --> 04:47:45.180
wings.

04:47:45.240 --> 04:47:47.639
She's lucky there are dark color.

04:47:47.700 --> 04:47:49.979
So it's easier to creep up on the hives

04:47:49.979 --> 04:47:50.340
at night.

04:47:50.400 --> 04:47:54.299
The dragon city towers over them, light

04:47:54.299 --> 04:47:56.459
glowing from the windows and archways on

04:47:56.459 --> 04:47:57.060
the higher levels.

04:47:57.119 --> 04:47:58.979
But she can't hear anything.

04:47:59.040 --> 04:48:02.759
Voices, music, any of the sounds that

04:48:02.759 --> 04:48:04.740
usually carry across the savannah at

04:48:04.740 --> 04:48:04.919
night.

04:48:04.979 --> 04:48:06.720
It's too quiet.

04:48:06.779 --> 04:48:10.020
And nothing moves in the webs overhead.

04:48:10.080 --> 04:48:13.080
They're empty and still, like she's never

04:48:13.080 --> 04:48:13.740
seen them before.

04:48:13.799 --> 04:48:16.259
All the silk wings.

04:48:16.319 --> 04:48:18.000
Where are they?

04:48:18.119 --> 04:48:20.880
Was this your hive?

04:48:21.000 --> 04:48:23.939
The small, dark orange dragon beside her

04:48:23.939 --> 04:48:24.360
whispers.

04:48:24.419 --> 04:48:27.180
Yes, she whispers back.

04:48:27.240 --> 04:48:29.400
They should have come here 1st.

04:48:29.459 --> 04:48:32.759
All her chrysalis friends, her parents.

04:48:32.880 --> 04:48:35.220
Is she too late to save them?

04:48:35.279 --> 04:48:38.459
She studies the map of Pantala in her

04:48:38.459 --> 04:48:38.580
head.

04:48:38.639 --> 04:48:41.400
They'd recruited silk wings from yellow

04:48:41.400 --> 04:48:45.060
jacket hive, wasp hive, and jewel hive to

04:48:45.060 --> 04:48:47.220
bring to the poison jungle, those had

04:48:47.220 --> 04:48:48.840
gone across the sea with the escaping

04:48:48.840 --> 04:48:49.380
dragons.

04:48:49.439 --> 04:48:52.080
The silk wings from bloodworm hive

04:48:52.080 --> 04:48:54.540
vanished into thin air after the hive

04:48:54.540 --> 04:48:55.020
burned.

04:48:55.080 --> 04:48:57.060
No one knows where they are.

04:48:57.119 --> 04:48:58.380
But they can't be dead.

04:48:58.500 --> 04:49:02.099
No bodies and no survivors, has to mean

04:49:02.099 --> 04:49:03.720
they all escaped somewhere, doesn't it?

04:49:03.779 --> 04:49:07.020
She'd sent 2 dragons to Set Sea Hive.

04:49:07.080 --> 04:49:09.360
So it had only made sense for her and

04:49:09.360 --> 04:49:11.639
Cinnabar to fly the other way, stopping

04:49:11.639 --> 04:49:13.680
briefly at each hive to warn whoever they

04:49:13.680 --> 04:49:16.139
could, then straight on to mantis hive.

04:49:16.200 --> 04:49:19.380
It was as far from the poison jungle as

04:49:19.380 --> 04:49:19.979
one could get.

04:49:20.040 --> 04:49:22.439
Her wings were still sore from the

04:49:22.439 --> 04:49:24.060
frantic full speed flight.

04:49:24.119 --> 04:49:26.639
Which meant there was a chance of getting

04:49:26.639 --> 04:49:28.979
there before Queen Wasp's zombie

04:49:28.979 --> 04:49:29.520
minions.

04:49:29.580 --> 04:49:31.319
And she'd been right.

04:49:31.380 --> 04:49:34.200
They'd found mantis hive empty of hive

04:49:34.200 --> 04:49:34.619
wings.

04:49:34.680 --> 04:49:37.560
Bewildered silk wings milled about its

04:49:37.560 --> 04:49:40.860
halls or rested on the webs, enjoying the

04:49:40.860 --> 04:49:43.259
unexpected days off, while also wondering

04:49:43.259 --> 04:49:44.400
where everyone had gone.

04:49:44.459 --> 04:49:49.080
Every hive wing had left, even the

04:49:49.080 --> 04:49:50.279
smallest dragonettes.

04:49:50.340 --> 04:49:53.580
Wasp had summoned every single one to the

04:49:53.580 --> 04:49:55.740
battlefield outside the poison jungle

04:49:55.740 --> 04:49:57.959
determined to crush the leaf wings once

04:49:57.959 --> 04:49:58.500
and for all.

04:49:58.560 --> 04:50:00.900
She clenches her talons.

04:50:00.959 --> 04:50:03.599
Those hive wings hadn't had to lift a

04:50:03.599 --> 04:50:03.959
claw.

04:50:04.020 --> 04:50:07.200
The leaf wings and the silkwing allies

04:50:07.200 --> 04:50:09.779
she brought them had lost before they

04:50:09.779 --> 04:50:10.799
even started to fight.

04:50:10.860 --> 04:50:12.180
They'd run away.

04:50:12.240 --> 04:50:15.779
And now Queen Wasp and the breath of evil

04:50:15.779 --> 04:50:18.599
were able to infect silk wings, which

04:50:18.599 --> 04:50:20.700
meant the entire tribe might lose the

04:50:20.700 --> 04:50:22.439
last bit of freedom they'd had.

04:50:22.500 --> 04:50:24.659
Stop, Io.

04:50:24.779 --> 04:50:27.180
Cinnabar was whispers, brushing one of

04:50:27.180 --> 04:50:28.020
her wings lightly.

04:50:28.080 --> 04:50:29.580
Stop worrying.

04:50:29.580 --> 04:50:32.400
We got everyone out of mantis hive and

04:50:32.400 --> 04:50:33.299
safely into hiding.

04:50:33.360 --> 04:50:35.639
We'll save the silk wings here too.

04:50:35.700 --> 04:50:39.060
It's too quiet, she whispers back.

04:50:39.119 --> 04:50:41.099
The hive wings must be here.

04:50:41.159 --> 04:50:43.560
I bet they've got all the silk wings

04:50:43.560 --> 04:50:44.400
trapped in there with them.

04:50:44.520 --> 04:50:48.240
Even if that's true, Cinnabar whispers.

04:50:48.299 --> 04:50:50.580
They can't have put all the silk wings in

04:50:50.580 --> 04:50:52.319
the hive under the mind control yet.

04:50:52.380 --> 04:50:54.720
They don't have enough of the plant to do

04:50:54.720 --> 04:50:54.900
that.

04:50:54.959 --> 04:50:57.900
They'll have to grow more, and Sandu said

04:50:57.900 --> 04:51:00.540
that without Hawthorne or her.

04:51:00.599 --> 04:51:01.139
It take a while.

04:51:01.200 --> 04:51:03.119
Not as long as it should.

04:51:03.180 --> 04:51:06.540
Some of the leaf wings wasp trapped have

04:51:06.540 --> 04:51:08.220
a little bit of leaf speak.

04:51:08.279 --> 04:51:09.479
They'll make it grow faster.

04:51:09.540 --> 04:51:12.360
And if the hive wings keep all the silk

04:51:12.360 --> 04:51:13.979
wings imprisoned until they have enough.

04:51:14.040 --> 04:51:16.080
We'll get them out.

04:51:16.139 --> 04:51:17.459
That's why we're here.

04:51:17.580 --> 04:51:21.119
Io sighs and looks up at the ghostly webs

04:51:21.119 --> 04:51:21.419
again.

04:51:21.479 --> 04:51:24.299
They're swaying slightly in a far up

04:51:24.299 --> 04:51:27.119
breeze, silvery pale in the light of the

04:51:27.119 --> 04:51:27.779
3 moons.

04:51:27.900 --> 04:51:29.099
Empty.

04:51:29.159 --> 04:51:33.240
How are 2 dragons supposed to save all

04:51:33.240 --> 04:51:35.279
the silk wings and cicada hive?

04:51:35.340 --> 04:51:38.340
They'll help us, she reminds herself.

04:51:38.400 --> 04:51:41.759
My friends will rise up when they realize

04:51:41.759 --> 04:51:43.500
it's time for the chrysalis to break

04:51:43.500 --> 04:51:43.799
free.

04:51:43.860 --> 04:51:46.200
The map is safe.

04:51:46.259 --> 04:51:47.639
Cinnabar asks.

04:51:47.700 --> 04:51:51.779
Hidden, IO promises, where we agreed.

04:51:51.840 --> 04:51:54.959
Even if Queen Wasp captures them and

04:51:54.959 --> 04:51:57.240
steals their minds, she can't access

04:51:57.240 --> 04:51:58.259
their secrets.

04:51:58.319 --> 04:52:01.080
The map to the other continent is

04:52:01.080 --> 04:52:03.659
somewhere that only Io or Cinnabar can

04:52:03.659 --> 04:52:04.860
find with their minds free.

04:52:04.919 --> 04:52:08.159
WASP won't even know it exists.

04:52:08.220 --> 04:52:12.479
Cinnabar smiles, and her wings rustle in

04:52:12.479 --> 04:52:13.259
the darkness.

04:52:13.319 --> 04:52:16.560
Then let's go rescue our tribe.

04:52:16.619 --> 04:52:20.939
Chapter 15.

04:52:21.299 --> 04:52:24.599
Snowfall floundered back into her own

04:52:24.599 --> 04:52:26.580
mind shouting, it's a trap.

04:52:26.700 --> 04:52:27.720
Don't go in there.

04:52:27.779 --> 04:52:30.240
She threw off the talons holding her down

04:52:30.240 --> 04:52:31.860
and tried to lunge into the air.

04:52:31.919 --> 04:52:34.740
But she was so disoriented that she

04:52:34.740 --> 04:52:37.319
crashed into somebody's wings and landed

04:52:37.319 --> 04:52:39.299
back in a soft pile of pine needles.

04:52:39.360 --> 04:52:44.040
Your majesty, said Winter's voice, and

04:52:44.040 --> 04:52:46.500
somehow that was disorienting too, her

04:52:46.500 --> 04:52:48.900
own cousin calling her that, when that

04:52:48.900 --> 04:52:51.240
voice, and that name, should only connect

04:52:51.240 --> 04:52:52.439
to Queen Glacier.

04:52:52.500 --> 04:52:56.159
Don't worry, Kibley said, touching one of

04:52:56.159 --> 04:52:57.119
her talons lightly.

04:52:57.180 --> 04:52:58.319
You're back.

04:52:58.439 --> 04:53:00.240
Your queen snowfall again.

04:53:00.299 --> 04:53:02.220
They're going to catch her.

04:53:02.279 --> 04:53:04.319
Snowfall said breathlessly.

04:53:04.380 --> 04:53:08.400
Cicada hive is full of wasp zombies, lying

04:53:08.400 --> 04:53:10.020
in wait for Io and cinnabar.

04:53:10.080 --> 04:53:12.240
I have to tell them, that's where blue

04:53:12.240 --> 04:53:12.540
is.

04:53:12.659 --> 04:53:14.040
They can't go in there.

04:53:14.099 --> 04:53:16.860
She struggled up again and then stopped

04:53:16.860 --> 04:53:19.139
standing with her wings outstretched

04:53:19.139 --> 04:53:21.000
along the ground, trying to breathe.

04:53:21.060 --> 04:53:24.060
I can't tell them, she said.

04:53:24.119 --> 04:53:25.500
There's no way.

04:53:25.560 --> 04:53:29.819
Um, Kibley said, looking at winter.

04:53:29.880 --> 04:53:31.500
Maybe there is?

04:53:31.560 --> 04:53:34.680
Don't you be needlessly optimistic at

04:53:34.680 --> 04:53:34.919
me?

04:53:34.979 --> 04:53:35.939
She snapped.

04:53:36.000 --> 04:53:37.919
Why?

04:53:38.040 --> 04:53:40.080
She screamed at the ring in her mind.

04:53:40.139 --> 04:53:42.840
Why would you show me this when there's

04:53:42.840 --> 04:53:43.979
nothing I can do?

04:53:44.040 --> 04:53:47.340
They were outside Winter's scavenger

04:53:47.340 --> 04:53:47.880
enclosure.

04:53:47.939 --> 04:53:51.240
The scavenger inside was squeaking loudly

04:53:51.240 --> 04:53:52.860
like an overwrought squirrel.

04:53:52.919 --> 04:53:55.860
All around them, the bushes rustled in

04:53:55.860 --> 04:53:57.599
the wind, or maybe, because of something

04:53:57.599 --> 04:53:57.840
else.

04:53:57.900 --> 04:54:01.319
Snowfall squinted at one of the trees, and

04:54:01.319 --> 04:54:02.880
thought she saw something move that was

04:54:02.880 --> 04:54:03.779
bigger than a squirrel.

04:54:03.840 --> 04:54:06.659
But then lynx came darting through the

04:54:06.659 --> 04:54:09.000
woods and sprinted up to snowfall side.

04:54:09.060 --> 04:54:10.860
Are you all right?

04:54:10.919 --> 04:54:12.000
She panted.

04:54:12.060 --> 04:54:13.439
Who were you this time?

04:54:13.560 --> 04:54:16.380
Someone very doomed.

04:54:16.439 --> 04:54:18.840
Snowfall bit out, frustrated.

04:54:18.900 --> 04:54:20.400
Never mind.

04:54:20.459 --> 04:54:21.840
Are all the queens here?

04:54:21.900 --> 04:54:25.500
Everyone but Queen Coral, Lang said.

04:54:25.560 --> 04:54:27.959
They've agreed to start without her, if

04:54:27.959 --> 04:54:28.259
you're ready.

04:54:28.319 --> 04:54:29.819
Are you ready?

04:54:29.880 --> 04:54:34.020
I'm fine, Snowfall said, waving away

04:54:34.020 --> 04:54:35.880
Winter's talons as he tried to help her

04:54:35.880 --> 04:54:36.060
up.

04:54:36.119 --> 04:54:38.580
She didn't have to tell anyone that her

04:54:38.580 --> 04:54:39.779
heartbeat was still racing.

04:54:39.840 --> 04:54:42.540
Or that part of her was still inside the

04:54:42.540 --> 04:54:44.520
heat and smell of the Savannah night.

04:54:44.639 --> 04:54:46.680
Calm down.

04:54:46.740 --> 04:54:49.439
You are not currently creeping into a

04:54:49.439 --> 04:54:51.840
giant, terrifying dragon city full of

04:54:51.840 --> 04:54:53.759
mind controlled monsters with bug

04:54:53.759 --> 04:54:54.360
powers.

04:54:54.360 --> 04:54:57.659
But Iowas, or would be.

04:54:57.779 --> 04:54:59.759
Or already had?

04:54:59.880 --> 04:55:01.740
Snowfall shook herself.

04:55:01.799 --> 04:55:04.259
She had no idea how to figure out the

04:55:04.259 --> 04:55:05.520
time frame for her visions.

04:55:05.580 --> 04:55:08.220
That one might have happened days and

04:55:08.220 --> 04:55:08.819
days ago.

04:55:08.880 --> 04:55:11.759
Io might be dead already.

04:55:11.819 --> 04:55:15.060
She flinched at the thought, then shot

04:55:15.060 --> 04:55:16.259
another glare at her ring.

04:55:16.319 --> 04:55:19.319
You'd better not be sending me visions of

04:55:19.319 --> 04:55:20.759
totally dead dragons.

04:55:20.819 --> 04:55:23.759
The other queens were assembled in the

04:55:23.759 --> 04:55:25.979
mouth of a pebbly cave halfway up one of

04:55:25.979 --> 04:55:26.639
the mountain peaks.

04:55:26.700 --> 04:55:29.459
The wind whipped around the snow caps

04:55:29.459 --> 04:55:31.380
above them, but the spot they'd chosen

04:55:31.380 --> 04:55:33.000
was an oasis of quiet.

04:55:33.180 --> 04:55:35.639
Each queen had brought one advisor as

04:55:35.639 --> 04:55:38.220
backup, and snowfall debated all the way

04:55:38.220 --> 04:55:39.779
up the mountain about whether it was

04:55:39.779 --> 04:55:42.060
idiotic to bring Lynx, who was clearly

04:55:42.060 --> 04:55:44.279
still a dragonette, instead of one of her

04:55:44.279 --> 04:55:44.759
guards.

04:55:44.819 --> 04:55:47.700
The Queen Thorn had summoned Kibley to

04:55:47.700 --> 04:55:48.060
join her.

04:55:48.119 --> 04:55:50.400
And he was about the same age as Lynx

04:55:50.400 --> 04:55:50.700
surely.

04:55:50.759 --> 04:55:53.819
Queen Ruby's choice was a quiet, older

04:55:53.819 --> 04:55:56.400
orange dragon, who took notes the entire

04:55:56.400 --> 04:55:58.319
time in a kind of miniature scroll.

04:55:58.380 --> 04:56:00.240
Snowfall never caught his name.

04:56:00.299 --> 04:56:03.240
Queen Morehen had a mud wing with her who

04:56:03.240 --> 04:56:04.259
looked so much like her.

04:56:04.319 --> 04:56:06.479
The snowfall nearly bowed at the wrong

04:56:06.479 --> 04:56:06.840
dragon.

04:56:06.959 --> 04:56:09.840
A sister, she guessed, remembering the

04:56:09.840 --> 04:56:11.459
way mud wings were about family.

04:56:11.580 --> 04:56:15.000
And of course, there was Queen Glory, with

04:56:15.000 --> 04:56:17.520
her floppy yaw noodle of a sloth curled

04:56:17.520 --> 04:56:18.959
around her neck, as usual.

04:56:19.319 --> 04:56:21.599
She'd brought a fidgety nightwing with

04:56:21.599 --> 04:56:24.419
her, which Snowfall didn't like, but she

04:56:24.419 --> 04:56:25.439
thought it was an interesting choice.

04:56:25.500 --> 04:56:28.080
Why not a fellow rain wing?

04:56:28.139 --> 04:56:30.840
What did the rain wings think of glory

04:56:30.840 --> 04:56:32.400
choosing a night wing over them for this

04:56:32.400 --> 04:56:32.819
council?

04:56:32.939 --> 04:56:35.159
Perhaps nothing at all.

04:56:35.220 --> 04:56:38.159
Did rain wings actually have opinions?

04:56:38.220 --> 04:56:41.580
Queen Hazel was there too, with Cricket

04:56:41.580 --> 04:56:42.479
and Luna.

04:56:42.540 --> 04:56:44.580
Sundew had been left down in the

04:56:44.580 --> 04:56:45.000
village.

04:56:45.060 --> 04:56:47.459
Most likely because Hazel didn't want her

04:56:47.459 --> 04:56:48.959
to do any more shouting in front of the

04:56:48.959 --> 04:56:49.979
Queens.

04:56:50.040 --> 04:56:53.819
Tsunami, Riptide, and Moon, for the final

04:56:53.819 --> 04:56:54.840
3 dragons in the council.

04:56:54.959 --> 04:56:57.659
If snowfall hadn't been the last one to

04:56:57.659 --> 04:56:59.520
arrive, she might have complained and

04:56:59.520 --> 04:57:01.500
tried to get them kicked out, but it was

04:57:01.500 --> 04:57:02.700
too late by the time she got there.

04:57:02.759 --> 04:57:05.400
Well, fine.

04:57:05.459 --> 04:57:08.040
Probably it made sense to get a report

04:57:08.040 --> 04:57:10.139
from one Pyrean dragon who'd actually

04:57:10.139 --> 04:57:11.040
been to Pentala.

04:57:11.099 --> 04:57:13.500
Although there's also me.

04:57:13.560 --> 04:57:16.619
I could tell them way too much about

04:57:16.619 --> 04:57:18.240
what's happening on Pentala right now.

04:57:18.299 --> 04:57:20.040
She shivered a little.

04:57:20.099 --> 04:57:21.659
Thinking of Io again.

04:57:21.720 --> 04:57:24.779
The other queens exchanged polite

04:57:24.779 --> 04:57:26.939
greetings with Snowfall, the kind that

04:57:26.939 --> 04:57:28.619
would normally make her freak out about

04:57:28.619 --> 04:57:30.720
what they really meant, and what they

04:57:30.720 --> 04:57:32.459
thought of her, and whether they talked

04:57:32.459 --> 04:57:33.599
about her when she wasn't there.

04:57:33.659 --> 04:57:36.779
Today she could barely even concentrate

04:57:36.779 --> 04:57:38.400
on saying the right things back to them.

04:57:38.459 --> 04:57:41.639
So what if Queen Ruby's smile looked

04:57:41.639 --> 04:57:43.020
suspiciously judgmental?

04:57:43.080 --> 04:57:45.240
Io and cinnabar.

04:57:45.299 --> 04:57:46.680
Wait.

04:57:46.740 --> 04:57:49.919
Didn't Cinnabar say, Something

04:57:49.919 --> 04:57:50.279
important.

04:57:50.340 --> 04:57:52.799
Right at the end of the vision?

04:57:52.919 --> 04:57:56.520
Her thoughts were interrupted by Tsunami

04:57:56.520 --> 04:57:58.200
standing up and calling the council to

04:57:58.200 --> 04:58:01.080
order. as though she was anybody at all.

04:58:01.139 --> 04:58:02.939
All right, fine.

04:58:03.000 --> 04:58:05.159
She was a royal sea wing princess, so

04:58:05.159 --> 04:58:07.380
technically, she could be standing in for

04:58:07.380 --> 04:58:10.259
Queen Coral, but still, it was very

04:58:10.259 --> 04:58:11.220
presumptuous.

04:58:11.279 --> 04:58:14.759
Tsunami told a long story about how Luna

04:58:14.759 --> 04:58:16.380
had been swept across the ocean in a

04:58:16.380 --> 04:58:19.139
storm carried by her silk, and how that

04:58:19.139 --> 04:58:21.180
was their 1st sign, there were dragons on

04:58:21.180 --> 04:58:22.860
a lost continent out beyond the sea.

04:58:22.919 --> 04:58:25.439
She explained that she and her brother

04:58:25.439 --> 04:58:27.900
had decided to swim across the ocean to

04:58:27.900 --> 04:58:30.720
find them, and to find out whether Luna's

04:58:30.720 --> 04:58:32.639
stories were true, that there were

04:58:32.639 --> 04:58:34.080
dragons over there who needed help.

04:58:34.139 --> 04:58:36.959
Luna jumped in to talk about the

04:58:36.959 --> 04:58:39.479
political system in Pentala, how the hive

04:58:39.479 --> 04:58:41.159
wings kept the silk wings under their

04:58:41.159 --> 04:58:43.319
control, and how the hive wings

04:58:43.319 --> 04:58:45.240
themselves were all controlled by Queen

04:58:45.240 --> 04:58:48.119
Wasp, who could take over any hive wings

04:58:48.119 --> 04:58:50.700
mind anytime she felt like it, from

04:58:50.700 --> 04:58:51.119
anywhere.

04:58:51.180 --> 04:58:55.439
Except mine, Cricket said quickly, when

04:58:55.439 --> 04:58:56.880
Kibley turned to look at her.

04:58:56.939 --> 04:58:58.500
And a few others.

04:58:58.560 --> 04:59:00.180
It's a whole thing.

04:59:00.240 --> 04:59:04.380
Hazel added the story of the leaf wings

04:59:04.380 --> 04:59:06.599
who had fought a war with Queen Wasp, and

04:59:06.599 --> 04:59:09.240
almost been wiped out, except for a small

04:59:09.240 --> 04:59:11.520
remnant of the tribe that fled to hide in

04:59:11.520 --> 04:59:12.360
a poison jungle.

04:59:12.419 --> 04:59:15.540
Snowfall drifted in and out for parts of

04:59:15.540 --> 04:59:16.020
the stories.

04:59:16.080 --> 04:59:19.740
She knew all this, from being Tao, and

04:59:19.740 --> 04:59:21.659
Briony, and Blue, and Io.

04:59:21.720 --> 04:59:23.939
She could still feel the weight of the

04:59:23.939 --> 04:59:25.619
history that rippled under their scales.

04:59:25.680 --> 04:59:28.860
She remembered knowing things they hadn't

04:59:28.860 --> 04:59:30.000
even thought consciously about.

04:59:30.060 --> 04:59:32.459
She could probably draw an accurate map

04:59:32.459 --> 04:59:33.540
of Pentala herself.

04:59:33.599 --> 04:59:37.259
I am actually the most informed dragon

04:59:37.259 --> 04:59:38.459
here, she thought.

04:59:38.520 --> 04:59:40.619
Glancing triumphantly around the circle.

04:59:40.680 --> 04:59:43.919
The one and only upside to the visions.

04:59:43.979 --> 04:59:47.279
Maybe that was why the ancient Ice Wing

04:59:47.279 --> 04:59:50.700
Queen had agreed to, or asked for, this

04:59:50.700 --> 04:59:51.540
gift in the 1st place.

04:59:51.599 --> 04:59:54.599
But knowing a lot about Pentala didn't

04:59:54.599 --> 04:59:56.580
seem like an even trade for Snowfall's

04:59:56.580 --> 04:59:56.939
sanity.

04:59:57.000 --> 05:00:00.599
Finally, after a long explanation of the

05:00:00.599 --> 05:00:03.479
new war, Queen Wasps Attack on the Jungle

05:00:03.479 --> 05:00:05.459
and the discovery of the plant that gave

05:00:05.459 --> 05:00:08.340
her the mind control power, the Pentalan

05:00:08.340 --> 05:00:10.020
dragons wound down into silence.

05:00:10.080 --> 05:00:13.380
The queens exchanged glances.

05:00:13.500 --> 05:00:16.020
So you need a new place to live.

05:00:16.080 --> 05:00:17.939
Queen Mohan asked.

05:00:18.000 --> 05:00:20.279
I suppose you could stay here in

05:00:20.279 --> 05:00:21.180
sanctuary.

05:00:21.240 --> 05:00:23.220
If it's all right with Queen Ruby and

05:00:23.220 --> 05:00:23.939
Queen Thorn.

05:00:24.060 --> 05:00:26.880
I'm afraid we don't have room in the mud

05:00:26.880 --> 05:00:27.299
kingdom.

05:00:27.360 --> 05:00:31.319
Yeah, right, Snowfall thought.

05:00:31.380 --> 05:00:34.020
The Mud Kingdom wasn't exactly packed

05:00:34.020 --> 05:00:35.639
wall to wall with mud wings.

05:00:35.700 --> 05:00:37.860
They could easily fit a whole other city

05:00:37.860 --> 05:00:40.200
of dragons in those endless swamps that

05:00:40.200 --> 05:00:40.680
they wanted to.

05:00:40.740 --> 05:00:43.560
How many dragons are we talking about?

05:00:43.619 --> 05:00:45.299
Ruby interjected.

05:00:45.360 --> 05:00:47.220
Who will be in charge of them?

05:00:47.279 --> 05:00:50.279
You, she asked Queen Hazel.

05:00:50.340 --> 05:00:52.860
I mean, what if you keep having more

05:00:52.860 --> 05:00:54.299
dragonettes and spreading out?

05:00:54.360 --> 05:00:56.580
Are we going to end out with a new

05:00:56.580 --> 05:00:58.139
kingdom in the middle of the continent?

05:00:58.200 --> 05:01:01.500
One that mostly takes over Sky Kingdom

05:01:01.500 --> 05:01:02.099
territory?

05:01:02.159 --> 05:01:04.319
She shot ripped hide a frown.

05:01:04.380 --> 05:01:06.720
That's not what I had in mind when I

05:01:06.720 --> 05:01:07.680
agreed to this settlement.

05:01:07.740 --> 05:01:10.439
I know your majesty, he said.

05:01:10.500 --> 05:01:12.900
But we can't possibly send them back to

05:01:12.900 --> 05:01:13.619
Pantala.

05:01:13.680 --> 05:01:16.799
Beside him, tsunami vigorously shook her

05:01:16.799 --> 05:01:19.500
head, and Moon looked horrified, as

05:01:19.500 --> 05:01:21.000
though someone had just suggested

05:01:21.000 --> 05:01:23.040
rounding up all the baby seals and

05:01:23.040 --> 05:01:23.759
setting them on fire.

05:01:23.819 --> 05:01:27.119
Is there anywhere else we can put them?

05:01:27.180 --> 05:01:28.259
Ruby asked.

05:01:28.319 --> 05:01:30.119
She turned to glory.

05:01:30.180 --> 05:01:32.400
It sounds like they might be happiest in

05:01:32.400 --> 05:01:33.119
the rainforest.

05:01:33.180 --> 05:01:36.840
So glory can be queen of 4 tribes.

05:01:36.959 --> 05:01:39.060
Snowfall hurt herself, Snap.

05:01:39.119 --> 05:01:41.939
Glory made a face she couldn't

05:01:41.939 --> 05:01:42.299
interpret.

05:01:42.360 --> 05:01:44.159
Was she laughing at Snowfall?

05:01:44.279 --> 05:01:46.799
Was she thinking that she could handle 4

05:01:46.799 --> 05:01:49.319
tribes easily when Snowfall could barely

05:01:49.319 --> 05:01:49.740
manage one?

05:01:49.799 --> 05:01:52.500
The part of her that had briefly been

05:01:52.500 --> 05:01:55.139
blue, the silk wing thought, or maybe

05:01:55.139 --> 05:01:57.000
she's thinking how impossible it would be

05:01:57.000 --> 05:01:59.880
to rule 4 tribes, and how much she's

05:01:59.880 --> 05:02:01.560
still struggling to bring together the 2

05:02:01.560 --> 05:02:01.979
she has.

05:02:02.040 --> 05:02:04.680
Shut up, you mushball.

05:02:04.740 --> 05:02:06.119
Snowball demanded.

05:02:06.180 --> 05:02:07.919
Wait.

05:02:07.979 --> 05:02:08.880
Wait.

05:02:08.939 --> 05:02:11.819
Hazel stood up, and spread her wings to

05:02:11.819 --> 05:02:12.659
catch their attention.

05:02:12.720 --> 05:02:14.099
That's not.

05:02:14.099 --> 05:02:16.680
We're not thinking about where we could

05:02:16.680 --> 05:02:17.099
live yet.

05:02:17.220 --> 05:02:18.659
Most of us.

05:02:18.720 --> 05:02:21.840
All of us, I think, want to go back to

05:02:21.840 --> 05:02:22.439
Pantala.

05:02:22.560 --> 05:02:26.459
Not Cobra Lily, Snowfall thought.

05:02:26.520 --> 05:02:29.099
She wondered if Hazel had actually asked

05:02:29.099 --> 05:02:30.299
anybody what they wanted.

05:02:30.360 --> 05:02:32.939
The leaf wings might be happier here

05:02:32.939 --> 05:02:35.159
among trees that weren't constantly

05:02:35.159 --> 05:02:35.939
trying to eat them.

05:02:36.000 --> 05:02:39.840
Oh, Ruby said, taken aback.

05:02:39.959 --> 05:02:42.659
Then, Do that?

05:02:42.720 --> 05:02:45.959
We all left dragons we care about over

05:02:45.959 --> 05:02:46.200
there.

05:02:46.259 --> 05:02:47.580
Hazel said.

05:02:47.700 --> 05:02:49.860
They're all in awful danger.

05:02:49.919 --> 05:02:53.220
That's true, Snowfall thought.

05:02:53.340 --> 05:02:55.020
Extremely true.

05:02:55.139 --> 05:02:58.799
We want to go back to rescue them, Hazel

05:02:58.799 --> 05:03:00.360
said, but we can't go back alone.

05:03:00.419 --> 05:03:04.200
Our numbers are no match for Queen Wasp

05:03:04.200 --> 05:03:06.479
especially once she mind controls

05:03:06.479 --> 05:03:07.680
everyone else in Pantala.

05:03:07.799 --> 05:03:09.240
We were hoping.

05:03:09.240 --> 05:03:11.520
Maybe you could help us.

05:03:11.580 --> 05:03:14.040
Oh.

05:03:14.099 --> 05:03:16.319
Ruby breathed out softly.

05:03:16.380 --> 05:03:19.500
You mean with armies, Thorn said.

05:03:19.560 --> 05:03:23.639
You want us to send our soldiers all the

05:03:23.639 --> 05:03:25.139
way to the other side of the ocean?

05:03:25.259 --> 05:03:26.639
Morehen said.

05:03:26.700 --> 05:03:30.900
To fight in a war that, I'm so sorry, but

05:03:30.900 --> 05:03:33.240
It has nothing to do with us.

05:03:33.299 --> 05:03:36.900
Nothing to do with us, Kibble burst out.

05:03:36.959 --> 05:03:38.939
Didn't you hear what's happening to those

05:03:38.939 --> 05:03:39.419
dragons?

05:03:39.540 --> 05:03:44.459
Yes, Morehen said, shooting a get your

05:03:44.459 --> 05:03:45.720
dragon under control.

05:03:45.779 --> 05:03:46.680
Look at Thorn.

05:03:46.740 --> 05:03:49.560
But our dragons are safe here.

05:03:49.680 --> 05:03:52.740
That thing over there doesn't even know

05:03:52.740 --> 05:03:53.159
about us.

05:03:53.220 --> 05:03:56.220
If we go rile it up.

05:03:56.279 --> 05:03:58.919
It might come back to attack us, and we

05:03:58.919 --> 05:04:00.479
could lose this whole continent too.

05:04:00.540 --> 05:04:02.520
At least right now.

05:04:02.580 --> 05:04:06.599
This is a safe place for us, and for

05:04:06.599 --> 05:04:06.840
you.

05:04:06.900 --> 05:04:11.639
Plus, we just got out of a war, Ruby said

05:04:11.639 --> 05:04:14.220
and a follow-up, almost war.

05:04:14.279 --> 05:04:17.220
Was that a dig at Snowfall?

05:04:17.340 --> 05:04:20.220
Was Ruby saying Snowfall was the kind of

05:04:20.220 --> 05:04:21.900
queen who would drag her tribe into war

05:04:21.900 --> 05:04:22.500
for no reason?

05:04:22.619 --> 05:04:25.319
Or was she saying that snowfall couldn't

05:04:25.319 --> 05:04:27.060
even finish a war, she tried to start.

05:04:27.119 --> 05:04:30.180
Dark Stalker didn't do anything to your

05:04:30.180 --> 05:04:32.159
tribe, Kibley pointed out.

05:04:32.220 --> 05:04:33.900
Oh.

05:04:33.959 --> 05:04:36.659
Was that the almost war she meant?

05:04:36.720 --> 05:04:39.240
Everyone against Dark Stalker?

05:04:39.299 --> 05:04:42.659
Well, if she was worried about that, she

05:04:42.659 --> 05:04:44.880
could have almost been a lot more helpful

05:04:44.880 --> 05:04:45.840
trying to fight him.

05:04:45.900 --> 05:04:49.500
I have a lot of dragons, who haven't

05:04:49.500 --> 05:04:51.060
recovered from the war of Sandwank

05:04:51.060 --> 05:04:52.740
succession, Ruby said.

05:04:52.799 --> 05:04:56.220
Or, to be honest, from my mother's reign

05:04:56.220 --> 05:04:58.020
as the super murdery queen of the

05:04:58.020 --> 05:04:58.380
mountains.

05:04:58.439 --> 05:05:00.360
I don't know if I can throw them back

05:05:00.360 --> 05:05:01.380
into another conflict.

05:05:01.500 --> 05:05:03.779
Both Morhen and her sister started

05:05:03.779 --> 05:05:04.380
nodding.

05:05:04.439 --> 05:05:08.040
We have a similar problem, Glory said

05:05:08.040 --> 05:05:10.439
looking thoughtful, as though she were

05:05:10.439 --> 05:05:11.759
running calculations in her head.

05:05:11.880 --> 05:05:14.819
Half my dragons are not cut out for war.

05:05:14.880 --> 05:05:17.279
They wouldn't be any help to you even if

05:05:17.279 --> 05:05:18.119
I tried to send them.

05:05:18.180 --> 05:05:19.680
And the other half?

05:05:19.680 --> 05:05:21.540
Have been through a lot lately.

05:05:21.599 --> 05:05:23.759
Oh, have they?

05:05:23.819 --> 05:05:26.040
Snowfall said isolately.

05:05:26.099 --> 05:05:27.360
Been to a lot?

05:05:27.419 --> 05:05:30.180
You mean such as raising an all knowing

05:05:30.180 --> 05:05:32.099
magic evil dictator from the dead?

05:05:32.159 --> 05:05:33.959
And then trying to help him murder a

05:05:33.959 --> 05:05:35.819
whole tribe and take over the continent?

05:05:36.060 --> 05:05:37.619
That does sound stressful.

05:05:37.680 --> 05:05:38.880
Poor things.

05:05:38.939 --> 05:05:40.619
What?

05:05:40.680 --> 05:05:42.900
Hazel said, bewildered.

05:05:43.020 --> 05:05:44.400
What?

05:05:44.520 --> 05:05:47.099
Cricket said at the same time, her eyes

05:05:47.099 --> 05:05:48.240
shining with curiosity.

05:05:48.299 --> 05:05:51.840
I think what we're all saying, Thorn

05:05:51.840 --> 05:05:54.000
interjected, is that it would be tough to

05:05:54.000 --> 05:05:56.400
justify sending our soldiers into such a

05:05:56.400 --> 05:05:58.439
dangerous situation, when it sounds like

05:05:58.439 --> 05:06:00.299
they could have their minds taken over

05:06:00.299 --> 05:06:02.040
exactly like your dragons have.

05:06:02.099 --> 05:06:03.479
Isn't that right?

05:06:03.540 --> 05:06:07.139
We don't know, Hazel said sadly.

05:06:07.200 --> 05:06:08.639
I'd guess.

05:06:08.700 --> 05:06:10.020
Probably.

05:06:10.080 --> 05:06:13.619
We can give you weapons, though, Gloria

05:06:13.619 --> 05:06:13.860
said.

05:06:13.919 --> 05:06:16.979
My tribe makes these blowguns with darts

05:06:16.979 --> 05:06:18.779
that can put dragons to sleep.

05:06:18.840 --> 05:06:21.180
You'll be able to stop your friends from

05:06:21.180 --> 05:06:23.220
hurting you without having to hurt them.

05:06:23.279 --> 05:06:25.439
Oh, wow.

05:06:25.500 --> 05:06:26.580
Cricket said.

05:06:26.639 --> 05:06:28.200
What's in the darts?

05:06:28.319 --> 05:06:30.000
Is it something that grows in your

05:06:30.000 --> 05:06:30.479
rainforest?

05:06:30.599 --> 05:06:31.259
Have you.

05:06:31.319 --> 05:06:33.840
Um, sorry, I'll ask you later.

05:06:33.900 --> 05:06:37.500
She subsided as Hazel put one talent over

05:06:37.500 --> 05:06:37.740
hers.

05:06:37.860 --> 05:06:40.680
We would appreciate that so much.

05:06:40.740 --> 05:06:42.479
Hazel said to Glory.

05:06:42.540 --> 05:06:45.540
Make a note, Glory said to her night

05:06:45.540 --> 05:06:45.959
wing.

05:06:46.020 --> 05:06:48.479
We can triple production starting tonight

05:06:48.479 --> 05:06:49.979
if we send a messenger back.

05:06:50.040 --> 05:06:53.759
We have some Dragon flame cacti, Ruby

05:06:53.759 --> 05:06:55.799
said, glancing awkwardly at Thorn.

05:06:55.860 --> 05:06:57.540
You're welcome to that.

05:06:57.599 --> 05:07:00.119
But I don't think we can send any of our

05:07:00.119 --> 05:07:00.779
soldiers.

05:07:00.840 --> 05:07:03.840
Wait, wait, Kibley said.

05:07:03.900 --> 05:07:06.659
Before you all decide, you have to hear

05:07:06.659 --> 05:07:07.619
Moon's prophecy.

05:07:07.740 --> 05:07:11.400
Tsunami let out a small huff, and a few

05:07:11.400 --> 05:07:13.799
other dragons looked uneasy, but Thorn

05:07:13.799 --> 05:07:15.659
and Glory beckoned Moon forward.

05:07:15.659 --> 05:07:18.000
A new prophecy?

05:07:18.119 --> 05:07:19.319
Glory asked.

05:07:19.380 --> 05:07:21.000
Moon nodded.

05:07:21.060 --> 05:07:24.000
It came with a vision that led me to Luna

05:07:24.000 --> 05:07:25.439
on the western coast.

05:07:25.500 --> 05:07:28.200
She cleared her throat and recited it

05:07:28.200 --> 05:07:28.439
again.

05:07:28.500 --> 05:07:31.319
Snowfall listened a bit more carefully

05:07:31.319 --> 05:07:31.680
this time.

05:07:31.740 --> 05:07:36.479
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire, to

05:07:36.479 --> 05:07:37.560
the land across the sea.

05:07:37.619 --> 05:07:40.740
We're dragons are poisoned, and dragons

05:07:40.740 --> 05:07:43.380
are dying, and no one can ever be free.

05:07:43.439 --> 05:07:46.740
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

05:07:46.799 --> 05:07:49.560
A secret hides within their book.

05:07:49.680 --> 05:07:54.299
A secret buried far below may save those

05:07:54.299 --> 05:07:55.139
brave enough to look.

05:07:55.200 --> 05:07:59.700
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

05:07:59.700 --> 05:08:02.279
to the dragons who flee from the hive.

05:08:02.340 --> 05:08:07.020
Face a great evil with talons united, or

05:08:07.020 --> 05:08:08.639
none of the tribes will survive.

05:08:08.700 --> 05:08:12.119
Moon glanced over at tsunami when she

05:08:12.119 --> 05:08:12.479
finished.

05:08:12.540 --> 05:08:14.580
Sorry, she added.

05:08:14.700 --> 05:08:16.560
They just happen, I swear.

05:08:16.619 --> 05:08:18.540
You all heard that, right?

05:08:18.599 --> 05:08:19.860
Kibley said.

05:08:19.919 --> 05:08:22.200
Turn your eyes to the land across the

05:08:22.200 --> 05:08:22.500
sea.

05:08:22.560 --> 05:08:26.040
Face a great evil with talons united.

05:08:26.099 --> 05:08:28.319
As cryptic prophecies go.

05:08:28.919 --> 05:08:30.419
I think this one is pretty clear.

05:08:30.540 --> 05:08:34.619
None of the tribes will survive, Glory

05:08:34.619 --> 05:08:37.319
echoed, meaning all of us over here as

05:08:37.319 --> 05:08:37.560
well.

05:08:37.619 --> 05:08:40.380
But how is that possible?

05:08:40.439 --> 05:08:41.279
Ribby said.

05:08:41.340 --> 05:08:44.220
How would the danger even get to us?

05:08:44.279 --> 05:08:45.959
I thought someone said it was almost

05:08:45.959 --> 05:08:47.520
impossible to cross the ocean.

05:08:47.580 --> 05:08:50.580
It is, Hazel agreed.

05:08:50.639 --> 05:08:53.340
We only made it because we found a map

05:08:53.340 --> 05:08:55.799
that was made a long time ago by clear

05:08:55.799 --> 05:08:56.220
sight.

05:08:56.279 --> 05:08:59.880
I think that's what a secret hides within

05:08:59.880 --> 05:09:01.200
their book means.

05:09:01.200 --> 05:09:04.380
It showed a trail of islands where we

05:09:04.380 --> 05:09:07.259
could rest on our way across the ocean.

05:09:07.319 --> 05:09:09.479
Without it, we wouldn't have survived.

05:09:09.540 --> 05:09:12.540
There you go, Ruby said.

05:09:12.599 --> 05:09:14.159
You had to use the map.

05:09:14.220 --> 05:09:16.740
The dragons over there, and whatever is

05:09:16.740 --> 05:09:18.779
controlling them, won't be able to follow

05:09:18.779 --> 05:09:19.080
you.

05:09:19.139 --> 05:09:21.240
So we're all safe here.

05:09:21.299 --> 05:09:23.279
That was it.

05:09:23.340 --> 05:09:25.020
That was it.

05:09:25.080 --> 05:09:27.659
That was the thing Cinnabar had said.

05:09:27.720 --> 05:09:32.040
Actually, we're not, Snowball

05:09:32.040 --> 05:09:32.580
interjected.

05:09:32.639 --> 05:09:35.639
She turned to Hazel, who looked as though

05:09:35.639 --> 05:09:37.619
she'd accidentally pushed them all into a

05:09:37.619 --> 05:09:40.319
Venus dragon trap, because you left a

05:09:40.319 --> 05:09:42.000
copy of the map there, didn't you?

05:09:42.060 --> 05:09:44.340
With IO and Cinnabar.

05:09:44.400 --> 05:09:45.840
What?

05:09:45.900 --> 05:09:47.040
Ruby cried.

05:09:47.099 --> 05:09:50.279
And Io and Cinnabar have been captured by

05:09:50.279 --> 05:09:52.560
Hive Wings, Snowfall informed her.

05:09:52.619 --> 05:09:55.979
So, Queen Wasp getting her claws on that

05:09:55.979 --> 05:09:56.220
map.

05:09:56.279 --> 05:09:58.680
It's only a matter of time.

05:09:58.740 --> 05:10:03.599
Chapter 16.

05:10:03.779 --> 05:10:09.840
Well, there was a lot of shouting and an

05:10:09.840 --> 05:10:12.959
unreasonable amount of questions, far too

05:10:12.959 --> 05:10:14.459
many of them directed at Snowfall.

05:10:14.520 --> 05:10:18.000
You had a vision about Io and Cinnabar?

05:10:18.060 --> 05:10:20.880
Cricket kept asking, did you see them get

05:10:20.880 --> 05:10:21.360
captured?

05:10:21.419 --> 05:10:23.520
Are you sure the High Wings got them?

05:10:23.580 --> 05:10:26.159
Unless my vision was of something that

05:10:26.159 --> 05:10:27.119
hasn't happened yet?

05:10:27.180 --> 05:10:28.439
Snowball said.

05:10:28.500 --> 05:10:30.000
That I don't know.

05:10:30.060 --> 05:10:33.240
But if it has happened, I definitely saw

05:10:33.240 --> 05:10:35.819
them going into Cicada Hive, which is

05:10:35.819 --> 05:10:37.380
definitely full of mind controlled

05:10:37.380 --> 05:10:40.020
dragons, like blue, lying in wait for

05:10:40.020 --> 05:10:40.200
them.

05:10:40.259 --> 05:10:43.439
We could try to warn them, tsunami

05:10:43.439 --> 05:10:43.979
interjected.

05:10:44.099 --> 05:10:47.159
We have a thing, I'll go try.

05:10:47.220 --> 05:10:50.159
She flew out of the cave and down the

05:10:50.159 --> 05:10:50.459
mountain.

05:10:50.520 --> 05:10:52.560
But that didn't help the noise levels

05:10:52.560 --> 05:10:54.060
because all the other queens were

05:10:54.060 --> 05:10:56.580
interrogating Hazel at once, and the poor

05:10:56.580 --> 05:10:58.259
leaf wing queen was trying to explain

05:10:58.259 --> 05:11:00.360
about the silk wings they'd hoped to

05:11:00.360 --> 05:11:00.720
rescue.

05:11:00.779 --> 05:11:04.740
Let's go, Snowfall said to Lynx.

05:11:04.799 --> 05:11:06.540
No one's going to make any great

05:11:06.540 --> 05:11:07.259
decisions today.

05:11:07.319 --> 05:11:10.799
It was trustful enough knowing that map

05:11:10.799 --> 05:11:12.180
was floating around on the other

05:11:12.180 --> 05:11:12.720
continent.

05:11:12.779 --> 05:11:15.900
Snowfall did not want to add explaining

05:11:15.900 --> 05:11:18.540
her visions, and by extension, the cursed

05:11:18.540 --> 05:11:21.240
ring she'd blithely put on, to all the

05:11:21.240 --> 05:11:23.459
queens, to the list of things stressing

05:11:23.459 --> 05:11:24.000
her out today.

05:11:24.060 --> 05:11:27.360
She slipped out of the cave quietly, and

05:11:27.360 --> 05:11:28.259
Lynx followed her.

05:11:28.319 --> 05:11:31.259
They flew down the mountain, and Snowfall

05:11:31.259 --> 05:11:33.360
found her wings turning toward Winter's

05:11:33.360 --> 05:11:35.459
corner of Sanctuary, where the scavenger

05:11:35.459 --> 05:11:36.299
enclosure was.

05:11:36.299 --> 05:11:40.560
Must be nice to be a scavenger. snowfall

05:11:40.560 --> 05:11:40.979
thought.

05:11:41.040 --> 05:11:44.340
No problems in the world, no scary things

05:11:44.340 --> 05:11:46.319
coming from across the ocean to steal

05:11:46.319 --> 05:11:46.979
your brains.

05:11:47.040 --> 05:11:50.340
She couldn't believe Hazel had left a

05:11:50.340 --> 05:11:51.840
copy of the map with IO.

05:11:51.900 --> 05:11:53.819
What kind of nitwit?

05:11:53.880 --> 05:11:57.360
But then she thought of Tao, and Jewel

05:11:57.360 --> 05:12:00.779
and Grayling, and Blue's sad mothers, and

05:12:00.779 --> 05:12:03.000
then Io's fervent, desperate hope to save

05:12:03.000 --> 05:12:05.159
them all swept through her so strongly.

05:12:05.220 --> 05:12:07.080
It felt like her own emotion.

05:12:07.139 --> 05:12:09.419
As ridiculous as that was.

05:12:09.479 --> 05:12:13.740
Maybe WASP won't find the map, but how

05:12:13.740 --> 05:12:14.700
will anyone else get it?

05:12:14.759 --> 05:12:18.000
If Iowa and Cinnabar are captured now, and

05:12:18.000 --> 05:12:19.619
they're the only ones who know where it's

05:12:19.619 --> 05:12:19.919
hidden.

05:12:19.979 --> 05:12:21.479
What can we do?

05:12:21.540 --> 05:12:23.279
How can we save them?

05:12:23.340 --> 05:12:27.299
Why do I care about this so much?

05:12:27.360 --> 05:12:30.840
She tried half-heartedly to pull off a

05:12:30.840 --> 05:12:31.200
ring again?

05:12:31.319 --> 05:12:32.459
With no success?

05:12:32.520 --> 05:12:35.580
They landed on the lake side of the

05:12:35.580 --> 05:12:37.740
enclosure, and Snowfall caught herself a

05:12:37.740 --> 05:12:40.020
fish, while Lynx told Winter everything

05:12:40.020 --> 05:12:41.520
that had happened during the council.

05:12:41.580 --> 05:12:44.580
I think your visions are more helpful

05:12:44.580 --> 05:12:45.360
than you realize.

05:12:45.479 --> 05:12:47.700
Lang said to Snowfall as she finished.

05:12:47.759 --> 05:12:49.380
Rubbish.

05:12:49.439 --> 05:12:51.299
Hazel would have told them about the map

05:12:51.299 --> 05:12:53.220
without me, Snowfall argued.

05:12:53.279 --> 05:12:55.680
She's all honest and tortured like that.

05:12:55.740 --> 05:12:58.380
But you know what's happening over there

05:12:58.380 --> 05:12:59.639
Link said.

05:12:59.700 --> 05:13:01.860
You're the only one who can see what's

05:13:01.860 --> 05:13:03.779
happened to all those dragons, since

05:13:03.779 --> 05:13:05.340
Hazel's group left.

05:13:05.400 --> 05:13:08.099
I think it would be much more useful.

05:13:08.159 --> 05:13:10.680
If the ring actually answered some of my

05:13:10.680 --> 05:13:13.619
actual questions, Snowfall hissed to the

05:13:13.619 --> 05:13:14.040
Opal.

05:13:14.099 --> 05:13:16.979
Have you tried lying down and closing

05:13:16.979 --> 05:13:18.659
your eyes and telling it to give you a

05:13:18.659 --> 05:13:19.020
vision?

05:13:19.080 --> 05:13:20.159
Winter asked.

05:13:20.220 --> 05:13:22.979
No, Snowfall barked.

05:13:23.040 --> 05:13:26.099
I mean, sort of, when I went to sleep

05:13:26.099 --> 05:13:28.380
last night, but did it listen to me?

05:13:28.439 --> 05:13:29.400
No, it did not.

05:13:29.459 --> 05:13:32.220
Maybe it's showing you the most important

05:13:32.220 --> 05:13:33.840
moments happening in the whole world.

05:13:33.900 --> 05:13:35.520
Length suggested.

05:13:35.580 --> 05:13:38.099
That seems like something a queen might

05:13:38.099 --> 05:13:39.119
have asked for, right?

05:13:39.180 --> 05:13:41.939
Perhaps you could try summoning a vision

05:13:41.939 --> 05:13:42.119
now?

05:13:42.240 --> 05:13:43.259
Winter said.

05:13:43.319 --> 05:13:45.659
Maybe it would tell you what happened to

05:13:45.659 --> 05:13:48.360
IO and Cinnabar, or the map, or if they

05:13:48.360 --> 05:13:49.080
really got caught.

05:13:49.139 --> 05:13:51.419
Snowfall side.

05:13:51.479 --> 05:13:52.439
Fine.

05:13:52.500 --> 05:13:53.520
Fine.

05:13:53.580 --> 05:13:56.700
I hate this idea, but if I have to have a

05:13:56.700 --> 05:13:58.680
vision, I'd rather have it when it's

05:13:58.680 --> 05:13:59.700
convenient for me anyway.

05:13:59.759 --> 05:14:03.000
She looked around and spotted a tall, flat

05:14:03.000 --> 05:14:04.139
boulder in the shade of the trees.

05:14:04.200 --> 05:14:07.500
In a moment, she was on top of it, lying

05:14:07.500 --> 05:14:08.279
on the cool stone.

05:14:08.340 --> 05:14:10.799
From up there she could see the little

05:14:10.799 --> 05:14:12.659
scavengers scampering around its den.

05:14:12.720 --> 05:14:14.759
It was pretty cute.

05:14:14.819 --> 05:14:18.419
Cuter than your average squirrel, not as

05:14:18.419 --> 05:14:19.500
cute as a polar bear cob.

05:14:19.560 --> 05:14:23.580
Stop staring at me, she yelled at Links

05:14:23.580 --> 05:14:23.939
in winter.

05:14:24.000 --> 05:14:25.979
Mind your own business.

05:14:26.040 --> 05:14:28.799
They turned away quickly, and started

05:14:28.799 --> 05:14:30.299
walking around the outside of the

05:14:30.299 --> 05:14:30.779
enclosure.

05:14:30.840 --> 05:14:34.080
Grumbling to herself, Snowfall rested her

05:14:34.080 --> 05:14:36.180
chin on her talons, took a deep breath

05:14:36.180 --> 05:14:37.080
and closed her eyes.

05:14:37.139 --> 05:14:40.619
What happened to Io and Cinnabar?

05:14:40.680 --> 05:14:42.000
She asked the ring.

05:14:42.060 --> 05:14:43.680
Is the map safe?

05:14:43.740 --> 05:14:45.959
Does queen wasp know about it?

05:14:46.020 --> 05:14:49.380
She waited to fall into someone else's

05:14:49.380 --> 05:14:49.740
scales.

05:14:49.799 --> 05:14:51.599
Nothing happened.

05:14:51.659 --> 05:14:54.479
And then some more nothing happened.

05:14:54.540 --> 05:14:57.540
Snowfall frowned and buried her head

05:14:57.540 --> 05:14:58.200
under one wing.

05:14:58.259 --> 05:15:00.720
She was definitely still herself.

05:15:00.779 --> 05:15:03.599
She had many very strong snowfall

05:15:03.599 --> 05:15:06.000
emotions barging around inside her, such

05:15:06.000 --> 05:15:08.040
as, for instance, fury.

05:15:08.279 --> 05:15:09.959
What was wrong with this ring?

05:15:10.020 --> 05:15:12.479
Why couldn't it do what it was told?

05:15:12.540 --> 05:15:15.479
Would it work properly for a better

05:15:15.479 --> 05:15:16.020
queen?

05:15:16.080 --> 05:15:18.720
Is it trying to tell me it also thinks

05:15:18.720 --> 05:15:19.740
I'm terrible at this?

05:15:19.799 --> 05:15:22.560
Snowfall waited for several more

05:15:22.560 --> 05:15:25.080
heartbeats of torture and insecurity and

05:15:25.080 --> 05:15:27.720
boredom, but she seemed to be lodged

05:15:27.720 --> 05:15:29.459
firmly inside her own anxious brain.

05:15:29.520 --> 05:15:32.279
She sighed and opened her eyes.

05:15:32.340 --> 05:15:35.340
Links and winter were perched on top of

05:15:35.340 --> 05:15:37.200
the scavenger fence, staring at her

05:15:37.200 --> 05:15:37.439
again.

05:15:37.500 --> 05:15:39.659
Did it work?

05:15:39.720 --> 05:15:40.740
Langs called.

05:15:40.799 --> 05:15:42.119
What did you see?

05:15:42.180 --> 05:15:45.119
That was very boring and frustrating

05:15:45.119 --> 05:15:46.560
Snowfall shouted.

05:15:46.619 --> 05:15:48.000
And it did not work.

05:15:48.060 --> 05:15:50.880
Probably because you were staring at me.

05:15:50.939 --> 05:15:52.319
Go away.

05:15:52.380 --> 05:15:54.599
They exchanged a glance.

05:15:54.659 --> 05:15:57.000
Alright, Winter said.

05:15:57.060 --> 05:15:59.880
We're going to find Tsunami and Kibli.

05:15:59.939 --> 05:16:01.680
Will you be okay, Jang here?

05:16:01.740 --> 05:16:03.360
She glared at him.

05:16:03.479 --> 05:16:05.220
Why wouldn't I be?

05:16:05.340 --> 05:16:07.919
We could send your guards over.

05:16:07.979 --> 05:16:09.240
Links offered.

05:16:09.299 --> 05:16:13.139
Oh, Snowfall said, remembering she was

05:16:13.139 --> 05:16:14.520
supposed to be guarded at all times.

05:16:14.580 --> 05:16:16.860
Yes, yes, sure.

05:16:16.919 --> 05:16:17.580
No rush.

05:16:17.639 --> 05:16:20.220
Can you keep an eye on pumpkin for me?

05:16:20.279 --> 05:16:21.299
Winter asked.

05:16:21.360 --> 05:16:23.939
Snowfall flicked her tail across the

05:16:23.939 --> 05:16:25.439
smooth coolness of the boulder.

05:16:25.500 --> 05:16:30.060
Do not tell me, she said, that you named

05:16:30.060 --> 05:16:31.139
your scavenger.

05:16:31.259 --> 05:16:33.840
And moreover, that you chose the name

05:16:33.840 --> 05:16:35.159
Pumpkin.

05:16:35.220 --> 05:16:39.240
I think it's adorable, Lang said, grinning

05:16:39.240 --> 05:16:41.040
at Winter, who looked gratifyingly

05:16:41.040 --> 05:16:41.520
embarrassed.

05:16:41.580 --> 05:16:45.000
I thought you wanted us not to eat your

05:16:45.000 --> 05:16:46.619
critter, Snowfall said.

05:16:46.680 --> 05:16:49.619
So why would you name her after food?

05:16:49.680 --> 05:16:52.799
It's supposed to be cute, he said.

05:16:52.860 --> 05:16:54.479
Because she's cute.

05:16:54.540 --> 05:16:56.639
Come on, winter.

05:16:56.700 --> 05:16:58.319
We'll be here forever if you start

05:16:58.319 --> 05:16:59.400
talking scavengers.

05:16:59.459 --> 05:17:02.279
Lynx batted his wing with hers, and they

05:17:02.279 --> 05:17:03.479
lifted up into the air.

05:17:03.540 --> 05:17:05.700
She's been acting a little funny.

05:17:05.759 --> 05:17:07.740
Winters said to Snowfall.

05:17:07.799 --> 05:17:09.840
She might be planning to break out of her

05:17:09.840 --> 05:17:11.099
enclosure again.

05:17:11.159 --> 05:17:12.180
If you wouldn't mind.

05:17:12.299 --> 05:17:14.220
Yes, yes.

05:17:14.279 --> 05:17:16.680
Snowfall said, waving him away.

05:17:16.740 --> 05:17:18.060
I'll watch her.

05:17:18.119 --> 05:17:19.619
Thank you.

05:17:19.680 --> 05:17:22.740
Your Majesty, he called, and the 2 of

05:17:22.740 --> 05:17:25.020
them flew away, leaving Snowfall in

05:17:25.020 --> 05:17:26.159
blessed silence.

05:17:26.159 --> 05:17:29.159
She watched the scavengers scamper

05:17:29.159 --> 05:17:29.400
around.

05:17:29.459 --> 05:17:31.799
Piling leaves and sticks by the fence.

05:17:31.919 --> 05:17:34.380
She tried to think about all the visions

05:17:34.380 --> 05:17:35.220
she'd had so far.

05:17:35.279 --> 05:17:38.520
Why had the ring chosen those dragons to

05:17:38.520 --> 05:17:38.880
show her?

05:17:38.939 --> 05:17:41.220
What was the meaning of any of this?

05:17:41.279 --> 05:17:43.560
Across the clearing.

05:17:43.619 --> 05:17:45.840
The bushes started wrestling in a very

05:17:45.840 --> 05:17:46.380
odd way.

05:17:46.439 --> 05:17:49.740
In fact, they were more than wrestling.

05:17:49.799 --> 05:17:51.959
They were thrashing about as though all

05:17:51.959 --> 05:17:53.639
the branches were wrestling furiously

05:17:53.639 --> 05:17:54.180
with one another.

05:17:54.240 --> 05:17:56.700
And then, all of a sudden, there was a

05:17:56.700 --> 05:17:57.659
very loud squeak.

05:17:57.720 --> 05:18:00.779
And at the same time, a dragon burst out

05:18:00.779 --> 05:18:02.520
of the leaves and careened into the

05:18:02.520 --> 05:18:02.759
open.

05:18:02.819 --> 05:18:06.720
He fell over and sat there, blinking for

05:18:06.720 --> 05:18:09.000
a moment, then hopped up to his feet and

05:18:09.000 --> 05:18:09.659
shook his wings.

05:18:09.720 --> 05:18:13.200
He lifted his head, saw snowfall watching

05:18:13.200 --> 05:18:16.560
him, and grinned a huge, ridiculous, sweet

05:18:16.560 --> 05:18:18.060
as baby hedgehog's grin.

05:18:18.180 --> 05:18:21.240
Good day, he cried.

05:18:21.299 --> 05:18:22.319
This day.

05:18:22.380 --> 05:18:23.340
So good.

05:18:23.400 --> 05:18:24.240
Right?

05:18:24.299 --> 05:18:26.520
She squinted at him.

05:18:26.580 --> 05:18:29.099
He was kind of weird looking.

05:18:29.159 --> 05:18:32.639
Maybe he was one of the many hybrids here

05:18:32.639 --> 05:18:34.680
in Sanctuary, although he looked older

05:18:34.680 --> 05:18:36.599
than the little dragonette she'd seen

05:18:36.659 --> 05:18:39.840
older than her, actually, if she had to

05:18:39.840 --> 05:18:40.080
guess.

05:18:40.139 --> 05:18:44.099
His gales were not quite skywing, not

05:18:44.099 --> 05:18:46.680
quite sandwing, but somewhere in between

05:18:46.680 --> 05:18:49.020
a sort of pale orange.

05:18:49.080 --> 05:18:52.259
He had no tail barb though, and his eyes

05:18:52.259 --> 05:18:53.400
were a washed out blue.

05:18:53.459 --> 05:18:56.880
He didn't look at all dangerous, partly

05:18:56.880 --> 05:18:58.979
thanks to the crooked daisy chain wound

05:18:58.979 --> 05:18:59.639
around his horns.

05:18:59.759 --> 05:19:02.700
Can I help you?

05:19:02.819 --> 05:19:03.900
Snfall asked.

05:19:03.959 --> 05:19:08.639
I've come to hear to bargain for this, uh

05:19:08.639 --> 05:19:10.860
delicious scavenger, the dragon

05:19:10.860 --> 05:19:11.279
declared.

05:19:11.400 --> 05:19:14.159
He waved one wing dramatically at the

05:19:14.159 --> 05:19:14.580
enclosure.

05:19:14.639 --> 05:19:16.560
Uh-huh.

05:19:16.619 --> 05:19:18.659
Snowfall said skeptically.

05:19:18.720 --> 05:19:21.540
I don't think she's for sale.

05:19:21.659 --> 05:19:25.979
But I just adore scavenger.

05:19:26.099 --> 05:19:28.380
Uh, chewing, he said.

05:19:28.439 --> 05:19:31.139
He made a weird, grimacy face.

05:19:31.259 --> 05:19:34.080
Chewing scavengers, meat.

05:19:34.139 --> 05:19:35.040
Yum.

05:19:35.099 --> 05:19:37.560
Want to eat them all day?

05:19:37.619 --> 05:19:38.819
Chomp, chomp.

05:19:38.880 --> 05:19:39.119
Yes.

05:19:39.180 --> 05:19:43.439
So go hunt down one of your own, Snowfall

05:19:43.439 --> 05:19:43.799
said.

05:19:43.860 --> 05:19:47.159
Somehow, the more he talked, the less she

05:19:47.159 --> 05:19:48.659
believed he actually wanted to eat the

05:19:48.659 --> 05:19:49.200
scavenger.

05:19:49.259 --> 05:19:54.659
I would, he said, but I. He trailed off

05:19:54.659 --> 05:19:56.459
and shot a panicked look at the bushes.

05:19:56.520 --> 05:20:00.240
Um, don't want to?

05:20:00.299 --> 05:20:03.180
Snowfall propped her chin on her front

05:20:03.180 --> 05:20:03.900
talons.

05:20:03.959 --> 05:20:06.479
This was the most entertainingly strange

05:20:06.479 --> 05:20:08.279
thing that had happened to her in days.

05:20:08.340 --> 05:20:12.180
You'd rather buy a scavenger that's not

05:20:12.180 --> 05:20:13.799
for sale than go catch your own.

05:20:13.860 --> 05:20:15.900
Could it be for sale?

05:20:15.959 --> 05:20:17.099
He said hopefully.

05:20:17.159 --> 05:20:19.080
I have blueberries?

05:20:19.139 --> 05:20:20.759
Snowfall laughed.

05:20:20.880 --> 05:20:24.000
Winter is not going to sell you his pet

05:20:24.000 --> 05:20:25.919
even for all the blueberries in the

05:20:25.919 --> 05:20:26.099
world.

05:20:26.220 --> 05:20:28.500
Oh, he said.

05:20:28.560 --> 05:20:30.240
Oh.

05:20:30.360 --> 05:20:34.020
He shot a look at the bushes like, I told

05:20:34.020 --> 05:20:34.919
you so, bushes.

05:20:35.040 --> 05:20:36.540
She's a pet?

05:20:36.599 --> 05:20:38.880
Not for chewy delicious eating.

05:20:38.939 --> 05:20:41.939
Snowfall couldn't begin to guess why this

05:20:41.939 --> 05:20:44.099
dragon spoke so oddly now and then.

05:20:44.220 --> 05:20:45.659
Yep.

05:20:45.720 --> 05:20:47.700
It's a pet, she said.

05:20:47.759 --> 05:20:50.220
My cousin loves these critters.

05:20:50.279 --> 05:20:52.020
He's been trying to catch a good one for

05:20:52.020 --> 05:20:52.439
ages.

05:20:52.560 --> 05:20:54.720
And she's a good one?

05:20:54.720 --> 05:20:57.779
he said, looking as pleased as if she had

05:20:57.779 --> 05:20:58.500
complimented him.

05:20:58.560 --> 05:21:03.000
Well, she is energetic, Snowfall said

05:21:03.000 --> 05:21:04.380
picking over at her again.

05:21:04.439 --> 05:21:07.139
The scavenger was leaning innocently

05:21:07.139 --> 05:21:09.540
against the far wall, spinning a stick in

05:21:09.540 --> 05:21:10.020
her paws.

05:21:10.080 --> 05:21:12.840
And Winter says she's a good mimic.

05:21:12.840 --> 05:21:15.240
She's made some very dragon like noises

05:21:15.240 --> 05:21:17.459
at him, which made him think she's

05:21:17.459 --> 05:21:18.360
terribly clever.

05:21:18.419 --> 05:21:21.119
The stranger gave a little snort of

05:21:21.119 --> 05:21:21.419
laughter.

05:21:21.479 --> 05:21:23.580
Hmm, he said.

05:21:23.639 --> 05:21:28.439
What if she doesn't want to be his pet?

05:21:28.560 --> 05:21:30.959
Snowfall tilted her head at him.

05:21:31.020 --> 05:21:33.599
Well, we can't exactly ask her.

05:21:33.659 --> 05:21:35.700
I'm sure she's perfectly happy.

05:21:35.759 --> 05:21:38.340
He feeds her like twice a day.

05:21:38.400 --> 05:21:42.840
What if I gave him a different pet, a

05:21:42.840 --> 05:21:43.439
better pet?

05:21:43.500 --> 05:21:45.900
the odd dragon suggested, with a

05:21:45.900 --> 05:21:47.580
triumphant flourish of his wings.

05:21:47.639 --> 05:21:50.220
I am quite sure he...

05:21:50.700 --> 05:21:52.560
How about a snail?

05:21:52.680 --> 05:21:54.299
The dragon cried.

05:21:54.360 --> 05:21:57.000
With a kind of rapturous delight, Snowfall

05:21:57.000 --> 05:21:59.520
had only ever seen on dragonettes tasting

05:21:59.520 --> 05:22:00.659
ice cream for the 1st time.

05:22:00.720 --> 05:22:04.680
A snail, Snowfall echoed.

05:22:04.799 --> 05:22:09.000
Snails are amazing, he said adoringly.

05:22:09.060 --> 05:22:10.740
Have you seen them?

05:22:10.799 --> 05:22:14.700
I have seen snails?

05:22:14.819 --> 05:22:16.380
Yes, she said.

05:22:16.439 --> 05:22:19.919
Queen Coral had served sea snails during

05:22:19.919 --> 05:22:22.259
her visit to the kingdom of the sea, but

05:22:22.259 --> 05:22:24.060
Snowfall had a feeling this dragon's

05:22:24.060 --> 05:22:25.680
heart would explode if she told him

05:22:25.680 --> 05:22:26.040
that.

05:22:26.099 --> 05:22:29.340
Or a turtle, he shouted.

05:22:29.400 --> 05:22:31.200
I could give him a turtle.

05:22:31.259 --> 05:22:34.619
Ah, don't you love turtles with their

05:22:34.619 --> 05:22:36.720
little flippery flippers and their sweet

05:22:36.720 --> 05:22:39.180
little shells and their tiny heads?

05:22:39.240 --> 05:22:41.159
Have you seen their tiny heads?

05:22:41.159 --> 05:22:42.779
They look like they're smiling.

05:22:42.840 --> 05:22:44.819
Little tiny turtle smiles.

05:22:44.939 --> 05:22:46.619
Wouldn't he love a turtle?

05:22:46.680 --> 05:22:48.299
He would not.

05:22:48.419 --> 05:22:50.400
Snowfall said positively.

05:22:50.459 --> 05:22:53.279
I must say, it sounds like you should get

05:22:53.279 --> 05:22:53.880
a turtle though.

05:22:53.939 --> 05:22:57.240
Yes, he said dreamily.

05:22:57.299 --> 05:23:00.180
That is exactly what I have been saying.

05:23:00.180 --> 05:23:02.639
He shot another Did you hear that

05:23:02.639 --> 05:23:03.180
bushes?

05:23:03.240 --> 05:23:04.680
Look at the shrubbery.

05:23:04.740 --> 05:23:07.560
How about you go get a turtle then

05:23:07.560 --> 05:23:10.380
Snowball said, and leave this scavenger

05:23:10.380 --> 05:23:11.520
to my obsessed cousin.

05:23:11.580 --> 05:23:15.599
Oh, he said, shaking his head as if he'd

05:23:15.599 --> 05:23:16.860
completely forgotten what he was there

05:23:16.860 --> 05:23:17.099
for.

05:23:17.159 --> 05:23:18.540
Right.

05:23:18.599 --> 05:23:19.319
No, no.

05:23:19.439 --> 05:23:21.479
I would like this scavenger very much.

05:23:21.540 --> 05:23:22.919
This one.

05:23:22.979 --> 05:23:23.700
Please.

05:23:23.759 --> 05:23:26.759
The bushes behind him made some highly

05:23:26.759 --> 05:23:28.380
suspicious squeaking noises.

05:23:28.439 --> 05:23:30.779
Snowfall squinted at them.

05:23:30.900 --> 05:23:33.659
Did he already have a scavenger?

05:23:33.720 --> 05:23:35.520
Maybe he collected them.

05:23:35.580 --> 05:23:38.939
Maybe he was Winter's dream brand.

05:23:39.000 --> 05:23:41.700
If you're so interested in scavengers.

05:23:41.759 --> 05:23:44.159
Wait and talk to Winter about them, she

05:23:44.159 --> 05:23:44.700
suggested.

05:23:44.759 --> 05:23:47.040
He can tell you everything he's learned

05:23:47.040 --> 05:23:49.799
from studying them if you have 20 days to

05:23:49.799 --> 05:23:51.659
listen to some outlandish theories.

05:23:51.779 --> 05:23:55.319
Can't I please have this scavenger?

05:23:55.380 --> 05:23:58.979
He said, with enormous baby seal eyes.

05:23:59.040 --> 05:24:01.080
Please, please, please?

05:24:01.200 --> 05:24:03.959
Being cute doesn't work on me.

05:24:04.020 --> 05:24:06.479
Nice try. she barked.

05:24:06.540 --> 05:24:09.240
I am the queen of the ice wings, and I

05:24:09.240 --> 05:24:09.900
have told you no.

05:24:10.020 --> 05:24:11.759
Queen of the what?

05:24:11.880 --> 05:24:12.779
Really?

05:24:12.840 --> 05:24:13.740
he said.

05:24:13.860 --> 05:24:15.599
Yes, really?

05:24:15.659 --> 05:24:17.400
How do you not know that?

05:24:17.520 --> 05:24:19.080
She lashed her tail.

05:24:19.139 --> 05:24:21.959
The settlement is full of queens right

05:24:21.959 --> 05:24:24.419
now, so you should practice being a

05:24:24.419 --> 05:24:26.340
little less adorable and a little more

05:24:26.340 --> 05:24:26.880
respectful.

05:24:26.939 --> 05:24:29.759
What the heck are you anyway?

05:24:29.819 --> 05:24:31.200
A hybrid of what?

05:24:31.259 --> 05:24:33.360
A startling thought struck her.

05:24:33.419 --> 05:24:36.599
Could he possibly be an ice wing sky wing

05:24:36.599 --> 05:24:37.020
hybrid?

05:24:37.080 --> 05:24:39.479
Not a hybrid, he said.

05:24:39.599 --> 05:24:41.819
Just a funny looking sky wing.

05:24:41.880 --> 05:24:44.220
He turned and hissed the bushes.

05:24:44.279 --> 05:24:46.200
She thinks I'm adorable.

05:24:46.259 --> 05:24:49.919
I do not. 3 moons.

05:24:50.040 --> 05:24:51.540
Who are you talking to?

05:24:51.599 --> 05:24:53.939
No one, he blurted.

05:24:54.000 --> 05:24:55.740
Sorry, nothing.

05:24:55.799 --> 05:24:56.459
Never mind.

05:24:56.520 --> 05:24:58.619
I am not needing the scavenger after

05:24:58.619 --> 05:24:58.860
all.

05:24:58.919 --> 05:25:00.000
Everything great.

05:25:00.060 --> 05:25:01.080
Nice to meet you.

05:25:01.139 --> 05:25:01.979
Bye forever.

05:25:02.040 --> 05:25:05.040
He turned and bolted into the woods.

05:25:05.099 --> 05:25:07.500
There was a bit more thrashing around in

05:25:07.500 --> 05:25:09.779
the greenery, and then Snowfall saw his

05:25:09.779 --> 05:25:11.400
tail darting away through the trees.

05:25:11.520 --> 05:25:15.000
Weirdest dragon of all time.

05:25:15.119 --> 05:25:18.479
But she had to admit, this feeling of

05:25:18.479 --> 05:25:21.240
amusement and slight confusion was

05:25:21.240 --> 05:25:23.340
preferable to the overwhelming anxiety

05:25:23.340 --> 05:25:24.479
she normally lived in.

05:25:24.540 --> 05:25:27.240
She wouldn't mind being distracted from

05:25:27.240 --> 05:25:28.560
the end of the world by him again.

05:25:28.619 --> 05:25:32.159
Shaking her head, she glanced over to

05:25:32.159 --> 05:25:33.000
check the enclosure.

05:25:33.060 --> 05:25:36.000
She should have noticed that it had

05:25:36.000 --> 05:25:37.020
gotten very quiet.

05:25:37.080 --> 05:25:39.959
She should have been more suspicious of a

05:25:39.959 --> 05:25:42.119
scavenger standing so still for once.

05:25:42.180 --> 05:25:45.360
She might have guessed that the scavenger

05:25:45.360 --> 05:25:47.459
had been standing right there to hide the

05:25:47.459 --> 05:25:48.779
new hole in the fence.

05:25:48.779 --> 05:25:52.259
If she had, she might have caught the

05:25:52.259 --> 05:25:53.639
scavenger before it escaped.

05:25:53.700 --> 05:25:54.959
But it was too late.

05:25:55.020 --> 05:25:58.139
Winter's pet was gone.

05:25:58.259 --> 05:26:02.759
Chapter 17.

05:26:03.000 --> 05:26:06.060
Oh, walruses.

05:26:06.119 --> 05:26:07.619
Snowball hissed.

05:26:07.680 --> 05:26:10.380
This was the last thing she needed to

05:26:10.380 --> 05:26:11.040
deal with right now.

05:26:11.099 --> 05:26:14.639
She flew down into the enclosure and

05:26:14.639 --> 05:26:16.619
marched around it, double checking.

05:26:16.680 --> 05:26:20.099
Yes, pumpkin was absolutely gone.

05:26:20.159 --> 05:26:22.500
The hole was just big enough for a

05:26:22.500 --> 05:26:24.599
scavenger, partly tunneled under the

05:26:24.599 --> 05:26:26.400
fence, and partly hacked out of the

05:26:26.400 --> 05:26:26.580
wood.

05:26:26.700 --> 05:26:30.060
Outside the fence, there was a scramble

05:26:30.060 --> 05:26:31.979
of marks in the dirt where the scavenger

05:26:31.979 --> 05:26:34.259
would have emerged, but it was hard to

05:26:34.259 --> 05:26:35.939
tell what kinds of marks they were.

05:26:36.000 --> 05:26:37.860
Hang on.

05:26:37.919 --> 05:26:41.520
Was that dragon distracting me so he

05:26:41.520 --> 05:26:42.299
could steal her?

05:26:42.360 --> 05:26:45.900
But he hadn't moved from his spot while

05:26:45.900 --> 05:26:46.560
they talked.

05:26:46.619 --> 05:26:48.599
So he must have had an accomplice.

05:26:48.659 --> 05:26:50.340
Another dragon?

05:26:50.400 --> 05:26:53.159
Why would 2 dragons go to all the trouble

05:26:53.159 --> 05:26:55.860
of stealing one scavenger, who was barely

05:26:55.860 --> 05:26:57.240
enough of a meal for one of them?

05:26:57.299 --> 05:27:00.240
Snowfall frowned at the marks in the

05:27:00.240 --> 05:27:00.540
dirt.

05:27:00.599 --> 05:27:03.060
She didn't see anything that looked like

05:27:03.060 --> 05:27:04.799
a talon or tail had made it.

05:27:04.860 --> 05:27:07.560
And the scavenger must have been digging

05:27:07.560 --> 05:27:08.639
from her side too.

05:27:08.700 --> 05:27:11.340
Unlucky that she escaped right into a

05:27:11.340 --> 05:27:12.299
dragon's claws.

05:27:12.419 --> 05:27:14.220
If that's what happened.

05:27:14.279 --> 05:27:17.040
This really made no sense.

05:27:17.099 --> 05:27:20.099
Snowfall sighed deeply.

05:27:20.159 --> 05:27:23.040
She should probably go into the forest

05:27:23.040 --> 05:27:26.279
and try to catch that dragon just in case

05:27:26.279 --> 05:27:27.299
he did have pumpkin.

05:27:27.419 --> 05:27:30.659
Grumbling to herself, she set off into

05:27:30.659 --> 05:27:31.080
the trees.

05:27:31.200 --> 05:27:33.479
Should I wait for my guards?

05:27:33.540 --> 05:27:37.380
No, she could handle an overly smiley

05:27:37.380 --> 05:27:39.119
dragon who went into raptures over

05:27:39.119 --> 05:27:39.779
turtles.

05:27:39.840 --> 05:27:40.860
No problem.

05:27:40.919 --> 05:27:44.939
Ooh, especially if she used her stealth

05:27:44.939 --> 05:27:45.720
armbands.

05:27:45.779 --> 05:27:48.240
She set them gleefully to make herself

05:27:48.240 --> 05:27:50.279
invisible and darted in the direction

05:27:50.279 --> 05:27:52.500
where she'd last seen his tail.

05:27:52.560 --> 05:27:55.380
It didn't take long before she heard his

05:27:55.380 --> 05:27:57.060
voice burbling away up ahead.

05:27:57.180 --> 05:28:00.840
Snowfall slowed to a stealthier pace, and

05:28:00.840 --> 05:28:01.619
crept toward him.

05:28:01.680 --> 05:28:04.200
He sounded utterly insane.

05:28:04.259 --> 05:28:07.860
Whatever he was saying was half words

05:28:07.860 --> 05:28:10.439
half yips and chitters, and meeping

05:28:10.439 --> 05:28:12.900
noises, as if his brain kept turning into

05:28:12.900 --> 05:28:14.340
a chipmunk mid sentence.

05:28:14.400 --> 05:28:17.040
She slipped through the trees to get

05:28:17.040 --> 05:28:19.740
ahead of him, which wasn't hard, as he

05:28:19.740 --> 05:28:21.900
was just ambling along chatting to thin

05:28:21.900 --> 05:28:22.139
air.

05:28:22.200 --> 05:28:24.840
There were clearly no other dragons with

05:28:24.840 --> 05:28:27.240
him, so perhaps his accomplice had gone

05:28:27.240 --> 05:28:27.959
in a different direction.

05:28:28.020 --> 05:28:31.619
Or perhaps she was wrong, and this dragon

05:28:31.619 --> 05:28:34.020
hadn't stolen pumpkin, but she smelled

05:28:34.020 --> 05:28:36.419
scavengers somewhere nearby, and his

05:28:36.419 --> 05:28:38.880
behavior had been very suspicious.

05:28:39.000 --> 05:28:41.340
So she didn't feel guilty about the heart

05:28:41.340 --> 05:28:41.880
attack.

05:28:41.939 --> 05:28:45.000
She was about to give him Aha!

05:28:45.060 --> 05:28:47.520
She shouted. leaping into his path and

05:28:47.520 --> 05:28:49.560
flinging off the invisibility magic.

05:28:49.619 --> 05:28:53.639
He shrieked.

05:28:53.700 --> 05:28:56.279
In a very gratifyingly terrified way.

05:28:56.400 --> 05:28:59.279
Give it back, she shouted.

05:28:59.340 --> 05:29:01.680
You stole Winter Scavenger.

05:29:01.740 --> 05:29:02.459
Give it back now.

05:29:02.580 --> 05:29:06.540
She wasn't his. somebody yelled back at

05:29:06.540 --> 05:29:06.779
her.

05:29:06.840 --> 05:29:08.639
Not the dragon, though.

05:29:08.700 --> 05:29:11.340
He was standing there, with his mouth

05:29:11.340 --> 05:29:13.319
closed, and his eyes wide open.

05:29:13.439 --> 05:29:15.240
What the?

05:29:15.540 --> 05:29:17.639
You can't own a scavenger.

05:29:17.700 --> 05:29:18.659
We're not pets.

05:29:18.720 --> 05:29:22.200
There was a scavenger.

05:29:22.259 --> 05:29:25.439
Standing On the dragon's head.

05:29:25.500 --> 05:29:28.200
Shouting at snowfall.

05:29:28.319 --> 05:29:29.520
In Dragon.

05:29:29.580 --> 05:29:31.319
Except you.

05:29:31.380 --> 05:29:34.560
You're my pet, the dragon said quickly

05:29:34.560 --> 05:29:37.200
almost under his breath, and then made a

05:29:37.200 --> 05:29:39.119
face as if he was trying very hard not to

05:29:39.119 --> 05:29:39.900
laugh.

05:29:39.959 --> 05:29:41.939
Not helpful Skye.

05:29:42.000 --> 05:29:44.580
The scavenger barked at him, poking the

05:29:44.580 --> 05:29:45.419
top of his head with her foot.

05:29:45.479 --> 05:29:50.759
But, but, Snowfall had never in her

05:29:50.759 --> 05:29:53.459
entire life been so at a loss for words.

05:29:53.580 --> 05:29:55.919
A scavenger.

05:29:55.979 --> 05:29:57.659
Speaking dragon.

05:29:57.720 --> 05:30:00.900
In a conversation, like it was really

05:30:00.900 --> 05:30:01.799
talking to her.

05:30:01.860 --> 05:30:05.340
How is this happening?

05:30:05.400 --> 05:30:07.860
She glanced down at her jewelry.

05:30:07.919 --> 05:30:10.500
Was this another animus curse?

05:30:10.560 --> 05:30:12.900
Was she hallucinating, intelligent

05:30:12.900 --> 05:30:14.099
talking scavengers now?

05:30:14.159 --> 05:30:16.080
Where's pumpkin?

05:30:16.139 --> 05:30:16.979
she demanded.

05:30:17.040 --> 05:30:20.520
The dragon started snorting with laughter

05:30:20.520 --> 05:30:22.680
so much that the scavenger on his head

05:30:22.680 --> 05:30:24.720
had to grab his horns so she wouldn't

05:30:24.720 --> 05:30:25.080
fall off.

05:30:25.139 --> 05:30:29.279
Her name is daffodil, said the

05:30:29.279 --> 05:30:29.819
scavenger.

05:30:29.880 --> 05:30:31.619
Oh.

05:30:31.680 --> 05:30:36.119
Ah, Snowball said, very much in denial

05:30:36.119 --> 05:30:37.560
that this conversation was real.

05:30:37.680 --> 05:30:39.900
Much more dignified.

05:30:39.959 --> 05:30:43.200
A small face peeked out from behind the

05:30:43.200 --> 05:30:45.659
dragon's neck, surrounded by a halo of

05:30:45.659 --> 05:30:46.020
dark hair.

05:30:46.139 --> 05:30:49.020
She waved one of her little paws at

05:30:49.020 --> 05:30:49.439
snowfall.

05:30:49.500 --> 05:30:52.439
Does she speak dragon too?

05:30:52.500 --> 05:30:53.700
Snowfall asked.

05:30:53.759 --> 05:30:57.479
She's supposed to, said the scavenger on

05:30:57.479 --> 05:30:58.139
the dragon's head.

05:30:58.259 --> 05:31:01.139
If she paid attention and studied more

05:31:01.139 --> 05:31:03.959
she'd be able to talk to any dragon to

05:31:03.959 --> 05:31:04.740
try to kidnap her.

05:31:04.799 --> 05:31:06.659
Daffa Dill.

05:31:06.720 --> 05:31:10.380
Daffodil, pumpkin, shouted in dragon.

05:31:10.439 --> 05:31:12.060
No eating.

05:31:12.119 --> 05:31:15.000
The pitch of her voice was too high, and

05:31:15.000 --> 05:31:17.040
the accents and growls were in all the

05:31:17.040 --> 05:31:19.319
wrong places, but now that Snowfall was

05:31:19.319 --> 05:31:21.240
listening for it, she could tell those

05:31:21.240 --> 05:31:22.139
were dragon words.

05:31:22.200 --> 05:31:25.380
Winter's former pet shook her head

05:31:25.380 --> 05:31:28.200
huffily, and squeaked something scavenger

05:31:27.119 --> 05:31:30.060
ish in what looked like indignant

05:31:30.060 --> 05:31:31.259
outrage.

05:31:31.319 --> 05:31:34.439
But scavengers couldn't be sentient.

05:31:34.500 --> 05:31:36.240
They couldn't be smart enough to learn

05:31:36.240 --> 05:31:39.240
dragon, and talk like dragons, and argue

05:31:39.240 --> 05:31:39.900
with queens.

05:31:39.959 --> 05:31:42.840
They were just big squirrels.

05:31:42.900 --> 05:31:44.099
Pray.

05:31:44.159 --> 05:31:46.799
This had to be some kind of party trick.

05:31:46.860 --> 05:31:50.040
This weird sky wing, if that's really

05:31:50.040 --> 05:31:52.560
what he was, must have trained his

05:31:52.560 --> 05:31:54.299
scavengers to make all the right funny

05:31:54.299 --> 05:31:54.720
noises.

05:31:54.779 --> 05:31:56.639
Surely that was it.

05:31:56.759 --> 05:31:59.819
Or else Snowfall would have to believe

05:31:59.819 --> 05:32:02.520
that there was a whole civilization of

05:32:02.520 --> 05:32:04.860
intelligent life living right under the

05:32:04.860 --> 05:32:07.860
dragon's talons all this time, stealing

05:32:07.860 --> 05:32:10.680
treasure, and getting eaten, and having

05:32:10.680 --> 05:32:11.700
feelings?

05:32:11.759 --> 05:32:13.619
Surely not.

05:32:13.680 --> 05:32:18.419
This is Snowfall pressed her talons to

05:32:18.419 --> 05:32:18.779
her head.

05:32:18.840 --> 05:32:22.259
I can't, this makes no...

05:32:22.319 --> 05:32:25.259
And then she realized the fuzziness and

05:32:25.259 --> 05:32:28.080
headache and creeping darkness weren't

05:32:28.080 --> 05:32:30.060
caused by the discovery that an everyday

05:32:30.060 --> 05:32:31.740
snack could have a conversation with

05:32:31.740 --> 05:32:31.979
her.

05:32:32.040 --> 05:32:35.759
It was another vision, arriving now

05:32:35.759 --> 05:32:37.380
whether she liked it or not.

05:32:37.439 --> 05:32:39.479
Oh, no.

05:32:39.540 --> 05:32:40.740
She muttered.

05:32:40.799 --> 05:32:43.319
And then her eyes closed, and she

05:32:43.319 --> 05:32:43.799
dropped.

05:32:43.860 --> 05:32:49.500
Down, down, into.

05:32:49.740 --> 05:32:51.360
What?

05:32:51.419 --> 05:32:54.599
She is very small.

05:32:54.720 --> 05:32:59.639
She is tiny and soft and furry and nimble

05:32:59.639 --> 05:33:02.220
leaping from rock to rock, high above the

05:33:02.220 --> 05:33:05.159
cave floor, unafraid, even though she has

05:33:05.159 --> 05:33:05.580
no wings.

05:33:05.639 --> 05:33:09.479
Below her, the green dragon growls and

05:33:09.479 --> 05:33:12.119
spins, but it doesn't see her in the dark

05:33:12.119 --> 05:33:13.680
shadows of the cave ceiling.

05:33:13.740 --> 05:33:17.880
Nice try, she thinks jubilantly.

05:33:17.939 --> 05:33:20.459
This particular dragon has been trying to

05:33:20.459 --> 05:33:22.680
catch one of them for days, but with no

05:33:22.680 --> 05:33:23.340
luck, of course.

05:33:23.400 --> 05:33:25.020
Ha ha.

05:33:25.080 --> 05:33:26.700
Big old slow moving lizard.

05:33:26.759 --> 05:33:28.139
Raven.

05:33:28.200 --> 05:33:31.020
She holds onto a stalactite and turns

05:33:31.020 --> 05:33:31.560
toward the voice.

05:33:31.619 --> 05:33:34.680
Of course, it's mole, picking out of one

05:33:34.680 --> 05:33:35.939
of the secret upper passages.

05:33:36.000 --> 05:33:37.680
Hey, mole.

05:33:37.740 --> 05:33:39.419
She says with a jaunty wave.

05:33:39.479 --> 05:33:42.720
Get in here before the dragon sees you, he

05:33:42.720 --> 05:33:43.139
hisses.

05:33:43.200 --> 05:33:46.979
Raven sighs, but Mole has enough stress

05:33:46.979 --> 05:33:48.000
without her adding to it.

05:33:48.119 --> 05:33:50.939
She leaps neatly to the ledge beside him

05:33:50.939 --> 05:33:53.340
and crawls through the hole in the wall.

05:33:53.400 --> 05:33:54.840
On the other side.

05:33:54.900 --> 05:33:57.180
The passages are only big enough for

05:33:57.180 --> 05:33:57.419
humans.

05:33:57.540 --> 05:34:00.360
These winding tunnels are the safe parts

05:34:00.360 --> 05:34:02.880
of the cave, which is to say, the boring

05:34:02.880 --> 05:34:03.180
parts.

05:34:03.240 --> 05:34:06.119
Are you trying to get caught by a

05:34:06.119 --> 05:34:06.540
dragon?

05:34:06.540 --> 05:34:07.139
he asks.

05:34:07.200 --> 05:34:10.500
Of course not, Raven says cheerfully.

05:34:10.560 --> 05:34:12.900
I just think it's funny to watch them get

05:34:12.900 --> 05:34:13.680
all grumpy about it.

05:34:13.740 --> 05:34:16.380
They set off toward their cave village.

05:34:16.439 --> 05:34:20.220
You mustn't provoke them, Mole argues.

05:34:20.279 --> 05:34:22.319
What if one of them catches you or gets

05:34:22.319 --> 05:34:24.540
really mad and smashes down some cave

05:34:24.540 --> 05:34:25.799
walls and finds all of us?

05:34:25.860 --> 05:34:28.500
There are too many dragons down here

05:34:28.500 --> 05:34:28.799
right now.

05:34:28.860 --> 05:34:31.799
We should stay hidden, not run around

05:34:31.799 --> 05:34:33.599
poking their noses and asking to be

05:34:33.599 --> 05:34:33.900
eaten.

05:34:33.959 --> 05:34:36.180
Raven rolls her eyes.

05:34:36.240 --> 05:34:38.279
Don't you want to know why they're

05:34:38.279 --> 05:34:38.759
suddenly here?

05:34:38.819 --> 05:34:41.279
Something is happening in the sky world.

05:34:41.340 --> 05:34:42.360
Something important.

05:34:42.419 --> 05:34:45.720
Important to dragons maybe, he says.

05:34:45.779 --> 05:34:47.520
Nothing to do with us.

05:34:47.580 --> 05:34:50.279
Unless it's related to the abyss.

05:34:50.400 --> 05:34:51.720
Raven points out.

05:34:51.779 --> 05:34:55.080
He looks around furtively.

05:34:55.139 --> 05:34:56.580
You know the rules.

05:34:56.639 --> 05:34:59.880
But it's acting weird, and everyone knows

05:34:59.880 --> 05:35:01.080
it, she says.

05:35:01.139 --> 05:35:03.479
I don't think we can keep pretending it's

05:35:03.479 --> 05:35:03.779
not there.

05:35:03.840 --> 05:35:07.139
Well, if you would like to climb down

05:35:07.139 --> 05:35:09.419
into the deepest, darkest hole in the

05:35:09.419 --> 05:35:11.520
universe to figure out what those noises

05:35:11.520 --> 05:35:14.159
are, then go ahead, Mole says.

05:35:14.220 --> 05:35:17.520
Believe me out of it, and stop teasing

05:35:17.520 --> 05:35:18.299
the dragons.

05:35:18.360 --> 05:35:21.000
He runs on ahead of her, and she feels

05:35:21.000 --> 05:35:23.099
guilty for a moment, that she's driven

05:35:23.099 --> 05:35:25.020
him past the edges of his patience once

05:35:25.020 --> 05:35:25.500
again.

05:35:25.560 --> 05:35:27.240
Still.

05:35:27.360 --> 05:35:30.540
It is strange that so many dragons came

05:35:30.540 --> 05:35:33.180
crowding into the caves, acting weird.

05:35:33.299 --> 05:35:35.459
Within days of the abyss changing for the

05:35:35.459 --> 05:35:36.299
1st time in years.

05:35:36.360 --> 05:35:38.700
Something is happening.

05:35:38.759 --> 05:35:41.099
And Mole is wrong.

05:35:41.159 --> 05:35:44.639
Whatever it is, if it scared the dragon.

05:35:44.819 --> 05:35:47.700
Then there's every chance it could be the

05:35:47.700 --> 05:35:49.200
end of the world for the humans.

05:35:49.319 --> 05:35:53.880
Chapter 18.

05:35:54.119 --> 05:35:56.639
Is she all right?

05:35:56.700 --> 05:35:59.040
A voice whispered near Snowball's ear.

05:35:59.099 --> 05:36:01.380
I've never seen a dragon paint before.

05:36:01.439 --> 05:36:05.220
I think Wren yelled her into fainting, the

05:36:05.220 --> 05:36:06.840
dragon's voice said disapprovingly.

05:36:06.900 --> 05:36:10.619
That's me, terrifier of dragons, said

05:36:10.619 --> 05:36:11.400
someone else.

05:36:11.580 --> 05:36:13.380
She was definitely scared of me, right?

05:36:13.500 --> 05:36:17.459
No, Snowball snapped, but she couldn't

05:36:17.459 --> 05:36:18.119
open her eyes yet.

05:36:18.180 --> 05:36:20.400
Everything was too strange.

05:36:20.459 --> 05:36:24.299
Her limbs, her scales, her wings all felt

05:36:24.299 --> 05:36:26.700
wrong, and it was taking forever for

05:36:26.700 --> 05:36:28.380
herself to settle back into place.

05:36:28.439 --> 05:36:33.000
Wait, did she just understand me?

05:36:33.060 --> 05:36:34.680
The 3rd voice said.

05:36:34.740 --> 05:36:37.259
They were speaking human.

05:36:37.319 --> 05:36:41.580
Human, a language of its own, not just a

05:36:41.580 --> 05:36:43.919
series of squeaks and grogs and gurgles

05:36:43.919 --> 05:36:44.939
that the scavengers made.

05:36:45.000 --> 05:36:47.939
I don't even want to know this word.

05:36:48.000 --> 05:36:49.979
Human.

05:36:50.040 --> 05:36:53.159
Should we be running away with a bishop?

05:36:53.220 --> 05:36:54.419
The 1st voice asked.

05:36:54.479 --> 05:36:57.419
Halfway through the sentence, the human

05:36:57.419 --> 05:37:00.299
language faded from Snowfall's brain, and

05:37:00.299 --> 05:37:02.520
her inner dragon breathed comforting

05:37:02.520 --> 05:37:03.720
frost all through her.

05:37:03.779 --> 05:37:07.500
I am Snowfall, she told herself

05:37:07.500 --> 05:37:08.159
frantically.

05:37:08.220 --> 05:37:10.259
Queen of the ice wings.

05:37:10.319 --> 05:37:11.819
I am a dragon.

05:37:11.880 --> 05:37:13.619
This is really, truly me.

05:37:13.680 --> 05:37:17.639
She sat up, touching her head gingerly.

05:37:17.700 --> 05:37:20.340
The pale orange dragon was crouched

05:37:20.340 --> 05:37:22.500
beside her, with the dragon speaking

05:37:22.500 --> 05:37:25.200
human, scavenger, on his shoulder.

05:37:25.259 --> 05:37:28.020
Pumpkin was standing just behind one of

05:37:28.020 --> 05:37:30.240
his talons, as if she was prepared to

05:37:30.240 --> 05:37:32.520
either duck out of sight, or one forward

05:37:32.520 --> 05:37:34.380
and attack, whichever was required.

05:37:34.439 --> 05:37:39.540
Sorry, the dragon said kindly, in dragon

05:37:39.540 --> 05:37:40.200
thank goodness.

05:37:40.259 --> 05:37:42.119
We didn't mean to frighten you.

05:37:42.180 --> 05:37:46.919
You did not frighten me, she growled.

05:37:46.979 --> 05:37:49.680
The scavenger on the dragon's shoulder

05:37:49.680 --> 05:37:51.540
put her hand on the sword at her belt.

05:37:51.599 --> 05:37:53.459
I mean I'm not scared.

05:37:53.520 --> 05:37:55.740
I get vision sometimes.

05:37:55.799 --> 05:37:56.880
That's all that was.

05:37:56.939 --> 05:37:59.159
It's a magic curse thing.

05:37:59.220 --> 05:38:01.500
She tugged on the intractable ring.

05:38:01.560 --> 05:38:05.220
That seemed very intentional, you rotten

05:38:05.220 --> 05:38:05.819
accessory.

05:38:05.880 --> 05:38:07.979
Were you enchanted to prove me wrong

05:38:07.979 --> 05:38:09.840
every time I have a thought you don't

05:38:09.840 --> 05:38:10.080
like?

05:38:10.139 --> 05:38:12.959
Have you ever thrown any other queens

05:38:12.959 --> 05:38:14.880
into the tiny edible body of something

05:38:14.880 --> 05:38:15.119
else?

05:38:15.180 --> 05:38:17.159
Well, why don't we all know about

05:38:17.159 --> 05:38:18.000
scavengers?

05:38:18.060 --> 05:38:18.959
If you have.

05:38:19.020 --> 05:38:22.200
And if you haven't, why are you torturing

05:38:22.200 --> 05:38:22.619
just me?

05:38:22.680 --> 05:38:24.959
What did you see?

05:38:25.020 --> 05:38:27.060
asked the strange scavenger.

05:38:27.119 --> 05:38:28.860
More of you.

05:38:28.919 --> 05:38:31.979
Snowfall answered, waving one of her

05:38:31.979 --> 05:38:32.819
wings of the creature.

05:38:32.880 --> 05:38:34.860
But I think they were on the other

05:38:34.860 --> 05:38:35.400
continent.

05:38:35.520 --> 05:38:38.040
It was harder to hold on to the memories

05:38:38.040 --> 05:38:40.380
from this vision, because they made so

05:38:40.380 --> 05:38:41.939
little sense to her dragon brain.

05:38:42.000 --> 05:38:45.180
She could still feel the weird little

05:38:45.180 --> 05:38:47.880
hairs and flat face and upright balance

05:38:47.880 --> 05:38:50.819
of the human, but everything it knew, like

05:38:50.819 --> 05:38:53.159
the details of its life underground, was

05:38:53.159 --> 05:38:54.360
muddled and bewildering.

05:38:54.419 --> 05:38:58.200
But the dragons hiding in the caves?

05:38:58.319 --> 05:39:01.020
That sounded like Brian and her group.

05:39:01.080 --> 05:39:03.720
And then something about an abyss?

05:39:03.779 --> 05:39:08.099
This is Wren, said the dragon, gently

05:39:08.099 --> 05:39:09.779
poking a scavenger on his shoulder with

05:39:09.779 --> 05:39:10.380
one claw.

05:39:10.439 --> 05:39:13.740
You've already met daffodil, and I'm

05:39:13.740 --> 05:39:14.099
Skye.

05:39:14.220 --> 05:39:17.220
No way, Snowfall said.

05:39:17.279 --> 05:39:20.759
He blinked innocently, and she added, Sky

05:39:20.759 --> 05:39:21.479
the Sky Wing.

05:39:21.599 --> 05:39:23.639
That's completely ridiculous.

05:39:23.700 --> 05:39:27.419
Oh, he said, his face relaxing.

05:39:27.479 --> 05:39:30.599
Well, Ren named me, and she didn't know

05:39:30.599 --> 05:39:32.040
what Skywings were called then about.

05:39:32.159 --> 05:39:35.279
He shragged, as if that made any sense.

05:39:35.400 --> 05:39:39.000
As if sure, scavengers named dragons all

05:39:39.000 --> 05:39:40.259
the time. totally normal.

05:39:40.319 --> 05:39:44.580
Winter is going to lose his entire mind.

05:39:44.639 --> 05:39:47.159
Snowfall suddenly realized.

05:39:47.220 --> 05:39:50.700
A scavenger that can talk to dragons, I

05:39:50.700 --> 05:39:52.619
mean, I think his head might literally

05:39:52.619 --> 05:39:53.520
explode.

05:39:53.580 --> 05:39:58.020
I guess this means moon was right.

05:39:58.139 --> 05:40:00.180
She contemplated not telling anybody

05:40:00.180 --> 05:40:00.720
about this.

05:40:00.779 --> 05:40:04.139
It would be insufferable to have to

05:40:04.139 --> 05:40:07.500
confirm that Nightwing's impressions of

05:40:07.500 --> 05:40:08.639
scavenger emotions.

05:40:08.700 --> 05:40:11.220
But the thought of the look on Winter's

05:40:11.220 --> 05:40:13.500
face outweighed everything else.

05:40:13.560 --> 05:40:15.659
Wait, said Skye.

05:40:15.720 --> 05:40:16.680
What?

05:40:16.740 --> 05:40:20.880
We should go, Ren said, tugging on Skye's

05:40:20.880 --> 05:40:21.180
ear.

05:40:21.240 --> 05:40:24.299
No, no, no, Snowfall said.

05:40:24.360 --> 05:40:25.560
No way.

05:40:25.619 --> 05:40:27.599
You cannot make me go back to winter

05:40:27.599 --> 05:40:31.139
alone to say, oh yes, pumpkin escaped, but

05:40:31.139 --> 05:40:31.919
guess what?

05:40:31.979 --> 05:40:34.200
She has a scavenger friend who speaks

05:40:34.200 --> 05:40:36.779
dragon, and a weirdo dragon who speaks

05:40:36.779 --> 05:40:37.380
scavenger.

05:40:37.439 --> 05:40:40.080
Ah, well, but I let them go.

05:40:40.200 --> 05:40:41.639
Didn't think you'd be interested.

05:40:41.700 --> 05:40:42.959
Seriously.

05:40:43.020 --> 05:40:45.840
Ren put her fists on her hips.

05:40:45.900 --> 05:40:49.020
And you can't make us go back into that

05:40:49.020 --> 05:40:51.959
city full of dragons to say, hello, we

05:40:51.959 --> 05:40:54.000
escaped, no problem, but we thought it

05:40:54.000 --> 05:40:55.560
would be great fun to come back and get

05:40:55.560 --> 05:40:57.779
eaten instead, seriously.

05:40:57.840 --> 05:41:01.500
Snowfall thought it was wildly funny that

05:41:01.500 --> 05:41:03.659
Wren seemed to speak dragon better than

05:41:03.659 --> 05:41:06.060
Sky himself did, and that she could even

05:41:06.060 --> 05:41:08.700
master the exact right growly intonation

05:41:08.700 --> 05:41:10.080
of seriously.

05:41:10.139 --> 05:41:13.680
No one's going to eat you, she said.

05:41:13.740 --> 05:41:16.979
Obviously, we don't eat things that talk

05:41:16.979 --> 05:41:17.639
back to us.

05:41:17.700 --> 05:41:19.560
That would be very unsettling.

05:41:19.619 --> 05:41:22.619
Guess what's more unsettling, Bren said.

05:41:22.680 --> 05:41:24.000
Being eaten.

05:41:24.119 --> 05:41:28.020
Ren, maybe it would be fun to meet them

05:41:28.020 --> 05:41:29.639
Skye said sweetly.

05:41:29.700 --> 05:41:32.040
Maybe they're all nice dragons.

05:41:32.159 --> 05:41:35.819
Well, not me, Snowfall said.

05:41:35.880 --> 05:41:38.099
I'm definitely not nice.

05:41:38.159 --> 05:41:40.919
I'm probably the least nice dragon in

05:41:40.919 --> 05:41:42.000
Sanctuary right now.

05:41:42.060 --> 05:41:45.060
So if I'm not going to eat you, most

05:41:45.060 --> 05:41:46.259
likely nobody else will either.

05:41:46.319 --> 05:41:48.779
And don't you want to talk to more

05:41:48.779 --> 05:41:49.500
dragons?

05:41:49.619 --> 05:41:50.459
Sky asked.

05:41:50.520 --> 05:41:53.400
Building human dragon communication.

05:41:53.459 --> 05:41:55.799
Isn't that our great quest or something?

05:41:55.860 --> 05:42:00.119
No, that's Ivy's Great Quest, Ren

05:42:00.119 --> 05:42:00.900
protested.

05:42:00.959 --> 05:42:03.299
My great quest is to be left alone.

05:42:03.360 --> 05:42:06.840
Snowfall didn't know if it was the vision

05:42:06.840 --> 05:42:08.939
making her soft, or this particular

05:42:08.939 --> 05:42:11.639
scavenger's personality, but she was

05:42:11.639 --> 05:42:12.840
starting to quite like Ren.

05:42:12.900 --> 05:42:15.900
Maybe I should get myself a scavenger pet

05:42:15.900 --> 05:42:17.040
too, she thought.

05:42:17.099 --> 05:42:20.520
The corners of her vision went blurry, and

05:42:20.520 --> 05:42:22.259
she glanced down at the ring in alarm.

05:42:22.319 --> 05:42:24.479
I mean, not a pet.

05:42:24.540 --> 05:42:26.639
Scavengers aren't pets, they're

05:42:26.639 --> 05:42:27.180
intelligent.

05:42:27.240 --> 05:42:29.580
I meant friend, a scavenger friend.

05:42:29.639 --> 05:42:33.419
To her enormous surprise, the blurriness

05:42:33.419 --> 05:42:35.520
vanished again, and she did not collapse

05:42:35.520 --> 05:42:36.419
or have a vision.

05:42:36.540 --> 05:42:38.340
Hmm.

05:42:38.459 --> 05:42:41.099
Can I actually talk this ring out of

05:42:41.099 --> 05:42:42.000
giving me visions?

05:42:42.060 --> 05:42:45.299
If I convince it I've learned whatever

05:42:45.299 --> 05:42:48.540
lesson it's teaching me, I guess, she

05:42:48.540 --> 05:42:49.020
sighed.

05:42:49.139 --> 05:42:52.259
But still, that was a small, interesting

05:42:52.259 --> 05:42:53.220
glimmer of hope.

05:42:53.340 --> 05:42:57.900
Tell you what, Snowfall said to Ren, you

05:42:57.900 --> 05:42:59.220
don't have to meet the entire city.

05:42:59.279 --> 05:43:01.560
Just come back and talk to winter, so

05:43:01.560 --> 05:43:02.459
he'll believe me.

05:43:02.520 --> 05:43:05.520
Also, by the way, it's in your best

05:43:05.520 --> 05:43:07.799
interest to prove to him that scavengers

05:43:07.799 --> 05:43:10.139
are as smart as dragons, because then

05:43:10.139 --> 05:43:12.060
he'll stop chasing you and locking you up

05:43:12.060 --> 05:43:14.040
and giving you silly names.

05:43:14.099 --> 05:43:17.819
I like the name pumpkin, Skye said.

05:43:17.880 --> 05:43:20.639
Ooh, I want to know what he would call

05:43:20.639 --> 05:43:21.419
Ren.

05:43:21.479 --> 05:43:22.919
His eyes lit up.

05:43:22.979 --> 05:43:25.200
Does he have any cute little hats?

05:43:25.259 --> 05:43:28.619
Enough with the hats, ran hollered

05:43:28.619 --> 05:43:30.959
whacking his neck, and then shaking out

05:43:30.959 --> 05:43:32.639
her hand with a grimace that suggested

05:43:32.639 --> 05:43:34.020
that had been a bad idea.

05:43:34.139 --> 05:43:35.759
All right, fine.

05:43:35.819 --> 05:43:38.099
We will come back with you to meet one

05:43:38.099 --> 05:43:38.880
dragon.

05:43:38.939 --> 05:43:40.619
Excellent.

05:43:40.680 --> 05:43:44.040
Snowfall swept her wings behind her, and

05:43:44.040 --> 05:43:45.180
led the way to sanctuary.

05:43:45.299 --> 05:43:48.840
Unfortunately, when they got there, winter

05:43:48.840 --> 05:43:50.580
was pacing around the outside of the

05:43:50.580 --> 05:43:53.340
enclosure, lashing his tail, and there

05:43:53.340 --> 05:43:54.779
were 3 other dragons with him.

05:43:54.840 --> 05:43:58.439
Lynx, Cricket, and Kibley, who were all

05:43:58.439 --> 05:44:00.060
helpfully searching through the grass and

05:44:00.060 --> 05:44:00.360
bushes.

05:44:00.419 --> 05:44:01.799
No wait.

05:44:01.860 --> 05:44:04.619
Four, the small hive wing was there as

05:44:04.619 --> 05:44:06.540
well, chasing a white butterfly.

05:44:06.599 --> 05:44:09.840
It gave Snowfall a weird shiver to see

05:44:09.840 --> 05:44:11.939
the baby hive wing tribe pouncing on the

05:44:11.939 --> 05:44:13.619
butterfly, even though she missed.

05:44:13.740 --> 05:44:16.619
She poked that discomfort for a moment

05:44:16.619 --> 05:44:20.040
puzzled, and realized that must have come

05:44:20.040 --> 05:44:22.740
from Tao or Io, who would see it as a

05:44:22.740 --> 05:44:24.900
sign of a young hive wing, learning to

05:44:24.900 --> 05:44:26.759
capture and control silk wings.

05:44:26.939 --> 05:44:28.860
She's just playing with a bug.

05:44:28.919 --> 05:44:30.479
Don't read into it.

05:44:30.540 --> 05:44:33.360
Snowfall ordered herself, and by

05:44:33.360 --> 05:44:35.700
extension, all the tangled up others

05:44:35.700 --> 05:44:36.360
inside her.

05:44:36.419 --> 05:44:38.759
Snowfall!

05:44:38.819 --> 05:44:39.599
winter cried.

05:44:39.659 --> 05:44:41.220
Pumpkin is missing.

05:44:41.279 --> 05:44:43.560
He caught sight of Skye behind her.

05:44:43.619 --> 05:44:45.479
Who, what?

05:44:45.599 --> 05:44:47.700
That's not one dragon.

05:44:47.759 --> 05:44:49.380
That's 5 dragons.

05:44:49.439 --> 05:44:51.119
Wren hissed at Snowfall.

05:44:51.180 --> 05:44:53.040
Snowball shrugged.

05:44:53.099 --> 05:44:55.139
They're all friendly turtles on the

05:44:55.139 --> 05:44:57.900
inside, though, she said, which earned

05:44:57.900 --> 05:44:59.520
her a gigantic grin from Skye.

05:44:59.580 --> 05:45:02.040
I'm very sure none of these will hurt you

05:45:02.040 --> 05:45:03.119
so calm down.

05:45:03.180 --> 05:45:07.020
He keeps saying pumpkin, Cricket said

05:45:07.020 --> 05:45:09.360
pointing to Winter, but what he's

05:45:09.360 --> 05:45:10.799
describing sounds much more like a

05:45:10.799 --> 05:45:13.020
reading monkey than a pumpkin to me.

05:45:13.080 --> 05:45:14.700
I don't know whether I'm looking for an

05:45:14.700 --> 05:45:17.099
orange gourd or a small furry thing with

05:45:17.099 --> 05:45:17.639
cute paws.

05:45:17.759 --> 05:45:20.340
I can't believe he didn't show you

05:45:20.340 --> 05:45:22.080
pumpkin earlier, Link said.

05:45:22.139 --> 05:45:25.080
He would talk about scavengers all day if

05:45:25.080 --> 05:45:26.159
he could find someone to listen.

05:45:26.220 --> 05:45:30.720
Scavengers, Cricket said, testing out the

05:45:30.720 --> 05:45:31.020
word.

05:45:31.080 --> 05:45:34.619
Cousin, Snowfall called to Winter.

05:45:34.740 --> 05:45:36.119
Pumpkin is fine.

05:45:36.180 --> 05:45:38.580
Get ready for your entire world to be

05:45:38.580 --> 05:45:40.020
flipped upside down, though.

05:45:40.080 --> 05:45:42.900
Winter tilted his head and took a stout

05:45:42.900 --> 05:45:43.799
towards snowfall.

05:45:43.860 --> 05:45:45.959
The cricket spotted the 2 scavengers on

05:45:45.959 --> 05:45:46.919
Sky's back first.

05:45:46.979 --> 05:45:50.220
She bounded over to them, her eyes as

05:45:50.220 --> 05:45:51.419
huge as the moons.

05:45:51.540 --> 05:45:54.479
Reading monkeys, she cried.

05:45:54.540 --> 05:45:57.000
He did mean reading monkeys.

05:45:57.060 --> 05:45:58.259
You have them here too.

05:45:58.319 --> 05:46:00.360
Is she talking about us?

05:46:00.479 --> 05:46:02.639
Ren whispered to Snowfall.

05:46:02.700 --> 05:46:05.580
And what the heck kind of dragon is

05:46:05.580 --> 05:46:05.819
that?

05:46:05.939 --> 05:46:08.520
I mean, can yours read?

05:46:08.639 --> 05:46:09.959
Cricket charged on.

05:46:10.020 --> 05:46:12.360
Or are they more like regular monkeys?

05:46:12.419 --> 05:46:14.520
The one I saw was holding something that

05:46:14.520 --> 05:46:15.959
looked just like a book.

05:46:16.020 --> 05:46:16.919
Can you imagine?

05:46:16.979 --> 05:46:19.979
Monkeys who can read must also be able to

05:46:19.979 --> 05:46:21.119
write, don't you think?

05:46:21.180 --> 05:46:22.979
Don't you wonder what they'd write

05:46:22.979 --> 05:46:23.220
about?

05:46:23.279 --> 05:46:25.020
Monkey stories?

05:46:25.080 --> 05:46:26.340
Can you think of anything more

05:46:26.340 --> 05:46:26.939
fascinating?

05:46:27.000 --> 05:46:28.560
Yes.

05:46:28.619 --> 05:46:31.319
Actually, if you'd shut up for a moment

05:46:31.319 --> 05:46:33.000
Snowfall interrupted.

05:46:33.060 --> 05:46:36.240
Try monkeys who can speak dragon, although

05:46:36.240 --> 05:46:36.959
they're not monkeys.

05:46:37.020 --> 05:46:39.119
We call them scavengers.

05:46:39.180 --> 05:46:43.619
And we call ourselves humans, Ren added.

05:46:43.740 --> 05:46:47.939
Oh yes, here were the awestruck faces

05:46:47.939 --> 05:46:49.200
Snowfall was looking for.

05:46:49.259 --> 05:46:51.840
Cricket and winter both seem to be on the

05:46:51.840 --> 05:46:53.400
verge of floating right off the planet

05:46:53.400 --> 05:46:54.479
and hitting the moons.

05:46:54.540 --> 05:46:57.720
Kibli recovered his voice first.

05:46:57.779 --> 05:46:59.340
Did she?

05:46:59.459 --> 05:47:01.680
Did she just?

05:47:01.919 --> 05:47:04.560
My name is Ren, she said.

05:47:04.680 --> 05:47:06.240
She pointed to the dragon.

05:47:06.299 --> 05:47:09.360
Sky and that's daffodil.

05:47:09.419 --> 05:47:11.880
Daffodils squeaked something.

05:47:11.939 --> 05:47:15.180
Not pumpkin, when added.

05:47:15.240 --> 05:47:17.279
She would like me to say that a couple

05:47:17.279 --> 05:47:17.880
more times.

05:47:17.939 --> 05:47:19.200
Daffodil.

05:47:19.259 --> 05:47:20.939
Definitely not pumpkin.

05:47:21.000 --> 05:47:24.119
Winter put one talent to his face and

05:47:24.119 --> 05:47:25.319
rubbed it in a dazed way.

05:47:25.439 --> 05:47:29.400
She kept making a noise that sounded like

05:47:29.400 --> 05:47:31.259
daffodil, he said.

05:47:31.319 --> 05:47:33.180
But of course I knew it couldn't be

05:47:33.180 --> 05:47:36.360
daffodil, because that's impossible.

05:47:36.419 --> 05:47:40.080
Ren chirped something at daffodil, and

05:47:40.080 --> 05:47:42.540
daffodil chirped indignantly back, waving

05:47:42.540 --> 05:47:42.959
her arms.

05:47:43.020 --> 05:47:46.139
Can all humans speak dragon?

05:47:46.200 --> 05:47:46.979
Cricket asked.

05:47:47.040 --> 05:47:49.799
Bandit couldn't Winter answered.

05:47:49.860 --> 05:47:52.380
Could he, do you know Bandit?

05:47:52.439 --> 05:47:53.580
he asked Wren.

05:47:53.700 --> 05:47:56.159
She raised her eyebrows at him, and

05:47:56.159 --> 05:47:58.979
Kibley said, I think we can safely assume

05:47:58.979 --> 05:48:00.419
that was not his real name.

05:48:00.479 --> 05:48:03.299
Rand speaks dragon better than any other

05:48:03.299 --> 05:48:06.000
human in the world, Sky said proudly.

05:48:06.060 --> 05:48:07.259
She's a natural.

05:48:07.319 --> 05:48:10.380
All that growling and roaring, you know

05:48:10.380 --> 05:48:11.639
it matches her personality.

05:48:11.700 --> 05:48:13.799
Do you have books?

05:48:13.860 --> 05:48:15.000
Cricket blurted.

05:48:15.060 --> 05:48:18.900
I mean, the human, I saw, was back on the

05:48:18.900 --> 05:48:21.000
other continent, and it looked like it

05:48:21.000 --> 05:48:21.599
was reading a book.

05:48:21.659 --> 05:48:24.060
So I just wondered if maybe you read

05:48:24.060 --> 05:48:25.020
books too?

05:48:25.080 --> 05:48:27.840
How is that your 1st question?

05:48:27.900 --> 05:48:29.340
Winter asked.

05:48:29.400 --> 05:48:32.279
I do read books, Ren said.

05:48:32.340 --> 05:48:34.919
She tipped her head to study cricket's

05:48:34.919 --> 05:48:37.200
delighted face, and the octagonal

05:48:37.200 --> 05:48:38.759
spectacles that rested on her snout.

05:48:38.880 --> 05:48:41.159
What kind of dragon are you?

05:48:41.220 --> 05:48:44.459
Did you say other continent?

05:48:44.520 --> 05:48:45.419
Sky asked.

05:48:45.479 --> 05:48:49.259
I'm a hivewing from Pantala, on the far

05:48:49.259 --> 05:48:50.040
side of the ocean.

05:48:50.159 --> 05:48:53.580
Cricket said, waving vaguely westward.

05:48:53.639 --> 05:48:55.560
That's wild.

05:48:55.680 --> 05:48:57.419
Did you have scavengers over there too

05:48:57.419 --> 05:48:58.680
Kibley said.

05:48:58.740 --> 05:49:00.900
I wonder if they speak the same language

05:49:00.900 --> 05:49:01.680
as these ones.

05:49:01.740 --> 05:49:04.979
They do, Snowfall said.

05:49:05.099 --> 05:49:07.619
She'd been replaying her vision in her

05:49:07.619 --> 05:49:07.799
mind.

05:49:07.860 --> 05:49:10.680
They live in the cave systems underneath

05:49:10.680 --> 05:49:11.400
the Savannah.

05:49:11.459 --> 05:49:14.939
And I think, I think they know something

05:49:14.939 --> 05:49:16.080
about the breath of evil.

05:49:16.139 --> 05:49:20.700
Chapter 19.

05:49:20.880 --> 05:49:24.900
Snowfall explained about her vision, about

05:49:24.900 --> 05:49:26.459
being inside a human on the other

05:49:26.459 --> 05:49:26.819
continent.

05:49:26.880 --> 05:49:30.299
She said something about an abyss.

05:49:30.360 --> 05:49:32.939
She said it was acting strangely, whatever

05:49:32.939 --> 05:49:33.540
that means.

05:49:33.599 --> 05:49:35.880
Snowfall looked around at the other

05:49:35.880 --> 05:49:36.360
dragons.

05:49:36.419 --> 05:49:38.639
Perhaps it's connected to the mind

05:49:38.639 --> 05:49:39.659
control in the plant.

05:49:39.779 --> 05:49:43.020
We should find out, Kibble said

05:49:43.020 --> 05:49:43.500
excitedly.

05:49:43.560 --> 05:49:44.819
That's it.

05:49:44.880 --> 05:49:46.740
Your Majesty, you found the perfect

05:49:46.740 --> 05:49:47.279
solution.

05:49:47.400 --> 05:49:48.959
Did I?

05:49:49.020 --> 05:49:49.799
She said.

05:49:49.860 --> 05:49:51.659
I mean, of course I did.

05:49:51.720 --> 05:49:53.520
But you explain it.

05:49:53.580 --> 05:49:56.279
We shouldn't send our armies to fight

05:49:56.279 --> 05:49:58.380
Queen Wasp, Kibley said.

05:49:58.439 --> 05:50:01.380
Cricket flinched, and he spread his front

05:50:01.380 --> 05:50:02.159
talons quickly.

05:50:02.220 --> 05:50:03.900
Wait, listen.

05:50:03.959 --> 05:50:06.540
Armies are for wars where you want to

05:50:06.540 --> 05:50:08.340
kill as many of their dragons as possible

05:50:08.340 --> 05:50:09.659
before they kill you.

05:50:09.720 --> 05:50:12.119
But we don't want to kill their dragons.

05:50:12.119 --> 05:50:14.759
Most of them are friends and family who

05:50:14.759 --> 05:50:16.080
wouldn't be fighting if they weren't

05:50:16.080 --> 05:50:17.159
under wasps' control.

05:50:17.279 --> 05:50:19.860
What we need is a way to free them.

05:50:19.979 --> 05:50:22.319
And not even all the armies in Pyria

05:50:22.319 --> 05:50:23.099
would be able to do that.

05:50:23.159 --> 05:50:26.700
Sure, but if we send all the armies in

05:50:26.700 --> 05:50:28.680
Pyria, they could at least kill Queen

05:50:28.680 --> 05:50:30.419
Wasp, Snowball said.

05:50:30.479 --> 05:50:32.639
Maybe that's all we have to do.

05:50:32.700 --> 05:50:35.159
I'm very into that plan.

05:50:35.220 --> 05:50:38.099
We don't think killing Queen Wasp will be

05:50:38.099 --> 05:50:39.779
enough, Cricket said with a little

05:50:39.779 --> 05:50:40.139
shiver.

05:50:40.200 --> 05:50:42.360
There's something or someone else

05:50:42.360 --> 05:50:44.939
controlling her, and that's the thing we

05:50:44.939 --> 05:50:45.599
really have to fight.

05:50:45.659 --> 05:50:49.979
Still, our armies could help, Snowfall

05:50:49.979 --> 05:50:50.340
said.

05:50:50.400 --> 05:50:53.099
With those rain wing tranquilizer darts

05:50:53.099 --> 05:50:55.380
we could knock out all the hive wings and

05:50:55.380 --> 05:50:57.119
imprison them while we work on the

05:50:57.119 --> 05:50:59.700
freeing them part, and the killing queen

05:50:59.700 --> 05:51:00.419
wasp part.

05:51:00.479 --> 05:51:03.659
Now Winter was giving her that look she

05:51:03.659 --> 05:51:05.700
kept getting, as though her horns had

05:51:05.700 --> 05:51:07.380
turned bright pink and were spouting

05:51:07.380 --> 05:51:07.919
lemonade.

05:51:07.979 --> 05:51:10.259
What?

05:51:10.259 --> 05:51:11.819
Snowfall demanded.

05:51:11.880 --> 05:51:14.400
Why is your face doing that at me?

05:51:14.459 --> 05:51:19.080
I'm sorry, Your Majesty. he said, ducking

05:51:19.080 --> 05:51:19.380
his head.

05:51:19.439 --> 05:51:20.880
I just...

05:51:20.880 --> 05:51:23.700
Never expected you to be one of the

05:51:23.700 --> 05:51:25.799
queens who argued for helping the

05:51:25.799 --> 05:51:26.759
Pentalan dragons.

05:51:26.819 --> 05:51:31.139
I am familiar with a concept of empathy.

05:51:31.200 --> 05:51:34.020
Cousin, Snowfall said frostily.

05:51:34.080 --> 05:51:36.959
Would you 2 please shut your glamorous

05:51:36.959 --> 05:51:38.099
ice wing snout?

05:51:38.159 --> 05:51:39.060
Kibley said.

05:51:39.119 --> 05:51:40.860
I'm not finished.

05:51:40.919 --> 05:51:42.240
Listen to my awesome plan.

05:51:42.299 --> 05:51:43.979
Instead of armies.

05:51:44.040 --> 05:51:47.279
We have to send a secret stealth team of

05:51:47.279 --> 05:51:48.659
dragons to Pantala.

05:51:48.720 --> 05:51:49.799
Their mission?

05:51:49.860 --> 05:51:51.840
To find out the truth about the breath of

05:51:51.840 --> 05:51:53.459
evil, and how to destroy it.

05:51:53.520 --> 05:51:55.680
That sounds.

05:51:56.159 --> 05:51:59.279
Much easier said than done, Winter

05:51:59.279 --> 05:51:59.700
observed.

05:51:59.759 --> 05:52:02.459
I want to go with the Secret Stealth team

05:52:02.459 --> 05:52:03.599
Cricket said.

05:52:03.659 --> 05:52:04.979
Me.

05:52:05.040 --> 05:52:07.439
The little hive wing shouted from the top

05:52:07.439 --> 05:52:08.040
of the boulder.

05:52:08.159 --> 05:52:09.659
Me stealth.

05:52:09.720 --> 05:52:12.240
She leaped off the boulder. flapped her

05:52:12.240 --> 05:52:14.220
wings wildly for a moment, and then

05:52:14.220 --> 05:52:15.540
somersaulted into the grass.

05:52:15.599 --> 05:52:19.259
Daffodil crouched and held out one hand

05:52:19.259 --> 05:52:21.000
and the tiny dragonette wobbled over to

05:52:21.000 --> 05:52:23.099
sniff it, warbling cheerfully.

05:52:23.159 --> 05:52:24.959
Find out the truth?

05:52:25.080 --> 05:52:26.220
Leng asked.

05:52:26.279 --> 05:52:27.720
How exactly?

05:52:27.779 --> 05:52:30.540
Kibley pointed at Snowfall.

05:52:30.599 --> 05:52:33.240
By going into the abyss.

05:52:33.360 --> 05:52:35.639
Everyone stared at him.

05:52:35.700 --> 05:52:38.459
He flapped his wings with dramatic

05:52:38.459 --> 05:52:39.180
exasperation.

05:52:39.240 --> 05:52:41.159
Come on, everybody.

05:52:41.220 --> 05:52:43.500
Haven't you been listening to Moon's

05:52:43.500 --> 05:52:44.040
prophecy?

05:52:44.099 --> 05:52:47.520
A secret buried far below may save those

05:52:47.520 --> 05:52:48.360
brave enough to look.

05:52:48.479 --> 05:52:52.380
What farther below than an abyss?

05:52:52.439 --> 05:52:53.520
Seriously?

05:52:53.580 --> 05:52:55.560
This one is much clearer than the last

05:52:55.560 --> 05:52:55.799
one.

05:52:55.919 --> 05:52:59.040
Three moons, Winter said.

05:52:59.159 --> 05:53:02.040
I sincerely hate to say this, but I think

05:53:02.040 --> 05:53:02.880
Kibli might be right.

05:53:02.939 --> 05:53:07.259
Also, bonus, a stealth team mission is

05:53:07.259 --> 05:53:09.180
something we can do without requiring

05:53:09.180 --> 05:53:11.220
armies and soldiers from all the queens

05:53:11.220 --> 05:53:13.020
Kibley pointed out.

05:53:13.080 --> 05:53:15.119
I think we could get everyone on board

05:53:15.119 --> 05:53:15.720
with this plan.

05:53:15.779 --> 05:53:18.659
And while the secret team is gone

05:53:18.659 --> 05:53:21.419
Snowfall said, we could get our armies

05:53:21.419 --> 05:53:23.880
ready, just in case we do need them to

05:53:23.880 --> 05:53:24.720
fight at some point.

05:53:24.840 --> 05:53:26.639
Far below.

05:53:26.700 --> 05:53:29.700
Cricket echoed, staring off toward the

05:53:29.700 --> 05:53:30.240
setting sun.

05:53:30.299 --> 05:53:32.400
It does make sense.

05:53:32.459 --> 05:53:34.380
If everything in that vision was true.

05:53:34.439 --> 05:53:37.139
But how are we going to find this abyss?

05:53:37.259 --> 05:53:39.479
Do we have to search all of Pantala?

05:53:39.540 --> 05:53:42.119
Kibli scratched his head awkwardly.

05:53:42.180 --> 05:53:46.319
Well, he said, it would be helpful if we

05:53:46.319 --> 05:53:47.580
had someone who could talk to the

05:53:47.580 --> 05:53:48.540
scavengers for us.

05:53:48.599 --> 05:53:51.659
He glanced sideways at Skye and Wren.

05:53:51.779 --> 05:53:54.540
Absolutely not, Ren said.

05:53:54.659 --> 05:53:56.580
I don't know what you're talking about

05:53:56.580 --> 05:53:58.560
but I'm very sure I don't like the sound

05:53:58.560 --> 05:53:58.919
of it.

05:53:59.099 --> 05:54:00.299
What?

05:54:00.419 --> 05:54:03.180
Sky tore his gaze away from a chipmunk

05:54:03.180 --> 05:54:04.919
that was adorably nibbling something near

05:54:04.919 --> 05:54:05.459
his talons.

05:54:05.520 --> 05:54:07.319
Sorry, what?

05:54:07.380 --> 05:54:09.900
We're offering to take you to the other

05:54:09.900 --> 05:54:11.400
continent, cricket said.

05:54:11.459 --> 05:54:13.619
To meet humans from all the way across

05:54:13.619 --> 05:54:14.220
the sea.

05:54:14.279 --> 05:54:15.180
Can you imagine?

05:54:15.240 --> 05:54:17.340
Just think, what are they like?

05:54:17.400 --> 05:54:19.979
How different are their lives from yours

05:54:19.979 --> 05:54:21.299
and how much is the same?

05:54:21.360 --> 05:54:23.819
Isn't that just amazing to think about?

05:54:23.880 --> 05:54:26.159
I'm all right where I am.

05:54:26.220 --> 05:54:27.840
Thank you, Ren said.

05:54:27.959 --> 05:54:30.119
I don't need another continent full of

05:54:30.119 --> 05:54:30.779
people to worry about.

05:54:30.840 --> 05:54:32.580
This one is quite sufficient.

05:54:32.639 --> 05:54:36.779
But you could save so many dragons, Kibley

05:54:36.779 --> 05:54:36.959
said.

05:54:37.080 --> 05:54:39.959
If you help us find the Pentalan humans

05:54:39.959 --> 05:54:42.540
and they can take us to the abyss, and we

05:54:42.540 --> 05:54:43.860
can stop the breath of evil.

05:54:43.919 --> 05:54:46.560
I mean, you'd be saving the entire world

05:54:46.560 --> 05:54:47.159
basically.

05:54:47.220 --> 05:54:49.380
Ren pointed at him.

05:54:49.439 --> 05:54:51.360
That does sound fun.

05:54:51.419 --> 05:54:54.000
Except for the part where I probably get

05:54:54.000 --> 05:54:57.000
eaten and Sky probably gets evil breath

05:54:57.000 --> 05:54:57.779
whatever that is.

05:54:57.900 --> 05:55:00.479
Sky snort chuckled.

05:55:00.599 --> 05:55:03.180
Leaves the one with evil breath, at least

05:55:03.180 --> 05:55:04.200
1st thing in the morning.

05:55:04.259 --> 05:55:08.220
Hush, you, Ren said, nudging him.

05:55:08.279 --> 05:55:10.439
We won't let you get eaten.

05:55:10.500 --> 05:55:14.400
Winter said in his most noble voice, Every

05:55:14.400 --> 05:55:16.680
dragon on the quest would protect you

05:55:16.680 --> 05:55:17.639
with his or her life.

05:55:17.759 --> 05:55:20.459
I would gladly sacrifice myself to keep

05:55:20.459 --> 05:55:20.939
you safe.

05:55:21.000 --> 05:55:22.619
Too much.

05:55:22.740 --> 05:55:25.619
Kibley said, patting Winter's talon

05:55:25.619 --> 05:55:26.040
gently.

05:55:26.099 --> 05:55:29.099
Very heroic and dashing, but you can take

05:55:29.099 --> 05:55:29.759
it down a notch.

05:55:29.880 --> 05:55:31.919
I can take care of myself.

05:55:31.979 --> 05:55:35.099
Sky is the one I'm worried about, Ren

05:55:35.099 --> 05:55:35.459
explained.

05:55:35.520 --> 05:55:39.360
He is not a super stealth or a fighting

05:55:39.360 --> 05:55:40.560
evil kind of dragon.

05:55:40.619 --> 05:55:43.860
He is a, But do the bad guys know about

05:55:43.860 --> 05:55:44.520
pandas?

05:55:44.580 --> 05:55:46.680
Because then I bet they wouldn't be evil

05:55:46.680 --> 05:55:48.119
anymore, kind of dragon.

05:55:48.180 --> 05:55:51.540
Well, but Sky protested.

05:55:51.599 --> 05:55:55.560
I mean, pandas, have you seen pandas?

05:55:55.680 --> 05:55:58.919
Is there any chance you're actually a

05:55:58.919 --> 05:55:59.639
rain wing?

05:55:59.700 --> 05:56:00.599
Winter asked.

05:56:00.659 --> 05:56:04.500
You can't take Sky into a war zone, Ren

05:56:04.500 --> 05:56:06.779
said, wrapping her arms around his neck

05:56:06.779 --> 05:56:07.799
as far as they would go.

05:56:07.860 --> 05:56:12.299
I'd be all right, Skye said, nudging her

05:56:12.299 --> 05:56:13.020
head with a snout.

05:56:13.080 --> 05:56:15.720
Everyone else could do the shouty, stabby

05:56:15.720 --> 05:56:17.520
parts, and I could just talk to the

05:56:17.520 --> 05:56:17.880
humans.

05:56:17.939 --> 05:56:20.159
And maybe the other continent has

05:56:20.159 --> 05:56:22.500
something even cuter than pandas.

05:56:22.619 --> 05:56:25.380
We have lots of different kinds of

05:56:25.380 --> 05:56:25.919
monkeys.

05:56:25.979 --> 05:56:27.720
Crickets said, hopefully.

05:56:27.779 --> 05:56:31.020
Snowfall could tell that Wren was not

05:56:31.020 --> 05:56:33.119
buying any of this, and that she was the

05:56:33.119 --> 05:56:34.319
one who made the decisions for these

05:56:34.319 --> 05:56:34.560
two.

05:56:34.680 --> 05:56:38.939
Think like a scavin- human, she thought.

05:56:39.000 --> 05:56:41.819
Remember what it felt like to be Raven.

05:56:41.880 --> 05:56:43.319
What did they want?

05:56:43.380 --> 05:56:45.060
What did they worry about?

05:56:45.119 --> 05:56:48.299
What do I know they could change Ren's

05:56:48.299 --> 05:56:48.419
mind?

05:56:48.479 --> 05:56:50.819
Human, she said.

05:56:50.939 --> 05:56:54.180
I mean, Wren. listen.

05:56:54.299 --> 05:56:56.759
What if the agreement went 2 ways?

05:56:56.819 --> 05:57:00.119
You and Skye help us save dragons, and we

05:57:00.119 --> 05:57:01.200
help you save humans?

05:57:01.259 --> 05:57:04.860
Ran glanced over at Daffodil, who was

05:57:04.860 --> 05:57:07.259
tossing the baby hive wing up in the air

05:57:07.259 --> 05:57:08.639
and then catching her again as the

05:57:08.639 --> 05:57:09.659
dragonette giggled.

05:57:09.720 --> 05:57:11.099
Keep talking.

05:57:11.159 --> 05:57:14.279
All the queens of the dragon tribes are

05:57:14.279 --> 05:57:16.740
here in sanctuary right now, Snowfall

05:57:16.740 --> 05:57:17.040
said.

05:57:17.099 --> 05:57:20.040
In exchange for your help, we could issue

05:57:20.040 --> 05:57:22.259
an edict that dragons are no longer

05:57:22.259 --> 05:57:25.080
allowed to hunt or eat humans in any of

05:57:25.080 --> 05:57:25.680
our kingdoms.

05:57:25.799 --> 05:57:31.080
Ooh, Skye said, nudging ran again.

05:57:31.139 --> 05:57:33.659
Ivy would love that.

05:57:33.779 --> 05:57:37.319
Every human would love that, Ren said.

05:57:37.439 --> 05:57:38.759
But would it work?

05:57:38.819 --> 05:57:41.159
Do dragons listen to their queens?

05:57:41.220 --> 05:57:42.720
How would it be enforced?

05:57:42.779 --> 05:57:45.419
And what if the next queen reverses the

05:57:45.419 --> 05:57:45.840
edict?

05:57:45.900 --> 05:57:49.380
My tribe listens to their queen.

05:57:49.500 --> 05:57:51.180
Snowfall said haughtily.

05:57:51.240 --> 05:57:54.299
And there isn't going to be a next queen

05:57:54.299 --> 05:57:55.860
for a very long time.

05:57:55.919 --> 05:57:58.979
It's worth a try, isn't it?

05:57:59.040 --> 05:58:00.959
Kibley said to Ren.

05:58:01.020 --> 05:58:03.180
It would probably save a lot of humans

05:58:03.180 --> 05:58:05.459
even if some dragons disobeyed the

05:58:05.459 --> 05:58:05.759
orders.

05:58:05.819 --> 05:58:07.919
I love this plan.

05:58:07.979 --> 05:58:09.599
Skye said happily.

05:58:09.659 --> 05:58:11.279
Let's do this plan.

05:58:11.340 --> 05:58:15.240
It is a great idea, Kibley said to

05:58:15.240 --> 05:58:15.659
Snowfall.

05:58:15.720 --> 05:58:20.099
See, Blank said, thwacking Kibli's wing

05:58:20.099 --> 05:58:20.459
with her own.

05:58:20.580 --> 05:58:23.700
I told you, best queen ever.

05:58:23.759 --> 05:58:26.939
Snowfall fluffed out her wings and gave

05:58:26.939 --> 05:58:29.340
Winter I, who's the best cousin for the

05:58:29.340 --> 05:58:31.319
throne now, face?

05:58:31.380 --> 05:58:34.500
which was a little unwarranted since he'd

05:58:34.500 --> 05:58:36.000
never shown any sign of preferring

05:58:36.000 --> 05:58:36.419
crystal.

05:58:36.479 --> 05:58:39.119
But he was the nearest ice wing she could

05:58:39.119 --> 05:58:40.020
make a smug face at.

05:58:40.080 --> 05:58:43.439
Truthfully, she thought the other queens

05:58:43.439 --> 05:58:45.119
would probably issue an edict like that

05:58:45.119 --> 05:58:47.639
with or without Wren's agreement to come

05:58:47.639 --> 05:58:48.360
to Pantala.

05:58:48.419 --> 05:58:51.360
Once they realized that scavengers could

05:58:51.360 --> 05:58:55.200
think and read and talk like dragons, she

05:58:55.200 --> 05:58:56.520
assumed they wouldn't be at all

05:58:56.520 --> 05:58:57.900
interested in eating them anymore.

05:58:57.959 --> 05:59:02.459
No more pet scavengers either, Ren said

05:59:02.459 --> 05:59:04.080
wagging her finger at winter again.

05:59:04.139 --> 05:59:06.779
She might have noticed the wistful

05:59:06.779 --> 05:59:08.880
glances he kept casting at daffodil.

05:59:08.939 --> 05:59:10.680
That should be in there too.

05:59:10.799 --> 05:59:15.180
Unless they want to be dragon pets, Skye

05:59:15.180 --> 05:59:17.939
said, or the hats are very cute.

05:59:18.000 --> 05:59:21.900
Do humans love hats, Winter asked

05:59:21.900 --> 05:59:22.380
hopefully.

05:59:22.439 --> 05:59:25.560
I could get put daffodilla hat.

05:59:25.680 --> 05:59:28.740
No, we do not love hats.

05:59:28.799 --> 05:59:30.659
Wren glared at Skye.

05:59:30.720 --> 05:59:33.299
And daffodil would be the worst pet

05:59:33.299 --> 05:59:33.479
really.

05:59:33.540 --> 05:59:35.700
She might be willing to stay and practice

05:59:35.700 --> 05:59:37.500
her dragon with you for a while, though

05:59:37.500 --> 05:59:40.319
if you'd actually listen and not lock her

05:59:40.319 --> 05:59:40.619
up.

05:59:40.619 --> 05:59:43.319
And if you let her keep playing with

05:59:43.319 --> 05:59:44.040
Bumblebee.

05:59:44.099 --> 05:59:45.299
Cricket observed.

05:59:45.360 --> 05:59:48.180
The hive wing dragonette was now curled

05:59:48.180 --> 05:59:50.939
around daffodil's shoulders, winding the

05:59:50.939 --> 05:59:52.560
human's hair between her claws.

05:59:52.619 --> 05:59:56.340
I promise, Winters said meekly.

05:59:56.400 --> 05:59:57.599
No more pets.

05:59:57.720 --> 06:00:00.060
I'll tell everyone else.

06:00:00.119 --> 06:00:02.700
He gave Kibley a suddenly horrified

06:00:02.700 --> 06:00:03.000
luck.

06:00:03.060 --> 06:00:05.459
Smolder has a pet human.

06:00:05.520 --> 06:00:07.560
He's had her for years.

06:00:07.799 --> 06:00:09.720
We must fly at once to convince him to

06:00:09.720 --> 06:00:10.080
free her.

06:00:10.200 --> 06:00:13.680
Oh no, she's fine, Ren said.

06:00:13.740 --> 06:00:15.659
We've met, and she's happy.

06:00:15.720 --> 06:00:16.380
Don't worry about her.

06:00:16.500 --> 06:00:20.099
Hmm, Winters said, subsiding.

06:00:20.159 --> 06:00:23.400
Let's go talk to the other queens

06:00:23.400 --> 06:00:24.419
Snowfall said.

06:00:24.540 --> 06:00:27.419
You 2 can stay here and think about our

06:00:27.419 --> 06:00:30.000
offer, and we hope you'll still be here

06:00:30.000 --> 06:00:31.619
to discuss it when we return.

06:00:31.680 --> 06:00:35.220
She beckoned imperiously to Kibley, and

06:00:35.220 --> 06:00:36.959
swept across the clearing with links

06:00:36.959 --> 06:00:37.979
trotting along beside her.

06:00:38.040 --> 06:00:39.900
Will this work?

06:00:40.020 --> 06:00:42.299
Snowfall flicked her tail.

06:00:42.360 --> 06:00:45.119
Sending a small group of dragons over to

06:00:45.119 --> 06:00:47.340
Pantala. armed with a talon full of

06:00:47.340 --> 06:00:49.439
tranquilizer darts, a line from a

06:00:49.439 --> 06:00:51.060
prophecy and a scavenger.

06:00:51.119 --> 06:00:54.599
She thought of the chillingly malevolent

06:00:54.599 --> 06:00:57.360
feel of wasps' brain, and the evil

06:00:57.360 --> 06:00:59.580
tendrils she'd felt wound all the way

06:00:59.580 --> 06:00:59.939
through it.

06:01:00.000 --> 06:01:03.900
Is there anything that can save Tao, and

06:01:03.900 --> 06:01:06.720
Bryony, and Blue, and Io, and everyone

06:01:06.720 --> 06:01:07.020
else?

06:01:07.080 --> 06:01:09.599
Or is the prophecy right?

06:01:09.659 --> 06:01:13.020
And none of the tribes will survive?

06:01:13.080 --> 06:01:17.040
Part 3.

06:01:17.340 --> 06:01:19.380
Walls of ice.

06:01:19.439 --> 06:01:21.720
Chapter 20.

06:01:22.080 --> 06:01:25.500
The night before their return to the Ice

06:01:25.500 --> 06:01:28.380
Kingdom, Snowfall had no dreams at all.

06:01:28.439 --> 06:01:31.080
She slept peacefully until quite some

06:01:31.080 --> 06:01:34.139
time past dawn, and woke up slowly to

06:01:34.139 --> 06:01:37.080
wrestling leaves, bars of sunlight, and

06:01:37.080 --> 06:01:39.299
several worried ice wing faces ducking

06:01:39.299 --> 06:01:40.439
away as she opened her eyes.

06:01:40.500 --> 06:01:42.659
Except for two.

06:01:42.720 --> 06:01:45.599
Links and crystals stayed where they were

06:01:45.599 --> 06:01:46.439
watching her.

06:01:46.560 --> 06:01:49.799
Lynx looked disgustingly cheerful, as

06:01:49.799 --> 06:01:52.680
usual, and Crystal wore a mask of boredom

06:01:52.680 --> 06:01:55.439
over something Snowfall now realized was

06:01:55.439 --> 06:01:56.040
nervousness.

06:01:56.099 --> 06:01:59.700
Her tail kept twitching, and she glanced

06:01:59.700 --> 06:02:01.439
at the trees occasionally as if she was

06:02:01.439 --> 06:02:02.759
thinking about flying away.

06:02:02.939 --> 06:02:07.200
Good morning, Snowfall said, stretching.

06:02:07.259 --> 06:02:09.779
Crystal, I have made a decision.

06:02:09.840 --> 06:02:12.119
If you would like to return to the ice

06:02:12.119 --> 06:02:14.819
kingdom anytime, for any reason.

06:02:14.880 --> 06:02:17.520
I give you my word, I will not have you

06:02:17.520 --> 06:02:17.939
killed.

06:02:18.000 --> 06:02:19.020
Wait.

06:02:19.080 --> 06:02:21.599
Unless you come with an army to try and

06:02:21.599 --> 06:02:23.939
steal my throne, then I will probably

06:02:23.939 --> 06:02:24.779
have to kill you.

06:02:24.900 --> 06:02:28.380
So, I guess I mean, if you would like to

06:02:28.380 --> 06:02:30.720
return to the ice kingdom anytime, for

06:02:30.720 --> 06:02:33.720
any not deposing snowfall reason, you are

06:02:33.720 --> 06:02:34.979
welcome, and you'll be safe.

06:02:35.040 --> 06:02:37.860
Oh, Crystal said.

06:02:37.919 --> 06:02:39.779
I, thank you.

06:02:39.840 --> 06:02:43.080
If it helps, I have no intention of ever

06:02:43.080 --> 06:02:45.840
bringing an army to steal the throne, I

06:02:45.840 --> 06:02:46.799
really don't want it.

06:02:46.860 --> 06:02:50.880
Weirdo, Snowfall said, but nicely.

06:02:50.939 --> 06:02:53.580
Also, you have my permission to marry

06:02:53.580 --> 06:02:54.180
Garyel.

06:02:54.299 --> 06:02:57.959
I wasn't aware I needed that, Crystal

06:02:57.959 --> 06:02:59.819
said wryly, but thank you for that as

06:02:59.819 --> 06:03:00.000
well.

06:03:00.060 --> 06:03:02.939
Snowfall waved one talent.

06:03:03.000 --> 06:03:06.180
Permission, blessing, whatever you want

06:03:06.180 --> 06:03:08.459
to call it, your queen will not be mad.

06:03:08.520 --> 06:03:10.020
You will not be banished.

06:03:10.139 --> 06:03:12.779
Crystal tipped her snout down for a

06:03:12.779 --> 06:03:14.700
moment, then looked back up with

06:03:14.700 --> 06:03:16.259
suspiciously shiny eyes.

06:03:16.380 --> 06:03:19.020
I appreciate that, she said.

06:03:19.080 --> 06:03:23.279
It is very silly, Snowfall said, that you

06:03:23.279 --> 06:03:25.200
are more emotional about me approving

06:03:25.200 --> 06:03:27.060
your mud wing than you were about me

06:03:27.060 --> 06:03:28.139
promising not to kill you.

06:03:28.200 --> 06:03:32.400
I know, Crystal said, with a little laugh

06:03:32.400 --> 06:03:33.360
wiping her eyes.

06:03:33.419 --> 06:03:35.639
I just came to say goodbye.

06:03:35.700 --> 06:03:37.740
I heard you're flying home today.

06:03:37.799 --> 06:03:40.500
Yes, Snowfall said.

06:03:40.560 --> 06:03:43.259
We had an excellent council of queens

06:03:43.259 --> 06:03:45.779
yesterday, and I was an extremely

06:03:45.779 --> 06:03:48.060
excellent queen part of it, wasn't I

06:03:48.060 --> 06:03:48.540
lynx?

06:03:48.599 --> 06:03:51.840
Absolutely marvelous, Link said.

06:03:51.900 --> 06:03:55.200
We need a better name than Secret Stealth

06:03:55.200 --> 06:03:55.799
team, though?

06:03:55.919 --> 06:03:56.819
Snowfall said.

06:03:56.880 --> 06:03:59.819
Anyway, the queens agree that we'll all

06:03:59.819 --> 06:04:02.520
stop eating scavengers, and we chose the

06:04:02.520 --> 06:04:04.560
group that's going to go to Pantala to

06:04:04.560 --> 06:04:06.540
search for the Abyss and the Pentalaan

06:04:06.540 --> 06:04:08.880
humans, which means I'll have to carry

06:04:08.880 --> 06:04:10.860
another map back over to that continent

06:04:10.860 --> 06:04:12.060
but it can't be helped.

06:04:12.119 --> 06:04:14.819
Personally, I think they should eat it

06:04:14.819 --> 06:04:15.479
when they get there.

06:04:15.540 --> 06:04:18.779
I can't believe it about scavengers

06:04:18.779 --> 06:04:21.419
Crystal said, looking a little green.

06:04:21.479 --> 06:04:23.159
When I think.

06:04:23.279 --> 06:04:25.319
I just can't think about it.

06:04:25.380 --> 06:04:27.240
I have a feeling.

06:04:27.299 --> 06:04:29.340
A lot of dragons are going to be pretty

06:04:29.340 --> 06:04:31.500
horrified, Lang said.

06:04:31.560 --> 06:04:34.560
And some others are going to violently

06:04:34.560 --> 06:04:37.020
deny that it's true, so that they don't

06:04:37.020 --> 06:04:38.279
have to feel bad about themselves.

06:04:38.340 --> 06:04:40.380
Snowball pointed out.

06:04:40.439 --> 06:04:42.540
But that is a problem for another day.

06:04:42.599 --> 06:04:45.299
Today, my problem is that going home

06:04:45.299 --> 06:04:47.819
means I'll have to rearrange all the

06:04:47.819 --> 06:04:49.380
names on the stupid wall again.

06:04:49.500 --> 06:04:53.759
Oh, wow, the wall, Crystal said with a

06:04:53.759 --> 06:04:53.939
laugh.

06:04:54.000 --> 06:04:55.979
I totally forgot about that.

06:04:56.040 --> 06:04:59.580
How can you forget about the wall

06:04:59.580 --> 06:05:00.840
Snowfall said, shocked.

06:05:00.959 --> 06:05:03.240
You're still near the top of the 1st

06:05:03.240 --> 06:05:03.720
circle.

06:05:03.779 --> 06:05:04.799
I kept you there.

06:05:04.860 --> 06:05:06.779
Crystal shrugged.

06:05:06.840 --> 06:05:09.060
I guess when you're away from it for long

06:05:09.060 --> 06:05:09.299
enough.

06:05:09.360 --> 06:05:11.700
You realize how pointless it is.

06:05:11.759 --> 06:05:15.479
Lynx made a phase that snowfall like, this

06:05:15.479 --> 06:05:16.200
is what I was saying.

06:05:16.259 --> 06:05:18.840
Remember that time you totally yelled at

06:05:18.840 --> 06:05:19.020
me?

06:05:19.080 --> 06:05:20.220
I was totally right.

06:05:20.279 --> 06:05:21.599
And look, she thinks so too.

06:05:21.720 --> 06:05:24.779
Well fine, Snowfall said.

06:05:24.840 --> 06:05:27.119
Say goodbye to our mud wing for us.

06:05:27.180 --> 06:05:29.580
I'm Asgobi and namely polite to the other

06:05:29.580 --> 06:05:31.080
queens for half the day before we can

06:05:31.080 --> 06:05:31.319
leave.

06:05:31.380 --> 06:05:34.500
You sound a lot more like yourself today

06:05:34.500 --> 06:05:35.759
Links observed.

06:05:35.819 --> 06:05:37.619
Was that true?

06:05:37.680 --> 06:05:40.560
Maybe a night with no visions had brought

06:05:40.560 --> 06:05:41.939
her back to herself completely?

06:05:42.000 --> 06:05:43.860
Maybe the visions were over?

06:05:43.919 --> 06:05:46.680
Snowfall hugged hopefully on the ring.

06:05:46.740 --> 06:05:49.500
Nope, still stuck.

06:05:49.560 --> 06:05:51.659
She'd have to tell the guards to stay

06:05:51.659 --> 06:05:53.759
close enough to catch her in case she

06:05:53.759 --> 06:05:55.200
suddenly fell out of the sky on the

06:05:55.200 --> 06:05:55.680
flight home.

06:05:55.740 --> 06:05:59.700
The queens had decided that face a great

06:05:59.700 --> 06:06:02.580
evil with talent united, meant they

06:06:02.580 --> 06:06:04.619
should send one dragon from each tribe on

06:06:04.619 --> 06:06:05.040
the mission.

06:06:05.099 --> 06:06:08.340
Personally, Snowfall thought a team of 10

06:06:08.340 --> 06:06:11.459
dragons wasn't the most stealthy idea, but

06:06:11.459 --> 06:06:12.959
she wasn't about to wade into the

06:06:12.959 --> 06:06:14.639
question of which tribes should be left

06:06:14.639 --> 06:06:14.880
out.

06:06:14.939 --> 06:06:17.639
Some of the choices were easy.

06:06:17.759 --> 06:06:20.580
They only had one hive wing, for instance

06:06:20.580 --> 06:06:23.159
and Skye had to be the Sky Wing, and

06:06:23.159 --> 06:06:24.959
tsunami didn't bother to ask anyone's

06:06:24.959 --> 06:06:27.240
permission to be the sea wing, although

06:06:27.240 --> 06:06:29.220
Queen Carl seemed fine with it once she

06:06:29.220 --> 06:06:29.580
arrived.

06:06:29.639 --> 06:06:33.060
Luna and Sundu convinced Hazel to let

06:06:33.060 --> 06:06:35.279
them be the Silk Wing and Leaf Wing

06:06:35.279 --> 06:06:35.880
representatives.

06:06:35.939 --> 06:06:38.639
Queen Thorn looked worried when Kibli

06:06:38.639 --> 06:06:40.799
said he wanted to go, but she agreed that

06:06:40.799 --> 06:06:41.759
he was the best choice.

06:06:41.819 --> 06:06:44.759
Snowfall could see how much she didn't

06:06:44.759 --> 06:06:45.299
want to lose him.

06:06:45.360 --> 06:06:48.900
Queen Morehen offered a brawny mud wing

06:06:48.900 --> 06:06:50.939
nearly twice the size of most of the

06:06:50.939 --> 06:06:52.799
other dragons, a volunteer named

06:06:52.799 --> 06:06:53.700
Bullfrog.

06:06:53.759 --> 06:06:56.520
Queen Glory had to choose 2 dragons.

06:06:56.580 --> 06:06:58.740
She settled on a serious looking rain

06:06:58.740 --> 06:07:01.020
wing with a very silly name of pineapple

06:07:01.020 --> 06:07:02.939
and moon for the night wing.

06:07:03.000 --> 06:07:06.479
Snowfall had the hardest choice, in her

06:07:06.479 --> 06:07:09.119
opinion, because she had 2 ice wings who

06:07:09.119 --> 06:07:10.200
really wanted to go.

06:07:10.259 --> 06:07:13.380
On the one talon, she wanted links to

06:07:13.380 --> 06:07:15.659
come back to the ice kingdom with her, to

06:07:15.659 --> 06:07:17.880
join her new council, and keep Snowfall

06:07:17.880 --> 06:07:18.240
sane.

06:07:18.299 --> 06:07:21.659
On the other talent, she trusted Links

06:07:21.659 --> 06:07:23.580
more than any other ice wing, and

06:07:23.580 --> 06:07:25.979
Snowfall knew for certain that Links was

06:07:25.979 --> 06:07:27.779
smart and clever enough to be very

06:07:27.779 --> 06:07:28.979
valuable on the mission.

06:07:29.340 --> 06:07:32.279
On the 3rd talent, Winter was

06:07:32.279 --> 06:07:34.979
occasionally quite smart too, and she

06:07:34.979 --> 06:07:36.119
wouldn't miss him nearly as much.

06:07:36.240 --> 06:07:39.299
But on the 4th talon, would sending him

06:07:39.299 --> 06:07:39.900
really count?

06:07:39.959 --> 06:07:42.479
If he was technically banished and not

06:07:42.479 --> 06:07:43.319
part of the tribe.

06:07:43.380 --> 06:07:45.840
Would Snowfall be risking the whole

06:07:45.840 --> 06:07:47.700
mission, just because she wanted to keep

06:07:47.700 --> 06:07:48.900
her friend close to her?

06:07:48.959 --> 06:07:52.439
She didn't say any of that to them, but

06:07:52.439 --> 06:07:54.060
she did gradually admit to herself that

06:07:54.060 --> 06:07:56.819
friend was the right word for links after

06:07:56.819 --> 06:07:57.000
all.

06:07:57.060 --> 06:08:00.180
In the end, she chose links.

06:08:00.240 --> 06:08:02.819
Winter would be useful in sanctuary

06:08:02.819 --> 06:08:05.580
overseeing the scavenger outreach project

06:08:05.580 --> 06:08:07.740
and keeping daffodil safe.

06:08:07.799 --> 06:08:09.959
Snowfall did not like to think about how

06:08:09.959 --> 06:08:12.299
Ren would react if she came back from

06:08:12.299 --> 06:08:14.520
Pantala and someone had accidentally

06:08:14.520 --> 06:08:15.779
stepped on daffodil.

06:08:15.840 --> 06:08:18.900
So the stealth team was gathered, and

06:08:18.900 --> 06:08:20.340
there was a ceremony for them that

06:08:20.340 --> 06:08:22.979
involved a lot of awkward talent holding

06:08:22.979 --> 06:08:24.419
and speeches from the queens.

06:08:24.479 --> 06:08:28.979
Boring, boring, snowfall thought, and

06:08:28.979 --> 06:08:31.319
tried not to look at links too often, in

06:08:31.319 --> 06:08:33.540
case something stupid and wet happened to

06:08:33.540 --> 06:08:34.439
her eyeballs.

06:08:34.680 --> 06:08:36.180
She'll be back.

06:08:36.240 --> 06:08:38.459
She has to come back.

06:08:38.520 --> 06:08:42.779
She watched Sky instead, who was so

06:08:42.779 --> 06:08:46.020
excited about all his new dragon friends

06:08:46.020 --> 06:08:48.360
and his valiant purpose, and heroic

06:08:48.360 --> 06:08:50.520
destiny, and absolutely everything.

06:08:50.580 --> 06:08:53.520
Then she realized how much she was going

06:08:53.520 --> 06:08:55.500
to worry about his sweet, grinning face

06:08:55.500 --> 06:08:57.959
going into danger, and she had to fix her

06:08:57.959 --> 06:08:59.279
gaze on bullfrog instead.

06:08:59.340 --> 06:09:02.159
There was no risk that she'd get sappy

06:09:02.159 --> 06:09:03.180
and sentimental about him.

06:09:03.240 --> 06:09:06.659
When the polite farewells finally began

06:09:06.659 --> 06:09:08.340
Snowfall took a deep breath.

06:09:08.340 --> 06:09:11.279
There was something she had to do, even

06:09:11.279 --> 06:09:13.200
though it made her anxiety spike right up

06:09:13.200 --> 06:09:13.680
to the moons.

06:09:13.740 --> 06:09:17.520
She crossed the clearing to sundew, who

06:09:17.520 --> 06:09:19.139
was sitting with her tail twined around

06:09:19.139 --> 06:09:21.119
willows, holding one of her talons.

06:09:21.240 --> 06:09:23.700
Willow looked as though she'd been crying

06:09:23.700 --> 06:09:24.540
all morning.

06:09:24.599 --> 06:09:27.900
Sundew tilted her head to meet Snowfall's

06:09:27.900 --> 06:09:28.080
eyes.

06:09:28.200 --> 06:09:29.279
Yes?

06:09:29.340 --> 06:09:33.119
We don't have weapons. like the rain wing

06:09:33.119 --> 06:09:36.419
darts to offer you, Snowfall said, nodding

06:09:36.419 --> 06:09:38.040
to the pile that pineapple was sorting

06:09:38.040 --> 06:09:38.700
into pouches.

06:09:38.759 --> 06:09:40.979
But I wanted to give you something else

06:09:40.979 --> 06:09:43.139
since I'm guessing you're going to be the

06:09:43.139 --> 06:09:45.840
leader of this team, or you should be, no

06:09:45.840 --> 06:09:47.099
matter what tsunami thinks.

06:09:47.159 --> 06:09:49.740
And you're right, that our magic should

06:09:49.740 --> 06:09:51.779
have been able to help you, and if any

06:09:51.779 --> 06:09:53.639
piece of magic can help defeat that thing

06:09:53.639 --> 06:09:54.060
over there?

06:09:54.180 --> 06:09:56.040
I think you should have it.

06:09:56.099 --> 06:09:59.099
She unclipped the gift of stealth from

06:09:59.099 --> 06:10:02.279
her wrists, and sundew sat up, shining

06:10:02.279 --> 06:10:03.240
like the northern lights.

06:10:03.360 --> 06:10:04.619
Magic?

06:10:04.680 --> 06:10:06.299
The leaf wing echoed.

06:10:06.419 --> 06:10:09.479
This is how I made my army invisible.

06:10:09.540 --> 06:10:12.599
Snowfall said, passing the wristbands to

06:10:12.599 --> 06:10:12.779
her.

06:10:12.840 --> 06:10:16.020
It felt a bit like snapping off her horns

06:10:16.020 --> 06:10:18.659
and passing them over after so many days

06:10:18.659 --> 06:10:20.819
of having the reassuring magic weight of

06:10:20.819 --> 06:10:22.139
them on her arms.

06:10:22.200 --> 06:10:24.840
We call them the gift of stealth, and

06:10:24.840 --> 06:10:26.819
since stealth is literally in the name

06:10:26.819 --> 06:10:30.479
and that's your whole mission, I mean, It

06:10:30.479 --> 06:10:31.080
just makes sense.

06:10:31.139 --> 06:10:34.860
Sundu put them on reverently, the pale

06:10:34.860 --> 06:10:36.959
silver metal strange against her dark

06:10:36.959 --> 06:10:38.159
green and gold scales.

06:10:38.220 --> 06:10:39.720
How do they work?

06:10:39.779 --> 06:10:42.900
Snowfall explained everything from the

06:10:42.900 --> 06:10:45.180
notes in the treasury, and Sundew

06:10:45.180 --> 06:10:47.580
practiced turning herself, then Willow

06:10:47.580 --> 06:10:49.200
then both of them invisible.

06:10:49.259 --> 06:10:50.819
When they reappeared.

06:10:50.939 --> 06:10:52.799
Willow wrapped her wings around

06:10:52.799 --> 06:10:53.340
Snowfall.

06:10:53.400 --> 06:10:55.200
Thank you.

06:10:55.259 --> 06:10:57.540
She whispered in Snowfall's ear.

06:10:57.599 --> 06:10:59.759
I feel a little less worried now.

06:10:59.819 --> 06:11:02.159
What am I doing?

06:11:02.220 --> 06:11:05.340
Snowfall thought. giving away one of the

06:11:05.340 --> 06:11:07.380
only animous treasures my tribe has.

06:11:07.439 --> 06:11:10.139
Maybe one of the last ones that will ever

06:11:10.139 --> 06:11:11.220
be made in this world.

06:11:11.340 --> 06:11:13.919
Giving up ice wing magic.

06:11:13.979 --> 06:11:16.799
To a strange dragon from a far away

06:11:16.799 --> 06:11:17.099
land.

06:11:17.220 --> 06:11:20.759
Snowfall straightened her shoulders as

06:11:20.759 --> 06:11:22.680
Willow went back to Sundew's side.

06:11:22.799 --> 06:11:25.200
I'm choosing to trust them.

06:11:25.259 --> 06:11:27.479
This is the right thing to do.

06:11:27.540 --> 06:11:30.419
They need it to defeat the breath of evil

06:11:30.419 --> 06:11:32.459
and we all need them to succeed.

06:11:32.580 --> 06:11:36.240
I'll bring them back, Sundu promised.

06:11:36.299 --> 06:11:39.000
When we've won, and everyone is safe.

06:11:39.060 --> 06:11:40.259
I'll return them to you.

06:11:40.319 --> 06:11:42.900
Thank you, Queen Snowfall.

06:11:42.959 --> 06:11:45.659
Good luck, Snowfall said.

06:11:45.720 --> 06:11:48.659
She took a step back, glancing at the

06:11:48.659 --> 06:11:50.340
gift of stealth one last time.

06:11:50.400 --> 06:11:53.040
And then she turned and went up to the

06:11:53.040 --> 06:11:54.299
lake to find winter.

06:11:54.360 --> 06:11:58.139
Hello, she said, startling him into

06:11:58.139 --> 06:11:59.400
dropping the fish he'd just caught.

06:11:59.459 --> 06:12:02.340
I hereby decree that you are not banished

06:12:02.340 --> 06:12:04.560
anymore, unless you would like to be.

06:12:04.619 --> 06:12:07.680
Also, you can go back to that school, if

06:12:07.680 --> 06:12:08.220
you want to.

06:12:08.279 --> 06:12:09.959
I still don't care.

06:12:10.020 --> 06:12:15.060
She hesitated, but I guess there's a very

06:12:15.060 --> 06:12:18.419
tiny part of me that wants you to be

06:12:18.419 --> 06:12:20.220
happy, she finished in a rush.

06:12:20.340 --> 06:12:23.040
Winter dipped his front talons in the

06:12:23.040 --> 06:12:25.259
cold lake and smiled down at the water

06:12:25.259 --> 06:12:27.119
looking a little surprised and

06:12:27.119 --> 06:12:29.340
embarrassed, and pleased at the same

06:12:29.340 --> 06:12:29.520
time.

06:12:29.580 --> 06:12:33.060
Thank you, Your Majesty. he said.

06:12:33.119 --> 06:12:35.279
Ah, she said.

06:12:35.400 --> 06:12:36.900
It's too weird.

06:12:36.959 --> 06:12:38.819
Just call me Queen Snowfall.

06:12:38.939 --> 06:12:41.759
He laughed, and then his face turned

06:12:41.759 --> 06:12:42.540
serious again.

06:12:42.599 --> 06:12:46.020
Snowfall, you're my queen, and the ice

06:12:46.020 --> 06:12:48.299
wings will always be my tribe, whether

06:12:48.299 --> 06:12:51.180
I'm banished or not, but Jade Mountain

06:12:51.180 --> 06:12:52.139
and Sanctuary.

06:12:52.200 --> 06:12:55.020
They've made me feel like I'm part of a

06:12:55.020 --> 06:12:55.860
bigger tribe.

06:12:55.919 --> 06:12:57.840
Like I'm worth something more than a

06:12:57.840 --> 06:12:58.619
place on a wall.

06:12:58.680 --> 06:13:00.299
Hmm.

06:13:00.360 --> 06:13:03.360
I suppose you are, Snowfall said.

06:13:03.419 --> 06:13:04.860
It's possible.

06:13:04.919 --> 06:13:06.779
Everyone is, but you didn't hear that

06:13:06.779 --> 06:13:07.259
from me.

06:13:07.319 --> 06:13:09.060
Good luck with that little daffodil

06:13:09.060 --> 06:13:09.419
human.

06:13:09.479 --> 06:13:11.459
Stay in touch, winter.

06:13:11.520 --> 06:13:14.340
Snowfall made her way through all the

06:13:14.340 --> 06:13:16.799
polite goodbyes to the other queens, and

06:13:16.799 --> 06:13:18.240
eventually found her guards waiting for

06:13:18.240 --> 06:13:19.500
her, ready to fly.

06:13:19.560 --> 06:13:22.919
Standing with them was links, who also

06:13:22.919 --> 06:13:23.580
looked ready to fly.

06:13:23.700 --> 06:13:26.580
Aren't you leaving on a mission

06:13:26.580 --> 06:13:26.939
tomorrow?

06:13:27.000 --> 06:13:29.220
Snowfall demanded frowning at her.

06:13:29.279 --> 06:13:32.700
Day after tomorrow, actually, Lang said.

06:13:32.759 --> 06:13:35.279
I'm going to fly home with you 1st and

06:13:35.279 --> 06:13:37.020
then meet the others on Jaboa's beach.

06:13:37.139 --> 06:13:40.139
Snowfall did not let herself make the

06:13:40.139 --> 06:13:42.060
silly sky phase.

06:13:42.119 --> 06:13:44.040
She felt her inner dragon making.

06:13:44.099 --> 06:13:46.080
Oh, she said.

06:13:46.139 --> 06:13:47.040
Very well.

06:13:47.099 --> 06:13:48.840
I suppose that's fine with me.

06:13:48.900 --> 06:13:50.580
Because you need something from the

06:13:50.580 --> 06:13:51.119
palace.

06:13:51.180 --> 06:13:52.860
Dragons to say goodbye to.

06:13:52.919 --> 06:13:55.500
Lynx nudged her side and smiled.

06:13:55.560 --> 06:13:57.659
Just wanted to hang out with you for a

06:13:57.659 --> 06:13:58.200
couple more days.

06:13:58.259 --> 06:14:01.860
Snowfall scrunched her snout at her, so

06:14:01.860 --> 06:14:03.720
that she wouldn't either start beaming or

06:14:03.720 --> 06:14:04.919
burst into tears.

06:14:05.040 --> 06:14:06.779
Wow, fine.

06:14:06.840 --> 06:14:07.979
All right.

06:14:08.040 --> 06:14:09.840
I suppose that's fine with me too.

06:14:09.900 --> 06:14:13.200
It was late in the day when snowfall and

06:14:13.200 --> 06:14:15.779
lynx and the other 10 ice wings reached

06:14:15.779 --> 06:14:16.799
the great ice cliff.

06:14:16.860 --> 06:14:20.220
Snowfall saw it first, ahead of them in

06:14:20.220 --> 06:14:22.680
the distance, huge and glowing red gold

06:14:22.680 --> 06:14:23.459
in the sunset.

06:14:23.580 --> 06:14:26.040
For 1000s of years.

06:14:26.099 --> 06:14:28.979
It's kept all other tribes out of the ice

06:14:28.979 --> 06:14:29.459
kingdom.

06:14:29.520 --> 06:14:31.919
We always thought it kept us safe.

06:14:31.979 --> 06:14:33.900
I thought it was so important.

06:14:33.959 --> 06:14:37.319
I wanted to extend it all around us, so

06:14:37.319 --> 06:14:39.479
my tribe could huddle safely in our

06:14:39.479 --> 06:14:42.659
igloos and ice palaces, and no one would

06:14:42.659 --> 06:14:44.580
ever be able to get through our walls of

06:14:44.580 --> 06:14:44.880
ice.

06:14:44.939 --> 06:14:48.000
But if we'd all stayed hidden in the ice

06:14:48.000 --> 06:14:50.400
kingdom, Dark Stalker's plague would have

06:14:50.400 --> 06:14:52.740
killed us, we needed dragons from other

06:14:52.740 --> 06:14:55.860
tribes, working together. to recognize

06:14:55.860 --> 06:14:58.139
his magic and find a way to save us.

06:14:58.139 --> 06:15:01.259
We needed hybrids like Typhoon, who could

06:15:01.259 --> 06:15:03.119
cross the wall, and were spared the

06:15:03.119 --> 06:15:05.220
plague, to bring us those earrings.

06:15:05.340 --> 06:15:08.400
We only survived because of our

06:15:08.400 --> 06:15:10.020
connections to the other kingdom.

06:15:10.080 --> 06:15:12.419
Her wing beats slowed.

06:15:12.540 --> 06:15:16.680
And if the breath of evil comes here, if

06:15:16.680 --> 06:15:20.099
it lands in the ice kingdom first, we may

06:15:20.099 --> 06:15:21.779
need those connections again.

06:15:21.840 --> 06:15:25.080
Besides, I want to know what happens on

06:15:25.080 --> 06:15:25.799
Pantala.

06:15:25.919 --> 06:15:27.959
I want dragons to be able to come tell

06:15:27.959 --> 06:15:28.139
me.

06:15:28.259 --> 06:15:31.740
I want sundew and sky to be able to fly

06:15:31.740 --> 06:15:34.500
right into my kingdom and find me if they

06:15:34.500 --> 06:15:34.799
need to.

06:15:34.860 --> 06:15:38.040
She veered suddenly into a wind current

06:15:38.040 --> 06:15:39.599
that dropped toward the cliff.

06:15:39.659 --> 06:15:42.540
Startled, the others wheeled around to

06:15:42.540 --> 06:15:42.900
follow her.

06:15:42.959 --> 06:15:45.959
Snowfall landed on top of the cliff.

06:15:46.020 --> 06:15:48.060
She could see the sheer face of it

06:15:48.060 --> 06:15:49.500
dropping away on either side of her

06:15:49.500 --> 06:15:49.979
talons.

06:15:50.040 --> 06:15:52.979
Length hovered beside her, beating the

06:15:52.979 --> 06:15:53.639
air with her wings.

06:15:53.700 --> 06:15:56.220
What's happening?

06:15:56.279 --> 06:15:57.180
Lang asked.

06:15:57.240 --> 06:16:00.419
Snowfall adjusted her small, elegant

06:16:00.419 --> 06:16:00.720
crown.

06:16:00.779 --> 06:16:03.840
Did I ever tell you what this does?

06:16:03.959 --> 06:16:05.220
She asked, pointing to it.

06:16:05.279 --> 06:16:07.740
It's the tiara of strength.

06:16:07.799 --> 06:16:09.240
All right, all right.

06:16:09.299 --> 06:16:10.139
Stop laughing.

06:16:10.200 --> 06:16:12.840
It makes me very, very, very strong.

06:16:12.900 --> 06:16:15.479
So laughing at me is an even less good

06:16:15.479 --> 06:16:16.619
idea than it usually is.

06:16:16.680 --> 06:16:19.919
Anyway, my point is, that I've hardly

06:16:19.919 --> 06:16:22.200
gotten to play with it at all, since this

06:16:22.200 --> 06:16:24.959
turned out not to be the punching dragons

06:16:24.959 --> 06:16:27.240
in the snout expedition I thought it was

06:16:27.240 --> 06:16:27.599
going to be.

06:16:27.659 --> 06:16:31.080
I, for one, am quite glad we didn't have

06:16:31.080 --> 06:16:33.360
to punch any dragons in the snout, Lynx

06:16:33.360 --> 06:16:33.720
observed.

06:16:33.779 --> 06:16:36.240
Want to see how strong I am?

06:16:36.299 --> 06:16:37.680
Snowfall asked.

06:16:37.740 --> 06:16:41.040
She slammed her fist into the ice below

06:16:41.040 --> 06:16:41.279
her.

06:16:41.340 --> 06:16:45.299
Cracks shot out from the spot where her

06:16:45.299 --> 06:16:47.459
talents met the ice, and the surface

06:16:47.459 --> 06:16:48.180
below her shook.

06:16:48.240 --> 06:16:52.080
She punched it again as hard as she could

06:16:52.080 --> 06:16:55.080
and then had to lift into the air as the

06:16:55.080 --> 06:16:57.479
cliff began to shake harder, and chunks

06:16:57.479 --> 06:17:00.299
of ice broke off, and started avalanching

06:17:00.299 --> 06:17:01.619
down toward the snow below.

06:17:01.680 --> 06:17:05.400
Snowfall hit the cliff again and again

06:17:05.400 --> 06:17:08.040
triggering more cascades of ice and snow

06:17:08.040 --> 06:17:10.380
until she had punched a pretty impressive

06:17:10.380 --> 06:17:12.479
hole in it, if she did say so herself.

06:17:12.540 --> 06:17:14.340
Oof.

06:17:14.400 --> 06:17:16.500
Now her fists hurt.

06:17:16.560 --> 06:17:19.319
And her muscles ached, and she was very

06:17:19.319 --> 06:17:19.979
tired.

06:17:20.040 --> 06:17:23.580
But the look on the other ice wing's

06:17:23.580 --> 06:17:24.659
faces was worth it.

06:17:24.720 --> 06:17:29.700
That's amazing, Link said, flying down to

06:17:29.700 --> 06:17:31.860
swoop through the gap in the cliff, as if

06:17:31.860 --> 06:17:32.700
to make sure it was real.

06:17:32.819 --> 06:17:34.740
Does that break the spell?

06:17:34.799 --> 06:17:37.439
Can other tribes fly through here safely

06:17:37.439 --> 06:17:37.619
now?

06:17:37.680 --> 06:17:39.419
I'm not sure.

06:17:39.479 --> 06:17:40.680
Snowfall said.

06:17:40.740 --> 06:17:43.020
We'll come back soon with many more

06:17:43.020 --> 06:17:44.819
dragons and tear down the rest of it.

06:17:44.880 --> 06:17:47.700
She shook out her claws with a wince.

06:17:47.759 --> 06:17:50.220
Maybe I will let someone else wear the

06:17:50.220 --> 06:17:52.680
magic strength tiara, and I will do the

06:17:52.680 --> 06:17:54.659
ordering everybody around part instead.

06:17:54.779 --> 06:17:56.400
Wow.

06:17:56.459 --> 06:17:59.880
Links gathered a talon full of snow and

06:17:59.880 --> 06:18:01.919
packed it around snowfall's claws.

06:18:01.979 --> 06:18:04.919
What happened to everyone is evil and

06:18:04.919 --> 06:18:05.639
can't be trusted.

06:18:05.759 --> 06:18:08.279
Snowfall looked at her severely.

06:18:08.340 --> 06:18:11.639
I have been 6 different dragons and a

06:18:11.639 --> 06:18:14.520
human this week, and only one of them was

06:18:14.520 --> 06:18:14.819
evil.

06:18:14.880 --> 06:18:17.520
I am basically an expert on other dragons

06:18:17.520 --> 06:18:18.299
now.

06:18:18.360 --> 06:18:20.759
And with my knowledge of everything, I

06:18:20.759 --> 06:18:22.740
can now say for a fact that several

06:18:22.740 --> 06:18:24.900
dragons are not evil after all.

06:18:25.020 --> 06:18:27.720
Several dragons?

06:18:27.840 --> 06:18:29.880
Lang said in mock surprise.

06:18:29.939 --> 06:18:30.959
Are you sure?

06:18:31.080 --> 06:18:33.840
Snowfall flicked her with her tail.

06:18:33.900 --> 06:18:37.500
I might even say most dragons.

06:18:37.560 --> 06:18:39.360
Still dubious about you, though.

06:18:39.479 --> 06:18:41.880
Pretty sure that face you make when you

06:18:41.880 --> 06:18:44.220
think you've won puts you right into the

06:18:44.220 --> 06:18:45.419
evil category.

06:18:45.540 --> 06:18:48.479
Fair, said Lynx grinning.

06:18:48.599 --> 06:18:50.340
As long as I still win.

06:18:50.459 --> 06:18:53.819
She glanced up at the darkening sky, where

06:18:53.819 --> 06:18:55.080
stars were starting to glitter.

06:18:55.139 --> 06:18:57.779
It's getting a bit late to fly the rest

06:18:57.779 --> 06:18:59.099
of the way to the ice palace.

06:18:59.159 --> 06:19:01.139
Maybe we could make camp in the snow.

06:19:01.200 --> 06:19:02.340
What do you think?

06:19:02.400 --> 06:19:04.619
One more night away from the palace.

06:19:04.680 --> 06:19:08.459
Yes, let's do that, Snowfall said.

06:19:08.520 --> 06:19:10.080
She turned to the guards.

06:19:10.139 --> 06:19:12.240
If that's all right with all of you.

06:19:12.299 --> 06:19:15.360
They did a lot of startled blinking

06:19:15.360 --> 06:19:17.759
before one of them said, of course, Your

06:19:17.759 --> 06:19:18.419
Majesty.

06:19:18.479 --> 06:19:20.459
Whatever you wish is fine with us.

06:19:20.580 --> 06:19:23.880
It was pretty thrilling to be back in the

06:19:23.880 --> 06:19:26.279
ice kingdom, to be making their beds and

06:19:26.279 --> 06:19:27.599
piles of snow again.

06:19:27.659 --> 06:19:30.360
Snowfall rolled around in hers for a

06:19:30.360 --> 06:19:32.459
while, cleaning all the dust off her

06:19:32.459 --> 06:19:35.159
scales, until she felt shiny and cold

06:19:35.159 --> 06:19:35.459
again.

06:19:35.580 --> 06:19:39.240
Then she curled up and stared at the opal

06:19:39.240 --> 06:19:39.419
ring.

06:19:39.479 --> 06:19:41.700
It had been silent all day.

06:19:41.759 --> 06:19:43.979
Where the visions really gone?

06:19:44.040 --> 06:19:47.400
If so, why was it still stuck on her

06:19:47.400 --> 06:19:47.700
finger?

06:19:47.759 --> 06:19:51.599
Was it just lying in wait to spring a

06:19:51.599 --> 06:19:53.400
whole bunch of terrible dragons on her at

06:19:53.400 --> 06:19:53.700
once?

06:19:53.759 --> 06:19:57.720
Hey, magic ring, she whispered.

06:19:57.779 --> 06:19:59.880
I put up with all your visions.

06:19:59.939 --> 06:20:02.639
I told those Pentalen dragons what you

06:20:02.639 --> 06:20:03.000
showed me.

06:20:03.060 --> 06:20:05.520
I made peace with scavengers.

06:20:05.520 --> 06:20:07.080
Is that what you wanted?

06:20:07.139 --> 06:20:09.479
Twinkle, twinkle.

06:20:09.540 --> 06:20:10.799
Smug twinkle.

06:20:10.860 --> 06:20:13.740
I'm all right with no more visions

06:20:13.740 --> 06:20:15.060
Snowfall whispered.

06:20:15.119 --> 06:20:17.819
No more visions would be totally fine.

06:20:17.880 --> 06:20:21.299
But if you do have to give me another one

06:20:21.299 --> 06:20:21.540
tonight.

06:20:21.659 --> 06:20:24.060
Could it please be the one I asked for?

06:20:24.180 --> 06:20:26.819
Can you tell me what happened to animus

06:20:26.819 --> 06:20:28.919
magic, and why it's not working?

06:20:28.979 --> 06:20:31.979
If there's a way to fix it, We could use

06:20:31.979 --> 06:20:33.540
it to help the Pentalan dragons.

06:20:33.599 --> 06:20:34.619
Or if not.

06:20:34.740 --> 06:20:37.439
Then, it would be good to know that too

06:20:37.439 --> 06:20:39.599
so we can stop worrying about it at

06:20:39.599 --> 06:20:39.779
least.

06:20:39.840 --> 06:20:41.220
What do you think?

06:20:41.279 --> 06:20:43.919
Twinkle, twinkle, twinkle.

06:20:43.979 --> 06:20:45.779
Mysterious opal thoughts.

06:20:45.900 --> 06:20:47.520
All right.

06:20:47.580 --> 06:20:50.400
Snowball said, feeling her eyelids

06:20:50.400 --> 06:20:50.819
droop.

06:20:50.880 --> 06:20:52.680
Whatever you can do.

06:20:52.799 --> 06:20:54.479
She yawned.

06:20:54.540 --> 06:20:55.979
Thanks.

06:20:56.099 --> 06:20:58.619
And let herself slip into sleep.

06:20:58.680 --> 06:21:03.240
Chapter 21.

06:21:03.479 --> 06:21:05.580
It is raining.

06:21:05.639 --> 06:21:07.259
As always.

06:21:07.319 --> 06:21:09.360
She hates the mud kingdom.

06:21:09.419 --> 06:21:10.740
Hates everything about it.

06:21:10.799 --> 06:21:13.860
From the gloppy swamp between her talons

06:21:13.860 --> 06:21:16.259
to the incessant gurgling sound of water

06:21:16.259 --> 06:21:17.279
coming from somewhere.

06:21:17.400 --> 06:21:20.520
It's never warm enough, and she never

06:21:20.520 --> 06:21:23.279
feels dry, even when she retreats to her

06:21:23.279 --> 06:21:23.580
cave.

06:21:23.639 --> 06:21:26.819
She is constantly worried that Queen

06:21:26.819 --> 06:21:28.740
Crane might find her and she'll have to

06:21:28.740 --> 06:21:30.419
flee to yet another kingdom.

06:21:30.479 --> 06:21:32.880
But she couldn't stay in the stronghold

06:21:32.880 --> 06:21:33.180
anymore.

06:21:33.299 --> 06:21:36.180
She's not sure she'll ever be able to set

06:21:36.180 --> 06:21:37.619
her talent in the desert again.

06:21:37.740 --> 06:21:40.860
At least not until Queen Scorpion is

06:21:40.860 --> 06:21:41.040
dead.

06:21:41.099 --> 06:21:43.680
Which won't be for a long time.

06:21:43.740 --> 06:21:46.680
Thanks to those healing and longevity

06:21:46.680 --> 06:21:48.419
spells, Jerboa was forced to make for

06:21:48.419 --> 06:21:48.659
her.

06:21:48.720 --> 06:21:51.779
I said no when it mattered though.

06:21:51.840 --> 06:21:55.380
She reminds herself, I saved the sky

06:21:55.380 --> 06:21:55.860
wings.

06:21:55.919 --> 06:21:58.860
And probably even more dragons than

06:21:58.860 --> 06:21:59.099
that.

06:21:59.159 --> 06:22:01.560
Queen Scorpion wouldn't have stopped.

06:22:01.619 --> 06:22:04.200
She would always want more.

06:22:04.319 --> 06:22:08.459
More land, more power, more of Jaboa's

06:22:08.459 --> 06:22:08.759
magic.

06:22:08.819 --> 06:22:12.659
It's almost as if she was the one losing

06:22:12.659 --> 06:22:13.919
her soul, not me.

06:22:14.040 --> 06:22:17.939
Treboa flexes her talons, trying to test

06:22:17.939 --> 06:22:18.360
herself.

06:22:18.479 --> 06:22:21.419
Do I feel like murdering anyone today?

06:22:21.479 --> 06:22:23.340
Not particularly?

06:22:23.400 --> 06:22:25.919
How about some senseless violence?

06:22:25.979 --> 06:22:27.299
Is that on the agenda?

06:22:27.360 --> 06:22:28.560
Don't think so.

06:22:28.619 --> 06:22:31.560
How do we feel about tiny dragonettes?

06:22:31.619 --> 06:22:32.939
Still think they're cute.

06:22:33.000 --> 06:22:36.000
No, impulse to kill any of those, right?

06:22:36.060 --> 06:22:39.240
She sighs and rests her head on her

06:22:39.240 --> 06:22:39.659
claws.

06:22:39.720 --> 06:22:42.900
She's always wanted a dragonette of her

06:22:42.900 --> 06:22:43.259
own.

06:22:43.319 --> 06:22:45.299
The Queen Scorpion kept her away from

06:22:45.299 --> 06:22:45.900
other dragons.

06:22:46.020 --> 06:22:49.259
And now that she's a fugitive, that dream

06:22:49.259 --> 06:22:50.939
is even further away than ever.

06:22:51.000 --> 06:22:53.639
Unless I use my magic.

06:22:53.700 --> 06:22:55.860
She sits up.

06:22:55.919 --> 06:22:58.979
Startled to full alert by the idea.

06:22:59.040 --> 06:23:01.020
I could do that.

06:23:01.080 --> 06:23:02.580
I think I could.

06:23:02.639 --> 06:23:05.099
I could enchant a rock to turn into a

06:23:05.099 --> 06:23:05.819
dragon egg.

06:23:05.880 --> 06:23:07.020
Would that work?

06:23:07.080 --> 06:23:09.599
Maybe it needs to already contain some

06:23:09.599 --> 06:23:10.259
kind of life.

06:23:10.319 --> 06:23:12.959
I've never brought something to life

06:23:12.959 --> 06:23:13.380
before.

06:23:13.439 --> 06:23:15.540
That might be on the list of things

06:23:15.540 --> 06:23:17.159
animus magic can't do.

06:23:17.220 --> 06:23:21.000
But I could steal someone else's egg and

06:23:21.000 --> 06:23:23.520
change the dragon inside into a sand wing

06:23:23.520 --> 06:23:24.060
like me.

06:23:24.180 --> 06:23:25.979
Hang on.

06:23:26.040 --> 06:23:28.139
That might have been an evil thought.

06:23:28.200 --> 06:23:31.319
She rubs her temples, reviewing the

06:23:31.319 --> 06:23:31.799
choices.

06:23:31.860 --> 06:23:34.200
Right, yes.

06:23:34.259 --> 06:23:36.779
Stealing someone else's egg would be

06:23:36.779 --> 06:23:37.080
bad.

06:23:37.139 --> 06:23:40.200
What if I found a different kind of egg?

06:23:40.259 --> 06:23:43.860
A snake egg or ostrich egg, and changed

06:23:43.860 --> 06:23:45.060
it into a dragon egg.

06:23:45.119 --> 06:23:48.540
And whatever's alive inside, I make it a

06:23:48.540 --> 06:23:51.180
dragonette, my own dragonette, who would

06:23:51.180 --> 06:23:52.979
love only me forever.

06:23:53.040 --> 06:23:56.819
She is so delighted with this plan that

06:23:56.819 --> 06:23:59.040
she almost runs out into the rain to find

06:23:59.040 --> 06:24:00.060
an egg right away.

06:24:00.119 --> 06:24:02.819
But she stops herself on the threshold of

06:24:02.819 --> 06:24:03.299
the cave.

06:24:03.360 --> 06:24:05.159
Wait.

06:24:05.220 --> 06:24:06.599
Be cautious.

06:24:06.659 --> 06:24:09.659
It would not be safe for a dragonette to

06:24:09.659 --> 06:24:10.560
be part of my life right now.

06:24:10.619 --> 06:24:14.220
If Scorpion found us, she could use it

06:24:14.220 --> 06:24:14.639
against me.

06:24:14.700 --> 06:24:17.340
Bide your time, Jerboa.

06:24:17.400 --> 06:24:19.979
Scorpion is not the only one enchanted

06:24:19.979 --> 06:24:20.759
with longevity.

06:24:20.819 --> 06:24:23.520
I could live forever if I wanted to.

06:24:23.580 --> 06:24:25.560
If I'm patient.

06:24:25.619 --> 06:24:28.439
She'll be gone, and then I can create my

06:24:28.439 --> 06:24:30.599
dragonette, and we could return to the

06:24:30.599 --> 06:24:32.400
kingdom of sand and live in peace.

06:24:32.459 --> 06:24:35.819
Yes, really good plan.

06:24:35.880 --> 06:24:37.319
Not evil, right?

06:24:37.439 --> 06:24:39.540
Right, not evil.

06:24:39.599 --> 06:24:42.419
Hugging herself with her wings.

06:24:42.540 --> 06:24:45.419
She rolls against the cave wall and falls

06:24:45.419 --> 06:24:46.860
asleep, dreaming of her beautiful

06:24:46.860 --> 06:24:47.759
dragonette.

06:24:47.880 --> 06:24:51.720
She is standing in the desert again at

06:24:51.720 --> 06:24:54.779
last. 60 years of hiding was quite long

06:24:54.779 --> 06:24:57.840
enough, and quite long enough for anyone

06:24:57.840 --> 06:25:00.240
to be queen, especially the power mad

06:25:00.240 --> 06:25:00.599
kind.

06:25:00.659 --> 06:25:04.080
Queens die in their sleep of unexpected

06:25:04.080 --> 06:25:05.400
heart attacks all the time.

06:25:05.459 --> 06:25:08.220
It might have happened at any moment, even

06:25:08.220 --> 06:25:09.659
without any magic help.

06:25:09.720 --> 06:25:14.279
And really, I mean, 60 years, more than

06:25:14.279 --> 06:25:14.759
long enough.

06:25:14.819 --> 06:25:18.840
Her daughter is perfect, and now she is

06:25:18.840 --> 06:25:19.919
perfect here.

06:25:19.979 --> 06:25:23.580
In this perfect place, surrounded by sand

06:25:23.580 --> 06:25:26.520
and wind and wide, wide open sky.

06:25:26.580 --> 06:25:30.119
Welcome home, she says.

06:25:30.180 --> 06:25:33.599
Treboa III doesn't answer.

06:25:33.659 --> 06:25:36.599
She is in a bit of a snit because she

06:25:36.599 --> 06:25:39.180
just found out about Jerboa the second

06:25:39.180 --> 06:25:40.259
which was an accident.

06:25:40.319 --> 06:25:44.099
Jerboa herself, the 1st Jerboa.

06:25:44.220 --> 06:25:46.439
Hadn't planned to ever talk about the

06:25:46.439 --> 06:25:47.639
daughter who went wrong.

06:25:47.759 --> 06:25:49.439
Because it didn't matter.

06:25:49.500 --> 06:25:51.119
She was gone.

06:25:51.180 --> 06:25:54.060
And now Jerboa and the next Turboa were

06:25:54.060 --> 06:25:55.799
together, and they could just be happy

06:25:55.799 --> 06:25:56.819
couldn't they?

06:25:56.880 --> 06:26:00.840
I want a different name, says the smaller

06:26:00.840 --> 06:26:02.939
Jerboa, one of my own.

06:26:03.000 --> 06:26:04.380
Why?

06:26:04.439 --> 06:26:06.240
Jerboa is a lovely name.

06:26:06.299 --> 06:26:10.740
Because I want to be my own dragon, she

06:26:10.740 --> 06:26:13.259
huffs, not just one of your 100s of

06:26:13.259 --> 06:26:14.099
copies of you.

06:26:14.099 --> 06:26:17.400
I haven't made 100s of copies of me.

06:26:17.459 --> 06:26:19.080
Jerboa argues.

06:26:19.200 --> 06:26:22.680
Although, come to think of it, she could

06:26:22.680 --> 06:26:23.700
couldn't she?

06:26:23.759 --> 06:26:26.700
She could test them out, and see which

06:26:26.700 --> 06:26:28.799
ones are pleasant company, and which ones

06:26:28.799 --> 06:26:30.479
end up as stolen grouches.

06:26:30.540 --> 06:26:33.060
She's sure she was never this bad

06:26:33.060 --> 06:26:33.779
tempered.

06:26:33.840 --> 06:26:35.639
So it's not like the current version is

06:26:35.639 --> 06:26:37.560
that close the copy of her.

06:26:37.619 --> 06:26:40.619
Maybe a closer copy would be nicer to

06:26:40.619 --> 06:26:41.340
have around.

06:26:41.400 --> 06:26:43.799
Was that an evil thought?

06:26:43.860 --> 06:26:46.799
Her mental voice whispers, as if from

06:26:46.799 --> 06:26:47.580
very far away.

06:26:47.639 --> 06:26:51.419
You could have made 100s, and I would

06:26:51.419 --> 06:26:53.759
never know, little Jerboa points out.

06:26:53.819 --> 06:27:00.000
I could be number 847 or something. 847

06:27:00.000 --> 06:27:00.840
dragonettes.

06:27:00.900 --> 06:27:01.740
Sounds exhausting.

06:27:01.799 --> 06:27:04.919
Even if she only tried them one at a time

06:27:04.919 --> 06:27:07.200
Turbo wouldn't want to go through that

06:27:07.200 --> 06:27:10.439
again and again, teaching each one how to

06:27:10.439 --> 06:27:12.419
hunt, listening to their endless

06:27:12.419 --> 06:27:12.959
questions.

06:27:13.020 --> 06:27:15.419
But I could try a few.

06:27:15.540 --> 06:27:18.119
Until I get a quiet, pleasant one.

06:27:18.240 --> 06:27:21.900
Jerboa doesn't even have a good nickname

06:27:21.900 --> 06:27:23.279
her daughter mutters.

06:27:23.340 --> 06:27:26.580
Jerb, Jerby, Boa?

06:27:26.639 --> 06:27:28.979
I guess you could call me Boa.

06:27:29.099 --> 06:27:31.080
Turboa shrugs.

06:27:31.139 --> 06:27:32.700
Ungrateful.

06:27:32.759 --> 06:27:34.139
That's what this one is.

06:27:34.259 --> 06:27:38.099
If I call you boa, she says, will you

06:27:38.099 --> 06:27:40.259
stop sulking and appreciate this lovely

06:27:40.259 --> 06:27:40.799
desert?

06:27:40.860 --> 06:27:42.599
Fine.

06:27:42.659 --> 06:27:46.259
Boa snaps, which doesn't sound like not

06:27:46.259 --> 06:27:48.540
sulking to Jaboa, but she lets it go for

06:27:48.540 --> 06:27:48.840
the moment.

06:27:48.900 --> 06:27:51.419
I don't have to put up with this

06:27:51.419 --> 06:27:51.779
forever.

06:27:51.840 --> 06:27:55.020
If she becomes unbearable, I can always

06:27:55.020 --> 06:27:55.500
start over.

06:27:55.619 --> 06:27:57.900
Wait, wait.

06:27:57.959 --> 06:27:59.040
Whispers the boys.

06:27:59.159 --> 06:28:00.479
And then what?

06:28:00.540 --> 06:28:01.979
You'd kill this one?

06:28:02.040 --> 06:28:05.880
Didn't we decide once, long ago, that

06:28:05.880 --> 06:28:07.560
killing dragonettes was always evil?

06:28:07.680 --> 06:28:11.040
Even my own, she argues back.

06:28:11.159 --> 06:28:14.400
Once I made myself, Yes.

06:28:14.459 --> 06:28:15.900
I think so.

06:28:15.959 --> 06:28:18.060
Hmm.

06:28:18.180 --> 06:28:21.000
It is hard to imagine disposing of this

06:28:21.000 --> 06:28:23.819
one neatly, and she can't just let her go

06:28:23.819 --> 06:28:25.020
wandering off.

06:28:25.080 --> 06:28:28.319
No one can find out that the long missing

06:28:28.319 --> 06:28:29.819
sandwing animus is still alive.

06:28:29.939 --> 06:28:32.279
Turboa does not want the hassle.

06:28:32.400 --> 06:28:34.619
What if I simply?

06:28:34.799 --> 06:28:36.959
Fix her a little, then.

06:28:37.020 --> 06:28:39.299
Just a little spell to make her more

06:28:39.299 --> 06:28:40.500
agreeable.

06:28:40.560 --> 06:28:44.040
Obedient would be a good start, helpful

06:28:44.099 --> 06:28:44.759
would be nice too.

06:28:44.819 --> 06:28:48.360
She sinks her claws into the warm sand

06:28:48.360 --> 06:28:51.419
picturing how perfect small turboa could

06:28:51.419 --> 06:28:51.900
be.

06:28:51.959 --> 06:28:54.599
But, Evil?

06:28:54.720 --> 06:28:57.000
Whispers the little voice again.

06:28:57.119 --> 06:28:58.380
Maybe?

06:28:58.439 --> 06:29:01.799
Shush you, she whispers back.

06:29:01.860 --> 06:29:03.479
I made this dragon.

06:29:03.540 --> 06:29:05.220
I can perfect her if I want to.

06:29:05.279 --> 06:29:06.659
Nobody gets hurt.

06:29:06.720 --> 06:29:08.520
No, no.

06:29:08.580 --> 06:29:10.139
I don't have to worry.

06:29:10.200 --> 06:29:12.060
That's not evil at all.

06:29:12.119 --> 06:29:16.799
She's flying over the ocean, wondering if

06:29:16.799 --> 06:29:17.819
they should try shark again.

06:29:17.880 --> 06:29:21.119
The last time it was a bit oily, but this

06:29:21.119 --> 06:29:22.560
time Boa could prepare it differently.

06:29:22.619 --> 06:29:26.340
That was such a good idea, making boa an

06:29:26.340 --> 06:29:26.880
excellent cook.

06:29:26.939 --> 06:29:29.819
A shame she had to add an extra spell to

06:29:29.819 --> 06:29:31.560
also make her enjoy cooking.

06:29:31.619 --> 06:29:33.959
She thought just being good at it would

06:29:33.959 --> 06:29:34.259
be enough.

06:29:34.319 --> 06:29:35.220
But no.

06:29:35.400 --> 06:29:37.259
Boa tends to be lazy.

06:29:37.380 --> 06:29:39.900
If she could do nothing at all, that

06:29:39.900 --> 06:29:41.220
would be her preferred life.

06:29:41.279 --> 06:29:44.580
Treboa thinks she wasn't always like

06:29:44.580 --> 06:29:44.880
this.

06:29:45.000 --> 06:29:48.060
When she was little, Boa had so much

06:29:48.060 --> 06:29:48.419
energy.

06:29:48.479 --> 06:29:51.299
Perhaps one of the spells went a little

06:29:51.299 --> 06:29:52.020
awry.

06:29:52.080 --> 06:29:55.500
Perhaps making her more placid, less

06:29:55.500 --> 06:29:58.080
argumentative, more likely to say yes to

06:29:58.080 --> 06:29:58.380
everything.

06:29:58.439 --> 06:30:01.259
Perhaps that resulted in a bit of

06:30:01.259 --> 06:30:02.759
laziness, too.

06:30:02.819 --> 06:30:04.979
She'll try again.

06:30:05.040 --> 06:30:07.680
Calibrating the right personality can be

06:30:07.680 --> 06:30:08.220
quite difficult.

06:30:08.279 --> 06:30:10.740
It turns out, even with magic.

06:30:10.799 --> 06:30:13.740
She isn't in the mood for shark, after

06:30:13.740 --> 06:30:13.979
all.

06:30:14.040 --> 06:30:16.740
She'll bank Boa, go get them a camel.

06:30:16.860 --> 06:30:18.720
It'll be good exercise for her.

06:30:18.779 --> 06:30:22.139
As she swoops back down to the beach, she

06:30:22.139 --> 06:30:23.340
spots something odd.

06:30:23.400 --> 06:30:26.459
Boa is crouched in the surf building a

06:30:26.459 --> 06:30:27.060
sand castle.

06:30:27.119 --> 06:30:30.479
But the castle is building itself.

06:30:30.599 --> 06:30:33.840
Turboa flips through several stages of

06:30:33.840 --> 06:30:36.119
panic before she realizes what's really

06:30:36.119 --> 06:30:36.360
happening.

06:30:36.419 --> 06:30:40.080
Bowie is using one of the objects Treboa

06:30:40.080 --> 06:30:42.599
enchanted, the stone that builds them a

06:30:42.599 --> 06:30:43.680
new home each time they move.

06:30:43.740 --> 06:30:47.580
But for a moment, she thought Boa had her

06:30:47.580 --> 06:30:50.040
own magic, and that was terrifying.

06:30:50.099 --> 06:30:52.439
What are you doing?

06:30:52.500 --> 06:30:55.500
She asked, as she lands in a squelch of

06:30:55.500 --> 06:30:56.040
wet sand.

06:30:56.099 --> 06:31:00.180
Sand castle, Boa replies serenely.

06:31:00.240 --> 06:31:03.119
Her tail swishes lightly as the waves

06:31:03.119 --> 06:31:04.080
wash over her talons.

06:31:04.139 --> 06:31:08.340
This is not a toy, Turboa hisses.

06:31:08.459 --> 06:31:11.099
She snatches the stone out of Boa's

06:31:11.099 --> 06:31:11.400
claws.

06:31:11.459 --> 06:31:14.040
Boa blinks and bows her head.

06:31:14.099 --> 06:31:15.360
Sorry.

06:31:15.419 --> 06:31:18.599
You never touch mother's magic things.

06:31:18.659 --> 06:31:21.959
Boa tips her head and looks slowly up at

06:31:21.959 --> 06:31:22.200
her.

06:31:22.259 --> 06:31:24.299
Can I have magic too?

06:31:24.360 --> 06:31:27.299
I think I like some magic things of my

06:31:27.299 --> 06:31:27.479
own.

06:31:27.540 --> 06:31:29.759
No, no, no.

06:31:29.819 --> 06:31:31.619
Treboa shakes her head.

06:31:31.680 --> 06:31:33.419
Magic isn't safe.

06:31:33.479 --> 06:31:35.700
It's very, very dangerous.

06:31:35.759 --> 06:31:38.700
Only very special dragons should have it

06:31:38.700 --> 06:31:40.979
and that's why it's so rare.

06:31:41.040 --> 06:31:44.819
Only one animus dragon at a time.

06:31:44.880 --> 06:31:45.840
That's the rule.

06:31:45.900 --> 06:31:48.119
This is a lie.

06:31:48.180 --> 06:31:49.740
But Boa will never know that.

06:31:49.799 --> 06:31:52.740
For a while, Turboa knows.

06:31:52.799 --> 06:31:55.380
There were 5 animus dragons coexisting

06:31:55.380 --> 06:31:58.380
Empirea, one in the ice kingdom, 2 in the

06:31:58.380 --> 06:32:00.599
kingdom of the sea, one in the night

06:32:00.599 --> 06:32:01.799
kingdom, and herself.

06:32:01.919 --> 06:32:04.560
She doesn't know exactly what happened to

06:32:04.560 --> 06:32:06.360
each of them, but they're all gone now.

06:32:06.419 --> 06:32:08.340
Everyone but her.

06:32:08.400 --> 06:32:12.000
Sometimes she casts the spell, just to

06:32:12.000 --> 06:32:13.860
check, but everything is quiet.

06:32:13.919 --> 06:32:17.759
Peaceful, much less worrying that way.

06:32:17.819 --> 06:32:20.759
Maybe she's a little bit right.

06:32:20.819 --> 06:32:23.759
Maybe that much animus magic in the world

06:32:23.759 --> 06:32:26.340
at once was like too many dragons

06:32:26.340 --> 06:32:28.259
drinking from an oasis at the same time.

06:32:28.319 --> 06:32:31.380
Maybe they sucked all the magic out of

06:32:31.380 --> 06:32:31.680
the world.

06:32:31.740 --> 06:32:34.799
Or maybe the magic is taking a break

06:32:34.799 --> 06:32:36.720
waiting for a future generation of

06:32:36.720 --> 06:32:38.759
dragons before letting another animus

06:32:38.759 --> 06:32:39.119
hatch.

06:32:39.180 --> 06:32:42.840
There are rules, Boa says.

06:32:42.900 --> 06:32:44.580
About the magic?

06:32:44.639 --> 06:32:47.099
Three moons.

06:32:47.159 --> 06:32:49.979
She talks so slowly.

06:32:50.040 --> 06:32:52.259
It's like all her words have to wade

06:32:52.259 --> 06:32:53.880
through the mud wing swamps to make it

06:32:53.880 --> 06:32:54.299
out of her mouth.

06:32:54.360 --> 06:32:56.580
Absolutely.

06:32:56.639 --> 06:32:57.959
Turboa says.

06:32:58.020 --> 06:33:00.299
One animus dragon at a time.

06:33:00.360 --> 06:33:02.819
If there are too many, can you imagine

06:33:02.819 --> 06:33:04.200
how dangerous that would be?

06:33:04.259 --> 06:33:07.200
They could get in a fight, start throwing

06:33:07.200 --> 06:33:09.180
spells around, and destroy the whole

06:33:09.180 --> 06:33:09.900
world by accident.

06:33:09.959 --> 06:33:14.220
But Boa says, even more slowly.

06:33:14.340 --> 06:33:18.000
One animus dragon could also destroy the

06:33:18.000 --> 06:33:20.700
whole world just by herself.

06:33:20.759 --> 06:33:22.979
You don't have to worry about that.

06:33:23.040 --> 06:33:27.299
Treboa says, I'm the only animus dragon

06:33:27.299 --> 06:33:29.099
right now, and I'm not going to destroy

06:33:29.099 --> 06:33:29.400
anything.

06:33:29.459 --> 06:33:32.459
Boa looks out at the sea, thinking

06:33:32.459 --> 06:33:34.560
something at the speed of fossils

06:33:34.560 --> 06:33:34.979
forming.

06:33:35.040 --> 06:33:38.819
Couldn't I have just...

06:33:38.819 --> 06:33:41.819
A little bit of magic.

06:33:41.880 --> 06:33:43.860
She says finally.

06:33:43.919 --> 06:33:48.060
Magic is also dangerous for your soul

06:33:48.060 --> 06:33:48.840
remember?

06:33:48.900 --> 06:33:50.220
Jaboa says.

06:33:50.279 --> 06:33:53.340
I want to protect your soul, sweetheart.

06:33:53.400 --> 06:33:56.459
Let me do all the magic, and take all the

06:33:56.459 --> 06:33:59.400
risk on myself, and you stay safe.

06:33:59.459 --> 06:34:01.380
All right.

06:34:01.439 --> 06:34:03.599
Boa says with a sigh.

06:34:03.659 --> 06:34:05.580
And Treboa can sense that one of her

06:34:05.580 --> 06:34:06.840
spells is kicking in.

06:34:06.900 --> 06:34:09.180
The one that stops Boa from arguing with

06:34:09.180 --> 06:34:09.360
her.

06:34:09.419 --> 06:34:11.040
That was a great one.

06:34:11.099 --> 06:34:14.939
Still, this boa definitely needs a few

06:34:14.939 --> 06:34:15.419
tweaks.

06:34:15.479 --> 06:34:18.479
And something to make her stop growing.

06:34:18.540 --> 06:34:21.360
Turboa enchanted herself to stop at a

06:34:21.360 --> 06:34:22.439
normal dragon size.

06:34:22.500 --> 06:34:26.400
If they both live for 1000s of years as

06:34:26.400 --> 06:34:28.740
Jerboa is planning, it would be very

06:34:28.740 --> 06:34:31.259
inconvenient if they wound up absurdly

06:34:31.259 --> 06:34:31.740
gigantic.

06:34:31.799 --> 06:34:34.979
She'll make Boa stop just a bit smaller

06:34:34.979 --> 06:34:37.020
than her, so they'll always look like

06:34:37.020 --> 06:34:37.740
mother and daughter.

06:34:37.799 --> 06:34:41.400
Maybe she could add a little fear into

06:34:41.400 --> 06:34:42.000
the mix as well.

06:34:42.060 --> 06:34:45.360
If Boa is more scared of animus magic.

06:34:45.419 --> 06:34:46.979
She won't keep asking for it.

06:34:47.040 --> 06:34:50.220
And then she'll keep her grubby talons

06:34:50.220 --> 06:34:52.020
off your boa's stash of magic items.

06:34:52.139 --> 06:34:55.259
Yes, this is a good idea.

06:34:55.319 --> 06:34:58.919
Did she once have 2nd thoughts about her

06:34:58.919 --> 06:34:59.819
magic spells?

06:34:59.880 --> 06:35:02.759
Wasn't there once a voice in her head

06:35:02.759 --> 06:35:05.520
that asked, Something.

06:35:05.639 --> 06:35:07.619
She shrugs it off.

06:35:07.680 --> 06:35:09.779
It probably wasn't important.

06:35:09.840 --> 06:35:14.099
She is curled beside the campfire at

06:35:14.099 --> 06:35:16.919
night with stars twinkling overhead, and

06:35:16.919 --> 06:35:18.419
Bowen nestled against her side.

06:35:18.479 --> 06:35:21.840
Boa is small again, and Gerboa has

06:35:21.840 --> 06:35:23.759
tripled the dragonette's usual love for

06:35:23.759 --> 06:35:25.680
her, so she's extra cute and

06:35:25.680 --> 06:35:26.159
affectionate.

06:35:26.279 --> 06:35:28.799
It was getting boring having another full

06:35:28.799 --> 06:35:30.900
grown dragon around, who never did

06:35:30.900 --> 06:35:32.220
anything new or surprising.

06:35:32.279 --> 06:35:35.279
Shrinking her down and starting her over

06:35:35.279 --> 06:35:37.740
as a 2 year old dragonette, has made

06:35:37.740 --> 06:35:39.419
things much more fun for the last couple

06:35:39.419 --> 06:35:39.779
of years.

06:35:39.840 --> 06:35:44.099
They've both been alive a very, very long

06:35:44.099 --> 06:35:44.520
time.

06:35:44.580 --> 06:35:47.520
Over 800 years.

06:35:47.580 --> 06:35:49.319
Can that be right?

06:35:49.380 --> 06:35:51.479
Turboa tries to think.

06:35:51.540 --> 06:35:54.360
Boa has started over as a dragonette

06:35:54.360 --> 06:35:56.880
several times in those centuries, and

06:35:56.880 --> 06:35:59.580
Jerboa has lightly kept track of any

06:35:59.580 --> 06:36:01.139
other animus dragons over the years.

06:36:01.200 --> 06:36:04.740
She spotted 2 in the Knight Kingdom.

06:36:04.799 --> 06:36:07.319
The granddaughter of a dragon named White

06:36:07.319 --> 06:36:09.720
Out, and then that dragon's great

06:36:09.720 --> 06:36:12.659
grandson, none in the ice kingdom in all

06:36:12.659 --> 06:36:15.900
that time, one in the kingdom of the sea

06:36:15.900 --> 06:36:18.419
in the royal family, but she didn't live

06:36:18.419 --> 06:36:19.979
very long after having her own eggs.

06:36:20.040 --> 06:36:22.259
Turboa doesn't know why.

06:36:22.319 --> 06:36:24.360
She hasn't gone digging for more

06:36:24.360 --> 06:36:25.020
information.

06:36:25.080 --> 06:36:27.419
As long as they don't find out about her

06:36:27.419 --> 06:36:30.419
or do anything earth shattering, she can

06:36:30.419 --> 06:36:30.900
ignore them.

06:36:30.959 --> 06:36:34.439
Mother, I think you should make me an

06:36:34.439 --> 06:36:35.400
animus dragon.

06:36:35.459 --> 06:36:37.020
Boa churps out of nowhere.

06:36:37.139 --> 06:36:39.540
This, again.

06:36:39.599 --> 06:36:43.200
Turboa thought she'd stomped down all of

06:36:43.200 --> 06:36:46.319
Boa's curiosity about magic, but it keeps

06:36:46.319 --> 06:36:49.560
coming up year after year, despite all

06:36:49.560 --> 06:36:51.720
the memory wipes, and implanted

06:36:51.720 --> 06:36:54.240
nightmares, and personality adjustments.

06:36:54.299 --> 06:36:56.880
What is wrong with this dragonette?

06:36:56.939 --> 06:36:59.639
Why can't Turboa fix it?

06:36:59.700 --> 06:37:01.560
She sighs.

06:37:01.680 --> 06:37:05.880
If you did have magic, she asks, or let's

06:37:05.880 --> 06:37:08.880
say, if you could cast just one spell

06:37:08.880 --> 06:37:10.259
what would it be?

06:37:10.319 --> 06:37:15.299
Boa thinks, and thanks, and thanks.

06:37:15.360 --> 06:37:18.240
Rewinding her age made her a faster

06:37:18.240 --> 06:37:20.459
thinker again, but she's gotten slower

06:37:20.459 --> 06:37:22.259
with each new spell since then.

06:37:22.259 --> 06:37:25.680
I know, she says sweetly.

06:37:25.740 --> 06:37:29.340
It would be a teleportation spell, one

06:37:29.340 --> 06:37:31.080
that would bring me home to you anytime I

06:37:31.080 --> 06:37:33.000
wanted, no matter where I was.

06:37:33.060 --> 06:37:38.040
Oh, Treboa says, snuggling her closer.

06:37:38.099 --> 06:37:39.659
But you don't need that.

06:37:39.720 --> 06:37:41.040
We're never apart.

06:37:41.099 --> 06:37:45.240
Is that a shadow flickering across Boa's

06:37:45.240 --> 06:37:45.360
face?

06:37:45.419 --> 06:37:48.180
I know, she said.

06:37:48.240 --> 06:37:50.520
It would be just in case.

06:37:50.580 --> 06:37:54.000
Just in case something very bad happened

06:37:54.000 --> 06:37:55.319
and we got separated.

06:37:55.380 --> 06:37:57.720
Treboa is pleased.

06:37:57.779 --> 06:38:01.020
I can make that for you, she says.

06:38:01.080 --> 06:38:04.319
She plugs a seashell from the sand, a

06:38:04.319 --> 06:38:06.540
pale fan shape edged with dark pink.

06:38:06.599 --> 06:38:08.700
Can't I?

06:38:08.759 --> 06:38:09.419
Boa starts.

06:38:09.479 --> 06:38:11.880
But your boa gently taps her snout with

06:38:11.880 --> 06:38:13.380
her tail. and she falls silent.

06:38:13.439 --> 06:38:16.919
It only takes a moment, and the spell is

06:38:16.919 --> 06:38:17.159
cast.

06:38:17.279 --> 06:38:20.340
This seashell will bring boa to her

06:38:20.340 --> 06:38:23.040
mother instantly, at just a flicker of a

06:38:23.040 --> 06:38:24.479
thought from either one of them.

06:38:24.540 --> 06:38:29.580
It's quite neat, actually. 620 years ago

06:38:29.580 --> 06:38:34.860
and 250 years ago, and 250 years ago, and

06:38:34.860 --> 06:38:35.700
a few other times.

06:38:35.759 --> 06:38:37.799
Jerboa can't remember exactly.

06:38:37.860 --> 06:38:40.020
Boa tried to run away.

06:38:40.080 --> 06:38:42.659
She doesn't remember any of that

06:38:42.659 --> 06:38:44.040
misbehavior now, of course.

06:38:44.099 --> 06:38:47.700
Each time Boa runs, she thinks it's the

06:38:47.700 --> 06:38:48.119
1st time.

06:38:48.180 --> 06:38:51.419
And it has been a real pain in the tail

06:38:51.419 --> 06:38:52.139
to drag her back.

06:38:52.200 --> 06:38:55.740
So it's perfect, that now Jerboa will be

06:38:55.740 --> 06:38:57.599
able to do it with a snap of her claws.

06:38:57.720 --> 06:39:01.619
Turboa pokes a hole in the shell, threads

06:39:01.619 --> 06:39:03.720
a coconut fiber rope through it, and

06:39:03.720 --> 06:39:05.099
loops it over Boa's neck.

06:39:05.159 --> 06:39:07.919
There, she says.

06:39:07.979 --> 06:39:10.740
See, you don't need magic.

06:39:10.799 --> 06:39:13.080
Just ask me for whatever you need.

06:39:13.139 --> 06:39:15.959
And if I think it's a good idea, I'll

06:39:15.959 --> 06:39:16.560
make it for you.

06:39:16.680 --> 06:39:19.380
Boa nods faintly.

06:39:19.439 --> 06:39:22.439
She doesn't seem as delighted with a gift

06:39:22.439 --> 06:39:23.639
as Jerboa would like.

06:39:23.759 --> 06:39:25.500
For a moment.

06:39:25.560 --> 06:39:27.659
Treboa considers making her more grateful

06:39:27.659 --> 06:39:30.060
but really, it's too late now.

06:39:30.119 --> 06:39:33.180
Bo has ruined what could have been a very

06:39:33.180 --> 06:39:33.720
nice moment.

06:39:33.779 --> 06:39:36.180
Treboa size.

06:39:36.240 --> 06:39:38.340
A 1000 years.

06:39:38.400 --> 06:39:41.520
Maybe it's time for something new.

06:39:41.580 --> 06:39:45.779
What if I made you a brother?

06:39:45.779 --> 06:39:47.340
she asked Boa.

06:39:47.459 --> 06:39:49.020
Wouldn't that be fun?

06:39:49.139 --> 06:39:52.139
Something flickers in Boa's eyes again.

06:39:52.200 --> 06:39:53.639
Jealousy?

06:39:53.700 --> 06:39:55.080
Poor dear.

06:39:55.139 --> 06:39:56.819
It would be hard to share her mother

06:39:56.819 --> 06:39:57.779
after all this time.

06:39:57.840 --> 06:40:00.959
Would his name be Jerboa too?

06:40:01.080 --> 06:40:02.220
She asks.

06:40:02.340 --> 06:40:04.319
Turboa laughs.

06:40:04.380 --> 06:40:06.240
No, of course not.

06:40:06.299 --> 06:40:08.040
What do you want him to be like?

06:40:08.099 --> 06:40:09.959
Funny, clever.

06:40:10.080 --> 06:40:12.959
Boa traces a shape in the sand with her

06:40:12.959 --> 06:40:13.380
claw.

06:40:13.439 --> 06:40:15.000
You can do that?

06:40:15.060 --> 06:40:16.020
she asks.

06:40:16.080 --> 06:40:19.319
Make him turn out any way you want?

06:40:19.380 --> 06:40:22.200
Of course, Traboa says.

06:40:22.259 --> 06:40:25.319
We can even make him love to do all the

06:40:25.319 --> 06:40:28.139
boring stuff we hate. like gathering

06:40:28.139 --> 06:40:30.180
firewood, or cracking the lobster

06:40:30.180 --> 06:40:30.720
shells.

06:40:30.779 --> 06:40:33.479
Boa stares at her talons with a strange

06:40:33.479 --> 06:40:34.200
expression.

06:40:34.259 --> 06:40:37.200
I love gathering firewood.

06:40:37.259 --> 06:40:39.119
She says in an odd voice.

06:40:39.180 --> 06:40:41.939
Oh, that's right.

06:40:42.000 --> 06:40:44.939
Turboa added that to the spell a little

06:40:44.939 --> 06:40:47.040
while ago, when she got tired of either

06:40:47.040 --> 06:40:49.380
doing it herself, or listening to Boa

06:40:49.380 --> 06:40:50.040
whine about it.

06:40:50.099 --> 06:40:52.979
Something else then, she says.

06:40:53.099 --> 06:40:55.020
Whatever we don't want to do.

06:40:55.080 --> 06:40:58.860
We can also make him age very slowly, so

06:40:58.860 --> 06:41:01.139
he stays a cute little dragonette for as

06:41:01.139 --> 06:41:01.919
long as we want.

06:41:01.979 --> 06:41:04.680
Oh, and will make him a really good

06:41:04.680 --> 06:41:07.380
sleeper, so he'll nap easily and fall

06:41:07.380 --> 06:41:09.360
asleep whenever he starts fussing.

06:41:09.419 --> 06:41:10.560
Not like you.

06:41:10.619 --> 06:41:12.180
Miss up all night.

06:41:12.240 --> 06:41:14.880
Boa tips her head up to the stars.

06:41:15.000 --> 06:41:21.479
But, I sleep really well, she says, I

06:41:21.479 --> 06:41:24.540
sleep all night, and sometimes during the

06:41:24.540 --> 06:41:24.659
day.

06:41:24.779 --> 06:41:28.560
I'm a really good sleeper.

06:41:28.680 --> 06:41:30.840
Of course, you are now.

06:41:30.900 --> 06:41:33.000
Turboa says impatiently.

06:41:33.060 --> 06:41:34.680
So what do you think?

06:41:34.740 --> 06:41:36.959
Would you like a new toy to play with?

06:41:37.020 --> 06:41:40.139
Her daughter doesn't answer for a

06:41:40.139 --> 06:41:41.220
boringly long time.

06:41:41.279 --> 06:41:44.700
Just as Jerboa is about to snap at her

06:41:44.700 --> 06:41:47.459
she suddenly turns and burrows under

06:41:47.459 --> 06:41:48.299
Jerboa's wing.

06:41:48.360 --> 06:41:52.619
No, she says, no, thank you.

06:41:52.680 --> 06:41:53.220
Please?

06:41:53.279 --> 06:41:54.900
I don't want a brother.

06:41:54.959 --> 06:41:56.819
I like it just us.

06:41:56.880 --> 06:42:00.119
I want to be your only dragonette.

06:42:00.180 --> 06:42:01.139
Please?

06:42:01.259 --> 06:42:03.779
Trabo is surprised.

06:42:03.840 --> 06:42:07.680
Well, this is her own fault, phrasing it

06:42:07.680 --> 06:42:08.340
like a question.

06:42:08.400 --> 06:42:10.619
Instead of presenting the idea in a way

06:42:10.619 --> 06:42:11.700
that Boa couldn't argue with.

06:42:11.819 --> 06:42:14.639
Anyway, it's fine.

06:42:14.700 --> 06:42:17.459
Boa is enough entertainment on her own

06:42:17.459 --> 06:42:20.040
especially during the periods when Jerboa

06:42:20.040 --> 06:42:22.200
makes her a talented musician. or

06:42:22.200 --> 06:42:22.860
storyteller.

06:42:22.919 --> 06:42:25.380
Another dragonette would probably be a

06:42:25.380 --> 06:42:26.040
lot of trouble.

06:42:26.099 --> 06:42:28.139
Boa is trembling.

06:42:28.200 --> 06:42:30.000
Shivers running through both their

06:42:30.000 --> 06:42:30.360
scales.

06:42:30.419 --> 06:42:32.700
All right, all right.

06:42:32.819 --> 06:42:34.020
Treboa says.

06:42:34.080 --> 06:42:36.900
Just us, no more dragonettes.

06:42:36.959 --> 06:42:38.159
Don't worry.

06:42:38.220 --> 06:42:41.400
Look at her, sounding all nurturing and

06:42:41.400 --> 06:42:41.700
kind.

06:42:41.759 --> 06:42:43.860
She's such a great mom.

06:42:43.919 --> 06:42:46.080
Promise?

06:42:46.139 --> 06:42:47.279
Boa asks.

06:42:47.340 --> 06:42:48.779
I promise.

06:42:48.900 --> 06:42:50.819
Treboa says easily.

06:42:50.880 --> 06:42:54.119
It's always easy to make promises to Boa

06:42:54.119 --> 06:42:56.340
since she can erase them from Boa's mind

06:42:56.340 --> 06:42:57.240
just as easily.

06:42:57.299 --> 06:43:00.779
If Jerboa designs, She does want another

06:43:00.779 --> 06:43:01.740
dragonette one day.

06:43:01.799 --> 06:43:04.439
She'll have one, and Boa won't complain

06:43:04.439 --> 06:43:06.119
or even remember this conversation.

06:43:06.180 --> 06:43:09.299
For now, she'll have to think of

06:43:09.299 --> 06:43:10.380
something else to make their lives

06:43:10.380 --> 06:43:10.979
interesting.

06:43:11.040 --> 06:43:14.040
They haven't abducted an enchanted

06:43:14.040 --> 06:43:14.939
servant in a while.

06:43:15.060 --> 06:43:17.459
Maybe a rain wing this time.

06:43:17.520 --> 06:43:20.220
That would be pretty, and they don't eat

06:43:20.220 --> 06:43:20.580
very much.

06:43:20.639 --> 06:43:24.360
Yes, that would be a nice change of pace

06:43:24.360 --> 06:43:24.779
around here.

06:43:24.840 --> 06:43:28.200
She is very tired.

06:43:28.319 --> 06:43:31.500
They have been flying all day to get to

06:43:31.500 --> 06:43:33.659
their summer hut, and they weren't able

06:43:33.659 --> 06:43:36.060
to stop at an oasis on the way because

06:43:36.060 --> 06:43:38.220
there were so many sand wings milling

06:43:38.220 --> 06:43:38.939
about below.

06:43:39.000 --> 06:43:40.619
Every century.

06:43:40.680 --> 06:43:42.779
It seems like there are more and more

06:43:42.779 --> 06:43:43.619
dragons everywhere.

06:43:43.680 --> 06:43:46.259
Jerboa prefers to avoid them.

06:43:46.319 --> 06:43:48.959
After a few awkward incidents where Boa

06:43:48.959 --> 06:43:52.319
tried to get someone to rescue her of all

06:43:52.319 --> 06:43:52.919
the nonsense.

06:43:53.040 --> 06:43:56.700
Her wings ache, and her head is fuzzy.

06:43:56.759 --> 06:43:59.759
And that is the only reason Boa is able

06:43:59.759 --> 06:44:00.900
to catch her unawares.

06:44:00.959 --> 06:44:03.720
Jerboa doesn't realize what has happened

06:44:03.720 --> 06:44:04.200
at first.

06:44:04.259 --> 06:44:08.159
She is frozen, one step inside the

06:44:08.159 --> 06:44:09.119
doorway of the cabin.

06:44:09.180 --> 06:44:11.040
Literally frozen.

06:44:11.099 --> 06:44:14.400
No part of her can move, and ice is

06:44:14.400 --> 06:44:16.259
starting to travel rapidly up from her

06:44:16.259 --> 06:44:17.340
claws.

06:44:17.400 --> 06:44:20.639
She whips her head from side to side, and

06:44:20.639 --> 06:44:23.040
finally spots Boa in the far corner

06:44:23.040 --> 06:44:25.020
pointing something at her.

06:44:25.080 --> 06:44:27.299
The porcupine quills.

06:44:27.360 --> 06:44:31.080
Boa had gathered them all so carefully in

06:44:31.080 --> 06:44:33.360
the mountain forest, then bound them

06:44:33.360 --> 06:44:35.040
together with a length of thin vines.

06:44:35.159 --> 06:44:38.939
She'd shown them to Draboa, proud and

06:44:38.939 --> 06:44:40.979
sweet and asked for a new spell.

06:44:41.040 --> 06:44:44.819
When I point us at my prey, she said.

06:44:44.880 --> 06:44:47.939
I want them to freeze in place, so I can

06:44:47.939 --> 06:44:48.900
catch them more easily.

06:44:49.020 --> 06:44:52.799
Turboa had chuckled at her lazy, lazy

06:44:52.799 --> 06:44:54.720
daughter, but she'd given her the spell.

06:44:54.779 --> 06:44:56.159
Why not?

06:44:56.220 --> 06:44:59.220
Boa hadn't asked for a spell in so many

06:44:59.220 --> 06:45:02.580
years, and she'd been so good and quiet

06:45:02.580 --> 06:45:04.020
and biddable lately.

06:45:04.139 --> 06:45:07.200
Easier hunting was a harmless request.

06:45:07.259 --> 06:45:09.419
Or so she'd thought.

06:45:09.479 --> 06:45:11.939
What are you doing?

06:45:12.000 --> 06:45:14.159
Jerboa says with a hiss.

06:45:14.279 --> 06:45:17.400
She catches herself, and in a long pause

06:45:17.400 --> 06:45:20.400
before Boa speaks, she tries pouring

06:45:20.400 --> 06:45:21.659
honey through her voice instead.

06:45:21.779 --> 06:45:26.459
Boa, dear, you've accidentally used your

06:45:26.459 --> 06:45:27.419
hunting weapon on me.

06:45:27.479 --> 06:45:28.680
Let me go.

06:45:28.799 --> 06:45:32.639
It's not an accident, Boa says

06:45:32.639 --> 06:45:33.240
trembling.

06:45:33.299 --> 06:45:35.220
You're stuck now.

06:45:35.279 --> 06:45:37.680
It seems that way.

06:45:37.740 --> 06:45:39.479
Draboa says.

06:45:39.599 --> 06:45:42.119
She's trying to remember the words of the

06:45:42.119 --> 06:45:42.419
spell.

06:45:42.479 --> 06:45:45.000
Does Boa have to say something specific

06:45:45.000 --> 06:45:46.259
to release the prey?

06:45:46.319 --> 06:45:49.619
The cold is crawling higher on her legs.

06:45:49.680 --> 06:45:52.680
She tries to breathe fire on the blocks

06:45:52.680 --> 06:45:55.139
of ice around her talons, but this is

06:45:55.139 --> 06:45:57.479
magic ice, and her fire does nothing.

06:45:57.599 --> 06:46:00.599
So now you have to listen to me.

06:46:00.659 --> 06:46:02.040
Boa says.

06:46:02.099 --> 06:46:04.860
I want you to tell me the truth for

06:46:04.860 --> 06:46:05.040
once.

06:46:05.099 --> 06:46:07.979
How many spells have you cast on me?

06:46:08.099 --> 06:46:10.380
Turboa barks a laugh.

06:46:10.439 --> 06:46:12.900
I couldn't possibly remember all of

06:46:12.900 --> 06:46:13.139
them.

06:46:13.200 --> 06:46:15.479
I've been trying to fix you for literally

06:46:15.479 --> 06:46:16.500
centuries.

06:46:16.560 --> 06:46:19.860
Boa's eyes go a little unfocused for a

06:46:19.860 --> 06:46:20.220
moment.

06:46:20.279 --> 06:46:21.779
Centuries?

06:46:21.900 --> 06:46:22.979
She whispers.

06:46:23.040 --> 06:46:25.979
Treboa tries to remember when the last

06:46:25.979 --> 06:46:28.919
memory wipe was, but she's too cold to

06:46:28.919 --> 06:46:29.520
think straight.

06:46:29.580 --> 06:46:32.520
Yes, she hisses instead.

06:46:32.580 --> 06:46:35.040
Nearly 11 centuries.

06:46:35.099 --> 06:46:37.200
Three moons.

06:46:37.319 --> 06:46:39.840
Boa presses her free talent to her eyes.

06:46:39.959 --> 06:46:42.299
Why don't I remember that?

06:46:42.360 --> 06:46:45.900
Turboa would shrug, if she could move her

06:46:45.900 --> 06:46:46.259
shoulders.

06:46:46.380 --> 06:46:49.560
Because you keep erasing my memory.

06:46:49.619 --> 06:46:51.779
Boa answers herself.

06:46:51.840 --> 06:46:54.779
That's why I get so confused.

06:46:54.840 --> 06:46:57.119
That's why you keep talking about things

06:46:57.119 --> 06:46:58.799
I don't remember at all.

06:46:58.860 --> 06:47:02.040
Let's be fair, says Draboa.

06:47:02.099 --> 06:47:04.380
You also have an uncommonly stupid

06:47:04.380 --> 06:47:04.860
brain.

06:47:04.919 --> 06:47:08.580
How would we know, Boa Flares?

06:47:08.639 --> 06:47:11.220
Is any of it really me anymore?

06:47:11.279 --> 06:47:14.340
She brandishes the quills at your boa?

06:47:14.400 --> 06:47:16.799
I only love you because of magic.

06:47:16.860 --> 06:47:18.959
She says, right?

06:47:19.020 --> 06:47:21.540
You've been enchanting me to love you.

06:47:21.659 --> 06:47:24.599
No, that's all real.

06:47:24.720 --> 06:47:26.639
Treboa lies.

06:47:26.700 --> 06:47:27.900
Silkier now.

06:47:27.959 --> 06:47:31.919
If you love me so much, let me go.

06:47:32.040 --> 06:47:34.439
She looks down at the ice that now

06:47:34.439 --> 06:47:35.819
encases her legs and tail.

06:47:35.939 --> 06:47:38.159
Her scales are so cold.

06:47:38.220 --> 06:47:42.060
Her wings are raised slightly immobile

06:47:42.060 --> 06:47:43.919
but the ice will reach them any moment.

06:47:44.040 --> 06:47:48.540
It's not fair to make me love you when

06:47:48.540 --> 06:47:49.680
you don't love me at all.

06:47:49.799 --> 06:47:52.500
Boa angrily wipes her tears away.

06:47:52.560 --> 06:47:56.040
I love you when you're not like this

06:47:56.040 --> 06:47:57.540
Treboa points out.

06:47:57.599 --> 06:48:00.240
You're exceptionally unlovable right

06:48:00.240 --> 06:48:00.419
now.

06:48:00.479 --> 06:48:03.060
Well, Boa says.

06:48:03.180 --> 06:48:05.639
I guess we can fix that, can't we?

06:48:05.700 --> 06:48:08.880
Just a little tweak here, a correction

06:48:08.880 --> 06:48:09.119
there.

06:48:09.180 --> 06:48:12.419
All you need is this, right?

06:48:12.479 --> 06:48:15.599
She holds up an unrolled scroll.

06:48:15.659 --> 06:48:17.279
Uh-oh.

06:48:17.340 --> 06:48:19.139
Herboa spells.

06:48:19.259 --> 06:48:22.139
She should have been more careful, kept

06:48:22.139 --> 06:48:23.700
them all in her head the way she used

06:48:23.700 --> 06:48:23.880
to.

06:48:24.000 --> 06:48:26.520
But it was getting so hard to keep track

06:48:26.520 --> 06:48:28.439
of them, and some of them were

06:48:28.439 --> 06:48:28.919
complicated.

06:48:29.040 --> 06:48:32.040
It was just easier to make an enchanted

06:48:32.040 --> 06:48:33.419
scroll where she could write down

06:48:33.419 --> 06:48:35.700
whatever she wanted to change about Boa

06:48:35.700 --> 06:48:36.599
and it would happen.

06:48:36.720 --> 06:48:39.540
Boba wasn't supposed to see it.

06:48:39.599 --> 06:48:42.479
She wasn't supposed to get her claws on

06:48:42.479 --> 06:48:42.599
it.

06:48:42.659 --> 06:48:44.880
Where did you find that?

06:48:45.000 --> 06:48:46.740
Treboa snaps.

06:48:46.860 --> 06:48:50.400
More obedient, Boa reads from the

06:48:50.400 --> 06:48:50.700
scroll.

06:48:50.759 --> 06:48:52.799
Even more obedient.

06:48:52.860 --> 06:48:55.319
Chew with her mouth closed.

06:48:55.380 --> 06:48:58.139
Stop asking about talking to other

06:48:58.139 --> 06:48:58.799
dragons.

06:48:58.860 --> 06:49:01.560
Forget that other dragons exist.

06:49:01.619 --> 06:49:04.979
Remember that other dragons exist and

06:49:04.979 --> 06:49:06.659
stop asking inane questions.

06:49:06.720 --> 06:49:09.840
Always let mother have the bigger fish.

06:49:09.900 --> 06:49:11.700
She narrows her eyes.

06:49:11.759 --> 06:49:14.159
This certainly explains a lot.

06:49:14.220 --> 06:49:17.700
Treboa has never been so cold.

06:49:17.759 --> 06:49:19.860
Guess what?

06:49:19.919 --> 06:49:21.119
Boa says.

06:49:21.180 --> 06:49:24.119
It turns out, anybody can add notes to

06:49:24.119 --> 06:49:24.720
this scroll.

06:49:24.779 --> 06:49:25.680
Watch.

06:49:25.799 --> 06:49:28.860
She picks up Jerboa's quill. and writes

06:49:28.860 --> 06:49:34.979
on the scroll, green, tail, bar, bah.

06:49:35.040 --> 06:49:37.200
She says slowly as she writes.

06:49:37.259 --> 06:49:40.380
Her tail barb turns a beautiful shade of

06:49:40.380 --> 06:49:41.159
emerald green.

06:49:41.220 --> 06:49:42.720
See?

06:49:42.779 --> 06:49:44.279
Exciting, isn't it?

06:49:44.340 --> 06:49:46.380
Boa writes on the scroll again.

06:49:46.439 --> 06:49:50.099
Normal color tail barb.

06:49:50.159 --> 06:49:52.200
And her tail goes back to normal.

06:49:52.259 --> 06:49:55.439
Jerboa can't feel her wings.

06:49:55.500 --> 06:49:57.900
The ice is up around her neck now.

06:49:57.959 --> 06:50:00.119
She can't even move her head to look at

06:50:00.119 --> 06:50:00.720
the rest of her.

06:50:00.779 --> 06:50:04.560
But you know what I really want, Boa

06:50:04.560 --> 06:50:04.799
says.

06:50:04.919 --> 06:50:07.200
More than a green tail mother.

06:50:07.319 --> 06:50:10.080
You might remember this, because I've

06:50:10.080 --> 06:50:10.860
asked for it before.

06:50:10.919 --> 06:50:12.720
More than once, I think.

06:50:12.840 --> 06:50:16.200
Maybe quite a lot in all those memories

06:50:16.200 --> 06:50:16.979
you erased.

06:50:17.040 --> 06:50:20.220
I'd like to be an animus dragon.

06:50:20.279 --> 06:50:22.680
No, never.

06:50:22.740 --> 06:50:26.099
Turboa tries to cast a spell with her

06:50:26.099 --> 06:50:26.279
mind.

06:50:26.340 --> 06:50:29.580
She tries to rip the scroll out of Boa's

06:50:29.580 --> 06:50:31.919
claws, but it only flutters feebly.

06:50:31.979 --> 06:50:35.220
Oh, sorry to disappoint you?

06:50:35.279 --> 06:50:36.599
For what?

06:50:36.659 --> 06:50:38.099
The 8000000th time?

06:50:38.220 --> 06:50:41.459
Boa says, as the quill snaps in half.

06:50:41.580 --> 06:50:43.799
You actually can't stop me from writing

06:50:43.799 --> 06:50:45.779
it down, because I already did.

06:50:45.840 --> 06:50:48.240
She looks down at the quill with a smile

06:50:48.240 --> 06:50:50.580
and it smooths back into one piece.

06:50:50.639 --> 06:50:53.459
She's not going to save me.

06:50:53.520 --> 06:50:55.740
Treboa realizes for the 1st time.

06:50:55.799 --> 06:50:57.180
Not ever.

06:50:57.240 --> 06:50:59.400
This isn't a negotiation.

06:50:59.459 --> 06:51:01.439
It's a final performance.

06:51:01.500 --> 06:51:04.439
Boa has freed herself from her mother's

06:51:04.439 --> 06:51:04.799
spells.

06:51:04.860 --> 06:51:07.560
She doesn't need turboa anymore.

06:51:07.619 --> 06:51:10.439
These are my last moments.

06:51:10.500 --> 06:51:12.299
After all this time.

06:51:12.419 --> 06:51:16.020
She finds she's not as sad as she would

06:51:16.020 --> 06:51:16.380
have expected.

06:51:16.439 --> 06:51:20.040
She has lived or really, really long

06:51:20.040 --> 06:51:20.400
time.

06:51:20.459 --> 06:51:23.639
And most of it was quite delightful when

06:51:23.639 --> 06:51:24.599
it wasn't irritating.

06:51:24.659 --> 06:51:28.560
Goodbye, mother, Boa says, and she

06:51:28.560 --> 06:51:30.659
actually looks much sadder than Jerboa

06:51:30.659 --> 06:51:31.080
feels.

06:51:31.139 --> 06:51:34.080
She's crying, but Jaboa doesn't know if

06:51:34.080 --> 06:51:36.659
those are real tears, or ones caused by

06:51:36.659 --> 06:51:38.279
the spell that makes Boa love her.

06:51:38.340 --> 06:51:40.380
I only have a moment.

06:51:40.439 --> 06:51:42.959
One last spell.

06:51:43.020 --> 06:51:44.939
Not to save myself.

06:51:45.060 --> 06:51:47.880
Just to make sure that Boa isn't as

06:51:47.880 --> 06:51:49.439
triumphant as she thinks.

06:51:49.500 --> 06:51:52.860
Something to ensure she never, never

06:51:52.860 --> 06:51:54.419
forgets me.

06:51:54.479 --> 06:51:57.840
She casts the spell on Boa herself.

06:51:57.959 --> 06:52:01.080
Making her daughter, her last animus

06:52:01.080 --> 06:52:02.220
touched object.

06:52:02.279 --> 06:52:04.799
And then she has gone.

06:52:04.919 --> 06:52:09.479
Chapter 22.

06:52:09.659 --> 06:52:11.880
She is free.

06:52:11.939 --> 06:52:13.979
She can't believe it.

06:52:14.040 --> 06:52:16.919
Boa steps toward the block of eyes that

06:52:16.919 --> 06:52:18.119
has her mother trapped inside.

06:52:18.240 --> 06:52:21.479
It is fascinating to see her like this

06:52:21.479 --> 06:52:23.759
through the bubbles and glaze of the ice

06:52:23.759 --> 06:52:24.299
walls.

06:52:24.360 --> 06:52:27.360
It's hard to see her expression, although

06:52:27.360 --> 06:52:29.459
Boa will always remember the contorted

06:52:29.459 --> 06:52:30.419
fury on her face.

06:52:30.479 --> 06:52:32.700
I did it.

06:52:32.759 --> 06:52:34.020
I tricked her.

06:52:34.080 --> 06:52:35.520
I freed myself.

06:52:35.580 --> 06:52:39.840
Finally, after all this time, longer than

06:52:39.840 --> 06:52:41.159
she could possibly have guessed.

06:52:41.279 --> 06:52:44.220
I'm the only jerboa now.

06:52:44.279 --> 06:52:47.040
She hesitates, then writes in the

06:52:47.040 --> 06:52:47.340
scroll.

06:52:47.400 --> 06:52:50.700
Return all boa's memories.

06:52:50.759 --> 06:52:54.299
Gently, she adds in a hasty scroll.

06:52:54.419 --> 06:52:56.340
It still too much.

06:52:56.400 --> 06:52:58.740
It's so much.

06:52:58.799 --> 06:53:02.520
All the times they fought, and Jerboa

06:53:02.520 --> 06:53:05.099
just flicked the memories away like bugs

06:53:05.099 --> 06:53:06.779
so Boa would be pleasant again.

06:53:06.840 --> 06:53:11.220
All the promises she made, and broke. with

06:53:11.220 --> 06:53:12.180
a snap of her claws.

06:53:12.299 --> 06:53:15.240
The conversation about making a brother

06:53:15.240 --> 06:53:17.880
came back, and Boa clutched her stomach.

06:53:17.939 --> 06:53:19.319
Did it ever happen?

06:53:19.380 --> 06:53:22.919
Was there another damaged dragonette in

06:53:22.919 --> 06:53:24.779
their past, or had she convinced her

06:53:24.779 --> 06:53:27.119
mother and spared someone else her fate?

06:53:27.180 --> 06:53:29.400
No brothers appeared.

06:53:29.459 --> 06:53:30.840
No sisters either.

06:53:30.900 --> 06:53:33.599
Boa was alone with her mother throughout

06:53:33.599 --> 06:53:34.979
all the centuries of memories.

06:53:35.099 --> 06:53:37.979
But there were servants here and there.

06:53:38.040 --> 06:53:40.560
Dragons that Jerboa kidnapped and

06:53:40.560 --> 06:53:41.099
enchanted.

06:53:41.220 --> 06:53:43.380
Boa had loved some of them.

06:53:43.439 --> 06:53:45.659
She would have run away with them if she

06:53:45.659 --> 06:53:45.959
could have.

06:53:46.020 --> 06:53:49.080
Her memories gave her no clues about what

06:53:49.080 --> 06:53:51.240
happened to them when Jerboa was done.

06:53:51.299 --> 06:53:54.060
Did she wipe their memories and throw

06:53:54.060 --> 06:53:55.259
them back out into the world?

06:53:55.319 --> 06:53:57.240
Or something worse?

06:53:57.299 --> 06:54:00.240
All Boa could see were days where she was

06:54:00.240 --> 06:54:02.759
happy. building sand castles with a rain

06:54:02.759 --> 06:54:05.520
wing, or swimming with a sea wing, and

06:54:05.520 --> 06:54:07.560
then the next day they'd be gone, along

06:54:07.560 --> 06:54:08.880
with all her memories of them.

06:54:08.939 --> 06:54:11.220
I have had friends.

06:54:11.279 --> 06:54:13.560
I just never knew it.

06:54:13.619 --> 06:54:16.799
Maybe she can cast a spell to find them.

06:54:16.919 --> 06:54:19.200
Maybe some of them are still alive.

06:54:19.259 --> 06:54:22.619
Maybe she can restore their memories, and

06:54:22.619 --> 06:54:24.119
they'll be so happy to see her.

06:54:24.180 --> 06:54:27.540
What if I search for them and find out

06:54:27.540 --> 06:54:28.740
something terrible, though.

06:54:28.860 --> 06:54:32.159
She's not sure she's ready to face every

06:54:32.159 --> 06:54:33.540
truth about her mother right now.

06:54:33.599 --> 06:54:37.020
And there are so many other less

06:54:37.020 --> 06:54:39.419
traumatizing things she can do with all

06:54:39.419 --> 06:54:40.259
her wonderful magic.

06:54:40.319 --> 06:54:42.779
She can make everyone on the whole

06:54:42.779 --> 06:54:44.040
continent be friends with her.

06:54:44.099 --> 06:54:47.220
She can make herself queen of the kingdom

06:54:47.220 --> 06:54:48.479
of sand if she wants to.

06:54:48.540 --> 06:54:52.259
She has all the power her mother had, but

06:54:52.259 --> 06:54:54.180
she's not going to use it to torture one

06:54:54.180 --> 06:54:55.680
dragonette for 100s of years.

06:54:55.740 --> 06:54:58.139
She's going to use it to be happy.

06:54:58.200 --> 06:55:00.479
To have a completely different life.

06:55:00.540 --> 06:55:03.959
But, 1st things first.

06:55:04.020 --> 06:55:07.080
She needs to get this frozen monster out

06:55:07.080 --> 06:55:07.740
of her doorway.

06:55:07.860 --> 06:55:10.799
Boa touches the shell around her neck.

06:55:10.860 --> 06:55:13.979
It gives her instant teleportation to

06:55:13.979 --> 06:55:14.880
wherever her mother is.

06:55:14.939 --> 06:55:18.060
The 1st spell Jerboa ever made at her

06:55:18.060 --> 06:55:18.299
request.

06:55:18.419 --> 06:55:20.759
That could still be useful.

06:55:20.819 --> 06:55:22.740
If she puts her mother in the right

06:55:22.740 --> 06:55:23.040
place.

06:55:23.099 --> 06:55:27.479
She rests one talon, lightly against the

06:55:27.479 --> 06:55:29.880
chilly ice wall, and looks through the

06:55:29.880 --> 06:55:32.340
dark whorls to where she thinks she can

06:55:32.340 --> 06:55:33.360
see her mother's eyes.

06:55:33.419 --> 06:55:36.779
I enchant this block of ice to bury

06:55:36.779 --> 06:55:39.599
itself under this hut and stay frozen

06:55:39.599 --> 06:55:40.319
there forever.

06:55:40.380 --> 06:55:44.759
The ice and her mother vanish, and the

06:55:44.759 --> 06:55:46.860
hut shakes slightly, as though something

06:55:46.860 --> 06:55:48.779
is settling in the sand below it.

06:55:48.840 --> 06:55:52.139
But Boa doesn't even get a moment to be

06:55:52.139 --> 06:55:52.619
thrilled.

06:55:52.680 --> 06:55:56.639
Pain, lances through her sharp and

06:55:56.639 --> 06:55:59.040
blinding, and she shrieks at the

06:55:59.040 --> 06:56:00.240
unexpected agony.

06:56:00.299 --> 06:56:04.020
When the 1st wave of pain passes, she

06:56:04.020 --> 06:56:06.659
opens her eyes, gasping, and sees that

06:56:06.659 --> 06:56:08.040
one of her claws is gone.

06:56:08.099 --> 06:56:11.400
It's been sliced off as if someone took a

06:56:11.400 --> 06:56:13.439
hatchet to it, and there is blood

06:56:13.439 --> 06:56:16.560
everywhere, although the claw itself has

06:56:16.560 --> 06:56:17.819
vanished into thin air.

06:56:17.939 --> 06:56:19.799
What?

06:56:19.860 --> 06:56:20.939
She whispers.

06:56:21.000 --> 06:56:22.200
What?

06:56:22.259 --> 06:56:24.959
Did she cast the spell wrong?

06:56:25.020 --> 06:56:27.840
Maybe she was accidentally touching the

06:56:27.840 --> 06:56:30.060
ice block with that talon, and it took a

06:56:30.060 --> 06:56:30.900
piece of her with it?

06:56:30.959 --> 06:56:32.400
Or?

06:56:32.880 --> 06:56:34.080
No.

06:56:34.200 --> 06:56:35.520
No, no, no.

06:56:35.580 --> 06:56:37.799
Somehow she knows.

06:56:37.860 --> 06:56:39.659
In a space beyond knowing.

06:56:39.720 --> 06:56:42.360
She can't see the shape of it yet.

06:56:42.419 --> 06:56:44.759
She still has to figure out how and what

06:56:44.759 --> 06:56:47.220
exactly this is, but she is certain of

06:56:47.220 --> 06:56:47.520
one thing.

06:56:47.580 --> 06:56:50.340
Her mother did this to her.

06:56:50.400 --> 06:56:54.900
She is sitting by the fresh water pond

06:56:54.900 --> 06:56:56.939
washing the blood off her newest stump.

06:56:57.060 --> 06:56:59.159
Six claws gone.

06:56:59.220 --> 06:57:02.220
When she has lost all of them, what will

06:57:02.220 --> 06:57:02.520
go next?

06:57:02.580 --> 06:57:04.139
Her ears.

06:57:04.200 --> 06:57:06.900
Her horns, her tail barb.

06:57:07.020 --> 06:57:10.259
Her wings, she shudders.

06:57:10.319 --> 06:57:13.919
She has to be so, so careful with her

06:57:13.919 --> 06:57:14.279
spells.

06:57:14.340 --> 06:57:17.099
There's no way to know which one will

06:57:17.099 --> 06:57:18.599
cause enough damage to kill her.

06:57:18.720 --> 06:57:22.259
She lost her 2nd claw trying to heal the

06:57:22.259 --> 06:57:24.659
1st one, and did only half worked.

06:57:24.720 --> 06:57:28.020
The wound closed, covered over with a

06:57:28.020 --> 06:57:30.419
shiny new layer of scales, but her claw

06:57:30.419 --> 06:57:31.020
did not grow back.

06:57:31.139 --> 06:57:34.500
She used a normal bandage on the 2nd

06:57:34.500 --> 06:57:37.080
injury and thought for a long time.

06:57:37.139 --> 06:57:41.220
Her 3rd claw, sacrificed for

06:57:41.220 --> 06:57:41.639
information.

06:57:41.700 --> 06:57:44.639
She enchanted a scroll to truthfully

06:57:44.639 --> 06:57:47.580
answer any question she asked of it

06:57:47.580 --> 06:57:50.040
through the pain, and the spinning stars

06:57:50.040 --> 06:57:52.560
around her head, she made it tell her

06:57:52.560 --> 06:57:53.580
what her mother had done.

06:57:53.700 --> 06:57:56.639
One final curse.

06:57:56.700 --> 06:57:59.880
She should have expected it, should have

06:57:59.880 --> 06:58:01.740
enchanted something to protect herself.

06:58:01.860 --> 06:58:04.740
But she'd had to move fast when she found

06:58:04.740 --> 06:58:07.560
the boa changing scroll, in the piles of

06:58:07.560 --> 06:58:09.240
bags her mother had forced her to carry

06:58:09.240 --> 06:58:10.380
across the desert.

06:58:10.380 --> 06:58:13.619
Her mother was so rarely careless, or

06:58:13.619 --> 06:58:16.200
perhaps boa was rarely smart and alert

06:58:16.200 --> 06:58:19.619
enough to catch her when she was, and now

06:58:19.619 --> 06:58:21.360
Jerboa has left her this.

06:58:21.419 --> 06:58:25.500
A last spell that was a masterpiece of

06:58:25.500 --> 06:58:26.279
awfulness.

06:58:26.340 --> 06:58:29.939
Every time Boa tries to use animus magic

06:58:29.939 --> 06:58:33.659
she will lose a piece of herself, bit by

06:58:33.659 --> 06:58:35.759
bit, until she dies of her wounds.

06:58:35.880 --> 06:58:39.360
The spell specifies that the pieces could

06:58:39.360 --> 06:58:42.240
not grow back, even with magic, and it is

06:58:42.240 --> 06:58:44.700
reinforced, with words of binding that

06:58:44.700 --> 06:58:47.040
mean there is no way to reverse it or

06:58:47.040 --> 06:58:47.459
fight it.

06:58:47.580 --> 06:58:51.360
Boa tried anyway, which is how she lost

06:58:51.360 --> 06:58:52.919
clause 4 and 5.

06:58:53.099 --> 06:58:55.500
It didn't seem fair that she could be

06:58:55.500 --> 06:58:57.240
injured by spells that didn't even work.

06:58:57.299 --> 06:59:00.659
Her mother learned a lot over the years

06:59:00.659 --> 06:59:03.000
about what animus dragons could do to

06:59:03.000 --> 06:59:05.279
each other, and how to word spells so

06:59:05.279 --> 06:59:06.479
other dragons couldn't break them.

06:59:06.599 --> 06:59:09.479
Boa remembers all the horror stories

06:59:09.479 --> 06:59:09.840
now.

06:59:09.900 --> 06:59:12.479
Everything her mother told her to try to

06:59:12.479 --> 06:59:14.340
scare her away from animus magic.

06:59:14.400 --> 06:59:17.279
But she'd never taught her anything.

06:59:17.340 --> 06:59:20.099
Boa knows nothing about protecting

06:59:20.099 --> 06:59:21.479
herself as an animus.

06:59:21.599 --> 06:59:24.599
And I'm not a normal animus.

06:59:24.659 --> 06:59:25.979
I'm cursed.

06:59:26.040 --> 06:59:27.840
All right.

06:59:27.900 --> 06:59:31.439
So, she can live without magic.

06:59:31.500 --> 06:59:33.720
She is still free of her mother.

06:59:33.779 --> 06:59:36.299
This is her chance to have the normal

06:59:36.299 --> 06:59:39.599
life she always wanted, free in the world

06:59:39.599 --> 06:59:41.099
meeting other dragons.

06:59:41.159 --> 06:59:44.099
Maybe it wouldn't be the glamorous

06:59:44.099 --> 06:59:46.740
enchanted whirlwind she'd imagined, but

06:59:46.740 --> 06:59:48.599
it would be a 1000 times happier than her

06:59:48.599 --> 06:59:49.380
life up to now.

06:59:49.439 --> 06:59:52.020
She would be herself.

06:59:52.080 --> 06:59:54.540
She would choose her own path.

06:59:54.599 --> 06:59:56.639
She would be free.

06:59:56.700 --> 07:00:00.299
At that point, she had looked at her

07:00:00.299 --> 07:00:03.060
maimed talons and realized it would be

07:00:03.060 --> 07:00:05.459
hard to walk into any dragon village and

07:00:05.459 --> 07:00:06.840
make friends looking like this.

07:00:06.900 --> 07:00:09.840
She'd have a lot of explaining to do.

07:00:09.900 --> 07:00:15.240
So then, goodbye to her 6th claw, as a

07:00:15.240 --> 07:00:17.400
new spell was added to the shell necklace

07:00:17.400 --> 07:00:19.680
casting a glamour, so that she looks

07:00:19.680 --> 07:00:22.080
normal and intact to any dragons who see

07:00:22.080 --> 07:00:22.319
her.

07:00:22.380 --> 07:00:25.439
No one will ever see what her mother did

07:00:25.439 --> 07:00:28.259
to her, or know how much pain she is in.

07:00:28.380 --> 07:00:31.500
Boa still has several objects her mother

07:00:31.500 --> 07:00:32.340
enchanted.

07:00:32.400 --> 07:00:34.319
And she knows what about half of them

07:00:34.319 --> 07:00:34.560
do.

07:00:34.619 --> 07:00:37.439
Her information scroll can tell her the

07:00:37.439 --> 07:00:37.619
rest.

07:00:37.680 --> 07:00:40.740
She might even be able to sell a few of

07:00:40.740 --> 07:00:43.380
them to a queen somewhere if she dares to

07:00:43.380 --> 07:00:43.860
risk it.

07:00:43.919 --> 07:00:46.380
And if she's ever in danger.

07:00:46.439 --> 07:00:48.840
One thought will bring her right back

07:00:48.840 --> 07:00:51.659
here, to this hut by the ocean, to the

07:00:51.659 --> 07:00:53.759
floorboards that cover her mother's grave

07:00:53.759 --> 07:00:58.380
where she can dance and dance, and no one

07:00:58.380 --> 07:01:00.659
will ever tell her to stop, or cast a

07:01:00.659 --> 07:01:02.700
spell to make her fall over, or enchant

07:01:02.700 --> 07:01:04.619
away her love of music for 100 years.

07:01:04.680 --> 07:01:08.340
I hope you didn't die thinking you'd won

07:01:08.340 --> 07:01:10.020
mother, she says out loud.

07:01:10.080 --> 07:01:13.020
Because unlike you, I can control

07:01:13.020 --> 07:01:13.500
myself.

07:01:13.560 --> 07:01:15.959
I don't need to use my magic.

07:01:16.020 --> 07:01:19.080
I'm going to be happy despite everything

07:01:19.080 --> 07:01:20.040
you've done to me.

07:01:20.099 --> 07:01:24.060
She spreads her wings and lifts into the

07:01:24.060 --> 07:01:24.299
sky.

07:01:24.360 --> 07:01:28.979
She is taking a break from other

07:01:28.979 --> 07:01:29.580
dragons.

07:01:29.639 --> 07:01:33.419
She does this occasionally, goes back to

07:01:33.419 --> 07:01:36.360
her hut for 50 years or longer, until

07:01:36.360 --> 07:01:38.700
everyone she's met, this time around, has

07:01:38.700 --> 07:01:40.919
forgotten about her, and she can come

07:01:40.919 --> 07:01:42.000
back as someone new.

07:01:42.060 --> 07:01:44.880
It might have been longer than 50 years

07:01:44.880 --> 07:01:45.840
this time, though.

07:01:45.900 --> 07:01:47.880
Has it been closer to 100.

07:01:48.060 --> 07:01:52.080
It's so peaceful on her beach, all alone

07:01:52.080 --> 07:01:53.099
with the waves.

07:01:53.159 --> 07:01:56.220
In the cities, around other dragons.

07:01:56.279 --> 07:01:58.380
She is constantly tempted to use her

07:01:58.380 --> 07:02:01.020
magic, even knowing the pain it will

07:02:01.020 --> 07:02:01.380
cause her.

07:02:01.439 --> 07:02:04.500
But here, she never thinks of spells she

07:02:04.500 --> 07:02:05.459
wishes she could use.

07:02:05.520 --> 07:02:07.619
She can just be.

07:02:07.740 --> 07:02:11.340
She has one friend, a dragon who knows

07:02:11.340 --> 07:02:12.000
the truth about her.

07:02:12.060 --> 07:02:15.360
They met by accident before Glacier

07:02:15.360 --> 07:02:16.200
became queen.

07:02:16.259 --> 07:02:18.060
But glacier is not like other queens.

07:02:18.119 --> 07:02:21.479
She believes in solving her own problems

07:02:21.479 --> 07:02:24.360
and she knows how dangerous animus magic

07:02:24.360 --> 07:02:24.720
can be.

07:02:24.779 --> 07:02:26.700
She also knows.

07:02:26.759 --> 07:02:30.419
The cost Turboa has to pay every time she

07:02:30.419 --> 07:02:31.740
uses her magic.

07:02:31.799 --> 07:02:34.860
Jerboa took off her glamour once, so

07:02:34.860 --> 07:02:36.599
Glacier could see her as she really is.

07:02:36.659 --> 07:02:39.840
She was surprised when Glacier cried.

07:02:39.900 --> 07:02:42.659
No one has ever felt sorry for her before

07:02:42.720 --> 07:02:46.020
or told her that it's not fair, everything

07:02:46.020 --> 07:02:46.680
she went through.

07:02:46.680 --> 07:02:49.740
In all the years they've known each other

07:02:49.740 --> 07:02:52.619
even through the recent war, Glacier has

07:02:52.619 --> 07:02:54.840
never asked Turboa for a single spell.

07:02:54.900 --> 07:02:58.200
Once, Treboa asked her about that.

07:02:58.259 --> 07:03:00.959
And Glacier said, You should save your

07:03:00.959 --> 07:03:01.319
magic.

07:03:01.380 --> 07:03:04.259
Someday, the world might really need it

07:03:04.259 --> 07:03:06.479
and you'll be the only dragon who can

07:03:06.479 --> 07:03:06.959
save everyone.

07:03:07.020 --> 07:03:09.119
Treboa had laughed.

07:03:09.240 --> 07:03:11.400
Me, like a hero?

07:03:11.459 --> 07:03:12.900
Why not?

07:03:12.959 --> 07:03:14.340
Glacier had answered.

07:03:14.400 --> 07:03:16.200
Don't you think you're here for a

07:03:16.200 --> 07:03:16.560
purpose?

07:03:16.619 --> 07:03:21.599
2000 years was a long time to wait for a

07:03:21.599 --> 07:03:23.580
purpose, Treboa thinks.

07:03:23.639 --> 07:03:25.799
Maybe she'll have to invent one

07:03:25.799 --> 07:03:26.520
eventually.

07:03:26.580 --> 07:03:29.639
She is strolling down the empty beach

07:03:29.639 --> 07:03:31.319
toward the water, thinking about what

07:03:31.319 --> 07:03:33.599
kind of fish she'll catch for dinner, when

07:03:33.599 --> 07:03:36.180
the universe suddenly crumples inward, and

07:03:36.180 --> 07:03:38.939
an unfamiliar voice says, clear as a

07:03:38.939 --> 07:03:39.240
bell.

07:03:39.360 --> 07:03:41.340
Bring them here.

07:03:41.400 --> 07:03:44.700
Every animus dragon in all the 7 tribes.

07:03:44.759 --> 07:03:46.979
Bring them here to my throne room right

07:03:46.979 --> 07:03:47.279
now.

07:03:47.340 --> 07:03:51.240
And before she can think, or breathe, or

07:03:51.240 --> 07:03:53.580
run, she finds herself standing in a

07:03:53.580 --> 07:03:55.439
sunlit black marble throne room.

07:03:55.500 --> 07:03:58.919
In front of her is the largest dragon

07:03:58.919 --> 07:03:59.700
she's ever seen.

07:03:59.759 --> 07:04:03.299
A night wing ice wing hybrid, menace

07:04:03.299 --> 07:04:04.259
radiating off him.

07:04:04.319 --> 07:04:07.439
He has his back to her, and as she

07:04:07.439 --> 07:04:09.659
appears, 3 more dragons appear in front

07:04:09.659 --> 07:04:12.419
of him, 2 sea wings, and another night

07:04:12.419 --> 07:04:15.419
wing, all looking completely terrified.

07:04:15.479 --> 07:04:17.580
Turboa doesn't hesitate.

07:04:17.639 --> 07:04:20.639
Centuries of reacting to fear have

07:04:20.639 --> 07:04:21.360
trained her well.

07:04:21.419 --> 07:04:23.400
She is barely in the room for a moment

07:04:23.400 --> 07:04:26.400
before she seizes her necklace and whisks

07:04:26.400 --> 07:04:27.119
herself home again.

07:04:27.180 --> 07:04:30.959
She is in her hut, her heart pounding.

07:04:31.020 --> 07:04:33.599
Her claws sinking into the weathered

07:04:33.599 --> 07:04:35.639
wooden floor. which she has replaced

07:04:35.639 --> 07:04:38.639
several times over the years, but always

07:04:38.639 --> 07:04:41.279
in the same spot, where her mother is

07:04:41.279 --> 07:04:41.639
buried.

07:04:41.759 --> 07:04:43.799
Thank you, mother.

07:04:43.860 --> 07:04:46.860
For once, one of your spells has saved

07:04:46.860 --> 07:04:47.099
me.

07:04:47.159 --> 07:04:50.639
The magic has brought her home, but is

07:04:50.639 --> 07:04:51.180
she actually safe?

07:04:51.240 --> 07:04:52.979
Who was that?

07:04:53.040 --> 07:04:55.919
And all those other dragons?

07:04:55.979 --> 07:04:58.860
Are there really 5 animus dragons in

07:04:58.860 --> 07:04:59.639
Pyria right now?

07:04:59.700 --> 07:05:02.340
Didn't mother say the limit was one?

07:05:02.400 --> 07:05:04.200
How is this possible?

07:05:04.259 --> 07:05:07.380
She scrambles over to her trunk and

07:05:07.380 --> 07:05:09.599
tosses everything in it aside to get to

07:05:09.599 --> 07:05:10.680
our answers, scroll.

07:05:10.740 --> 07:05:13.500
Tell me who that was, she says.

07:05:13.560 --> 07:05:16.200
The riding goes on for a while.

07:05:16.259 --> 07:05:20.340
The scroll is usually very concise, but

07:05:20.340 --> 07:05:22.020
it seems to have a lot to say about this

07:05:22.020 --> 07:05:23.340
dark stalker.

07:05:23.400 --> 07:05:26.099
His past, his history?

07:05:26.220 --> 07:05:29.459
He was alive back when my mother was, she

07:05:29.459 --> 07:05:32.279
thinks, the spell that tucked him away

07:05:32.279 --> 07:05:35.159
the mistake that freed him, the night

07:05:35.159 --> 07:05:36.240
wings who follow him.

07:05:36.299 --> 07:05:39.779
What does he want with animus dragons?

07:05:39.840 --> 07:05:40.500
she asks.

07:05:40.619 --> 07:05:43.979
To control them, the scroll answers.

07:05:44.099 --> 07:05:47.220
To use their magic instead of his own, to

07:05:47.220 --> 07:05:49.500
preserve his soul, and to be sure that

07:05:49.500 --> 07:05:51.419
they can never be any threat to him.

07:05:51.479 --> 07:05:54.419
Treboa shudders, feeling sick.

07:05:54.479 --> 07:05:56.580
What if he'd been facing her?

07:05:56.639 --> 07:05:59.520
What if he'd gotten his claws on her and

07:05:59.520 --> 07:06:00.720
forced her to use her magic?

07:06:00.840 --> 07:06:04.020
What if he found it amusing to watch her

07:06:04.020 --> 07:06:06.119
slowly slice into pieces until she died?

07:06:06.180 --> 07:06:09.180
I have to protect myself against him.

07:06:09.240 --> 07:06:11.939
I have to cast something to make myself

07:06:11.939 --> 07:06:14.700
invulnerable to his spells, or something

07:06:14.700 --> 07:06:16.139
to make me more powerful than him.

07:06:16.259 --> 07:06:19.080
She reaches for one of her copper

07:06:19.080 --> 07:06:22.139
bracelets, then hesitates, struck by a

07:06:22.139 --> 07:06:22.619
chilling thought.

07:06:22.680 --> 07:06:26.520
Why did he summon all the animus dragons

07:06:26.520 --> 07:06:26.880
right now?

07:06:26.939 --> 07:06:30.419
Because his magic told him someone was

07:06:30.419 --> 07:06:33.000
casting anima spells, and he was afraid

07:06:33.000 --> 07:06:34.319
they might be against him.

07:06:34.380 --> 07:06:36.599
She asks quietly.

07:06:36.659 --> 07:06:39.299
He can tell when someone uses animus

07:06:39.299 --> 07:06:39.599
magic.

07:06:39.659 --> 07:06:41.340
Yes.

07:06:41.400 --> 07:06:43.439
Can he sense me right now?

07:06:43.500 --> 07:06:45.299
No.

07:06:45.360 --> 07:06:47.400
His spell only searches for new

07:06:47.400 --> 07:06:48.240
enchantments.

07:06:48.299 --> 07:06:51.000
How can I protect myself against him?

07:06:51.060 --> 07:06:53.639
That answer is not available yet.

07:06:53.700 --> 07:06:56.040
She knew it would say that.

07:06:56.099 --> 07:06:59.040
It can't see the future or tell her

07:06:59.040 --> 07:06:59.880
what's going to happen.

